{"_id":"07sj6WPEt2NIt8p7","name":"Lesser Restoration (2nd Level)","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3,"jSIbaKrMQZ5trOzn":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<div>\n\t\t\t<div><i>Scroll, minor tier, uncommon</i></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"flex w-100\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-4\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-8 text-right\">  </div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<hr>\n\t\t<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p>A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written as a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.</p><p>If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make an ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. The DC is 12. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.</p><p>Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and the scroll itself crumbles to dust.</p><p>A spell cast from this scroll has a save DC of 13 and an attack bonus of [[/r 1d20+5]] (+5).</p><p>A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 12 Intelligence (<span class=\"help--hover\" onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseOver(event, this, 714, {})\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseMove(event, this)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseLeave(event, this)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Arcana</span>) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"DMG","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":"","autoDestroy":true,"autoUse":true},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"scroll","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"tMPMWheY9FGPdLEs","sort":900001,"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"items.html","source":"DMG","hash":"spell%20scroll%20(2nd%20level)_dmg","data":{"item":{"name":"Spell Scroll (2nd Level)","source":"DMG","page":201,"srd":true,"type":"SC","tier":"minor","rarity":"uncommon","entries":["A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written as a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.","If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make an ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. The DC is 12. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.","Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and the scroll itself crumbles to dust.","A spell cast from this scroll has a save DC of 13 and an attack bonus of {@hit 5}.","A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 12 Intelligence ({@skill Arcana}) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed."],"lootTables":["Magic Item Table A","Magic Item Table B"],"_isEnhanced":true,"_category":"Other","_typeListText":["scroll"],"_typeHtml":"scroll","_attunement":null,"_attunementCategory":"No","_fProperties":[],"_fMisc":["SRD","Magic"],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["minor"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Scroll"}}},"magicitems":{"enabled":true,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"1","chargeType":"c1","destroy":true,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l","destroyCheck":"d1","destroyType":"dt1","spells":{"0":{"id":"ZTBhNmVhNDgyNWQx","name":"Lesser Restoration","pack":"world","img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/heal-sky-1.jpg","baseLevel":"2","level":"2","consumption":"2","upcast":"2","upcastCost":"1","flatDc":false}}}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/tied-scroll.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Onion Sword","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This blade resembles the type of toy sword that a child may be seen playing with or the kind of training brand that an adolescent might use to practice their swordsmanship. The sword's pommel, grip, guard, and edge are all oversized in a bulbous, rounded fashion to give the weapon a cartoonish or prop-like aesthetic, however the object is far mightier than first appearances indicate and it brims with hidden potential. Although implements of this type are most often formed of wood, in this particular instance, the sword's creator opted to throw caution to wind and went with forged steel instead. The result is a sword that is far deadlier than it has any business being, as it is intended for use by a relative novice. Despite its curious irregularities, the blade is unusually light, fits comfortably in the hand of its wielder, and feels immediately intuitive to use.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Onion Sword is a training blade that's served as a gift from father to son, and sometimes daughter, on many occasions. Keen and sharp, the sword requires its recipient to be able to demonstrate a strong sense of responsibility and care&mdash;traits no doubt prized by the individual proudly gifting the blade to their offspring as they come of age. Most commonly the Onion Sword has been owned by noble families and has exchanged hands amongst the moneyed classes.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Onion Sword can be used as a shortsword.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Brave Blade</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Onion Sword is magically blessed to instill a sense of confidence in its young master and embolden their strikes. You gain a +2 bonus on checks made to resist fear while it is about your person.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Training Blade</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It takes time, practice, and experimentation for any young sword hand to find its preferred combat style. The Onion Sword benefits its wielder in the following ways:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It is considered to have the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Versatile weapon </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">trait, dealing 1d8 damage when wielded in two hands.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As a bonus action, you can will it to harden, elongate, or sharpen in order to deal bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage respectively.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When paired with a shield, it bestows you with a +1 bonus to your Armor Class against Opportunity Attacks.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","bludgeoning"],["","piercing"],["","slashing"]],"versatile":"1d8 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":1500000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"0B3ssJ4PW0d1TEg8"}
{"name":"Shroud of the Hedge Wizard","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Built for practicality instead of showiness, this wrap is a plain, unassuming garment. The cloak is well-suited to traveling and is made of thick cotton that is suitably warm during the winter but cool enough not to impede its wearer during the summer.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Shroud of the Hedge Wizard was created by an apprentice wizard who participated in a cultural exchange to spend time with a circle of druids and found herself smitten with the simple wonders of the natural world. Upon her return, her colleagues noticed a marked change in her appearance that included, but was not limited to, a preference for sandals, beaded necklaces and charms, dreadlocks, and a cloak of twigs and fine mosses. The apprentice was later suspended for pushing her newfound alternative ideology, and eventually abandoned her other studies.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Hedge Magic</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Shroud of the Hedge Wizard is the perfect garment for a student of the arcane with a healthy love of nature. While wearing it, as long as you can cast at least one spell, you always have the spells <em>Detect Poison and Disease</em>, <em>Purify Food and Drink</em>, <em>Speak with Animals</em>, and <em>Animal Friendship </em>prepared and these do not count against the number of spells that you can prepare each day. I</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">f cast, these spells use your spellcasting ability in place of Wisdom (unless it is Wisdom, in which case you use Wisdom as normal).</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":10100000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/cloak.png","effects":[],"_id":"0Kfsf5E0xpK5TWZn"}
{"name":"Cesti of Unbridled Fury","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This pair of fearsome gauntlets cast an imposing shadow over any conversation between their wearer and those they might encounter. This is because these are no mere gloves. In fact, these hand coverings are actually a set of studded leather cesti, stained red in places with the blood of those who've displeased their master. Each cestus slides comfortably over the knuckles and serves to buffer their wearer's hands so that they can strike harder than usual without feeling the full force of their blows.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Cesti of Unbridled Fury once belonged to a halfelf pit fighter named Ruhki Khan. It is said that Ruhki's ferocity was so pronounced, so infamous, that few opponents would face him in the arena unless the pot was life-changing. Consequently, he mostly fought beasts and monsters, spilling their blood on the sands in place of that of his contemporaries. According to those who knew him, despite whatever elf-blood pulsed through his veins, Ruhki couldn't have typified the poise and grace of his brethren less. In fact, he was often described as almost feral.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon.</strong> The Cesti of Unbridled Fury can be used as a set of two cestuses.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Cestus.</strong> R</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">ules for cestuses can be found in </span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">@Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Savage Strikes</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Cesti of Unbridled Fury deliver crippling, almost-concussive blows with devastating efficacy. Attacks made with the cestuses deal +1 damage on a hit. Additionally, critical strikes with them cause the target to suffer disadvantage on ability checks for 1 hour.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Frightful Presence</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It&rsquo;s difficult to look at the crimson patches that stain the Cesti of Unbridled Fury for too long before wondering whose claret has discoloured them so, and whose blood will next. You have advantage on Charisma checks made to physically threaten or intimidate others while wearing them openly.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Burgeoning Rage</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">After wearing the Cesti of Unbridled Fury for long enough, the noise someone&rsquo;s nose makes when it shatters starts to sound pretty good. As a result,</span>&nbsp;if you choose to don them<span class=\"fontstyle0\">&nbsp;you gain a Flaw<em> </em>in addition to any existing flaws you possess. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once you have gained a flaw, you must must not wear the Cesti of Unbridled Fury for twice as many days as it took to unlock it for it to fade again. Should you don them again at any time during this period, you resume accruing days from where you left off.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>1 Day.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&ldquo;My mood is regularly dour and I don&rsquo;t suffer fools gladly.&rdquo;</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>3 Day.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&ldquo;I&rsquo;m irritable and I constantly snap at those around me.&rdquo;</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>6 Day.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&ldquo;I find it very difficult to keep my temper under control. I&rsquo;m forever on the verge of exploding at those around me.&rdquo;</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>10+ Day.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&ldquo;I seethe constantly. I can barely restrain myself from lunging at those around me and ripping out their throats.&rdquo;</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":2,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod +1","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":4900000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"0cmbmHbQEkhl24je"}
{"name":"Imobius","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This dark longbow is formed of stained ash that appears to have been ravaged by fire. Scorch marks from where flames once licked at its flammable surface have been seared into its charred form and it looks like its ready to crumble to dust at a moment&rsquo;s notice. Despite its condition, the bow is strung and remains completely functional. More interestingly, while its bowstring is drawn, small embers swirl around both the implement and its wielder.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Imobius was crafted by a master fletcher who designed unusual implements for circus troupes. Many of these took the form of &lsquo;trick&rsquo; weapons that used dummy ammunition, while others used pyrotechnics or magic to create dramatic displays. For his part, the bow&rsquo;s fletcher, was terrified of fire and despised constructing devices that relied on it as a gimmick. So much so that, when he got around to creating Imobius, he replaced all of its practical effects with special effects<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>swapping the need to be near fire, for the impression that one was instead.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Imobius can be used as a longbow.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Flare</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Pyrotechnics add a splash of excitement to any event. Arrows fired from Imobius take on the guise of rockets, crackers, sparklers, pinwheels, or other fireworks. They shed bright light for 10 foot, and dim light for an additional 10 foot for 1 minute after being fired from it, after which they revert to their true form.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Torturous Temperament</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Some hallucinations are every bit as dangerous and damaging as physical trauma itself. When you strike a hostile creature with an arrow fired from Imobius</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, the target must make a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the target believes that it has been set on fire and takes 1d6 psychic damage. At the start of each of its subsequent turns it repeats this saving throw, taking an additional 1d4 psychic damage on a failed save until it &lsquo;extinguishes&rsquo; itself as an action. Success on its save means that the affected creature realises that the flames are only an illusion and the harmful effect ends. Once a creature has discerned that the projectiles Imobius fires are arrows, and not fireworks, it cannot be harmed by this feature again.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":150,"long":600,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialR","properties":{"amm":true,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":true,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":7400000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-ranged-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"0vcTC8RfCYe98Lqm"}
{"_id":"0w7YQILB4zXjqy0T","name":"Haste","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Choose a willing creature that you can see within range. Until the spell ends, the target's speed is doubled, it gains a +2 bonus to AC, it has advantage on Dexterity saving throws, and it gains an additional action on each of its turns. That action can be used only to take the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#attack_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'attack_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Attack</a> (one weapon attack only), <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#dash_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'dash_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Dash</a>, <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#disengage_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'disengage_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Disengage</a>, <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#hide_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'hide_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Hide</a>, or <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#use%20an%20object_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'use%20an%20object_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Use an Object</a> action.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>When the spell ends, the target can't move or take actions until after its next turn, as a wave of lethargy sweeps over it.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a shaving of licorice root","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":13600001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-haste.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"D1GU4qnpVXYxGgHv","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":