{"name":"King Thorostad","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb07/king-thorostad.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"238\" height=\"256\" />\"It wouldn&rsquo;t take a dwarven jeweller or bearded brewmaster to recognise that this collection of throwing knives and their shoulder-slung case are of dwarven design. Each blade in the set is identical, other than for the pair of jewels that are set into their guard and pommel. In order, the knives possess; a ruby and a garnet, an amethyst and a sugilite, a sapphire and a tanzanite, an aquamarine and a turquoise, and a tourmaline and an aventurine. Though the stones are legitimate and intended to impress, each is afflicted with impurities, of a low carat, and has somewhat dulled with age.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">King Thorostad was commissioned to be used as a set of trick knives for a small theatrical production about an assassination attempt against a dwarven king. Much like the regicidal conspiracy that spawned it, the play was later cancelled, but the knives stayed with the theater troupe for several years before finding their way into circulation elsewhere.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">King Thorostad can be used as a set of five daggers.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Rousing Reaction</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If there&rsquo;s one trick that owners of King Thorostad have utilized to elicit awed gasps from their audience more than any other, it&rsquo;s this one. As a reaction, you can attempt to throw one of its knives in order to knock a projectile out of the air if you have one in your hand or at least one free hand. If a projectile, either a thrown weapon or a form of ammunition, passes within 30 foot of you while it is in flight, you can attempt a Dexterity saving throw with a DC equal to half the result of the triggering attack roll (rounded down). On a success, the two objects collide and both fall harmlessly to the ground 5 foot from you. On a failure, the attack hits you as normal, and your blade lands 20 foot from you in the direction of the triggering projectile.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Unerring Aim</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">King Thorostad&rsquo;s former owners have all had an uncanny knack for not maiming their assistants. You suffer no penalty to your attack rolls as a result of being visually impaired or having the blinded condition when using a blade from the set to make an attack.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Impalement Arts</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">King Thorostad can be used to perform a multitude of tricks and illusions:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can painlessly swallow one or more knives from the set, only to have any knives swallowed reappear in your sheath ten minutes later.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have advantage on Charisma (performance) checks made to perform trick shots with knives from the set.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have advantage on Charisma (performance) or Dexterity (sleight of hand) checks made to juggle knives from the set.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":5,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":8500000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/ammunition.png","effects":[],"_id":"7PppUhjhvuELFXaZ"}
{"_id":"7QHthSGgilpFSYea","name":"Expeditious Retreat","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>This spell allows you to move at an incredible pace. When you cast this spell, and then as a bonus action on each of your turns until the spell ends, you can take the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#dash_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'dash_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Dash</a> action.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":12800001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-expeditious-retreat.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"d9W7ah2Kum15MANv","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-expeditious-retreat.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Carpalcross","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb02/carpalcross.png\" alt=\"\" />\"Discretely hidden within a metal-plated leather vambrace, this concealed crossbow is favored by assassins, cat burglars, and second-story men for both its discretion and the fact that it can be used to fire grappling hooks and pitons. Amidst a dangerous world of crumbling chimney stacks, loose tiles, and hidden hazards, the utility that this ornate gauntlet provides in aiding its user to access and navigate rooftops more easily is significant. A simple thumbs-up causes the object's crossbow to extend, while presenting a thumbs-down signal makes the mechanism retract. Once loaded, getting it to fire is as easy as forming a fist with the wearer's thumb pinched between their index and middle fingers. Should their hands be otherwise occupied, a creature can also trigger the crossbow with simple gestures using their wrist or motions of their arm.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon.</strong> Carpalcross can be used as a hand crossbow.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Concealed.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Carpalcross' gauntlet conceals a small, spring-loaded crossbow that is deployed and retracted with a gesture or simple flick of the wrist. It gains the <em>Concealed </em>weapon property. Thanks to its design, it can remain loaded and still be concealed with penalty.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Rule Clarification, Concealed.</strong> The Concealed property can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.wlHHsHmNANE9pSbd]{Weapon Properties}.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Free Hand</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once loaded, Carpalcross can be fired hands-free. Because it is affixed to the wrist and does not need to be carried in a hand, you can always fire Carpalcross if it is loaded, even if you are holding objects in one or both hands. You do, however, require a free hand to load it.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>High-level Escapades</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Though able to be used as a weapon, Carpalcross' true utility lies in its ability to get its wielder to places they might be otherwise unable to reach. You can use it to fire a grappling hook or a piton with a rope attached up to distances of 30 foot.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":120,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialR","properties":{"amm":true,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":true,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":3900000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-ranged-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"7W2zwVR9dN4Ibvxc"}
{"name":"Obeisance","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This ostentatious golden ring is presented in the style of those traditionally worn by senior or distinguished members of a religious faith and those who serve as part of a priesthood. Its head features a wide, flat amethyst with a pair of depictions&mdash;one of a serene ebony face, the other an ivory skull&mdash;positioned beside it on the band itself. The ring is traditionally worn on the right hand and possesses several hidden features that could serve to heighten the eminence of its wearer, or else provide a perfect fit for someone whose intentions are not at all what they might appear to be. For, although the significance of the two faces depicted on the ring might be mistaken for a representation of life and death, they actually allude to the object's contradictory nature as it might just as easily serve a charlatan or a leader of a cult as it does a priest.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Kiss the Ring</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This ornate ring harbors a dark secret, able to aid its wearer in performing terrible, underhanded acts. As an action, you can hold your hand aloft, aim your ring finger at a creature with 5 feet of you, and command it to kiss Obeisance. If you do so, the target must attempt a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw. On a fail, they're compelled to kiss the ring as a reaction. If they've already used their reaction for the round, they do so as a bonus action immediately at the start of their next turn. Only creatures with an Intelligence score of 3 or higher are affected by this feature, however you and the target of your instruction do not need to share a language as the compulsion to kiss the ring is primarily telepathic and can be gestured, spoke, or inferred. Once a creature has been the target of this feature, they cannot be affected by it for 24 hours.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Poisoner's Ring (3/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Each time you compel another creature to kiss Obeisance as per Kiss the Ring, you can will it to discharge a small amount of a liquid toxin which is absorbed by the creature who kisses it. A creature affected in this way must attempt a DC 13 Constitution saving throw or else be affected by one of the following poisonous effects:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">They suffer the poisoned condition for 1d4 rounds.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">They take 3d8 poison damage.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Their movement speed decreases by 10 foot, they have disadvantage on Dexterity saving throws, and they have disadvantage on any initiative checks that they make for the next minute.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">They cannot tell a lie for the next 5 minutes. This effect doesn't compel them to tell the truth or say anything at all, it just prevents them from lying. When it wears off, they do not recall being affected in this way, though they might consider their responses to questions strange or unusual.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">They have disadvantage on any ability checks that they undertake for the next 5 minutes.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":6400000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/ring.png","effects":[],"_id":"7gXVuwjoelXBAMCQ"}
{"_id":"7hPU0h82BDwgTBc8","name":"Fire Shield","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Thin and wispy flames wreathe your body for the duration, shedding bright light in a 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 feet. You can end the spell early by using an action to dismiss it.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The flames provide you with a warm shield or a chill shield, as you choose. The warm shield grants you resistance to cold damage, and the chill shield grants you resistance to fire damage.</p><p>In addition, whenever a creature within 5 feet of you hits you with a melee attack, the shield erupts with flame. The attacker takes [[/r 2d8]] fire damage from a warm shield, or [[/r 2d8]] cold damage from a cold shield.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"self","type":"self"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d8","fire"],["2d8","cold"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a bit of phosphorus or a firefly","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":1500001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/protect-red-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"7j3C5CGiXWzxkrv2","name":"Conjure Minor Elementals (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You summon elementals that appear in unoccupied spaces that you can see within range. You choose one the following options for what appears:</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">One <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&2,flsttype:elemental=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >elemental of challenge rating 2 or lower</a></li><li class=\"rd__li \">Two <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&1,flsttype:elemental=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >elementals of challenge rating 1 or lower</a></li><li class=\"rd__li \">Four <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&1/2,flsttype:elemental=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >elementals of challenge rating 1/2 or lower</a></li><li class=\"rd__li \">Eight <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&1/4,flsttype:elemental=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >elementals of challenge rating 1/4 or lower</a>.</li></ul><p>An elemental summoned by this spell disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p><p>The summoned creatures are friendly to you and your companions. Roll initiative for the summoned creatures as a group, which has its own turns. They obey any verbal commands that you issue to them (no action required by you). If you don't issue any commands to them, they defend themselves from hostile creatures, but otherwise take no actions.</p><p>The DM has the creatures' statistics.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"124\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using certain higher-level spell slots, you choose one of the summoning options above, and more creatures appear: twice as many with a 6th-level slot and three times as many with an 8th-level slot.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"any","type":"space"},"range":{"value":90,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":8100001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-conjure-minor-elementals.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"84gygGREhz7Mw5yi","name":"Heat Metal","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Choose a manufactured metal object, such as a metal weapon or a suit of heavy or medium metal armor, that you can see within range. You cause the object to glow red-hot. Any creature in physical contact with the object takes [[/r 2d8]] fire damage when you cast the spell. Until the spell ends, you can use a bonus action on each of your subsequent turns to cause this damage again.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If a creature is holding or wearing the object and takes the damage from it, the creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or drop the object if it can. If it doesn't drop the object, it has disadvantage on attack rolls and ability checks until the start of your next turn.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"18\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 2nd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"object"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d8","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a piece of iron and a flame","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":13700001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-heat-metal.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"TvNAEcwQmJIZcZ4O","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-heat-metal.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"8Cl7arblrp72uVvi","name":"Amulet of Health","permission":{"default":-1,"PRwyhZZZ2oBbM7RK":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<div>\n<div><em>Wondrous item, major tier, rare (requires attunement)</em></div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-4\">1 lb.</div>\n<div class=\"col-8 text-right\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<hr />\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<p>Your Constitution score is 19 while you wear this amulet. It has no effect on you if your Constitution score is already 19 or higher without it.</p>\n</div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"DMG","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":null,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":0,"type":"trinket","dex":0},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":null,"sort":200001,"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1"},"betterRolls5e":{"critRange":{"value":null}}},"img":"https://5e.tools/img/items%2FAmulet%20of%20Health.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8D0uWC6vfyk2uqNy","name":"Unarmed Strike","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 1st level, your practice of martial arts gives you mastery of combat styles that use unarmed strikes.</p>\n<p>You gain the following benefits while you are unarmed or wielding only monk weapons and you aren’t wearing armor or wielding a shield:</p>\n<p>• You can use Dexterity instead of Strength for the attack and damage rolls of your unarmed strikes</p>\n<p>• You can roll a d4 in place of the normal damage of your unarmed strike. This die changes as you gain monk levels, as shown in the Martial Arts column in the table below.</p>\n<p>• When you use the Attack action with an unarmed strike on your turn, you can make one unarmed strike as a bonus action, assuming you haven’t already taken a bonus action this turn.</p>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Monk Level</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Martial Arts</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1st - 4th</td>\n<td>1d4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5th - 10th</td>\n<td>1d6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>11th - 16th</td>\n<td>1d8</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>17th - 20th</td>\n<td>1d10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><em>**Foundry note: Note the damage die is set to the base default of 1d4. Please manually adjust as required.</em></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 77-78","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"wis"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"hvy":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false,"mgc":false,"nodam":false,"faulldam":false},"proficient":true,"bonus":{"value":0,"_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damage2":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damage2Type":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":null,"sort":1100001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""},"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"betterCurses":{"isCurse":false,"curseName":"","formula":"","mwak":false,"rwak":false,"msak":false,"rsak":false}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/ice_10.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Zanziver's Marvellous Pole","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"Assembled, this incredibly lightweight, wooden implement appears as a completely seamless quarterstaff or walking stick with no obvious joints or breaks in its construction. However, if it is gripped firmly and twisted, the object can be broken down segment by segment into four individual components, each around a foot tall. The four shorter batons which form the quarterstaff each have a symbol emblazoned across them. One of these depicts an arcane symbol, while the others showcase a snowflake, a flame, and a bolt of lightning.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Weapon</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zanziver's Marvellous Pole can be used as a quarterstaff.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Multitool</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Thanks to its miraculous construction and arcane enchantments, Zanziver&rsquo;s Marvellous Pole benefits from several advantages over less intelligently designed implements:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can assemble its components in any order and swap them as an action. When the segment with the arcane symbol is at its head, the object deals bludgeoning damage that is considered magical for the purposes of overcoming damage resistance. When the snowflake, flame, or lightning strike takes the principal spot, attacks made with it instead deal cold, fire, or lightning damage respectively.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can dismantled it into four small segments. When disassembled in this way, it is not easily recognisable as a quarterstaff and creatures may overlook it as a weapon.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Each of its segments is hollow and you can use each of them to discretely store a small object no larger than 1 foot and no heavier than 1 lb.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","bludgeoning"],["","cold"],["","fire"],["","lightning"]],"versatile":"1d8 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":19500000,"flags":{"mess":{"isBonusDamage":false,"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/staff.png","effects":[],"_id":"8JgT4hBgy4uqWu04"}
{"name":"Holgurel","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb10/holgurel.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"175\" />\"This unusual metal bulwark is encircled by a ring of protruding spikes, while several longer blades are also worked into its design. This bizarre arrangement of metal facade and dagger-like extensions allows the shield to strike a balance between utility, offense, and defense that other such objects never could, nor ever would, seek to replicate. The implement's peculiar design goes further still, with a powerful lamp nestled in its rear<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>the light from which can optionally be shone through the front of the shield via a small latch. The hole which this light pours through is tiny so as to focus it into a powerful beam used to illuminate specific objects or dazzle unsuspecting opponents. Despite its many discordant design features, it is for this component that the shield earns its moniker as a lantern shield. </span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Holgurel was commissioned by an insomniac watchman who grew tired of the rampant crime in his beat. Once it was completed, he vacated his official post each night to instead stalk the streets and shine a light on the criminal element that plagued his neighborhood. After numerous bust-ups, the infamous vigilante proved to be so effective at eradicating lawlessness that he spawned numerous imitators across the city who themselves began taking to the streets carrying little more than bullseye lanterns</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><em>&mdash;</em></span><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">the mere flash of their lights enough to send curfew-breakers running.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Holgurel can be used as a shield.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Shield of Light</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Holgurel can be used as a bullseye lantern. As a bonus action, you can flip its cover open or closed. While its cover is closed, it casts no bright or dim light.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Stab or Swipe</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The deadly spikes and protrusions that erupt from Holgurel render it much more than a mere defensive tool. As a bonus action, you can make an attack with it that deals 1d6 piercing or slashing damage (wielder's choice). If you're proficient in the use of shields, you can add your proficiency bonus to attacks made with it.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Flare</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Creatures who dwell in dark corners and thrive in shadowy recesses should beware of Holgurel and its wielder. While it is being used as a lantern but its cover is closed, you can flip its cover open and have it emit a blinding light as an action. If you do so, all creatures caught in its cone of bright light that can see must attempt a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw. On a fail, they're caught in the blast of light and take 1d4 radiant damage. On a success, they're able to close or cover their eyes in time to avoid taking damage. Creatures that have the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Sunlight Sensitivity</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> or </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Sunlight Weakness </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">traits take double damage from this feature. Creatures that have been damaged by this feature previously are prepared for it and have advantage on their saving throw.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6","piercing"],["","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":2,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":1000000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/shield.png","effects":[],"_id":"8LALEWMaXU1K8tOL"}
{"name":"Masquerade Charade (Tragedy)","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb07/masquerade-charade-tragedy.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"212\" height=\"256\" />\"This pair of superlative masquerade masks are not only striking in and of themselves but also stand out as deliciously discordant as a set. This is thanks to the striking dissimilarities between them. Though both present with the same baroque patterns, embellishments, and curlicued, bell-adorned swirls; their coloration, expressions, and themes couldn&rsquo;t be more disparate. One is a rich red and conveys a smile so contrived it feels almost like a sneer, while the other is a deep blue and reveals a sadness that is so stilted it seems more akin revulsion.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The set of twin masks known as Masquerade Charade was created by a visionary playwright who turned his hand to production and directing after becoming disillusioned with how his librettos were being &lsquo;butchered&rsquo; whilst making the transition to the stage. This ambitious trailblazer hoped that the creation of these masks marked the beginning of an explorative expedition into the true possibilities of magic-enhanced method acting. However, they never saw use in the theater after he asked two actors to don them for all their waking hours. One went on to kill himself, while the other was incarcerated for levels of exuberance and recklessness deemed dangerous for society.\"</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Attunement Requirement</strong>.&nbsp; Masquerade Charade includes two pieces, @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.IGwjX3pnJ09LFaqS]{Masquerade Charade (Comedy)} and Masquerade Charade (Tragedy).&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">For any of Masquerade Charade&rsquo;s other features to function, two Medium or Small humanoids must be wearing and attuned to one of its masks each.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Twinned Timing</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Creatures wearing Masquerade Charade&rsquo;s masks share an intrinsic, unspoken bond. When two creatures wearing the masks make an initiative check while within 60 foot of each other, only the one with the highest bonus to initiative makes the check, doing so with advantage. Both creatures act on this result, choosing each round which one will act first. If they cannot agree on who should act first, they should each roll a D20 to determine the order, with the creature with the highest result going first.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tragedy</strong>. The creature wearing this particular mask adopts a pessimistic outlook and a miserable, morose, and otherwise gloomy demeanour.</p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tragic Flaw</strong>. You gain the following flaw while wearing this mask<span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">: &lsquo;I believe almost all endeavours are doomed to end in failure.&rsquo;</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Perpetual Pessimist</strong>. You have advantage on checks made to resist being charmed while wearing this mask.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Misfortunate</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If you roll 1 on an ability check while wearing this mask, you start to cry uncontrollably for 1 minute, until they take damage, or until another creature uses an action to shake you out of it.</span></span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":18700000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/headgear.png","effects":[],"_id":"8XzUsfW9vBxCeZ6M"}
{"name":"Final Sting","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb02/final-sting.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"244\" height=\"256\" />\"This set of iron claws sits comfortably within the palms of their wearer, held in place by two ring-like loops that slide over the pinkie and index fingers. They are comfortable and easy to conceal due to two clever features of their design. Firstly, the claws are spring-loaded, neatly and safely folding into themselves as the creature wearing them </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">curls their fingers into a fist. Secondly, the blades protruding from either side are similarly designed to spring open, and lock into place with a satisfying click when not needed. Consequently, when a creature wearing these bagh nakh closes its fist completely, only a set of innocuous rings can be seen. Though bagh nakh have fallen out of favor of late, these insidious implements remain popular amongst assassins, political agents, and certain monastic orders; and are as quiet, efficient, and deadly as ever. Once belonging to a nameless killer-for-hire who was as notorious for his deeds as he was his anonymity, Final Sting has claimed kings and queens alike, and has proven to be a useful asset in any assassin's arsenal.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Final Sting can be used as a set of two bagh nakhs.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Rule Clarification: Bagh Nakh.</strong> Rules for bagh nakhs can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>An Assassin's Tool</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Final Sting has been developed with a singular purpose in mind, to take life, and it accomplishes this task with startling efficacy. Roll 3 damage dice for critical hits made with it, instead of 2. Additionally, attacks made using Final Sting deal an additional 1d4 damage to creatures that are surprised.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Concealed Killer</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Final Sting is subject to a powerful enchantment that allows you to slip it undetected into places that might be otherwise difficult to gain access to while armed. Once either bagh nakh is placed onto your hand, you can close your fist and then uncurl your pinkie or index finger before gently tugging the ring from it. The ring comes away easily and as it does so the implement vanishes without a trace other than the two rings, which remain. It then reappears only if both rings are placed on their correct digits at the same time or the pair are touched together. In this way, one or both pieces of Final Sting can be completely concealed until the creature in possession of the set is ready to make use of them</span>.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":2,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","piercing"],["","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":6600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"8lVswtrlEl7nGAMe"}
{"name":"Whaler's Harpoon","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This barbed throwing implement is similar in length and form to a spear, though it has a silklen spool of light-weight rope affixed to it. It is used to snare sea creatures and haul them aboard a ship or hoist them onto shore. The object's wood is stained darkly red and the implement has seen much use over the years. It was most famously used to skewer a particularly voracious shark that preyed on a port known as Ableton Anchorage for several seasons.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Whaler's Harpoon can be used as a harpoon with a 50 ft. silk rope attached to it via a spool.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Harpoon.</strong> Rules for harpoons can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Big Game Hunter</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Whaler's Harpoon is designed with the express purpose of 'landing' juvenile whales and larger sea creatures in mind. You are able to grapple creatures up to two sizes larger than you while using a rope with the harpoon's Special weapon property.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Reeled</strong>. With a flick of the wrist, the spool on the Whaler's Harpoon reels its way back to you. You can recall it as a bonus action, causing it to move 10 feet closer to you. If you have a creature grappled with the Whaler's Harpoon, this creature is dragged along with the harpoon.</span></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Barbed</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Whaler's Harpoon's jagged edge cuts and tears with startling efficacy. As a bonus action, you can shockload its line by abruptly jerking on the rope while you are using it to grapple a creature. If you do so, the ensnared creature is released, however it takes 2d4 piercing damage as the harpoon rips free.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":9,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":true,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":13100000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"8um8Gk3B68TblmsO"}
{"name":"Cutlass of the Corsair","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb05/cutlass-of-the-corsair.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"135\" />\"As flashy as it is functional, this curved saber and scabbard is of a fine quality and has seen use in exotic locales the world over. Leather wraps tightly bind its guard and give it a comfortable and firm grip. While most such implements merely hang from their wielder's hip when not in use, this particular edge comes complete with a red leather belt and scabbard which requires the blade to be turned as it is inserted into its housing, effectively rolling into place.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Cutlass of the Corsair is the perfect arm of a rakish cad or swashbuckling freebooter and has accompanied a myriad of such individuals over the years, always at their side or within arm's length of them lest their luck should turn. These cheerful chancers have always somehow gotten by on their luck, sharp wit, and this strange sword.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Cutlass of the Corsair can be used as a scimitar.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Barbed Words</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The weapon of a knave, the Cutlass of the Corsair can aid in the delivery of cutting </span></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">words as easily as it can a cutting blow. As a bonus action, you can hurl an insult at a sentient creature that you share a common language with while within 5 feet of the blade or wielding it, in order to throw them off-guard. If you do so, the target must succeed on a DC 13 Charisma saving throw or else they make opportunity attacks against you with disadvantage until the start of their next turn.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Always Welcome</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">For some reason, the individual who carries the Cutlass of the Corsair just has one those faces that's instantly familiar. Bar, inn, and tavern staff are perpetually convinced that they recognize you while it is within 5 feet of you, and that they like you. In all but the most scrupulous of bars, where the management are sticklers for policy and pricing, you're able to arrange accommodation, order drinks, and purchase food at half the usual rate.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Well-Traveled</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Cutlass of the Corsair has, at one time or another, passed through most of the ports throughout the known world, no doubt its latest owner will too. You have a certain advantage when traveling to exotic and far-flung hubs in that you are able to mimic the accent and speech patterns of the people of a particularly region flawlessly, as long as you've heard a group of indigenous people from the area speak for at least an hour. This can include conversing with them, or merely listening to them talk in a public area, such as a bar or tavern.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":5000000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"8vk1yoJtbIygOQWV"}
{"name":"Barkskin Barrier","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb01/barkskin-barrier.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"182\" height=\"256\" /></span></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Though this rough-hewn shield may appear as any other strip of uncarved wood, it is every bit as hardy, durable, and tough as folded steel. A rudimentary leather clasp on its inside provides ample purchase for a creature to grip the shield and hold it aloft. Its exterior surface is rugged and coarse to the point of being abrasive, its gnarled outer rim sharp and jagged, and its inside facade smooth and polished.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Ripped from the remains of a chestnut treant, the Barkskin Barrier has a profound affinity to trees. So much so that its wielder feels a great sense of calm while in open, wooded areas, and an oppressive sense of foreboding and confinement while in subterranean locations or inside great stone citadels and fortresses.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor.&nbsp;</strong>Barkskin Barrier can be used as a shield.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Take Root (1/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The stalwart Barkskin Barrier can be as implacable and stubborn as a tree. You can command the shield to take root </span>as a reaction to being pushed or shoved<span class=\"fontstyle0\">&nbsp;while standing on soil, grass, or soft earth. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you do so, thick roots shoot out from the shield and into the ground, granting you advantage on saving throws made to resist being forcibly moved until the start of your next turn. This benefit extends to include the triggering action.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Treesense</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Barkskin Barrier is a friend to all trees and bonded to them. While</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> within a densely wooded area&mdash;such as a woodlands,</span> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">forest, or jungle&mdash;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, you are aware of the presence, movements, and actions of all visible Medium or larger creatures within 60 foot of you, </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">so long as you're carrying or holding the Barkskin Barrier. Additionally, you get a vague sense of the physical description of any such creatures.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Kind to Kindling</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Barkskin Barrier neither condones nor permits the needless destruction of wood. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Should you start a fire using wood, enjoy the advantages of a log campfire, or do anything else that shatters, harms, or consumes; trees, kindling, or objects made of wood, you lose attunement to it and cannot attune to it again for 1d4 days.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"Being pushed or shoved while standing on soil, grass, or soft earth"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":2,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":20500000,"flags":{"mess":{"isBonusDamage":false,"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/shield.png","effects":[],"_id":"96NeJ993YbFG6mt4"}
{"name":"Morninglobe","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb06/morninglobe.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"111\" height=\"256\" />\"An intricate globe of the world sitting atop a metal shaft forms this curious, esoteric morningstar. A cartographer, explorer, or navigator acquainted with an atlas of their world will no doubt recognise familiar landmarks and landmasses immediately. The globe spins on an axis and parts of it grow light and dark naturally, in time with the movement of the relevant astral bodies. A creature who takes the time to study it closely might even notice that the surface of the morningstar's head is shrouded in small clouds and other little details that provide a scarily accurate map of the planet's current meteorological conditions.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Morninglobe is not an inherently malicious object, though it has a dark history behind it. The implement was originally created by a rogue mage who was working towards the completion of a powerful and terrible ritual that required the blood sacrifice of other magically gifted individuals. This despotic mage used Morninglobe to track the whereabouts of old friends, colleagues, and fellow wizards, many of whom he later killed.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Morninglobe can be used as a morningstar.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Global Insights</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">To a creature who takes the time to study it properly, Morninglobe can reveal much about the world:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can study Morninglobe's head to track the time of day, changes to temperature and season, and the weather throughout the world. Observing environmental patterns and cloud formations as they develop also provides you with advantage on checks made to predict upcoming weather conditions if you are experienced or versed in such things.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can nominate up to ten creatures or objects. The precise location of each of these is then highlighted on its surface in real time, revealed by distinctive lights. In order to nominate a creature or object to track, you must be touching them. Creatures that are hidden from scrying are immune to Morninglobe&rsquo;s magic. Should you attempt to exceed the maximum number of creatures or objects being tracked, you must choose one that you're tracking already and replace it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A unique light appears just above Morninglobe's head and reveals its current position in the world via a spotlight. The light disappears if it enters a different realm or plane, or it is more than a mile underground.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can only use Morninglobe to track things on your plane of existence.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+@mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":7000000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"9ccjtIbVESdQViBF"}
{"_id":"9eVMvzRDt2nA78qs","name":"Cure Wounds","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A creature you touch regains a number of hit points equal to [[/r 1d8]] + your spellcasting ability modifier. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1039\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the healing increases by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":""},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","healing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d8"},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":2600001,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"betterRolls5e":{"quickDamage":{"context":{"0":""},"value":{"0":true},"altValue":{"0":true}}}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/heal-jade-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9qeCH4dgAmwSxdyM","name":"Alter Self","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You assume a different form. When you cast the spell, choose one of the following options, the effects of which last for the duration of the spell. While the spell lasts, you can end one option as an action to gain the benefits of a different one.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"7\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Aquatic Adaptation.</span></span> <p>You adapt your body to an aquatic environment, sprouting gills and growing webbing between your fingers. You can breathe underwater and gain a swimming speed equal to your walking speed.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"8\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Change Appearance.</span></span> <p>You transform your appearance. You decide what you look like, including your height, weight, facial features, sound of your voice, hair length, coloration, and distinguishing characteristics, if any. You can make yourself appear as a member of another race, though none of your statistics change. You also can't appear as a creature of a different size than you, and your basic shape stays the same; if you're bipedal, you can't use this spell to become quadrupedal, for instance. At any time for the duration of the spell, you can use your action to change your appearance in this way again.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"9\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Natural Weapons.</span></span> <p>You grow claws, fangs, spines, horns, or a different natural weapon of your choice. Your unarmed strikes deal [[/r 1d6]] bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage, as appropriate to the natural weapon you chose, and you are proficient with your unarmed strikes. Finally, the natural weapon is magic and you have a +1 bonus to the attack and damage rolls you make using it.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":13200001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-alter-self.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"nKxzIdsxY7XBmhyf","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-alter-self.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"9z01aXXfC5clq9hG","name":"Disintegrate (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A thin green ray springs from your pointing finger to a target that you can see within range. The target can be a creature, an object, or a creation of magical force, such as the wall created by <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#wall%20of%20force_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'wall%20of%20force_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >wall of force</a>.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>A creature targeted by this spell must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the target takes [[/r 10d6 + 40]] force damage. The target is disintegrated if this damage leaves it with 0 hit points.</p><p>A disintegrated creature and everything it is wearing and carrying, except magic items, are reduced to a pile of fine gray dust. The creature can be restored to life only by means of a <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#true%20resurrection_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'true%20resurrection_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >true resurrection</a> or a <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#wish_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'wish_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >wish</a> spell.</p><p>This spell automatically disintegrates a Large or smaller nonmagical object or a creation of magical force. If the target is a Huge or larger object or creation of force, this spell disintegrates a 10-foot-cube portion of it. A magic item is unaffected by this spell.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"126\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 7th level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 3d6]] for each slot level above 6th.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["10d6 + 40","force"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":6,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a lodestone and a pinch of dust","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"3d6"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":8600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-disintegrate.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Pin of the Excavator","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This brightly-colored brooch has a cheap, flimsy, and almost-gaudy look about it. It depicts the stylized bust of a mummified body encased in a dark black outline. At a glance, it looks like something acquired at the kind of tacky souvenir stall that might be found on the outskirts of a large city. Though it isn't, and this misdirection is intentional.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Made by an archeologist and historian who fancied himself an intrepid explorer and favored field research to sitting in stuffy libraries, the Pin of the Excavator was designed to protect its creator from traps, curses, and worse. Its creator also made sure that it didn't look like the kind of thing that someone would want to steal from him, in case he ended up dead in a dungeon somewhere and it was the only thing watching over him and warding him against evil.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Shroud of Protection</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature wearing the Pin of Excavator is well-prepared to venture into the deep, dark places of the world. The brooch affords you the following advantages:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have a +1 bonus to Wisdom (perception) or Intelligence (investigation) checks made to notice magical or mechanical traps.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Whenever you trigger a magical or mechanical trap, there is a 5% chance that the trap fails to activate.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once per long rest, when you trigger a magical or mechanical trap and take damage as a result, you can immediately spend one of your hit die as a reaction. If you do so, roll the die, add your Constitution modifier to the result, and reduce the amount of damage received by this amount.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While wearing it, your physical remains cannot be reanimated through necromancy.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Should you attune to a cursed magic item while wearing it, you can make a check to end your attunement to the object once per day with a 5% chance of success.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":8200000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"A9mARd3gAwiUM6jI"}
{"name":"Whytewern","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This fine example of hide armor represents one of the more unique objects that an adventurer is likely to encounter throughout their storied travels and thrilling adventures. Unlike other kinds of armor, it is able to shift its form to match that of its wearer when their own form changes. Though it remains as armor, it resembles barding specifically developed to accommodate the creature in question. Should an elf wildshape into a spider it might cover their body and legs up to and including their coxa, trochanter, and femur. Whereas, it might instead cover the body, upper legs, and shoulders of a bear; or the entirety of a fish with just an opening for its tail and small slits for its gills. In each instance, whatever form the shapeshifter has adopted appears to have vitiligo while they occupy it when wearing this protection. Once back in their usual form, the armor bears a striking resemblance to whatever beast they most recently assumed the form of, though afflicted with albinism. For example, if they turned into a wolf, the amor might appear to be made from an albino wolf's pelt.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Whytewern was created by an unusually irksome and irate druid who simply refused to be confined to a single form, transforming into all manner of beasts and animals. Consequently, he manufactured this unusual, magical armor that was designed to be able to accommodate his love for assuming the forms of many creatures.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Whytewern can be worn as hide armor.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Attunement Requirement.</strong> Only a druid or a creature capable of Wildshaping is able to attune to Whytewern.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Shaper's Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As per the wishes of its creator, Whytewern's magical blessings allow it to mold itself to meet the ever-changing needs of its wearer. It reconfigures and resizes itself as necessary to ensure that it can always be worn by you when you wildshape, irrespective of what form you take. While wildshaped, you appear to have vitiligo. While in your humanoid form, the object resembles armor formed of whatever form you last assumed, except an albino version of it.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Pack Leader</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The curious barding marks you as unique to others of your species. While wildshaped you seem more dominant and imposing to other beasts as a result of being more unique and distinct from them. This provides you with advantage on Wisdom (animal handling) checks made to interact with others of the species that you've wildshaped into. However, other alphas of the species may see you as a threat.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":12,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":12,"type":"medium","dex":2},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":12700000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/medium-armor.png","effects":[],"_id":"ADuyhUjONjqYn9Bd"}
{"_id":"APZBr7yOxF6bZrt4","name":"Shocking Grasp (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Lightning springs from your hand to deliver a shock to a creature you try to touch. Make a melee spell attack against the target. You have advantage on the attack roll if the target is wearing armor made of metal. On a hit, the target takes [[/r 1d8]] lightning damage, and it can't take reactions until the start of its next turn.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The spell's damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] when you reach 5th level ([[/r 2d8]]), 11th level ([[/r 3d8]]), and 17th level ([[/r 4d8]]).</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"msak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8","lightning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"cantrip","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":6700001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-shocking-grasp.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"AUiwxrH1WSSqwNcz","name":"Jump (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You touch a creature. The creature's jump distance is tripled until the spell ends.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a grasshopper's hind leg","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":9700001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-jump.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"AXTXPFhmpdljncAt","name":"Green-Flame Blade (SCAG)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>As part of the action used to cast this spell, you must make a melee attack with a weapon against one creature within the spell's range, otherwise the spell fails. On a hit, the target suffers the attack's normal effects, and green fire leaps from the target to a different creature of your choice that you can see within 5 feet of it. The second creature takes fire damage equal to your spellcasting ability modifier.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>This spell's damage increases when you reach higher levels. At 5th level, the melee attack deals an extra [[/r 1d8]] fire damage to the target, and the fire damage to the second creature increases to [[/r 1d8]] + your spellcasting ability modifier. Both damage rolls increase by [[/r 1d8]] at 11th level and 17th level.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"SCAG","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["@mod","fire"],["1d8","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a weapon","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"cantrip","formula":"{{spellcasting_mod}}"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":11900001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/scag-greenflame-blade.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ApCR7XduCHS08hAJ","name":"Frost Fingers","permission":{"default":-1,"ZTQ5MTU5OTJhOWMx":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Freezing cold blasts from your fingertips in a 15-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a Constitution saving throw, taking [[/r 2d8]] cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The cold freezes nonmagical liquids in the area that aren't being worn or carried.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"7\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"IDRotF","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d8","cold"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":12200001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Robes of the Conjuror","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb06/robes-of-the-conjuror.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"125\" height=\"256\" />\"Grandiose to the point of being ostentatious, these princely red robes serve as both a fine example of what a little magical talent can do to one's ego, and a warning against such hubris. Fusing fabric and metal, the robe's collar is formed of a lightweight alloy that is designed not to encumber its wearer, while the silken fabric that drapes down beneath it ensures that their deliberate movements and gestures go unimpeded when casting spells.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">These robes were created at a renowned university for the magically gifted, by one of its teachers who specialized in the school of conjuration. The tutor in question was relatively junior when he earned his esteemed position&mdash;the result of good fortune and timing&mdash;however, he didn't let this serve to temper his pride at receiving tenure in his new role. The unfortunate tutor disappeared when a lesson went horribly wrong and he was accidentally relocated to another plane of existence, one less tolerant of his hauteur attitude. The robes were located, and subsequently conjured in a later lesson, however the tutor was never found.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Conjuror&rsquo;s Tricks</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You gain the following benefits while wearing the Robes of the Conjuror:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When you cast a spell that belongs to the Conjuration school, your spell save DC for the spell is increased by 1.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A +3 bonus is applied to the result of your Intelligence (arcana) checks made to identify spells if they belong to the Conjuration school.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A +3 bonus is applied to your checks to dispel the magic of a Conjuration spell.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can cast the <em>Find Familiar</em> spell in half the usual time and without spending the normal material component cost</span>.</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":9300000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/clothing.png","effects":[],"_id":"ArFegtzdxFkffzFw"}
{"_id":"AsR9rhPO0himZR9M","name":"Eyebite","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>For the spell's duration, your eyes become an inky void imbued with dread power. One creature of your choice within 60 feet of you that you can see must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be affected by one of the following effects of your choice for the duration. On each of your turns until the spell ends, you can use your action to target another creature but can't target a creature again if it has succeeded on a saving throw against this casting of eyebite.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Asleep.</span></span> <p>The target falls <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#unconscious_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'unconscious_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >unconscious</a>. It wakes up if it takes any damage or if another creature uses its action to shake the sleeper awake.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"2\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Panicked.</span></span> <p>The target is <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#frightened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'frightened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >frightened</a> of you. On each of its turns, the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#frightened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'frightened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >frightened</a> creature must take the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#dash_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'dash_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Dash</a> action and move away from you by the safest and shortest available route, unless there is nowhere to move. If the target moves to a place at least 60 feet away from you where it can no longer see you, this effect ends.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"3\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Sickened.</span></span> <p>The target has disadvantage on attack rolls and ability checks. At the end of each of its turns, it can make another Wisdom saving throw. If it succeeds, the effect ends.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":6,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":12600001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-eyebite.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"QIp2OoBhRzl3v9MT","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-eyebite.jpg","label":"Concentration","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Grick Carnyx","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"tool","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb03/grick-carnyx.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"256\" />\"Standing at a little over eight-foot-tall when assembled, and reaching even greater heights when held aloft, this towering and impressive bronze object takes the form of a rarely encountered musical instrument, known as a carnyx. Also a wind instrument, this apparatus is functionally similar to a trumpet, although aesthetically the two appear very different. It is formed of a mouthpiece that the user holds at head height and blows into to produce a sound. This embouchure connects to a long, slender pipework tubing that is held upright and extends vertically up to a figurehead from which the note being played emanates. Due to the length of its cylinder, sounds produced by the carnyx are broadcast over the heads of those around it and can be heard out to great distances. For convenience, the instrument can be dismantled, breaking down into three smaller sections that are just a few feet in length each. This </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">particular carnyx has a very sinister appearance due to its snarling figurehead, which resembles a monstrous grick that has reared up and is ready to strike.</span></em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Grick Carnyx is an instrument of war, intended to motivate allied troops and spur them to victory, whilst also sowing confusion, disharmony, and fear in the ranks of opposing forces. Though its onerous sounds are not entirely unappealing, they are discordant and melancholic&mdash;not at all dissimilar from the desperate, guttural howls of a wounded beast that has been cornered.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Musical Instrument</strong>. The Grick Carnyx can be used as a horn.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Recitals (1/Day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">In the right hands, the Grick Carnyx is a very useful instrument, able to spur some to action and dash the morale of others. In order for you to play it, it must be assembled and held aloft in a space with a roof clearance that equals at least 7 foot + your height. Assembling or dismantling it takes 1 minute. Additionally, you can only play it if you are proficient in the use of wind instruments.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Grick Carnyx can be used to perform one of the following feats once per day:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong>Beastly Blast!</strong>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">At just the right pitch and intonation, the Grick Carnyx can produce a warble that mimics a trainer's whistle and agitates domesticated beasts. For up to 1 minute, you can use your action on each of your turns to recite this disruptive melody while playing the carnyx.</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&nbsp;At the commencement of the recital, all beasts of burden, steeds, hunting dogs, pets, and other domesticated beasts within 120 foot that can hear must attempt a DC 10 Wisdom saving throw, becoming unresponsive and despondent until the recital ends on a fail. While affected in this way the only action they can take on their turn is to defend themselves. A trainer or handler can attempt a DC 15 Wisdom (animal handling) check as an action to regain control of a creature affected in this way, ending the effect on them.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong>Deafening Ditty.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Used to produce a shrill, shrieking sound similar to that of a distressed bird, the Grick Carnyx can make it very difficult for creatures to concentrate. For up to 1 minute, you can use your action on each of your turns to recite this headache inducing melody. For the duration, creatures within 120 foot that can hear suffer a 1d4 penalty to their attack rolls and must make concentration checks each round if they have ongoing spell effects that require concentration.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong>Sound the Alarm!</strong>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Few things rouse sleepers back to the world of the waking more effectively than a sharp note played on the Grick Carnyx. As an action, you can use it to issue a stark warning to those around you. When you do so, all sleeping creatures that can hear within 120 foot wake up and can stand up from being prone immediately as a reaction.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Stampeders' Song!&nbsp;</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When used to play a stirring song of war, few things inspire courage and haste quite like the Grick Carnyx. For up to 1 minute, you can use your action on each of your turns to recite this inspiring call to arms. For the duration, allied creatures of yours within 120 foot that can hear you can take the Dash action as a bonus action on each of their turns.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":8,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"ability":"cha","chatFlavor":"","proficient":0,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":15900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/instrument.png","effects":[],"_id":"AtnVWiojXiJBkymt"}
{"name":"Spoor","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"To think that this ridiculous accoutrement could ever be worn as an accessory or for cosmetic purposes beggar's belief. Though this porcine snout might seem like a garish gift for a child, a revolting tool in the arsenal of a prankster, or else part of a disguise bordering on the absurd; in truth, it is none of these things.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Spoor is the snout of a boar that has been severed and dried to preserve it. A short loop of chord has been sewn into it at two points so that it can be pulled over a humanoid's existing nose and fastened securely in place. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Why a creature would want to do such a thing isn't immediately obvious given how ridiculous Spoor makes them look and how disgusting the hollowed snout might appear to be. However, for most, the advantages that this curious object has to offer provides more than enough incentive to dismiss how ridiculous they'll look while wearing it.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Keen Smell</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature wearing Spoor benefits from enhanced senses. You have advantage on Wisdom (perception) checks that rely on smell while wearing it. This doesn't affect your passive Perception score&mdash;unless its use is connected to a discovery relating to a scent, odor, or other smell&mdash;and the game master always has final ruling on whether a smell or odor is downwind of you or cannot be detected for some other reason. You might use this to, for example, detect if living creatures have passed through an area recently; locate specific herbs, plants, and reagents; or tell if a natural cave is occupied by predators or not.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Bloodhound</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">All non-magical creatures leave some kind of a trace in their wake. W</span>hile wearing Spoor, you add your proficiency bonus to Wisdom (survival) checks made to track creatures, as long as they passed through your area within the last 48-hours, it hasn't rained since they were nearby, and there isn't another, overwhelming smell present in the area. If you are already proficient in Survival, you instead add double your proficiency bonus. Additionally, if the creature being tracked is of the beast subtype, you roll your ability check with advantage.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":0.1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":13700000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"AxukZjlQidY9m2z0"}
{"name":"Wracket","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Right at home in the hands of a brutal enforcer, cruel heavy, or the unscrupulous lieutenant of some criminal syndicate, this large, two-handed maul looks every bit as mean and wicked as many of those who might choose to wield it. It has a long wooden handle that has been painted a bright red color, however this has faded and receded to a blackish shade from years of heavy use. Around two thirds of the way up the object's shaft, cast-iron metalwork replaces the wood and continues upward to form the head of the maul. The metal is jagged and rough, much like the wood beneath it. Weighty and hefty, large and imposing, and jagged and haphazard in nature, Wracket is a maul that is designed to intimidate and elicit feelings of fear from those who see it. Historically, it has most commonly been used by those involved in protection rackets where cruel enforcers extort money from vendors, homeowners, and others.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Wracket can be used as a maul.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Thuggish</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Wracket is brutally effective at intimidating and terrorizing others. It provides the following benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You deal +1 bonus damage on attacks made with Wracket.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You deal 1d6 extra damage to objects that aren't being worn or carried when attacking with Wracket.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You have advantage on Strength checks to break down doors and barricades while you are wielding Wracket.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Objects smashed by Wracket make an audible crunching sound reminiscent of bones cracking or being shattered to those who hear it.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Upheaval (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Wracket's destructive power threatens everything around it. When you use it to strike an object that isn't being worn or carried, you can choose to make your attack a critical hit. When Upheaval is activated, fragile objects within 5 foot of you that are not being worn or carried also take 1d6 damage. This ability resets at dawn.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":10,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6 + @mod +1","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":true,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":13300000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"B0bbGmpGSy3UeE1e"}
{"name":"Murgrog's Black Label Rum","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>\"This corked bottle contains a liquor known as Murgrog's Black Label Rum, as attested to by its label which showcases a ferocious kraken in the middle of tearing a ship in half. And the liquid interned within the flask is no less impressive than the depiction that adorns it. This fluid is jet black for several hours after being shaken, however its coloration begins to change after the container been left to sit. This occurs as the black substance within it separates from the transparent ethanol and settles to the bottom of the container.</em></p>\n<p><em>Murgrog's Black Label Rum is legendary amongst seafaring folk. It is said that the bottle contains ink taken from an actual kraken and that's why it changes color. It is also said that it's so brutally strong that a creature who takes a swig from it experiences a burning sensation across their body so pronounced that it feels like being keelhauled. Reported side effects include; breathlessness, uncontrollable crying, involuntary incontinence, begging for mercy, and even death&mdash;though these are likely tall tales. For his part, Murgrog does nothing to decry them, enjoying all the attention his latest tipple has garnered.\"</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Piratey Punch</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Distilled by mighty Murgrog himself, Murgrog's Black Label Rum is renowned for its viciousness. When full, this brutal bottle of booze contains 6&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">generous shots of Grog. Each time a creature imbibes a shot from it, they should roll 1d8 and reduce the result by their Constitution modifier. They are intoxicated by the liquor for a number of hours, if any, equal to the result of this roll. Should a creature already intoxicated in this way consume another shot of Murgrog's Black Label Rum before its effects wear off, the duration is extended by 8 hours minus their Constitution modifier. Any intoxicated creature that completes a long rest without imbibing any more shots must make a DC 13 Constitution saving throw at the end of the rest, ending their intoxication and triggering the rum's hour-long after effects on a success. If a creature has taken a shot and has not become intoxicated due to their Constitution modifier being higher than their result, they must roll twice&nbsp;</span>and take the higher result when taking any subsequent shots until they haven't taken a shot for at least 1 hour.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The statistics of a creature intoxicated by Murgrog's Black Label Rum are modified in the following ways:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Their Strength and Charisma modifiers increase by +2 when making ability checks or saving throws.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Their Dexterity, Wisdom, and Intelligence modifiers decrease by -1 when making ability checks or saving throws.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">For 1 hour after a creature intoxicated by Murgrog's Black Label Rum sobers up, they suffer a -1 to their Constitution modifier for the purposes of calculating ability checks and saving throws and suffer 1 level of exhaustion.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The rum within the bottle of Murgrog's Black Label Rum refills itself to full by an amount of liquid equal to 1d6 shots each dawn.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Loose Lips</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It is difficult to think or speak straight while under the influence of this powerful beverage. A creature intoxicated by Mugrog's Black Label Rum as per its&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Piratey Punch&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">feature, has disadvantage on Charisma (deception) checks.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"special","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":6,"max":"6","per":"charges","autoDestroy":false},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"potion","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":21000000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/potion.png","effects":[],"_id":"BJj50CbL0Jw1DNzr"}
{"name":"Phantasmal Rail","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb08/phantasmal-rail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"248\" height=\"256\" />\"Once belonging in the bathroom of a stately home, this gothic curtain rail has clearly not been used in some time and has long since lost its tarred canvas curtain. It was once gold plated although the gold has chipped in places, and dulled in others. Perhaps most strikingly of all, the rail appears to be steadily emitting a thin wispy fog. This vapor disperses quickly if it is disturbed or while the rail is in motion, however any time it is still, the fog coalesces to form a thin film that looks just like the canvas curtain it has lost. Sometimes a humanoid male's face appears behind the ghostly, spectral curtain for a moment, or a hand can be seen brushing against it from beyond.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Unsurprisingly, the Phantasmal Rail has a dark history. Its former owner was slaughtered getting out of the bathtub by one his adulterous wife's spurned lovers after a messy altercation, his spirit now tethered to the last thing he touched. Tragically, his trapped soul is no longer able to tell its sorry tale, reveal the identity of the person who murdered him&mdash;who is likely long since deceased themselves&mdash;, </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">or find true and lasting peace. While nothing approaching justice may be achieved in this lifetime, or perhaps the next, the addled spirit bound to the Phantasmal Rail is determined to aid the creature to which it is linked.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Phantasmal Rail can be used as a quarterstaff.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Grasping Hands</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The ghostly presence anchored to the Phantasmal Rail is not idle in protecting the creature who safeguards its last link to the mortal coil. When you use the Phantasmal Rail to make an attack against a Medium or smaller creature and score a critical hit, a frightening spectral form bursts from the mist surrounding curtain rail. The target of the triggering attack must attempt a DC 18 Wisdom saving throw. On a failure, it is frightened until the start of your next turn.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Shifting Temperament</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Though the ghostly presence anchored to the Phantasmal Rail works to protect the creature who bears it, its mood is fickle and liable to change quickly from benevolent to belligerent. The ghost anchored to this object is always present and can interact with the world at will. Roll a d6 each dawn and record the result. On a result of 1-2, the game master controls the ghost and it attempts to make a nuisance of itself. On a result of 3-4, the ghost does nothing. On a result of 5-6, you control the ghost. The ghost functions as per the spell </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><em>Mage Hand</em>, except </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">directing it does not cost an action. The disposition of the ghost improves or sours with your fortunes. Anytime you score a natural 20 on an ability check, attack roll, or saving throw, a cumulative +1 bonus is added to the recorded d6 roll (max 6). Conversely, any time you roll a 1, the ghost's mood grows darker and a -1 penalty is applied to the tracked result (minimum 1).</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Macabre Manifestations</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The spirit that haunts the Phantasmal Rail frequently makes its presence known in the following ways:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">There is often an uncomfortable chill around it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A light mist emanates from it. When the object is not in motion, this pervasive mist wraps itself into the form of the screen that once hung from it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The distant sound of sobbing, screaming, and discordant whispers can sometimes be heard in the presence of it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You sometimes leave bloody footprints behind you.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It is often wet to the touch, and you often wake from sleep with wet hair.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":"1d8 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":7800000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"BQqbYc6MOvD7FUUK"}
{"_id":"BX7HBPAweeExbcBu","name":"Incite Greed","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>When you cast this spell, you present the gem used as the material component and choose any number of creatures within range that can see you. Each target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> by you until the spell ends, or until you or your companions do anything harmful to it. While <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> in this way, a creature can do nothing but use its movement to approach you in a safe manner. While an affected creature is within 5 feet of you, it cannot move, but simply stares greedily at the gem you present.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>At the end of each of its turns, an affected target can make a Wisdom saving throw. If it succeeds, this effect ends for that target.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"AI","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a gem worth at least 50 gp","consumed":false,"cost":5000,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":3300001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Veteran's Vesture","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Despite its ceremonial purpose, this fine dress uniform is tailored to be as comfortable as it is smart. The garment is black with a gold trim, and its coat is outfitted with a stand up collar, epaulets, and a matching set of gold cufflinks. Several chevrons adorn its left shoulder, marking its wearer as a senior officer, while a purple and gold sash with a tassel at the base is draped across the other. Lastly, a set of platinum cufflinks add an additional air of grandeur to the piece.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Veteran's Vesture was the dress uniform of a ranking military officer who served in his nation's armed forces for many years. Though he rarely had cause to wear this exquisite garment, he took it everywhere with him and keeping it clean, pressed, and folded were some of his favorite hobbies.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Veteran's Instinct</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The person who first wore the Veteran's Vesture endured many ambushes by his enemies, able to escape each intact. When you are surprised while&nbsp;</span>wearing it, you and up to five companions within 30 feet of you can still take Dodge action on your turns in the surprise round. Allies who were not surprised can still act as normal on their turns.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Lingering Memories</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Memories permeate the Veteran's Vesture like blood might stain a cotton shirt, both forever marked by the touch of such things. While wearing it, you have advantage on checks made to recall military tactics and traditions; as well as lore about wars and pivotal battles throughout history. Additionally, you have advantage on Charisma (persuasion) checks made to interact with soldiers and you can pass yourself off as a soldier without having to make Charisma (deception) checks even if you aren't a soldier. Lastly, you gain several aches and pains that you're not used to, strong cravings for coffee and cigarettes, and a nagging weirdness about your left leg&mdash;often accompanied by the sensation that you lost it somehow or that it was amputated even if that isn't the case.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":13000000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/clothing.png","effects":[],"_id":"CEtrIB4zsjsy5YGb"}
{"name":"Fireflute","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"tool","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This long, end-blown flute is formed from a giant reed that has been dried, perforated with a series of six finger holes, and had a brass mouthpiece installed to protect the fragile object from accidental damage on the part of its player, or neyzen. The object has been treated with some kind of resin designed to increase its durability, which gives it a sleek, reflective sheen. Other than for a series of sketches of a dancing fire djinn running down its shaft, the instrument looks perfectly mundane.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Musical Instrument</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Fireflute can be used as a flute.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Fire Charmer</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">While playing the Fireflute, you can attempt to charm a fire elemental to do your bidding. If you do so, you can choose a fire-aligned elemental being with a challenge rating of up to 1 that can hear the flute&rsquo;s melody and have it make a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw, becoming charmed by you on a fail. An elemental charmed in this way follows your commands to the best of its ability as per the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><em>Dominate Monster</em>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">spell, but it repeats its saving throw at the end of each of its turns. Fire elementals above challenge 1 cannot be charmed in this way but can be temporarily compelled to complete a basic action as per the spell </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Command</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">. This feature can only be used to affect one elemental at a time and an elemental that makes its save cannot be affected in this way again for 24 hours.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Fire Affinity</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">While the fireflute is being played, its tune imparts several interesting effects:</span></span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Listeners feel a warm tingling sensation.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Lit candles, campfires, torches, and other small fires dance, flicker, and sway in time with the melody.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You gain a preternatural sense if any creatures that you can see within 60 foot are vulnerable to fire damage.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can detect the presence of fire-aligned elementals up to a challenge of 5 within 1 mile. Though you cannot determine their number, challenge, or precise location.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"ability":"cha","chatFlavor":"","proficient":0,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":15800000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/instrument.png","effects":[],"_id":"CNfQjEGvcWJUGSx1"}
{"name":"Rechabubu","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb09/rechabubu.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"244\" height=\"256\" />\"This ceramic tea set is formed of china and has a wonderfully ornate appearance thanks to its unique dragon motif. Stylized artist's impressions of dragons have been painted across its porcelain surface in fine red brush strokes, and the tea pot's handle and spout are also cleverly designed to resemble a long, slender wyrm. In addition to the pot itself&mdash;complete with removable lid&mdash;, the set also comprises a serving tray and ten handleless cups, which share the pot's exquisite aesthetic.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Rechabubu originally belonged to a traveling monk who took it with him on a twenty-seven year, or ten-thousand days to be more specific, pilgrimage. Everywhere the monk ventured, he earned a reputation for being able to cure diseases and infirmities. Though wide-spread, these claims have never been fully substantiated. The monk's name has been lost to time, however his china tea set was declared an artifact of religious significance by the priest who undertook his funeral rites upon his death. It was stolen less than a year later and hasn't been recovered since.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Healing Tea (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">There's nothing quite like a good cup of tea, doubly so when it's laced with restorative arcane energies. Once per day, you can use Rechabubu to brew a special tea. It takes 10 minutes to properly prepare this concoction and it must be consumed within 1 minute of brewing. There is enough to fill all 10 of the set's cups, however a creature can only benefit from drinking this tea once per day. When a creature imbibes the special brew, they gain each of the following benefits:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">They can pick one of their hit die and roll it to recover hit points without expending it.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If they're suffering from a disease, they immediately make a check to overcome it with advantage.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">As long as it doesn't kill them outright, they can ignore the adverse effects of their highest level of exhaustion. Though their current level of exhaustion doesn't decrease and they still gain levels of exhaustion as usual.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tea Time</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">It's tea time all the time when Rechabubu is around. The teapot is magical in nature and can be used to pour fresh, piping hot tea any time, even if it is not placed over a fire or near a heat source, doesn't have tea leaves in it, and is bone dry. All you need to do in order to pour tea from the teapot's spout is lift it over one of the set's 10 cups and pour.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tea Ceremony</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tea ceremonies have long been a part of many faiths and traditions. If you are casting a divination spell as a ritual, you complete the ritual 5 minutes faster if you incorporate Rechabubu into your preparations.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":8,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":15400000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/potion.png","effects":[],"_id":"COwdU1tVm6phSLsb"}
{"name":"Woodland Warriors' Chainmail","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb04/woodland-warrior-mail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"112\" height=\"256\" />\"This set of armor</span></em><em>&mdash;</em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">formed of a long, flowing chain shirt, tabard, and helm&mdash;has often found itself employed in the service of paladins, wardens, and clerics dedicated to protecting nature and preserving the natural world. It has a strong unicorn motif worked into its design, complete with a spiked helmet and a depiction of a unicorn's head evident across its green tabard.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Much like the legendary unicorns for which it is styled, the Woodland Warriors' Mail rightfully belongs to any guardian of sacred woodlands, and it has a curious habit of making its way into the possession of one who might be viewed or described as a true 'child of the forest'.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Woodland Warriors' Mail can be worn as chain mail armor.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Attunement Requirement</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Only a good-aligned creature can attune to the Woodland Warriors' Mail.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Favored of the Forest</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The forest aids the wearer of the Woodland Warriors' Mail, just as the wearer protects it. You gain the following benefits while wearing it in a woodlands, forest, or jungle:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">If you become lost at night, phosphorescent flowers and mushrooms, fireflies, and glow worms begin to manifest around you. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">These light sources provide dim light around you out to a distance of 5 foot.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The weather tends to be favorable to your immediate needs and intentions.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You find small bunches of fruit and nuts, as well as small fetishes made out of leaves and twigs, left close to your camp each morning as gifts.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">If you, or anyone traveling with you, successfully attempts a Wisdom (survival) check to hunt game, you find nuts, berries, recently deceased carcasses, and other substitute foodstuffs; prior to any living creatures.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You're more easily able to pass without notice as creatures tracking you have disadvantage on checks made to do so.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You can detect the presence of any tree over a century old within 1 mile of you, as well as sense the presence of any dryads out to the same radius.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">If you fail a check made to navigate and get lost, woodland critters sometimes appear to help you get back on track.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":55,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":16,"type":"heavy","dex":0},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":13,"stealth":true,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":13200000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/heavy-armor.png","effects":[],"_id":"CYzeGEf54v7l6KDY"}
{"_id":"Cyc029HwtbhLSqsY","name":"Glaive","permission":{"default":-1,"bOqyKS8LL2EWqEnK":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<div>\n\t\t\t<div><i>Martial weapon, melee weapon</i></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-4\">20 gp, 6 lb.</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-8 text-right\">[[/r 1d10]] slashing  - heavy, reach, two-handed</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<hr>\n\t\t<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"753\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Heavy.</span></span> <p>Creatures that are Small or Tiny have disadvantage on attack rolls with heavy weapons. A heavy weapon's size and bulk make it too large for a Small or Tiny creature to use effectively.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"754\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Reach.</span></span> <p>This weapon adds 5 feet to your reach when you attack with it. This property also determines your reach for opportunity attacks with a reach weapon.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"755\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Two-Handed.</span></span> <p>This weapon requires two hands to use. This property is relevant only when you attack with the weapon, not when you simply hold it.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":20,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"None","identified":false,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d10 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"hvy":true,"two":true,"rch":true,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"ver":false,"mgc":false,"nodam":false,"faulldam":false},"proficient":true},"folder":null,"sort":500001,"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"items.html","source":"PHB","hash":"glaive_phb","data":{"item":{"name":"Glaive","source":"PHB","page":149,"srd":true,"type":"M","rarity":"none","weight":6,"value":2000,"weaponCategory":"martial","property":["H","R","2H"],"dmg1":"1d10","dmgType":"S","weapon":true,"_category":"Basic","entries":[],"_isEnhanced":true,"_fullEntries":[{"type":"entries","name":"Heavy","entries":["Creatures that are Small or Tiny have disadvantage on attack rolls with heavy weapons. A heavy weapon's size and bulk make it too large for a Small or Tiny creature to use effectively."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Reach","entries":["This weapon adds 5 feet to your reach when you attack with it. This property also determines your reach for opportunity attacks with a reach weapon."]},{"type":"entries","name":"Two-Handed","entries":["This weapon requires two hands to use. This property is relevant only when you attack with the weapon, not when you simply hold it."]}],"_typeListText":["martial weapon","melee weapon"],"_typeHtml":"martial weapon, melee weapon","_attunement":null,"_attunementCategory":"No","_fProperties":["heavy","reach","two-handed"],"_fMisc":["SRD","Mundane"],"_fValue":20,"_fTier":["none"],"_fIsMundane":true,"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Martial weapon, melee weapon"}}},"pick-up-stix":{"pick-up-stix":{"tokenData":{"width":1,"height":1}}}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/items/weapons/glaive.png","effects":[{"_id":"1WkK2Quc9JmWRsAR","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"transfer":true}},"changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.str.mod","value":"0","mode":2,"priority":0}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"New Effect","origin":"Item.Cyc029HwtbhLSqsY","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"name":"Riverreed Ewer","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb01/riverreed-receptacle.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"163\" height=\"256\" /></span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Despite being technically edible and looking somewhat like a fruit or vegetable, this strangely colored plant doesn't taste very nice. Besides which, it often retains toxins and impurities within it that, while no match for the iron constitution of a dwarf, can be harmful if imbibed. It does however serve another, equally useful purpose&mdash;that of a rainwater tank. This curious plant sucks moisture and </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">condensation from the air and stores them internally whereupon they can be siphoned and drank later.</span></span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Riverreed Ewer appears to be one-of-a-kind since no other similar plant has ever been discovered.\"</span></span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Remarkable Plant</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Riverreed Ewer is a wonder of the natural world. It possesses the following unusual abilities:</span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It acts as a rain catcher, collecting rain droplets, morning dew, and airborne vapor overnight. Unless it is covered over, it gathers enough water each night&nbsp;to hydrate 1d4 Medium or smaller humanoids for a day in all but the most arid environments.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It is deceptively deep and it acts as a filtration device. It can store enough water to hydrate 8 Medium humanoids for a day and water interned within it is purified; removing impurities, poisons, parasites, and diseases from it.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It sucks moisture from the atmosphere around it. Unless covered, it dehydrates creatures who spend time in close proximity to it. Additionally, it can be used to dry wet clothes and other items if they are left to hang near it.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As water passes through it, the Riverreed Ewer extracts and collects contaminants and impurities from it. These gather at the jug's bottom before being drawn through its soft substrate, crushed and treated until they form into a fine pearl worth 5 GP, and birthed out of the bottom of it. The leaves on the bottom of Riverreed Ewer curl inwards as the pearl begins to emerge&mdash;cupping it softly&mdash;and can be peeled back to release it afterwards. Each morning, there is a 1d10 chance of a pearl having formed overnight</span>.<br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":10300000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/goblet.png","effects":[],"_id":"D1rjolfUK05Q972y"}
{"_id":"DKDmBdAhO2FTIPAV","name":"Unseen Servant (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>This spell creates an <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#invisible_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'invisible_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >invisible</a>, mindless, shapeless, Medium force that performs simple tasks at your command until the spell ends. The servant springs into existence in an unoccupied space on the ground within range. It has AC 10, 1 hit point, and a Strength of 2, and it can't attack. If it drops to 0 hit points, the spell ends.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Once on each of your turns as a bonus action, you can mentally command the servant to move up to 15 feet and interact with an object. The servant can perform simple tasks that a human servant could do, such as fetching things, cleaning, mending, folding clothes, lighting fires, serving food, and pouring wine. Once you give the command, the servant performs the task to the best of its ability until it completes the task, then waits for your next command.</p><p>If you command the servant to perform a task that would move it more than 60 feet away from you, the spell ends.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"space"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":true,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a piece of string and a bit of wood","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":11600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-unseen-servant.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Dg09EFlOKGUFzcc4","name":"Spider Climb","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Until the spell ends, one willing creature you touch gains the ability to move up, down, and across vertical surfaces and upside down along ceilings, while leaving its hands free. The target also gains a climbing speed equal to its walking speed.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a drop of bitumen and a spider","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":14100001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-spider-climb.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"MB4qMYRL0CW67w3k","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-spider-climb.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Sanctus Roserium","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"What looks like any perfectly ordinary, utterly mundane set of prayer beads actually harbors a much closer link with the gods than might otherwise seem to be the case, one god in particular. This deity&mdash;known for being a virtuous advocate of compassion, forgiveness, and awareness&mdash;has tenets focused around absolution and redemption, and her followers speak often of the need to apply understanding and experience in all things.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Spellcasting Focus</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Sanctus Roserium can be used as a holy symbol.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Divine Protection (3/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature wearing Sanctus Roserium is shrouded in the protection of the gods. The prayer beads provide you with the following benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When you are the target of the harmful effect of an abjuration spell that requires you to make a saving throw, you have advantage on the check.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have advantage on saving throws made to resist being possessed.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You gain a +2 bonus to a saving throw that is triggered as a result of being hit by an attack.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This feature activates each time one of the conditions specified above occurs until it has activated 3 times, after which it doesn't function until the following day.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Bless Water (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once per day, you can use the Sanctus Roserium in place of the material components required to make holy water.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Relic Hunter</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Sanctus Roserium is intrinsically linked with all holy objects, and it shares a measure of this divine insight with those around it. It gives off a faint glow whenever there are unclaimed religious relics within 120 foot.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Confession (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Sanctus Roserium is an accessory best befitting a priest or cleric. While wearing it, you can hear the confession of a creature whose alignment has changed and attempt to absolve them of their sins. To do so, you must touch one willing creature whose alignment has changed and make a DC 20 Wisdom check, restoring a target to its original alignment on a success. A paladin, doing this to another paladin, can instead use charisma to make this check. Hearing a creature's confession takes 1 hour and only 1 such check can be performed each day.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":9400000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"DiKmE0RfTnap5dpd"}
{"_id":"ENTG22d0va9w2uup","name":"Conjure Woodland Beings (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You summon fey creatures that appear in unoccupied spaces that you can see within range. Choose one of the following options for what appears:</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">One <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&2,flsttype:fey=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >fey creature of challenge rating 2 or lower</a></li><li class=\"rd__li \">Two <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&1,flsttype:fey=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >fey creatures of challenge rating 1 or lower</a></li><li class=\"rd__li \">Four <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&1/2,flsttype:fey=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >fey creatures of challenge rating 1/2 or lower</a></li><li class=\"rd__li \">Eight <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&1/4,flsttype:fey=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >fey creatures of challenge rating 1/4 or lower</a></li></ul><p>A summoned creature disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p><p>The summoned creatures are friendly to you and your companions. Roll initiative for the summoned creatures as a group, which have their own turns. They obey any verbal commands that you issue to them (no action required by you). If you don't issue any commands to them, they defend themselves from hostile creatures, but otherwise take no actions.</p><p>The DM has the creatures' statistics.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"125\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using certain higher-level spell slots, you choose one of the summoning options above, and more creatures appear: twice as many with a 6th-level slot and three times as many with an 8th-level slot.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"any","type":"space"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"one holly berry per creature summoned","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":8200001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-conjure-woodland-beings.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"EVGGpUaKceruJdF8","name":"Chill Touch (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You create a ghostly, skeletal hand in the space of a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the creature to assail it with the chill of the grave. On a hit, the target takes [[/r 1d8]] necrotic damage, and it can't regain hit points until the start of your next turn. Until then, the hand clings to the target.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If you hit an undead target, it also has disadvantage on attack rolls against you until the end of your next turn.</p><p>This spell's damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] when you reach 5th level ([[/r 2d8]]), 11th level ([[/r 3d8]]), and 17th level ([[/r 4d8]]).</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"round"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rsak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"cantrip","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":7700001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-chill-touch.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Tabard of the Raging Bull","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This knightly surcoat has been dyed a dark red and has the silhouette of a large bull painted onto its front and rear in white paint. The garment is tough and durable thanks to its thickness and weighs a considerable amount. On the tabard's rear, a murky stain on the fabric makes it appear as if the bull is sharply exhaling a puff of steam from its nostrils.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Tabard of the Raging Bull once belonged to a large, barrel-chested knight who possessed might and good humor in equal measure. He claimed that the bull was the national symbol for the country from which he hailed, though no one could say if this were true, where he actually came from, or what boat he arrived on. Whatever his origins, the knight earned great renown as a sellsword and brought his country, wherever it may lie, great honor. He later won a parcel of land and retired from the adventuring business to become an innkeeper.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Goring Dash</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Tabard of the Raging Bull instills an aspect of a minotaur's strength and ferocity in its wearer in a very literal sense. When you use your action to Dash while wearing it, you can use a bonus action to manifest a set of spectral horns and use them to gore one creature. You are considered proficient with the spectral horns and they deal 1d6 piercing damage on a hit. If you move at least 20 feet straight toward your target before hitting it with your spectral horns, they take an extra 1d4 piercing damage.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Bull's Brawn</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Bulls are mighty, though a creature adorned in the Tabard of the Raging Bull may be mightier still. You gain a 1d4 bonus to Strength (athletics) checks while wearing it. Additionally, if you are called upon to make a Strength saving throw, you can use your reaction to roll 1d4 and add the result to your check.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Cattle Affinity</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Smelling strongly of their kind, the Tabard of the Raging Bull speaks to the spirit of cattle. While wearing it, you have advantage on Wisdom (animal handling) checks made to influence bulls and cows.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":2000000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/clothing.png","effects":[],"_id":"EWXXNCPVektQKD8T"}
{"_id":"EY3OKXru2qcyOZqj","name":"Skywrite","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You cause up to ten words to form in a part of the sky you can see. The words appear to be made of cloud and remain in place for the spell's duration. The words dissipate when the spell ends. A strong wind can disperse the clouds and end the spell early.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"XGE","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"spec","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"spec"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":true,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":14500001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/xge-skywrite.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"7LjxZrVsnWNTxKS8","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/xge-skywrite.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Zaru-Macaque","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"tool","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb08/zaru-macaque.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"92\" height=\"256\" />\"Standing at almost three foot in height, this macabre drum prominently features three skulls which are stacked vertically to form the drum's shaft. A closer inspection reveals that these are not real skulls but are actually elaborate ivory carvings. Each skull has a pair of skeletal hands affixed to it, though each set is posed a little bit differently to the others. The hands cover the mouth of one skull, the ears of another, and the eyes of the last. Atop the highest skull sits a gilded crown which has thick, durable canvas stretched across it to form the drum head. Peculiarly, the order of the skulls, or perhaps rather their pose, changes from time to time.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Musical Instrument</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zaru-Macaque can be used as a drum.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">No Evil (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zaru-Macaque is an especially useful tool in hands of swift-tongued bards and rogues whose mouths sometimes move too swiftly for their minds. Once per day, when you attempt a Charisma (deception) check while playing Zaru-Macaque, you can immediately attempt to smooth over a bungled deceit. You must announce your intention to do so after attempting your roll but before the GM determines the result. If you do so you still attempt the deception however all creatures close enough to have heard it simply ignore, overlook, or otherwise disregard the lie as if hadn't been uttered.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Kikiwamirez (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The spirit of a wild and ferocious, six-armed ape called Kikiwamirez resides within&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zaru-Macaque. As an action, you can call the ape forth once per day. Should you do so, Kikiwamirez appears in an unoccupied space you can see within 30 foot of you. The ape is under your control and psychically obeys your commands to the best of its ability for 1 minute or until it drops to 0 hit points, at which time it disappears until it is summoned again. Kikiwamirez acts at the end of the initiative order.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 14px; font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Kikiwamirez.</strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 14px; font-style: italic;\"> Statistical information necessary to use Kikiwamirez in combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.fbNHrd2osuiBoYDV]{Kikiwamirez}</span><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 14px; font-style: italic;\">.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Veiled Alignment</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zaru-Macaque's three expressionless, skeletal faces are as inscrutable as the creature who bears them. Your alignment cannot be determined by scrying magic while you are carrying it.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"ability":"cha","chatFlavor":"","proficient":0,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":20000000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/instrument.png","effects":[],"_id":"EpInmaJeEJ5zGEvJ"}
{"_id":"FCWdw24S9gNOHorq","name":"Enlarge/Reduce","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You cause a creature or an object you can see within range to grow larger or smaller for the duration. Choose either a creature or an object that is neither worn nor carried. If the target is unwilling, it can make a Constitution saving throw. On a success, the spell has no effect.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If the target is a creature, everything it is wearing and carrying changes size with it. Any item dropped by an affected creature returns to normal size at once.</p><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"5\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Enlarge.</span></span> <p>The target's size doubles in all dimensions, and its weight is multiplied by eight. This growth increases its size by one category—from Medium to Large, for example. If there isn't enough room for the target to double its size, the creature or object attains the maximum possible size in the space available. Until the spell ends, the target also has advantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws. The target's weapons also grow to match its new size. While these weapons are enlarged, the target's attacks with them deal [[/r 1d4]] extra damage.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"6\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Reduce.</span></span> <p>The target's size is halved in all dimensions, and its weight is reduced to one-eighth of normal. This reduction decreases its size by one category—from Medium to Small, for example. Until the spell ends, the target also has disadvantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws. The target's weapons also shrink to match its new size. While these weapons are reduced, the target's attacks with them deal [[/r 1d4]] less damage (this can't reduce the damage below 1).</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a pinch of powdered iron","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":13100001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-enlargereduce.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"7FCJvcq65NC3IUEs","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-enlargereduce.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Helm of the Murmillo","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb07/helm-of-the-murmillo.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"215\" height=\"256\" />\"This gruesome steel helmet is permanently stained with the blood of the gladiators who&rsquo;ve worn it in the arena, and those whose lives they&rsquo;ve snuffed out. Imposing spikes protrude from it in places, including its attached spaulders, while a quaff of feathers jut out from its rear. The helm&rsquo;s face plate is latticed with small holes that protect the face of its wearer, at the expense of their peripheral vision.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Helm of the Murmillo has long been favored by career fighters and champions of bloodsports who enter the ring not just for mere survival or sport, but as entertainers who relish appealing to the macabre bloodlust of their audience. These gladiators thrive on piercing shriek of a creature entering its final death throes, the gasps that accompany the sickening sound of crunching bones, and the raucous cheers that follow a particularly gruesome decapitation.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Horned Headbutt</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Even the hardest heads still yield to steel spikes. While wearing the Helm of the Murmillo, your unarmed strikes deal 1d6 + your Strength modifier piercing damage if you choose to headbutt a creature, instead of the bludgeoning damage normal for an unarmed strike. You do not require a free hand to headbutt a creature while wearing the Helm of the Murmillo.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Terrifying Tyrant</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature donning the Helm of the Murmillo strikes a horrifying visage. While wearing it, you have advantage on Charisma (intimidation) checks and disadvantage on Charisma (persuasion) checks.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Dramatic Effect</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Helm of the Murmillo appeals to those who love the limelight, possess great showmanship, or thrive on the roar of a bloodthirsty crowd. While you are wearing it, the viscera that results from injuries you inflict or sustain is noticeably more gory, sounds of battle within 30 feet of you are dramatically intensified, and your strikes often lead to violent overkill.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":6700000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/headgear.png","effects":[],"_id":"FCXLYo2Sk2njxAhu"}
{"_id":"FKP0mJqfF2kn59pJ","name":"Bestow Curse","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You touch a creature, and that creature must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become cursed for the duration of the spell. When you cast this spell, choose the nature of the curse from the following options:</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">Choose one ability score. While cursed, the target has disadvantage on ability checks and saving throws made with that ability score.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">While cursed, the target has disadvantage on attack rolls against you.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">While cursed, the target must make a Wisdom saving throw at the start of each of its turns. If it fails, it wastes its action that turn doing nothing.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">While the target is cursed, your attacks and spells deal an extra [[/r 1d8]] necrotic damage to the target.</li></ul><p>A <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#remove%20curse_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'remove%20curse_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >remove curse</a> spell ends this effect. At the DM's option, you may choose an alternative curse effect, but it should be no more powerful than those described above. The DM has final say on such a curse's effect.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"3\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>If you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the duration is concentration, up to 10 minutes. If you use a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the duration is 8 hours. If you use a spell slot of 7th level or higher, the duration is 24 hours. If you use a 9th level spell slot, the spell lasts until it is dispelled. Using a spell slot of 5th level or higher grants a duration that doesn't require concentration.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":""},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":500001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/haste-fire-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FKQUnz6pkYBuW5Qc","name":"Levitate","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>One creature or loose object of your choice that you can see within range rises vertically, up to 20 feet, and remains suspended there for the duration. The spell can levitate a target that weighs up to 500 pounds. An unwilling creature that succeeds on a Constitution saving throw is unaffected.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The target can move only by pushing or pulling against a fixed object or surface within reach (such as a wall or a ceiling), which allows it to move as if it were climbing. You can change the target's altitude by up to 20 feet in either direction on your turn. If you are the target, you can move up or down as part of your move. Otherwise, you can use your action to move the target, which must remain within the spell's range.</p><p>When the spell ends, the target floats gently to the ground if it is still aloft.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"either a small leather loop or a piece of golden wire bent into a cup shape with a long shank on one end","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":13800001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-levitate.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"4sTohog08js2VLhT","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.ConditionalVisibility","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-levitate.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Corralop Clutch","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This simple pull-cord pouch doesn't look especially fancy or as a likely receptacle for priceless valuables, despite the awe and gasps the things pulled from it often elicit. Rather, it appears as a worn leather coin purse with a slightly unusual, clamshell design. The leather used to&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">form the object has been pulled taut over a metal framework, and the item has a plush satin inner lining. It snaps shut with a satisfying click when closed.</span></em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Corralop Clutch appeals to two very disparate types of people for very different reasons. Anxious and nervous individuals find comfort in its ability to enable them to carry tremendous wealth about their person without fear of robbery. Meanwhile, ploy of the desperate, opportunistic, and reckless, it also allows callous schemers to trick others into giving them whatever they want. Though such deception has led to the downfall of many whose crimes have eventually caught up to them.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Magical Mix-up</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Corralop Clutch can hide a fortune just as easily as conjure one from almost nothing. Precious and semi-precious stones interned within it for at least 5 minutes are glamored to resemble worthless trash objects for 24-hours after removal. For example, diamonds may appear as lumps of coal, a zircon as broken pottery, and pearls as mere marbles. Meanwhile, the </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">same trick also works in reverse. Worthless objects placed within Corralop Clutch for at least 5 minutes appear as precious stones for 24-hours after removal. For example, a fragment from a broken brick might appear as a sliver of moonstone, a pebble as a spinel, or a broken finger nail as a small sapphire. Each object glamored in this way has a value equal to the result of a d6 x 50 GP. The total combined value of all objects affected in this way at once cannot exceed 500 GP. Exceeding this limit causes the illusion affecting all object to end simultaneously and Corralop Clutch ceases to function for 24 hours.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The true nature of objects affected by Corralop Clutch can be discovered with a DC 15 Intelligence (investigation) check or revealed through the use of spellcasting, such as the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><em>Detect Magic</em>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">spell. Otherwise, the illusion appears to be genuine until the objects revert to their true forms.</span></p>\n<blockquote style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Rule Clarification, Defined Item Values.&nbsp;</strong>Although this feature specifies the value of items affected by Corralop Clutch</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">, this doesn't determine how much an NPC in a game might offer a PC for their purchase. Just like all equipment has a specific value, the figures provided simply confer a baseline valuation for the purposes of comparing their worth against other items. NPCs may arrive at different valuations, be generous, be stingy, or be inclined to haggle as the GM sees fit.&nbsp;</span></p>\n</blockquote>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"weight","value":0,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":14300000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/backpack.png","effects":[],"_id":"FNt0PRv8jJidzMoH"}
{"_id":"FZ6hj53qE3LQHbMl","name":"Calm Emotions (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You attempt to suppress strong emotions in a group of people. Each humanoid in a 20-foot-radius sphere centered on a point you choose within range must make a Charisma saving throw; a creature can choose to fail this saving throw if it wishes. If a creature fails its saving throw, choose one of the following two effects.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>You can suppress any effect causing a target to be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> or <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#frightened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'frightened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >frightened</a>. When this spell ends, any suppressed effect resumes, provided that its duration has not expired in the meantime.</p><p>Alternatively, you can make a target indifferent about creatures of your choice that it is hostile toward. This indifference ends if the target is attacked or harmed by a spell or if it witnesses any of its friends being harmed. When the spell ends, the creature becomes hostile again, unless the DM rules otherwise.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"cha","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":11800001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-calm-emotions.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Empyrean","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb04/empyrean.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"179\" height=\"256\" />\"This illustrious shield is formed in its entirety from heavy stained glass in much the same style as that commonly found in churches and other religious sites, its dense structure held securely within a silver frame. If there were any doubt as to its legitimacy as a bulwark to the righteous, its ability to withstand blows that should not only shatter glass but sunder most other shields ought prove its magical divinity, rather than its superior form.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Empyrean once sat in its rightful place at the zenith of a great basilica. That structure, named after the fields of purple flowers that grew around it, was a site of tremendous religious significance until it fell into a great fissure that opened up during an earthquake many years ago. The individual depicted in the stained glass is that of the basilica's patron and first protector as he preached amongst the lisianthus flowers outside the shrine on the day of the summer solstice. Bizarrely, it is all that remains of the temple.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Empyrean can be used as a shield.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Dazzling Radiance (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Some signs are subtle, but when Empyrean issues a sanction, there is no mistaking its righteous condemnation. Once per day, as an action you can utter a command word while wielding it. If you do so, the shield erupts with holy light in a 15 foot cone, dazzling those who behold it. Creatures caught in the blast that can see and don't have their eyes covered must attempt a DC 8 Constitution saving throw. On a fail, they have disadvantage on attack rolls until the start of your next turn. Undead creatures affected by this feature have disadvantage on their saving throw and those who fail it also take 1d4 radiant damage and are incapacitated for the duration. Additionally, the light emitted from the shield is so intense that it continues to glow for 5 minutes after this feature is activated, shedding bright light out to a distance of 10 foot and dim light a further 10 foot.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Blessed Be The Earth (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Just as its wielder can feel a touch of the divine lingering over them, Empyrean can also be used to bathe the ground around it in holiness. You can undertake a ritual with the shield once per day that takes 1 hour to perform. During this ritual, the shield must be laid on the ground and cannot be moved or disturbed. For 24 hours after the ritual is complete, the ground in a 30 foot cube centered on where Empyrean was placed during the ritual fills with purple flowers and is considered consecrated ground. During this time, the ground becomes difficult terrain for undead creatures and they have disadvantage on Dexterity saving throws while in the affected area. Once 24 hours has elapsed, the ground returns to whatever state it was in before the ritual was performed.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Divine Shieldbearer</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Empyrean makes for an impressive and imposing aegis, commanding attention and reverence from those who behold it. While bearing it, you can add double your proficiency bonus to Charisma checks made to influence deeply religious people&mdash;such as acolytes, clerics, cultists, and priests&mdash;as long as you're proficient in the skill that you're using.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":2,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":4200000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/shield.png","effects":[],"_id":"FZCVKbkbAJ1Za2Ro"}
{"name":"Fehln's Legacy","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb01/fehlns-legacy.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"89\" height=\"256\" /></span></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This exquisite set of gloves and boots is formed from what appears to be four paws cut from a bear. In truth, the creature they were taken from was a half-elf druid who had wildshaped into a bear. Why he did not simply revert to his human form upon death is a mystery that shall perhaps never be answered. Tellingly, it seems much of the magic that permeated him in life remains within this set of garments, lying dormant until needed.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Fehln's Legacy can be used as a set of two cestuses.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong style=\"font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification: Cestus.</strong><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"> Rules for cestuses can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Bear's Strength</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Fehln's Legacy imbues its wearer with the strength and ferocity of a bear. You are affected in the following way while wearing its pieces on your hands and feet:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your carrying capacity is calculated with your Strength score multiplied by 20, instead of 15. This also affects the limit of how much weight you can push, drag, or lift.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You&rsquo;re considered to have proficiency in the Athletics skill, and gain double your proficiency bonus on Strength (athletics) checks if you are already proficient in it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You cannot grasp or hold objects, and you&rsquo;re unable to interact with complicated or fiddly ones.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your movement speed increases by 10 foot so long as your hands are empty and you&rsquo;re able to move on all fours.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can choose to deal bludgeoning or slashing damage when attacking with Fehln's Legacy.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":2,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","bludgeoning"],["","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":5400000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"FiGssL2vnt4S7rr9"}
{"_id":"FvV5hvhW0Me6no6r","name":"Tasha's Hideous Laughter (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A creature of your choice that you can see within range perceives everything as hilariously funny and falls into fits of laughter if this spell affects it. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or fall <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#prone_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'prone_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >prone</a>, becoming <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#incapacitated_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'incapacitated_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >incapacitated</a> and unable to stand up for the duration. A creature with an Intelligence score of 4 or less isn't affected.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>At the end of each of its turns, and each time it takes damage, the target can make another Wisdom saving throw. The target has advantage on the saving throw if it's triggered by damage. On a success, the spell ends.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"tiny tarts and a feather that is waved in the air","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":11500001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-tashas-hideous-laughter.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Captain Dreadwing's Diorama","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb05/captain-dreadwings-diorama.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"241\" />\"This one-of-a-kind diorama proudly displays a stuffed parrot that has been mounted atop the bust of a small tropical island. The scene has been expertly designed, showcasing the talents of a fine taxidermist and artisan modeler. The parrot at the center of the piece is dressed as a pirate, sporting a tricorn, eyepatch, and pegleg; and embellished with a small replica scimitar that hangs from its hip.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Captain Dreadwing's Diorama belonged to a cautious and calculating pirate who preferred assembling models to pilfering treasure. In life, his beloved pet parrot kept an eye out while he rested, in case any enterprising members of his crew who saw him as a weak leader attempted to slit his throat in his sleep. Unfortunately, one such individual did eventually poison Dreadwings. In response, the captain created this diorama, both in memoriam and also as an ace up his sleeve if the same individual were to come after him or attempt to turn the rest of the crew against him&ndash;bestowing upon the object a number of blessings that would be useful should he ever find himself marooned on a remote island.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Providing Parrot</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Captain Dreadwing's Diorama was created to aid an individual trapped alone somewhere inhospitable. It possesses the following unusual properties:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Its base is actually a basin that contains 4 pints of clean drinking water and refills each morning at dawn.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tiny coconuts or bunches of bananas grow on its palm trees each morning at dawn, providing 1d4 fruit identical to the berries created by the spell </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Goodberry</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Though inanimate, the taxidermy parrot that serves as its centerpiece is considered to have blindsight out to a range of 30 foot and a passive Perception score of 15. It notes the presence of creatures around it when it is taken out and set down. Should it notice the approach of additional Small or larger creatures, it squawks loudly and flaps its wings.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The small replica scimitar that hangs from its taxidermy parrot's flank grows into a real scimitar&mdash;though still pretty small&mdash;if you utter the command phrase, 'Dreadwings want a cracker?'. The scimitar can be used as a cutting tool and functions as a dagger that deals slashing damage instead of piercing. The same phrase can be used to make the foil revert back to being a tiny replica so that it can be replaced after use.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Captain Dreadwing's Diorama can learn and recite up to ten simple phrases that its parrot repeats on your command.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":7,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":14100000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"GAIKNFpXvElI9lGL"}
{"name":"Monstrous Matryoshkas","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This mephistophelian set of stacking dolls is diabolical in more senses than one. The four piece collection of brightly painted oval-shaped dolls is designed so that each of them can be split in half, with the next in line fitting snuggling inside it. Each doll in the set is decorated to resemble a different kind of demon, with the largest resembling a marilith; followed by a hezrou, balor, and quasit respectively. Within the quasit doll rests a small vial of dark, foul-smelling blood.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Monstrous Matryoshkas provide a safe place to intern that which doesn't truly belong on the physical plane, demon blood. How, and indeed why, the small vial stored within them steadily fills with something so abhorrent isn't clear, however that doesn't stop the process repeating again, and again, and again.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Demonic Defences</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A creature closely aligned with the Monstrous Matryoshkas benefits from the same innate protection against magic as demons. You gain a +1 bonus to saving throws against spells and other magical effects while carrying it.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Beastly Blood</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Monstrous Matryoshkas can provide great power, for one willing to partake in the drinking of demon blood. You can drink the small vial of blood that is contained within the smallest doll as an action. If you do so and return it to the set, the vial refills after 24 hours. The vial of blood always fills with the blood of one type of demon and confers powers related to the type of demon it is linked to. Roll a d4 to determine what benefits a creature who drinks the blood gains:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">1. Marilith</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The effects of this blood last for 1 minute. During this period, the imbiber can add a +3 bonus to their AC against one attack that would hit them as a reaction. In order to use this feature, they must be wielding a melee weapon and able to see the attacker.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">2. Hezrou</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The effects of this blood last for 10 minutes. During this period, any creature that starts its turn within 5 foot of the imbiber must succeed on a DC 13 Constitution saving throw or be poisoned until the start of their next turn. On a successful throw, the creature is immune to this feature for 24 hours.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">3. Balor</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The effects of this blood last for 1 minute. During this period, at the start of each of the imbiber's turns, each creature within 5 foot of them takes 1d4 fire damage, and flammable objects in the affected area that aren't being worn or carried ignite. A creature that touches the imbiber or hits them with a melee attack while within 5 foot of it takes 1 fire damage.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">4. Quasit</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When the imbiber drinks this blood, they magically turn invisible until they attack, cast a spell, or 1 minute elapses. Any equipment they wear or carry also turns invisible.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"self","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day","autoDestroy":false},"consume":{"type":"charges","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"potion","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":18000000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/potion.png","effects":[],"_id":"GQr8pbwwnUSDDEgr"}
{"name":"Tandem Longsadyll","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb03/tandem-saddle.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"167\" />\"This long and ornate saddle is unusual in the sense that it is designed to accommodate two riders, instead of the usual one. It comes complete with a two comfortable, padded seats; two pairs of stirrups; and enough satchels, packs, and containers to easily allow a pair of riders to share a single steed, even for extended journeys. It is also has a uniquely exotic appearance, thanks to its overall design motif, which incorporates elaborate embroidery, dark leathers, and rich red tassels that hang down beneath it.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Tandem Longsadyll, along with the beast who bore it, once belonged to a pair of scouts. These two would ride ahead of the vanguard, one armed with a bow and concentrated on keeping a vigilant eye out for danger and signs of ambush, while the other focused on riding the beast and safely traversing their environment.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Second Rider.&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Tandem Longsadyll has two seats allowing a mount wearing it to accommodate a second rider, distributing the extra weight comfortably across its back and shoulders. A Medium creature wearing it can carry two Small creatures, instead of one; and a Large creature wearing it can carry two Medium or Small creatures, instead of one. For the purposes of calculating rider weight limits, only the weight of the larger creature counts towards a mount's carrying capacity. Only the creature in the saddle's front seat can control the mount.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Saddlebags.&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Tandem Longsadyll is as useful to a common traveler as it is a pair of hardened veterans, riding tandem into a ferocious battle. It provides ample storage up to a mount's carrying capacity.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Extra Perks. </strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Many riders grow attached to their steeds, however a horseman equipped with the Tandem Longsadyll can forge a bond so significant with their mount that it borders on symbiotic. You gain the following perks whenever you place it on a mount:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You have advantage on Wisdom (animal handling) checks made to influence the mount, domesticate it, or train it to obey your commands.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can whistle at any volume and have the mount hear you up to 4 miles away. If you do this, the mount can identify your approximate distance and direction.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If the mount whinnies in distress or cries out in pain, you can hear its anguish from up to 4 miles away. If you hear it call out, you can identify its approximate distance and direction from you.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Should the mount be required to make any Constitution saving throws to avoid gaining levels of exhaustion as the result of undertaking a forced march for an hour, it has advantage on the check so long as it has only been bearing you for the duration.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":8,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"weight","value":0,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":17700000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/saddle.png","effects":[],"_id":"Gbsu0Mw7GGfx6HJA"}
{"_id":"H4wddADeterkcvZV","name":"Motivational Speech","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p class=\"rd__quote-line rd__quote-line--last\"><i>I once heard a motivational speech by Jim and it was the worst ninety seconds of my life. What does Omin see in him, anyway?</i></p><p><span class=\"rd__quote-by\">— Walnut Dankgrass</span></p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>You address allies, staff, or innocent bystanders to exhort and inspire them to greatness, whether they have anything to get excited about or not. Choose up to five creatures within range that can hear you. For the duration, each affected creature gains 5 temporary hit points and has advantage on Wisdom saving throws. If an affected creature is hit by an attack, it has advantage on the next attack roll it makes. Once an affected creature loses the temporary hit points granted by this spell, the spell ends for that creature.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"160\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>At Higher Levels. When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the temporary hit points increase by 5 for each slot level above 3rd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"AI","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":3600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Meditative Mat","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"Whether stowed or laid out flat, this unadorned charcoal grey mat could easily be mistaken for a bedroll, thanks to its lack of distinctive features to speak as to its origin and significance. When rolled up, two simple buckles fasten to keep it from unravelling, though it has a knack for accommodating its owners wishes even when these aren't employed. It originally belonged to a charlatan who purported to be a powerful psionist. He claimed that anyone could learn to use his unique gifts, if they could only focus their mind sufficiently to unlock their innate true potential. When he was exposed as a fraud, he had to sell most of his belongings to make ends meet, including this unusual mat.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Mindful</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Meditative Mat serves as a perfect venue for reflection and introspection.&nbsp;</span>You feel refreshed and focused i<span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">f you spend one hour using it to exercise or stretch, gaining temporary hit points equal to your </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Constitution modifier. Until you lose or replace these temporary hit points, you also gain a +1 bonus to Dexterity and Wisdom saving throws, a +1 bonus to checks made to maintain concentration, and a +1 bonus to Dexterity (acrobatics) checks. You can only benefit from using the Meditative Mat once per day.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":14500000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"HD9Z8icG725mWb4R"}
{"_id":"HJstHmL4WQ7Vxyqd","name":"Parry (Giant)","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><span style=\"color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">The death giant adds 6 to its AC against one melee attack that would hit it. To do so, the death knight must see the attacker and be wielding a melee weapon.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"self","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"folder":"","sort":100001,"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"betterCurses":{"isCurse":false,"curseName":"","formula":"","mwak":false,"rwak":false,"msak":false,"rsak":false}},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[{"_id":"cOTSnxUTIg11SE4O","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":"None","transfer":true}},"changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.ac.value","value":6,"mode":2,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":1,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Parry","origin":"Item.HJstHmL4WQ7Vxyqd","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"HMIWOf49Dancz5Ug","name":"Banishment","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You attempt to send one creature that you can see within range to another plane of existence. The target must succeed on a Charisma saving throw or be banished.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If the target is native to the plane of existence you're on, you banish the target to a harmless demiplane. While there, the target is <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#incapacitated_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'incapacitated_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >incapacitated</a>. The target remains there until the spell ends, at which point the target reappears in the space it left or in the nearest unoccupied space if that space is occupied.</p><p>If the target is native to a different plane of existence than the one you're on, the target is banished with a faint popping noise, returning to its home plane. If the spell ends before 1 minute has passed, the target reappears in the space it left or in the nearest unoccupied space if that space is occupied. Otherwise, the target doesn't return.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"11\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 4th.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"cha","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"an item distasteful to the target","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":1300001,"flags":{"dae":{"activeEquipped":false,"alwaysActive":false},"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/link-eerie-3.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"1kiHjLteqvORzJwX","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"transfer":false}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/link-eerie-3.jpg","label":"Concentration","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"HdH9wipiZJQRGXll","name":"Suggestion (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You suggest a course of activity (limited to a sentence or two) and magically influence a creature you can see within range that can hear and understand you. Creatures that can't be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> are immune to this effect. The suggestion must be worded in such a manner as to make the course of action sound reasonable. Asking the creature to stab itself, throw itself onto a spear, immolate itself, or do some other obviously harmful act ends the spell.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The target must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, it pursues the course of action you described to the best of its ability. The suggested course of action can continue for the entire duration. If the suggested activity can be completed in a shorter time, the spell ends when the subject finishes what it was asked to do.</p><p>You can also specify conditions that will trigger a special activity during the duration. For example, you might suggest that a knight give her warhorse to the first beggar she meets. If the condition isn't met before the spell expires, the activity isn't performed.</p><p>If you or any of your companions damage the target, the spell ends.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":8,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a snake's tongue and either a bit of honeycomb or a drop of sweet oil","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":6500001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-suggestion.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"HpKNCxyooQW3Gco5","name":"Alarm","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You set an alarm against unwanted intrusion. Choose a door, a window, or an area within range that is no larger than a 20-foot cube. Until the spell ends, an alarm alerts you whenever a Tiny or larger creature touches or enters the warded area. When you cast the spell, you can designate creatures that won't set off the alarm. You also choose whether the alarm is mental or audible.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>A mental alarm alerts you with a ping in your mind if you are within 1 mile of the warded area. This ping awakens you if you are sleeping.</p><p>An audible alarm produces the sound of a hand bell for 10 seconds within 60 feet.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":8,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cube"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":true,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a tiny bell and a piece of fine silver wire","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":2100001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/runes-royal-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Brummer","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"The perfect crook's companion, this dark leather sap has been used to silently subdue and suppress resistance during many home invasions, random attacks down backstreet alleys, and ambitious heists where early exposure could spell downfall for the would-be thieves. It has a molded leather grip that leads down to a short loop, designed to prevent the object being dropped or discarded during a scuffle. The leather is scuffed in places from repeated use, however the item has lost none of its potency.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon.&nbsp;</strong>Brummer can be used as a blackjack.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Rule Clarification, Blackjack.</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\"> Rules for blackjacks can be found in </span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">@Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Dastardly Sap</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Used properly, Brummer is as effective a tool to roguish types as any set of thieves' tools. It confers the following benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A surprised creature that is hit with Brummer must attempt a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or be stunned until the end of their next turn. Additionally, they cannot speak or cry out for 1d4 - 2 rounds.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Whenever you hit a humanoid creature with Brummer, they can only speak falteringly until the start of your next turn.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When you hit a creature with Brummer, they have disadvantage on any concentration check that they have to make as a result of that hit.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While wielding Brummer, you have advantage on saving throws made to avoid dropping it or being disarmed, and you impose disadvantage on checks made to disarm you.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Rule Clarification: Verbal Spells.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span style=\"color: #191813; font-style: normal;\">One of Brummer's features allows it to cause creatures to speak only falteringly. While a creature is only able to speak falteringly, spells that have verbal or spoken components have a 50% chance of failing. Should a spell fail in this way, the creature in question does not expend a spell slot, however they do waste whatever time or action they took to attempt to cast the spell.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":true,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":3100000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"HxKWmcTKzJhUYUjE"}
{"_id":"IPHZuOjKJhrwGIpK","name":"Blade Barrier (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You create a vertical wall of whirling, razor-sharp blades made of magical energy. The wall appears within range and lasts for the duration. You can make a straight wall up to 100 feet long, 20 feet high, and 5 feet thick, or a ringed wall up to 60 feet in diameter, 20 feet high, and 5 feet thick. The wall provides three-quarters cover to creatures behind it, and its space is difficult terrain.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>When a creature enters the wall's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/r 6d10]] slashing damage. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":100,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"wall"},"range":{"value":90,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["6d10","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":6,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":10300001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-blade-barrier.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"IiG8LXuyClgPDVU3","name":"Summon Shadowspawn","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You call forth a shadowy spirit. It manifests in an unoccupied space that you can see within range. This corporeal form uses the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#shadow%20spirit_tce\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'bestiary.html', 'TCE', 'shadow%20spirit_tce', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Shadow Spirit</a> stat block. When you cast the spell, choose an emotion: Fury, Despair, or Fear. The creature resembles a misshapen biped marked by the chosen emotion, which determines certain traits in its stat block. The creature disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The creature is an ally to you and your companions. In combat, the creature shares your initiative count, but it takes its turn immediately after yours. It obeys your verbal commands (no action required by you). If you don't issue any, it takes the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#dodge_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'dodge_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Dodge</a> action and uses its move to avoid danger.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, use the higher level wherever the spell's level appears in the stat block.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"TCE","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":90,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"tears inside a gem worth at least 300 gp","consumed":false,"cost":300,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":12500001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[{"_id":"quMipSVKi3JkCB5N","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"Ilr9WyGGhljpyKvu","name":"Thunderwave (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A wave of thunderous force sweeps out from you. Each creature in a 15-foot cube originating from you must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes [[/r 2d8]] thunder damage and is pushed 10 feet away from you. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage and isn't pushed.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>In addition, unsecured objects that are completely within the area of effect are automatically pushed 10 feet away from you by the spell's effect, and the spell emits a thunderous boom audible out to 300 feet.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"143\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cube"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d8","thunder"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":10900001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-thunderwave.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Ipw9vuQZrbVqkoKe","name":"Protection from Energy","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>For the duration, the willing creature you touch has resistance to one damage type of your choice: acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":14000001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-protection-from-energy.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"Zu7M02mHu48ZJBUt","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-protection-from-energy.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"IwX7iQSHpBKv14Hz","name":"Scrying","permission":{"default":-1,"bOqyKS8LL2EWqEnK":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You can see and hear a particular creature you choose that is on the same plane of existence as you. The target must make a Wisdom saving throw, which is modified by how well you know the target and the sort of physical connection you have to it. If a target knows you're casting this spell, it can fail the saving throw voluntarily if it wants to be observed.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><table class=\" stripe-odd-table\"><caption>Knowledge of Target</caption><thead><tr><th class=\"col-11\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\" >Knowledge</th><th class=\"col-1 text-center\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\" >Save Modifier</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"col-11\"  >Secondhand (you have heard of the target)</td><td class=\"col-1 text-center\"  >+5</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-11\"  >Firsthand (you have met the target)</td><td class=\"col-1 text-center\"  >+0</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-11\"  >Familiar (you know the target well)</td><td class=\"col-1 text-center\"  >-5</td></tr></tbody></table><table class=\" stripe-odd-table\"><caption>Connection to Target</caption><thead><tr><th class=\"col-11\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\" >Connection</th><th class=\"col-1 text-center\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\" >Save Modifier</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"col-11\"  >Likeness or picture</td><td class=\"col-1 text-center\"  >-2</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-11\"  >Possession or garment</td><td class=\"col-1 text-center\"  >-4</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-11\"  >Body part, lock of hair, bit of nail, or the like</td><td class=\"col-1 text-center\"  >-10</td></tr></tbody></table><p>On a successful save, the target isn't affected, and you can't use this spell against it again for 24 hours.</p><p>On a failed save, the spell creates an invisible sensor within 10 feet of the target. You can see and hear through the sensor as if you were there. The sensor moves with the target, remaining within 10 feet of it for the duration. A creature that can see <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#invisible_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'invisible_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >invisible</a> objects sees the sensor as a luminous orb about the size of your fist.</p><p>Instead of targeting a creature, you can choose a location you have seen before as the target of this spell. When you do, the sensor appears at that location and doesn't move.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":10,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"self","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":5,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a focus worth at least 1,000 gp, such as a crystal ball, a silver mirror, or a font filled with holy water","consumed":false,"cost":1000,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":null,"sort":900001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-scrying.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"834WtqgW16CfaPnr","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"transfer":true}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Concentraation","origin":"Item.IwX7iQSHpBKv14Hz","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"Ix6kmkPQbVHKkwRB","name":"Mislead","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You become <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#invisible_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'invisible_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >invisible</a> at the same time that an illusory double of you appears where you are standing. The double lasts for the duration, but the invisibility ends if you attack or cast a spell.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>You can use your action to move your illusory double up to twice your speed and make it gesture, speak, and behave in whatever way you choose.</p><p>You can see through its eyes and hear through its ears as if you were located where it is. On each of your turns as a bonus action, you can switch from using its senses to using your own, or back again. While you are using its senses, you are <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#blinded_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'blinded_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >blinded</a> and <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#deafened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'deafened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >deafened</a> in regard to your own surroundings.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":5,"school":"ill","components":{"value":"","vocal":false,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":10100001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-mislead.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"ydSROZ5iijA6a5EK","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"transfer":true}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Concentration","origin":"Item.Ix6kmkPQbVHKkwRB","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"JAtJBCIvyBBJgTxs","name":"Spirit Guardians","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You call forth spirits to protect you. They flit around you to a distance of 15 feet for the duration. If you are good or neutral, their spectral form appears angelic or fey (your choice). If you are evil, they appear fiendish.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>When you cast this spell, you can designate any number of creatures you can see to be unaffected by it. An affected creature's speed is halved in the area, and when the creature enters the area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/r 3d8]] radiant damage (if you are good or neutral) or [[/r 3d8]] necrotic damage (if you are evil). On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"142\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 3rd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d8","radiant"],["3d8","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a holy symbol","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":10800001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-spirit-guardians.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"dtuZLs4qpI6Gx6DJ","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-spirit-guardians.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"JBAK0iSEJSwufRMR","name":"Daylight (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A 60-foot-radius sphere of light spreads out from a point you choose within range. The sphere is bright light and sheds dim light for an additional 60 feet.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If you chose a point on an object you are holding or one that isn't being worn or carried, the light shines from the object and moves with it. Completely covering the affected object with an opaque object, such as a bowl or a helm, blocks the light.</p><p>If any of this spell's area overlaps with an area of darkness created by a spell of 3rd level or lower, the spell that created the darkness is dispelled.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":60,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":8500001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-daylight.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Eye of Ojib","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb08/eye-of-ojib.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"152\" height=\"256\" />\"This eerie dream catcher acts as a powerful ward for those who slumber under its vigilant gaze and has been carefully crafted to resemble a tower of three unblinking eyes. Its frame is made of willow bound together with purple string to form a web and is tipped with a pair of bird skulls; while a collection of bones, fangs, claws, feathers, beads, and gemstones dangle below it. Willow hoops are strung into the center of the dream catcher's eyes and a set of eldritch runes is stitched into each of its irises. The object radiates an amaranthine glow in the gloaming hours that lasts until dawn, giving it an unsettling appearance and creating a maudlin ambience around it.</em></p>\n<p><em>While there are several conflicting theories on who exactly the 'Ojib' was for whom the Eye of Ojib was named, the stories of the object's creation all weave a similar narrative. They speak of an old crone, gifted with power over the dark arts. The stories say that she crafted the dream catcher to protect her against the machinations of a vengeful spirit whom she had wronged. However, something went wrong and the object was unable to fulfil its purpose.\"</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Dreamwatcher</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The unsleeping Eye of Ojib maintains an unfaltering vigil over its charge. If it is hung within 30 foot of you, it grants you a measure of awareness while you're at your most vulnerable. While sleeping, you remain dimly conscious of your surroundings as if you were awake and you can choose to wake up as a reaction at any time.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Symbiotic Hibernation</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Eye of Ojib has steered more than one coven through a long, harsh winter. If you choose to, you and up to five willing creatures within 30 foot of you, can enter a special state of rest, during which your metabolisms slow and you're able to survive ten times longer than usual without eating or drinking and consume one-tenth the oxygen you normally would. You remain conscious of the passage of time while in this state and can choose to end the effect on yourself at any time as a bonus action. Anyone affected in this way wakes if the Eye of Ojib is disturbed, you move more than 30 foot from them, they're injured, they begin to asphyxiate, or if they take a level of exhaustion due to hunger or thirst.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Warded Sleep</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The foul beldam who created the Eye of Ojib had many enemies and intended for it to protect her from them all. All creatures within 30 foot of the Dream catcher are warded against scrying magic while sleeping.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":15200000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"JCu7T9n1umRIFsiO"}
{"name":"Alchemist’s Reserve","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"tool","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This collection of alchemist's supplies is of exceptional quality, design, and function. It comes complete with a variety of rare ingredients and has a series of small containers and receptacles designed to intern reagents with unusual requirements. It includes a small pouch, the interior of which is always dank and humid; a triangular box that has an aura of supernatural darkness within it; and an airtight vial that noise and vibrations cannot pass through.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The herbalist who assembled Alchemist's Reserve died in a mysterious fire that consumed both him and his store. What remained of his assets, including this kit, were later auctioned off by the benefactors of his estate. Suspiciously, many who have since owned these tools have met with similar misfortune. Though, perhaps this is more an indication of how dangerous and volatile the field of alchemy is, than a suggestion of foul play or some ancient curse.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tool.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Alchemist&rsquo;s Reserve can be used as a set of Alchemist&rsquo;s Supplies.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Better Equipped</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Alchemist's Reserve is compromised of superior instruments. You benefit from a 1d4 bonus to any alchemy checks you make while using it.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Alchemist Approved</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Alchemist's Reserve belongs in the hands of an expert. Alchemical items made using it are improved in the following ways:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Alchemist&rsquo;s Fire&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">deals 1d6 fire damage, in place of the usual 1d4.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Acid&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">deals double damage to objects.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Oil&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">set alight burns for an additional round.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Perfume&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">grants a +1 bonus to Charisma (persuasion) checks.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When imbibing a vial of&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Antitoxin</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">, a creature can immediately make a saving throw to end any ongoing effects related to poison with advantage on their check.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":8,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"ability":"int","chatFlavor":"","proficient":0,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":13800000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/tool.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"JlJQNk8i9lMkdiGu"}
{"name":"Champion's Caparison","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb10/champions-caparison.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"236\" />\"This heavy metal armor takes the form of barding in the style worn by a horse, most specifically one belonging to a prominent knight or esteemed commander. The barding is formed from metal plates that have been polished until they glisten and are molded to the shape of a large quadruped. Many of these plates are articulated and layered over each other to allow their wearer to move freely. Rich red-and-cream-colored cloth drapes down from the armor in numerous places, while its thick and comfy upholstered saddle is adorned in much the same way.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Champion's Caparison can be used by a quadrupedal mount as plate armor.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Commanding</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A steed adorned in the noble finery of the Champion's Caparison is befitting a commander of great repute. While riding a mount that's wearing it, your voice is amplified, doubling its volume and the distance from which you can be heard. Additionally, while your voice is amplified, you have a +1 bonus to Charisma (performance) checks related to public speaking or addressing groups of soldiers.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Readiness</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A battalion's readiness never exceeds that of its commander, doubly so when </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">that commander's steed wears the Champion's </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Caparison. While you are riding a mount that's wearing it, your allies fingers' find their buckles and catches more easily, clasps are always where they expect them to be, and that things fit into place more snugly. Such allies are able to don and doff armor at twice the usual speed while within 120 feet of you.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":130,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":18,"type":"heavy","dex":0},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":15,"stealth":true,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":700000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/saddle.png","effects":[],"_id":"JutYtmtheOJejFTC"}
{"name":"Thickpile Jerkin","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Worn beneath other clothes or armor, this thin undershirt is formed of a strange material quite unlike any of those in common usage. It appears to be some kind of fibrous yarn or thread that changes color under different lighting conditions&ndash;its flaxen tint sometimes appearing to be punctuated with a red streak and at other times infused with a blue one. The filament that forms this vest&mdash;whatever it is&mdash;is incredibly flexible, durable, and stretchy, able to extend to as much as eight times its original size. Consequently, though it seems like the garment might be a little bit too tight and restrictive to fit even a small creature, it can actually accommodate medium ones with ease and looks every bit as good on an orc or bugbear as it might a halfling or gnome. Once on, its elasticated strands create a sense of compression which manages to be reassuring without feeling confining.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Who or what manufactured the Thickpile Jerkin, as well as what material they used to perform such a feat, is something of an enigma. The object itself always attracts the interest and awe of weavers, needleworkers, tailors, and seamstresses.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Compressive</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Thickpile Jerkin is skintight, placing pressure on wounds and keeping them closed in much the same way that a securely fastened bandage might, and reminiscent of how handwraps are used to prevent swelling. Each time you take bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage while</span> wearing Thickpile Jerkin, the damage is reduced by 1 point.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Insulating</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Thickpile Jerkin acts as a thin layer of insulation whilst still remaining relatively breathable. While wearing it, you find it much easier to maintain a </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">comfortable body temperature and suffer the depredations of extreme conditions much slower than you normally would. It grants you advantage on checks made to resist suffering penalties as the result of hot or cold environments. You can, for example, forgo building a campfire while wearing it, even on the coldest night of the year.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Protection Against the Elements</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Whatever incredible polymers or fibers Thickpile Jerkin is formed of possess an innate resistance to both searing heat and frigid chills. The first time you take cold or fire damage while wearing it, you have resistance to the damage taken. Once this feature activates, the garment provides resistance to damage of the opposite element instead, swapping each time it activates. This trait resets to neutral each day at dawn.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":20100000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/clothing.png","effects":[],"_id":"JxnQ8n58K2TpZUVH"}
{"_id":"K3npMdxkFh60isNW","name":"Eldritch Blast (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A beam of crackling energy streaks toward a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target takes [[/r 1d10]] force damage.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The spell creates more than one beam when you reach higher levels: two beams at 5th level, three beams at 11th level, and four beams at 17th level. You can direct the beams at the same target or at different ones. Make a separate attack roll for each beam.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rsak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d10","force"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":4600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-eldritch-blast.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Ingastrimyte","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"As uncommon as ventriloquist puppets are already, this one is unusually unique thanks to its exquisite, and utterly misplaced, detailing. Impeccably painted, its brush strokes, flourishes, and overall preparation are so carefully administered that it looks hyper-realistic in some ways, whilst its accentuated and cartoonish proportions leave it looking plainly fake and false in others. Standing at a little over three foot tall, the dummy is adorned in a smart suit, complete with a bowtie and a top hat.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Ingastrimyte was created to be a magically-enhanced ventriloquist puppet, allowing for a relative amateur in the stagecraft of ventriloquy to perform extremely proficient acts. However, when the puppet was close to completion, it was bought by a wealthy aristocrat who, filled with grief over the recent death of his son, paid for the marionette to be finished off in a style reminiscent of his lost child.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Puppet&rsquo;s Perspective (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The bond between Ingastrimyte and the individual it considers its master is unusually strong. Once per day as an action, you can assume direct control of it for 1 minute, taking control of its motor functions and seeing through its eyes and hearing through its ears as if they were your own. Ingastrimyte has AC 10, 3 hit points, a Strength of 2, a Dexterity of 8, a 15 foot movement speed, and it can&rsquo;t attack. If it drops to 0 hit points, it reverts to just being an inanimate puppet again.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Dummy Divination (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Many of Ingastrimyte&rsquo;s former owners have dabbled with augury and clairvoyance, with surprising success. Once per day,&nbsp;</span>you can pick a skill or ability check as an action while it is within 5 foot of you. If you choose to do so, roll a d20, add any relevant ability modifiers or proficiency bonuses you have, and bank the result of the check. The next time you attempt this type of check before the next dawn, you must use the banked result instead of rolling.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Voice Throwing</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">All ventriloquists master the art of throwing their voice, though the job is made far easier with the aid of Ingastrimyte. You can throw your voice while it is within 5 foot of you, causing it to sound like your voice originates from a space that you can see within 60 foot.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":16500000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"K8ajKTdGNvXxtHDT"}
{"name":"Shangan (Battleaxe)","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb01/shangan.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"105\" height=\"256\" /></span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This large battleaxe is carved from rough wooden branches and held together by tough leather strips. Its butt splinters off into three sections which form a tripod, allowing it to stand upright freely if placed upon the ground. Meanwhile, the object's shaft also splits above its axehead to form a V-shape. A long elasticated band connects these two protrusions, enabling the axe to also be used as a slingshot.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Shangan can be used as a battleaxe and as a </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">@Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.XrcVGFwz4AE4bYIj]{Shangan (sling)}</span>.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Dual Purpose</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In the right hands, Shangan is both accurate and deadly. When you use it as a battleaxe, it confers a +1 bonus to damage. When you use it as a sling, it instead grants a +1 bonus to your attack rolls.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>A Test of Brawn</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Shangan is a hefty weapon to wield and it requires great strength to fully draw back the elasticated rubber band that holds its leather pad and ammunition. Whether being used as a battleaxe or a sling, attacks you make with it use your Strength modifier for the purposes of calculating attack and damage bonuses.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Violently Versatile</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It takes but a moment to set Shangan down and line up a shot. As a bonus action, you can choose to make a single ranged sling attack with it while wielding it. This attack is made with disadvantage.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod +1","slashing"]],"versatile":"1d10 + @mod +1"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":11600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"KAJfK4dxhIWnGcj0"}
{"name":"Sickle of the Crescent Moon","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb08/sickle-of-the-crescent-moon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"204\" height=\"256\" />\"This striking sickle has a rich mahogany handle that ends in a small crescent moon. Another, much larger crescent moon gripped by a monstrous hand graces the handle's business end, allowing the implement to serve as a sickle. The two satellites face away from each other, representing the juxtaposition between beasts that are naturally nocturnal and the monstrous and supernatural abominations that also stalk the night. Though the side of the sickle that represents evil and corruption is much larger, it is also this side that's used as a weapon&mdash;signifying that the implement is a tool in the war against the shadows.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Sickle of the Crescent Moon has a long and storied history battling vampires, werewolves, and other creatures of the night. Many famous monster, demon, and vampire hunters have wielded it over the years and the individual who carries it is usually either fated for greatness in future battles against the night, or else has a short expiry date on their life and is merely carrying the instrument until it reaches its next true recipient.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Sickle of the Crescent Moon can be used as a sickle.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Werewarrior</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Sickle of the Crescent Moon thirsts for the blood of shifters. It counts as a silvered weapon at all times, and you also have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls that use it against lycanthropic creatures if the moon is waning or in decline.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Lunar Awareness</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Sickle of the Crescent Moon is inexorably linked to the heavenly body from which it derives its name. It grants you the following insights while you are holding it or it is about your person:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can always tell precisely which direction the moon is in&mdash;even underground&mdash;and you can extrapolate from this when the next dawn or dusk will arrive and how long has passed since the last.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You always know at what phase of the lunar calendar the world is in.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have darkvision out to a distance of 30 foot.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can always tell when you're interacting with a lycanthropic creature.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Friend of the Night</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Sickle of the Crescent Moon's bearer belongs to the shadows and is a friend to the natural creatures of the night. You have advantage on Wisdom (animal handling) checks made to interact with nocturnal creatures and disadvantage on Wisdom (animal handling) checks to interact with diurnal ones</span>.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":9600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"KDlPbidOTF2fqXcM"}
{"name":"Auburn Wind (Longbow)","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This striking longbow is formed of cherry tree wood and sinew laminated together with a rich red lacquer that serves to protect its properties throughout use. Its top and bottom limbs have been overlaid with sharp, slightly curved oryx horns which elegantly match its contours.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The recurve is extremely flexible and hidden joints on the tip of each of its tillers allow its bowstring to be unfastened and removed. Without the tension that the bowstring provides, the bow straightens up to serve as a deadly, double-tipped spear.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. A</span></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">uburn Wind can be used as a longbow or a @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.fBcQEljAB3MyoUQ7]{spear (Auburn Wind)}</span></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">. It benefits from the </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Finesse </span></em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">weapon </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">property when you use it as a spear </span></span>in addition to its usual properties, and it takes a bonus action to attach or remove its bowstring.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Fickle</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Auburn Wind's identity is fluid, the object longing to change forms as often as possible. You gain a +1 bonus to the first attack roll you make with it after its bowstring has been attached or removed.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Protector of the wilds</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Auburn Wind loves the wilds as much as it despises the slow, unrelenting march of civilization. You deal an additional 1d4 points of damage to creatures of a lawful alignment when attacking with it, and 1 less damage to unaligned creatures.</span></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":150,"long":600,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialR","properties":{"amm":true,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":true,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":16300000,"flags":{"mess":{"isBonusDamage":false,"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-ranged-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"KPFZOnPX8Hl2WVNL"}
{"name":"Escapologist's Kit","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Other than for the fact that it has bright lettering plastered across its front and that it has been painted a deep cerulean blue with bright, lambent paint, this large wooden box doesn&rsquo;t look especially noteworthy at first glance. The lettering reads, &lsquo;Billings &amp; Beyond, Prepare To Be Astounded&rsquo; in a bold red font. If the box is jerked towards the ground and then its descent is halted abruptly, the object&rsquo;s momentum causes four folding wooden legs to spring out from its undercarriage, allowing it to stand up freely like a table. These legs are telescopic and easy to fold away, condensing back into place with a small amount of pressure.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Escapologist&rsquo;s Kit contains all the basic props and tools a budding escapologist would need to put on an amazing show. Better still, these useful objects have been enhanced with a number of minor enchantments that allow their owner to perform feats that would be impossible if not for the use of magic.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Escapologist Tricks</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Escapologist&rsquo;s Kit can be used to aid in numerous acts of escapology. It includes:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A set of wooden stocks that can be assembled to trap a humanoid&rsquo;s hands and head. The stocks seem secure but can be released by pushing a hidden catch in the mechanism.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A set of mundane iron manacles whose key reappears in your right hand exactly 30 seconds after being swallowed by you or another creature.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A thick black blindfold that seems mundane, but the fabric appears opaque to you and doesn&rsquo;t restrict your vision.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A set of herbs that, when chewed by you, render you catatonic for 5 minutes. During this time, you suffer the paralyzed condition but also do not need air to breathe.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A pair of gloves that allow you to cast the cantrip </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><em>Mage Hand</em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">as an action using only somatic components, instead of somatic and verbal.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A coin that, when rubbed, allows you to step through wooden surfaces up to 1 inch thick once per day.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":5100000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"Kkj0kf89TZ1QDJGG"}
{"name":"Stirrer of the Crone","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb08/stirrer-of-the-crone.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"233\" height=\"256\" />\"Standing at a little over two foot in length when its head isn't buried in thick, gloopy soup or some other, far fouler concoction, this large wooden ladle strikes an imposing figure. Serving as both stirrer and spoon, this diabolical implement appears every bit as sinister as the beings who created it and would look right at home in any witch's hut. Occult symbols have been scratched into its surface and a creepy, stitched fetish adorns the pinnacle of its handle. At a glance, this freakish effigy appears to be formed of dry, cracked leather and held together by twine, with a button and glass eyeball taken from a child's doll for eyes. However, a more thorough inspection reveals the reality to be far more sinister&mdash;the leather proving to be human skin, the twine hair, and the eyeball genuine. Whether these objects were all harvested from the same humanoid or several isn't clear.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Created as an item of convenience by a powerful brood mother that once stood as matriarch over a coven of cunning and cruel witches, ancient and forgotten magic lingers over the Stirrer of the Crone. While the implement was only ever intended on being used by her and her wretched kin, its unusual blessings can be unlocked by anyone&mdash;perhaps a by-product of her arrogance and hubris in believing that it would never fall out of her keeping. Not only is the object infused with old magic, but it is also lightweight and strong, and might be used as a weapon just as easily as a kitchen utensil.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Stirrer of the Crone can be used as a mace.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Spellcasting Focus</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Stirrer of the Crone can be used as an arcane focus (rod).</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Anti-Spillage Spoon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Fluids interned within the head of the Stirrer of the Crone are rarely spilt. Its head is large enough to hold up to 4 ounces of liquid and magical fluids poured into it do not lose their efficacy unless spilled, </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">imbibed, or due to a special property they possess. You can choose to attempt a DC 10 Dexterity check whenever you undertake a physical activity or strenuous task&mdash;including making an attack with it&mdash;, or a DC 10 Dexterity saving throw if affected by environmental factors or the actions of another creature, that would cause the liquid to spill. On a success, you're able to avoid spilling the fluid.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Wyrd Wonders</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Created by a coven of powerful pagans, Stirrer of the Crone has been blessed with several useful effects designed to make its mistresses' lives easier:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you leave it in a heated pot of soup; a bisque, broth, or chowder, it will continue to bubble and boil but never burn or overcook.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you place it in a cauldron or similar container which contains cold food that is then brought to the boil, it is seasoned to perfection.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Any liquid consumed from its head or served with it is always at a temperature safe for consumption.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you place it within a receptacle containing liquid and stir it three times in a&nbsp;clockwise&nbsp;circle, when you release the object, it continues to stir itself.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Potions of healing you pour out into its head heal an additional 1d4 hit points when drunk from it.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":11400000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/rod.png","effects":[],"_id":"Kzk87pz1BETjujs2"}
{"name":"Perceptive Purse","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This modest leather coin purse has been seared with a brand that resembles a bird of prey taking flight. The stamp that's left this mark has been pressed so tightly into the hide that it's left a deep recession in its surface. The object is large for a coin purse, larger than most satchels, though it is otherwise plain and uninteresting physically.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Perceptive Purse isn't at all unique in terms of its aesthetic. In fact, it's actually one of several thousand such identical coin purses manufactured for use by the tax collectors of a kingdom. What sets this one apart from others of its ilk are the special enchantments that its owner had placed upon it, to ensure that their on-the-job performance as a tax collector outshined that of their peers.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Reviled</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The original owner of the Perceptive Purse narrowly escaped disaster on more than one occasion. You can take the Dodge action on your turn in a surprise round, even if you are surprised.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Don't Blink</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">To those paying attention, it's as if the Perceptive Purse can smell fear. Though not a sentient artifact, it is considered to have a passive Insight score of 13. If it is in the presence of someone who is anxious, nervous, or otherwise tense, it emits a clinking noise periodically.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Liar Liar</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">It would be unwise for someone faced with the Perceptive Purse's owner to resort to deceit. You have advantage on contested checks&nbsp;</span></span>to discern when you're being told a lie pertaining to finances or financial matters when you use your Wisdom (insight) against another creature's Charisma (deception).</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"weight","value":6,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":1600000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/backpack.png","effects":[],"_id":"L0Y2e6M4oG3g2Zdn"}
{"name":"Acrobat's Pole","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This oaken quarterstaff has been treated with a rich teal lacquer which gives it a bright and reflective sheen. Thanks to its unusual glaze, the object glistens blue or green, depending on the angle at which it is viewed. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Other than for its peculiar coloration, the rod appears to be a perfectly ordinary quarterstaff, however in the right hands, it is immensely useful.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Originally belonging to a famous equilibrist with a love for all kinds of gymnastics, the Acrobat&rsquo;s Pole is able to extend to several times its usual length on the whim of its wielder. It was used for balance, pole vaulting, long jumping, and all manner of other remarkable and entertaining feats of athletics.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. The </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Acrobat&rsquo;s Pole can be used as a quarterstaff.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Reach</strong>. Whenever it is willed to do so, the Acrobat's Pole is able to grow long and strong. When you use it as a quarterstaff, it has a 10 foot reach.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Vaulter</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A creature wielding the Acrobat&rsquo;s Pole can often be seen flipping and tumbling across a battlefield at breakneck speed. When you make a long jump or a high jump while holding it in one or two hands, each foot you clear does not cost you a foot of movement&mdash;allowing you to move up to your speed before jumping.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":"1d8 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":true,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":20400000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/staff.png","effects":[],"_id":"LAzSFU7S49Om1him"}
{"_id":"LWqgsp18FwFcVqRL","name":"Gift of Gab","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p class=\"rd__quote-line rd__quote-line--last\"><i>When I met Jim Darkmagic, I wondered how he got anything done in that outfit. I have since learned that most of his talents involve standing and talking. His outfit is perfect for that.</i></p><p><span class=\"rd__quote-by\">— Môrgæn</span></p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Jim Darkmagic is said to have invented this spell, originally calling it <i>I said what?!</i> Have you ever been talking to the local monarch and accidentally mentioned how their son looks like your favorite hog from when you were growing up on the family farm? We've all been there! But rather than being beheaded for an honest slip of the tongue, you can pretend it never happened—by ensuring that no one knows it happened.</p><p>When you cast this spell, you skillfully reshape the memories of listeners in your immediate area, so that each creature of your choice within 5 feet of you forgets everything you said within the last 6 seconds. Those creatures then remember that you actually said the words you speak as the verbal component of the spell.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"AI","activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"which you take when you speak to another creature"},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"self","type":"self"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":3200001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Shrinking Skiff","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Easily mistaken for a child's toy, this diminutive wooden boat is actually a tiny scale model of a rowing boat, complete with a set of paddles. The kind that a collector or hobbyist might own, or else similar to one used as a part of a diorama in a museum. On the boat's hull is a faded stamp that depicts a shooting star placed at the head of a magic wand with colorful lines spiraling out of it, along with the caption 'Bipbip's Tinkerage'.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Shrinking Skiff was the creation of one Artie Bipbip, a gnomish wizard and tinkerer who delighted in taking common, everyday objects and imbuing them with strange and unusual powers. In the case of the Shrinking Skiff, he wanted to make a model boat that could serve as the real article in a pinch.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Capsule Craft</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It's difficult to imagine this tiny toy vessel could ever be used for anything practical, but it harbors an unexpected power. When placed into salt or fresh water, the Shrinking Skiff undergoes a rapid expansion that allows it to be used as a normal rowboat. This transformation takes 1 minute to complete. Once removed from the water</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> and allowed to dry, it shrinks back down to its original size over 1d6 hours.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Better Boat</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Despite what shipwrights, carpenters, and other boat builders might claim, the Shrinking Skiff is simply a superior vessel than those you might find </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">squatting in the mud or bobbing in the reeds in some insignificant little wharf in an unremarkable part of the world. While you are using it as a rowboat, you have advantage on checks made to steer or control it, and any rolls or checks made to flip or capsize it against your wishes are rolled twice and the more favorable result for you is used.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The following statistics apply to the Shrinking Skiff when being used as a rowboat:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It has an armor class of 13 and 75 hit points.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If reduced to 0 hit points, it reverts back to its model form and cannot expand to be used as a rowboat again for 24 hours.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It requires at least one creature to operate it, though it can drift with the currents or towed by a creature on land.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It can carry up to 8 Small or Medium creatures in total.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It travels at 1 mile per hour, but it travels at an additional 0.5 miles per hour for every two members of its maximum capacity that it isn't carrying; unless this weight is substituted for with cargo.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":13,"type":"vehicle","dex":null},"hp":{"value":75,"max":75,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":10800000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/vessel.png","effects":[],"_id":"Lczcb1SYbuUKwmvF"}
{"_id":"LoM564mvu3iqBtS9","name":"Armor of Agathys (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A protective magical force surrounds you, manifesting as a spectral frost that covers you and your gear. You gain 5 temporary hit points for the duration. If a creature hits you with a melee attack while you have these hit points, the creature takes 5 cold damage.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"120\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, both the temporary hit points and the cold damage increase by 5 for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"self","type":"self"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a cup of water","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":7500001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-armor-of-agathys.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Chameleon Flag","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb05/chameleon-flag.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"214\" />\"Flying proudly at the apex of a ship's mast, this pristine flag serves a much greater, and more nefarious, purpose than merely signaling the allegiance and intentions of the crew that sails beneath it. In truth, its likeness is as fluid and flighty as an indecisive sea breeze. Although its size and shape remains the same, the flag can be commanded to magically change its appearance to resemble that of any other banner in seconds. When it undergoes such a transformation, a blue wave of arcane energy rolls leisurely across its surface, washing away its former colors and appearance&mdash;replacing both with another set entirely.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Numerous pirates, slavers, smugglers, and others who wish to go unnoticed for sinister reasons have used the Chameleon Flag to trick and befuddle other seafaring vessels over the years. Though, ironically, the object was originally created by a merchant prince who simply wanted to be left alone by 'the-powers-that-be' and found being able to pass his vessel off as that of another faction a boon at times.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tom-Flaggery.&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A crew in possession of the Chameleon Flag is primed to stir up mischief and mayhem. As an action, you can will it to change its appearance to mimic the look of another flag while within 120 foot of it. You can either pick a generic appearance, or the guise of a specific flag that you've seen. It takes 30 seconds for the flag&rsquo;s transformation to complete. It requires a DC 17 Wisdom (perception) check and to get a good look at it for a creature that doesn't know any better to realize that the flag is fake. To cause the Chameleon Flag to resemble a specific flag, you must have studied the original close for at least 5 minutes.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Additionally, you can also will the Chameleon Flag to change in one of the following ways, using the same mechanics as described above:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Obscured.&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The flag becomes generic and turns hazy, as if being viewed through a light fog. Wisdom (perception) checks made to study its details have disadvantage and it can only be properly identified within half the usual distance.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Struck.&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The flag turns completely invisible, as if it has been struck and stowed.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">White.&nbsp;</strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The flag turns completely white, signaling surrender. The commander of any boat or ship currently engaged with the one flying the flag must attempt a DC 8 Wisdom saving throw or else their attitude towards it shifts from hostile to neutral. This doesn't mean that they'll allow the ship to leave the area, lower their guard, or blindly board it, only that they're compelled to temporarily cease fire.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":14900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"Lvpl8ttwB6ugH9sW"}
{"_id":"M2FiYzI1MmQxZmFk","name":"Misty Step","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Briefly surrounded by silvery mist, you teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space that you can see.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 260","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"space"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":920000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/wind-grasp-air-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"M2M1NmE4OWI2NDRm","name":"Counterspell","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You attempt to interrupt a creature in the process of casting a spell. If the creature is casting a spell of 3rd level or lower, its spell fails and has no effect. If it is casting a spell of 4th level or higher, make an ability check using your spellcasting ability. The DC equals 10 + the spell’s level. On a success, the creature’s spell fails and has no effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Higher Levels.&nbsp;</strong>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the interrupted spell has no effect if its level is less than or equal to the level of the spell slot you used.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 228","activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"which you take when you see a creature within 60 feet of you casting a spell"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"1d20 + @mod","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":false,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":960000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/slice-orange-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"M2NkYWQ0YTcwNzNi","name":"Unseen Servant","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This spell creates an Invisible, mindless, shapeless, Medium force that performs simple tasks at your command⁠ until the spell ends. The servant springs into existence in an unoccupied space on the ground within range. It has AC 10, 1 hit point, and a Strength of 2, and it can’t attack⁠. If it drops to 0 hit points⁠, the spell ends.</p>\n<p>Once on each of your turns as a Bonus Action, you can mentally command⁠ the servant to move up to 15 feet and interact with an object. The servant can perform simple tasks that a human servant could do, such as fetching things, cleaning, mending⁠, folding clothes, lighting fires, serving food, and pouring wine. Once you give the command⁠, the servant performs the task to the best of its ability until it completes the task, then waits for your next command⁠.</p>\n<p>If you command⁠ the servant to perform a task that would move it more than 60 feet away from you, the spell ends.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 284","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":true,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A piece of string and a bit of wood","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":830000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/wind-grasp-sky-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MDY3OTY1MzA2NDZl","name":"Water Breathing","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This spell grants up to ten willing creatures you can see within range the ability to breathe underwater until the spell ends. Affected creatures also retain their normal mode of respiration.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 287","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":24,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":10,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":true,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A short reed or piece of straw","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1000000,"flags":{"_sheetTab":"details"},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/blue_36.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Wheel of Prayer Casting","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb04/wheel-of-prayer-casting.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"81\" height=\"256\" />\"This handled, portable prayer wheel has been carefully balanced and is reinforced for use as a mace in battle. Besides its wooden handle, the rest of the mace is made of </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">brass that has been painted black and gold, and is inlaid with diminutive blue and red beryls. As is common with most prayer wheels, the cylindrical wheel that forms the mace's head rests on a spindle that can be turned or spun. A small chain affixes a metal weight to the wheel that whips around as it spins in order to prolong its momentum.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Wheel of Prayer Casting's top can be opened and removed like a lid, allowing small scraps of paper to be rolled up and inserted into it. While the object's head is in motion, a careful listener can hear the distant sounds of several baritonevoiced men chanting the words that are written on the parchment stored within it. Their recitation of the words is rhythmic, sonorous, and solemn.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Wheel of Prayer Casting can be used as a mace.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Spellcasting Focus</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Wheel of Prayer Casting can be used as a holy symbol.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Prayer Casting (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Some prayers fly further than others. Once per day, you can spin the Wheel of Prayer Casting's head as an action in an attempt to 'cast' your prayer in the hopes that it will be heard. If you spin its head and there is a written prayer interned within it that asks for Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma&mdash;or uses equivalent terms&mdash;you roll a D6. If the prayer doesn't relate to one of these attributes, nothing happens. The prayer rings out&nbsp;</span>in the form of a cube centered on you to a distance in feet equal to the result of your roll multiplied by 5. Allies of yours, including yourself, within the affected area should roll 1d4. Each creature affected gains a +2 bonus to any ability checks, attack rolls, or saving throws related to the attribute that was requested for a number of rounds equal to the result of their roll.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":12200000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"MFLwQaZft9Muf6Ye"}
{"_id":"MGMwZmE2NGM2NzEy","name":"Imprisonment","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You create a magical restraint to hold a creature that you can see within range. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be bound by the spell; if it succeeds, it is immune to this spell if you cast it again. While affected by this spell, the creature doesn’t need to breathe, eat, or drink, and it doesn’t age. Divination Spells can’t locate or perceive the target.</p>\n<p>When you cast the spell, you choose one of the following forms of imprisonment.</p>\n<p><strong>Burial</strong>. The target is entombed far beneath the earth in a Sphere of magical force that is just large enough to contain the target. Nothing can pass through the sph⁠ere, nor can any creature Teleport or use Planar Travel to get into or out of it. The spec⁠ia⁠l component for this version of the spell is a small mithral orb.</p>\n<p><strong>Chaining</strong>. Heavy chains, firmly rooted in the ground, hold the target in place. The target is Restrained until the spell ends, and it can’t move or be moved by any means until then. The speci⁠al component for this version of the spell is a fine chain of precious metal.</p>\n<p><strong>Hedged Prison</strong>. The spell transports the target into a tiny Demiplane that is warded against teleportation and Planar Travel. The Demiplane can be a labyrinth, a cage, a tower, or any similar confined structure or area of your choice. The speci⁠al component for this version of the spell is a miniature representation of the prison made from jade.</p>\n<p><strong>Minimus Containment</strong>. The target shrinks to a height of 1 inch and is imprisoned inside a gemstone or similar object. Light can pass through the gemstone normally (allowing the target to see out and other creatures to see in), but nothing else can pass through, even by means of teleportation or Planar Travel. The gemstone can’t be cut or broken while the spell remains in effect. The s⁠pec⁠ial component for this version of the spell is a large, transparent gemstone, such as a corundum, diamond, or ruby.</p>\n<p><strong>Slumber</strong>. The target falls asleep and can’t be awoken. The specia⁠l component for this version of the spell consists of rare soporific herbs.</p>\n<p><strong>Ending the Spell</strong>. During the casting of the spell, in any of its versions, you can specify a condition that will cause the spell to end and release the target. The condition can be as specific or as elaborate as you choose, but the DM must agree that the condition is reasonable and has a likelihood of coming to pass. The Conditions can be based on a creature’s name, identity, or deity but otherwise must be based on observable Actions or qualities and not based on intangibles such as level, class, or Hit Points.</p>\n<p>A Dispel Magic spell can end the spell only if it is cast as a 9th-level spell, targeting either the prison or the spe⁠cial component used to create it.</p>\n<p>You can use a particular spec⁠ial component to create only one prison at a time. If you cast the spell again using the same component, the target of the first casting is immediately freed from its binding.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 252","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"perm"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":9,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A vellum depiction or a carved statuette in the likeness of the target, and a special component that varies according to the version of the spell you choose, worth at least 500 gp per Hit Die of the target","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1160000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/shielding-fire-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MGYwY2ViMjVjNTQ2","name":"Polymorph","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This spell transforms a creature that you can see within range into a new form. An unwilling creature must make a Wisdom saving throw to avoid the effect. The spell has no effect on a Shapechanger or a creature with 0 Hit Points.</p>\n<p>The transformation lasts for the Duration, or until the target drops to 0 Hit Points or dies. The new form can be any beast whose Challenge rating is equal to or less than the target’s (or the target’s level, if it doesn’t have a c⁠hallenge rating). The target’s game s⁠tatistics, including mental Ability Scores, are replaced by the Statistics of the chosen beast. It retains its Alignment and personality.</p>\n<p>The target assumes the Hit Points of its new form. When it reverts to its normal form, the creature returns to the number of hit po⁠ints it had before it transformed. If it reverts as a result of dropping to 0 h⁠it points, any excess damage carries over to its normal form. As long as the excess damage doesn’t reduce the creature’s normal form to 0 hit poin⁠ts, it isn’t knocked Unconscious.</p>\n<p>The creature is limited in the Actions it can perform by the Nature of its new form, and it can’t speak, cast Spells, or take any other action that requires hands or s⁠peech.</p>\n<p>The target’s gear melds into the new form. The creature can’t activate, use, wield, or otherwise benefit from any of its Equipment.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 266","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"A caterpillar cocoon","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1050000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/link-eerie-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MGYzMTgwY2NkZmU3","name":"Magic Weapon","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You touch a nonmagical weapon. Until the spell ends, that weapon becomes a magic weapon with a +1 bonus to Attack rolls and Damage Rolls.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the bonus increases to +2. When you use a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the bonus increases to +3.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 257","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":910000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/enchant-blue-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MGZjMzk2NmYwMDc2","name":"Rope Trick","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You touch a length of rope that is up to 60 feet long. One end of the rope then rises into the air until the whole rope hangs perpendicular to the ground. At the upper end of the rope, an invisible entrance opens to an extradimensional space that lasts until the spell ends.</p><p>The extradimensional space can be reached by climbing to the top of the rope. The space can hold as many as eight Medium or smaller creatures. The rope can be pulled into the space, making the rope disappear from view outside the space.</p><p>Attacks and spells can't cross through the entrance into or out of the extradimensional space, but those inside can see out of it as if through a 3-foot-by-5-foot window centered on the rope.</p><p>Anything inside the extradimensional space drops out when the spell ends.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 272","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"Powdered corn extract and a twisted loop of parchment","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":930000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/slice-spirit-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MLBSBHTkL8xgyoMW","name":"Bane (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Up to three creatures of your choice that you can see within range must make Charisma saving throws. Whenever a target that fails this saving throw makes an attack roll or a saving throw before the spell ends, the target must roll a [[/r d4]] and subtract the number rolled from the attack roll or saving throw.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"116\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":3,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"cha","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a drop of blood","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":6900001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-bane.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MPImnYeXNe8Nfs19","name":"Globe of Invulnerability (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>An immobile, faintly shimmering barrier springs into existence in a 10-foot radius around you and remains for the duration.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Any spell of 5th level or lower cast from outside the barrier can't affect creatures or objects within it, even if the spell is cast using a higher level spell slot. Such a spell can target creatures and objects within the barrier, but the spell has no effect on them. Similarly, the area within the barrier is excluded from the areas affected by such spells.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"136\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 7th level or higher, the barrier blocks spells of one level higher for each slot level above 6th.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":10,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":6,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a glass or crystal bead that shatters when the spell ends","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":9200001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-globe-of-invulnerability.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MTE1ZmM0Yzc4MzA3","name":"False Life","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Bolstering yourself with a necromantic facsimile of life, you gain 1d4 + 4 Temporary Hit Points for the Duration.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you gain 5 additional Temporary Hit Points for each slot level above 1st.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 239","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":null,"type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4","temphp"],["4","temphp"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A small amount of alcohol or distilled spirits","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":810000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/heal-royal-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MTc4NjJjZTY2N2My","name":"Fireball","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A bright streak flashes from your pointing finger to a point you choose within range and then blossoms with a low roar into an explosion of flame. Each creature in a 20-foot-radius sphere centered on that point must make a Dexterity saving throw. A target takes 8d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>The fire spreads around corners. It ignites flammable objects in the area that aren’t being worn or carried.</p>\n<p><strong>Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 3rd.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 241","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":150,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["8d6","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A tiny ball of bat guano and sulfur","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d6"}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":800000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/fireball-red-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MWZlNzU5MDQxNjVm","name":"Speak with Dead","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You grant the semblance of life and intelligence to a corpse of your choice within range, allowing it to answer the questions you pose. The corpse must still have a mouth and can't be undead. The spell fails if the corpse was the target of this spell within the last 10 days.</p><p>Until the spell ends, you can ask the corpse up to five questions. The corpse knows only what it knew in life, including the languages it knew. Answers are usually brief, cryptic, or repetitive, and the corpse is under no compulsion to offer a truthful answer if you are hostile to it or it recognizes you as an enemy. This spell doesn't return the creature's soul to its body, only its animating spirit. Thus, the corpse can't learn new information, doesn't comprehend anything that has happened since it died, and can't speculate about future events.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 277","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"Burning incense","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1400000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/horror-acid-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MjQzYzAxNjcxMTNi","name":"Greater Invisibility","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You or a creature you touch becomes Invisible until the spell ends. Anything the target is wearing or carrying is Invisible as long as it is on the target’s person.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 246","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":4,"school":"ill","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":770000,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/fog-water-air-3.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"pyh709mhnkb0wsj9","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/fog-water-air-3.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"MmRhMzU1NGFlNDgw","name":"Conjure Animals","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You summon fey spirits that take the form of beasts and appear in unoccupied spaces that you can see within range. Choose one of the following options for what appears:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>One beast of challenge rating 2 or lower</li>\n<li>Two beasts of challenge rating 1 or lower</li>\n<li>Four beasts of challenge rating 1/2 or lower</li>\n<li>Eight beasts of challenge rating 1/4 or lower</li>\n<li>Each beast is also considered fey, and it disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The summoned creatures are friendly to you and your companions. Roll initiative for the summoned creatures as a group, which has its own turns. They obey any verbal commands that you issue to them (no action required by you). If you don’t issue any commands to them, they defend themselves from hostile creatures, but otherwise take no actions.</p>\n<p><strong>Higher Levels.&nbsp;</strong>When you cast this spell using certain higher-level spell slots, you choose one of the summoning options above, and more creatures appear: twice as many with a 5th-level slot, three times as many with a 7th-level.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 225","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":"space"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1140000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/wild-orange-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MzA5OWE1OTUxYzY3","name":"Suggestion","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You suggest a course of activity (limited to a sentence or two) and magically influence a creature you can see within range that can hear and understand you. Creatures that can't be charmed are immune to this effect. The suggestion must be worded in such a manner as to make the course of action sound reasonable. Asking the creature to stab itself, throw itself onto a spear, immolate itself, or do some other obviously harmful act ends the spell.</p>\n<p>The target must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, it pursues the course of action you described to the best of its ability. The suggested course of action can continue for the entire duration. If the suggested activity can be completed in a shorter time, the spell ends when the subject finishes what it was asked to do.</p>\n<p>You can also specify conditions that will trigger a special activity during the duration. For example, you might suggest that a knight give her warhorse to the first beggar she meets. If the condition isn't met before the spell expires, the activity isn't performed.</p>\n<p>If you or any of your companions damage the target, the spell ends.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 279","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":8,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"A snake's tongue and either a bit of honeycomb or a drop of sweet oil","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":940000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/air-burst-magenta-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MzYxMjE2Y2M3MThk","name":"Cone of Cold","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A blast of cold air erupts from your hands. Each creature in a 60-foot cone must make a Constitution saving throw. A creature takes 8d8 cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>A creature killed by this spell becomes a frozen statue until it thaws.</p>\n<p><strong>Higher Levels.&nbsp;</strong>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 5th.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 224","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":60,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["8d8","cold"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":5,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A small crystal or glass cone","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1060000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/ice-blue-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"N2FmMGZlMWU0NzNm","name":"Legend Lore","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Name or describe a person, place, or object. The spell brings to your mind a brief summary of the significant lore about the thing you named. The lore might consist of current tales, forgotten stories, or even secret lore that has never been widely known. If the thing you named isn't of legendary importance, you gain no information. The more information you already have about the thing, the more precise and detailed the information you receive is.</p><p>The information you learn is accurate but might be couched in figurative language. For example, if you have a mysterious magic axe on hand, the spell might yield this information: \"Woe to the evildoer whose hand touches the axe, for even the haft slices the hand of the evil ones. Only a true Child of Stone, lover and beloved of Moradin, may awaken the true powers of the axe, and only with the sacred word Rudnogg on the lips.\"</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 254","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":10,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":5,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"Incense worth at least 250gp, which the spell consumes, and four ivory strips worth at least 50gp each.","consumed":true,"cost":250,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":100000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/runes-royal-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NDg0Mjc2NDdkYjAy","name":"Fabricate","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You convert raw materials into products of the same material. For example, you can fabricate a wooden bridge from a clump of trees, a rope from a patch of hemp, and clothes from flax or wool.</p>\n<p>Choose raw materials that you can see within range. You can fabricate a Large or smaller object (contained within a 10-foot cube, or eight connected 5-foot cubes), given a sufficient quantity of raw material. If you are working with metal, stone, or another mineral substance, however, the fabricated object can be no larger than Medium (contained within a single 5-foot cube). The quality of Objects made by the spell is commensurate with the quality of the raw materials.</p>\n<p>Creatures or Magic Items can’t be created or transmuted by this spell. You also can’t use it to create items that ordinarily require a high degree of craftsmanship, such as jewelry, Weapons, glass, or armor, unless you have proficiency with the type of artisan’s tools used to craft such Objects.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":10,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":10,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cube"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":4,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1020000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/explosion-royal-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NGRjYjQzNzdjMDE4","name":"Animal Messenger","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>By means of this spell, you use an animal to deliver a message. Choose a Tiny beast you can see within range, such as a squirrel, a blue jay, or a bat. You specify a location, which you must have visited, and a recipient who matches a general description, such as \"a man or woman dressed in the uniform of the town guard\" or \"a red-haired dwarf wearing a pointed hat.\" You also speak a message of up to twenty-five words. The target beast travels for the duration of the spell toward the specified location, covering about 50 miles per 24 hours for a flying messenger, or 25 miles for other animals.</p>\n<p>When the messenger arrives, it delivers your message to the creature that you described, replicating the sound of your voice. The messenger speaks only to a creature matching the description you gave. If the messenger doesn't reach its destination before the spell ends, the message is lost, and the beast makes its way back to where you cast this spell.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> If you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the duration of the spell increases by 48 hours for each slot level above 2nd.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 212","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":24,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":true,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A morsel of food.","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/wild-jade-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NTNkM2I3MzJkZmVj","name":"Gentle Repose","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You touch a corpse or other remains. For the duration, the target is protected from decay and can't become undead.</p><p>The spell also effectively extends the time limit on raising the target from the dead, since days spent under the influence of this spell don't count against the time limit of spells such as raise dead.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 245","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"day"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":true,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A pinch of salt and one copper piece placed on each of the corpse's eyes, which must remain there for the duration","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1300000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/light-blue-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NTc1NTU1ZDY1OWJk","name":"Remove Curse","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At your touch, all curses affecting one creature or object end. If the object is a cursed magic item, its curse remains, but the spell breaks its owner’s Attunement to the object so it can be removed or discarded.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 271","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":200000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/heal-royal-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NVPJFj1K5dyFJOS4","name":"Dispel Magic (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Choose one creature, object, or magical effect within range. Any spell of 3rd level or lower on the target ends. For each spell of 4th level or higher on the target, make an ability check using your spellcasting ability. The DC equals 10 + the spell's level. On a successful check, the spell ends.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"119\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you automatically end the effects of a spell on the target if the spell's level is equal to or less than the level of the spell slot you used.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":7400001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-dispel-magic.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NWFkZWMyNThjZDg0","name":"Greater Restoration","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You imbue a creature you touch with positive energy to undo a debilitating effect. You can reduce the target’s Exhaustion level by one, or end one of the following Effects on the target:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>One effect that Charmed or Petrified the target</li>\n<li>One curse, including the target’s Attunement to a cursed magic item</li>\n<li>Any reduction to one of the target’s Ability Scores</li>\n<li>One effect reducing the target’s hit point maximum</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 246","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":5,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A diamond dust worth at least 100gp, which the spell consumes","consumed":true,"cost":100,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":300000,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/heal-sky-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NWMwYTg5ZDdkM2Rl","name":"Detect Thoughts","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>For the duration, you can read the thoughts of certain creatures. When you cast the spell and as your action on each turn until the spell ends, you can focus your mind on any one creature that you can see within 30 feet of you. If the creature you choose has an Intelligence of 3 or lower or doesn't speak any language, the creature is unaffected.</p><p>You initially learn the surface thoughts of the creature—what is most on its mind in that moment. As an action, you can either shift your attention to another creature's thoughts or attempt to probe deeper into the same creature's mind. If you probe deeper, the target must make a Wisdom saving throw. If it fails, you gain insight into its reasoning (if any), its emotional state, and something that looms large in its mind (such as something it worries over, loves, or hates). If it succeeds, the spell ends. Either way, the target knows that you are probing into its mind, and unless you shift your attention to another creature's thoughts, the creature can use its action on its turn to make an Intelligence check contested by your Intelligence check; if it succeeds, the spell ends.</p><p>Questions verbally directed at the target creature naturally shape the course of its thoughts, so this spell is particularly effective as part of an interrogation.</p><p>You can also use this spell to detect the presence of thinking creatures you can't see. When you cast the spell or as your action during the duration, you can search for thoughts within 30 feet of you. The spell can penetrate barriers, but 2 feet of rock, 2 inches of any metal other than lead, or a thin sheet of lead blocks you. You can't detect a creature with an Intelligence of 3 or lower or one that doesn't speak any language.</p><p>Once you detect the presence of a creature in this way, you can read its thoughts for the rest of the duration as described above, even if you can't see it, but it must still be within range.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 231","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"A copper piece","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1100000,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/light-eerie-2.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"Al9TALIjAZIx2ZTi","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/light-eerie-2.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"NWQ0M2M4N2Y0NmQ5","name":"Continual Flame","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A flame, equivalent in brightness to a torch, springs forth from an object that you touch. The effect looks like a regular flame, but it creates no heat and doesn't use oxygen. A continual flame can be covered or hidden but not smothered or quenched.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 227","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"perm"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"object"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"Ruby dust worth 50 gp, which the spell consumes","consumed":true,"cost":50,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1900000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/explosion-orange-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NWVkNDgzNDM1NjFh","name":"Magic Missile","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You create three glowing darts of magical force. Each dart hits a creature of your choice that you can see within range. A dart deals 1d4 + 1 force damage to its target. The darts all strike simultaneously, and you can direct them to hit one creature or several.</p>\n<p><strong>Higher Levels.&nbsp;</strong>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the spell creates one more dart for each slot level above 1st.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 257","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"enemy"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rsak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d4","force"],["3","force"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d4+1"}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":880000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/fire-arrows-magenta-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NWvh9wQBEHsJbvCO","name":"Intellect Fortress","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>For the duration, you or one willing creature you can see within range has resistance to psychic damage, as well as advantage on Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma saving throws.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"20\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 3rd. The creatures must be within 30 feet of each other when you target them.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"TCE","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":14300001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[{"_id":"ZNqNmhfQLG9h0OCi","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura"