{"name":"Mask of the Oni","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb09/mask-of-the-oni.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"193\" height=\"256\" />\"This fearsome cross-eyed mask closely resembles the striking visage of an oni<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>complete with wild and unkempt hair that forms a mane around its face, pronounced horns, sharp tusks, and a rich emerald skin tone. Though the item is clearly a mask when viewed from behind, its thick, reddish hair appears real and its flesh too is soft, squishy, and difficult to tell apart from the genuine article.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">An old legend surrounds the Mask of the Oni. The story goes than an oni called Akatinoka was once preying on a small hamlet when it stumbled, or so it thought, across a young lost girl beside the road. Thinking itself clever and wise, the oni assumed the guise of a boy her age and led her away to be eaten. However, just as Akatinoka revealed its true form and swore to devour her, the girl simply smiled and, with a wave of her withered hand, the oni collapsed into a mask. With that, the unknown female simultaneously defeated the terrible ogre and sparked the superstition that oni are afraid of children wearing masks and disguises.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Bogeyman-Guise</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Every bit as tricky as the oni from whence it sprung, the Mask of the Oni serves as a handy aid to aspiring tricksters or wannabe pranksters. While wearing it, your appearance shifts to resemble that of a large-sized oni. While in this form, you can speak and understand Giant. You can also cast the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><em>Minor Illusion</em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">cantrip using your Charisma modifier for your spellcasting ability. Additionally, you can use Deception in place of Intimidation when attempting to pass yourself off as an oni to scare or startle others.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If a creature uses its action to examine you while you're wearing the Mask of the Oni's, it can determine that your guise is illusory with a successful Intelligence (investigation) check equal to 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier. If a creature discerns your illusion for what it is, the illusion becomes faint to the creature. Physical interaction with you also reveals your appearance to be an illusion, unless your size is Large.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":5800000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/headgear.png","effects":[],"_id":"Nc05HLqIvkXIDhIf"}
{"_id":"NjQ5YmEwZDRjNGY0","name":"Darkvision","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You touch a willing creature to grant it the ability to see in the dark. For the duration, that creature has darkvision out to a range of 60 feet.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 230","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":8,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"Either a pinch of dried carrot or an agate","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":890000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/evil-eye-red-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NmI3YmViY2UxMDdh","name":"Detect Magic","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>For the duration, you sense the presence of magic within 30 feet of you. If you sense magic in this way, you can use your action to see a faint aura around any visible creature or object in the area that bears magic, and you learn its school of magic, if any.</p><p>The spell can penetrate most barriers, but it is blocked by 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood or dirt.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 231","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":true,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1000000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/light-blue-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NmZjNzdlNzBiNzk0","name":"Dispel Magic","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Choose one creature, object, or magical effect within range. Any spell of 3rd level or lower on the target ends. For each spell of 4th level or higher on the target, make an ability check using your spellcasting ability. The DC equals 10 + the spell's level. On a successful check, the spell ends.</p>\n<p><strong>Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you automatically end the effects of a spell on the target if the spell’s level is equal to or less than the level of the spell slot you used.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 234","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":970000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/slice-orange-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Nta3iHhCWdW5dP0o","name":"Fog Cloud","permission":{"default":-1,"bOqyKS8LL2EWqEnK":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You create a 20-foot-radius sphere of fog centered on a point within range. The sphere spreads around corners, and its area is heavily obscured. It lasts for the duration or until a wind of moderate or greater speed (at least 10 miles per hour) disperses it.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"7229\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the radius of the fog increases by 20 feet for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":null,"sort":1200001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""},"betterCurses":{"isCurse":false,"curseName":"","formula":"","mwak":false,"rwak":false,"msak":false,"rsak":false}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-fog-cloud.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NzA5MWZiM2EzZmQx","name":"Disguise Self","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You make yourself—including your clothing, armor, weapons, and other belongings on your person—look different until the spell ends or until you use your action to dismiss it. You can seem 1 foot shorter or taller and can appear thin, fat, or in between. You can't change your body type, so you must adopt a form that has the same basic arrangement of limbs. Otherwise, the extent of the illusion is up to you.</p><p>The changes wrought by this spell fail to hold up to physical inspection. For example, if you use this spell to add a hat to your outfit, objects pass through the hat, and anyone who touches it would feel nothing or would feel your head and hair. If you use this spell to appear thinner than you are, the hand of someone who reaches out to touch you would bump into you while it was seemingly still in midair.</p><p>To discern that you are disguised, a creature can use its action to inspect your appearance and must succeed on an Intelligence (Investigation) check against your spell save DC.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 233","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":null,"type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"int","dc":0,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"ill","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":700000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/wind-grasp-eerie-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NzIyNzU2Njg4NGNk","name":"Arcane Eye","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You create an invisible, magical eye within range that hovers in the air for the duration.</p><p>You mentally receive visual information from the eye, which has normal vision and darkvision out to 30 feet. The eye can look in every direction.</p><p>As an action, you can move the eye up to 30 feet in any direction. There is no limit to how far away from you the eye can move, but it can't enter another plane of existence. A solid barrier blocks the eye's movement, but the eye can pass through an opening as small as 1 inch in diameter.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 214","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":4,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"A bit of bat fur.","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1010000,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""},"autoanimations":{"killAnim":false,"override":false,"animType":"t1","animName":"","hmAnim":"a1","color":"n1","dtvar":"dt1","explosion":false,"explodeVariant":"ev1","explodeColor":"ec1","explodeRadius":"0","explodeLoop":"1","selfRadius":"5","animTint":"#ffffff","auraOpacity":0.75,"ctaOption":false}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/evil-eye-eerie-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NzRhZDkzNGUyOWU1","name":"Nondetection","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>For the Duration, you hide a target that you touch from Divination magic. The target can be a willing creature or a place or an object no larger than 10 feet in any dimension. The target can’t be targeted by any d⁠ivination magic or perceived through magical Scrying sensors.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 263","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":8,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A pinch of diamond dust worth 25 gp sprinkled over the target, which the spell consumes","consumed":true,"cost":25,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":990000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/evil-eye-red-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NzhlYWRkMmIzOGEz","name":"Animate Objects","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Objects come to life at your command. Choose up to ten nonmagical objects within range that are not being worn or carried. Medium targets count as two objects, Large targets count as four objects, Huge targets count as eight objects. You can't animate any object larger than Huge. Each target animates and becomes a creature under your control until the spell ends or until reduced to 0 hit points.</p>\n<p>As a bonus action, you can mentally command any creature you made with this spell if the creature is within 500 feet of you (if you control multiple creatures, you can command any or all of them at the same time, issuing the same command to each one). You decide what action the creature will take and where it will move during its next turn, or you can issue a general command, such as to guard a particular chamber or corridor. If you issue no commands, the creature only defends itself against hostile creatures. Once given an order, the creature continues to follow it until its task is complete.</p>\n<p><strong>Animated Object Statistics</strong></p>\n<p>Size&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; HP&nbsp; &nbsp;AC&nbsp; &nbsp;Attack&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Str Dex</p>\n<p>Tiny&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 20&nbsp; &nbsp;18&nbsp; &nbsp;+8 to hit, 1d4 + 4 damage&nbsp; &nbsp; 4&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;18</p>\n<p>Small&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;25&nbsp; &nbsp;16&nbsp; &nbsp;+6 to hit, 1d8 + 2 damage&nbsp; &nbsp; 6&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;14</p>\n<p>Medium 40&nbsp; &nbsp;13&nbsp; +5 to hit, 2d6 + 1 damage&nbsp; &nbsp; 10&nbsp; &nbsp;12</p>\n<p>Large&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 50&nbsp; &nbsp;10&nbsp; +6 to hit, 2d10 + 2 damage&nbsp; 14&nbsp; &nbsp;10</p>\n<p>Huge&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;80&nbsp; &nbsp;10&nbsp; +8 to hit, 2d12 + 4 damage&nbsp; 18&nbsp; &nbsp;6</p>\n<p>An animated object is a construct with AC, hit points, attacks, Strength, and Dexterity determined by its size. Its Constitution is 10 and its Intelligence and Wisdom are 3, and its Charisma is 1. Its speed is 30 feet; if the object lacks legs or other appendages it can use for locomotion, it instead has a flying speed of 30 feet and can hover. If the object is securely attached to a surface or a larger object, such as a chain bolted to a wall, its speed is 0. It has blindsight with a radius of 30 feet and is blind beyond that distance. When the animated object drops to 0 hit points, it reverts to its original object form, and any remaining damage carries over to its original object form.</p>\n<p>If you command an object to attack, it can make a single melee attack against a creature within 5 feet of it. It makes a slam attack with an attack bonus and bludgeoning damage determined by its size. The DM might rule that a specific object inflicts slashing or piercing damage based on its form.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> If you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, you can animate two additional objects for each slot level above 5th.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 213","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":10,"width":null,"units":"","type":"object"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":5,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1800000,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""},"autoanimations":{"killAnim":false,"override":false,"animType":"t1","animName":"","hmAnim":"a1","color":"n1","dtvar":"dt1","explosion":false,"explodeVariant":"ev1","explodeColor":"ec1","explodeRadius":"0","explodeLoop":"1","selfRadius":"5","animTint":"#ffffff","auraOpacity":0.75,"ctaOption":false}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-animate-objects.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"9GOavzr3aJgJbbrr","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.itemMacro","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-animate-objects.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"Nzk5NGJkNDIyZDhl","name":"Locate Creature","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Describe or name a creature that is familiar to you. You sense the direction to the creature's location, as long as that creature is within 1,000 feet of you. If the creature is moving, you know the direction of its movement.</p><p>The spell can locate a specific creature known to you, or the nearest creature of a specific kind (such as a human or a unicorn), so long as you have seen such a creature up close—within 30 feet—at least once. If the creature you described or named is in a different form, such as being under the effects of a polymorph spell, this spell doesn't locate the creature.</p><p>This spell can't locate a creature if running water at least 10 feet wide blocks a direct path between you and the creature.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 256","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":4,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"A bit of fur from a bloodhound","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1040000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/leaf-royal-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NzljMjJlYWE5MGM4","name":"Burning Hands","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>As you hold your hands with thumbs touching and fingers spread, a thin sheet of flames shoots forth from your outstretched fingertips. Each creature in a 15-foot cone must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 3d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>The fire ignites any flammable objects in the area that aren't being worn or carried.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 220","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d6","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d6"}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":2100000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/fog-orange-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ODQyZmMzOWUzNjQ3","name":"Fly","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You touch a willing creature. The target gains a flying speed of 60 feet for the Duration. When the spell ends, the target falls if it is still aloft, unless it can stop the fall.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 3rd.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 243","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"A wing feather from any bird","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":980000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/link-spirit-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ODdjYzcyYjBmYmEz","name":"Mage Armor","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You touch a willing creature who isn't wearing armor, and a protective magical force surrounds it until the spell ends. The target's base AC becomes 13 + its Dexterity modifier. The spell ends if the target dons armor or if you dismiss the spell as an action.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 256","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":8,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A piece of cured leather","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":870000,"flags":{"_sheetTab":"details"},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/protect-blue-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ODg1MTEwZjY2MWE0","name":"Animal Friendship","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This spell lets you convince a beast that you mean it no harm. Choose a beast that you can see within range. It must see and hear you. If the beast's Intelligence is 4 or higher, the spell fails. Otherwise, the beast must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be charmed by you for the spell's duration. If you or one of your companions harms the target, the spell ends.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can affect one additional beast for each slot level above 1st.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 212","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":24,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A morsel of food.","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1090000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/wild-jade-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Cloak of the Chaperone","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Its edges feathered by an elaborate pattern of crisscrossing embroidery that's set on an auburn backdrop and crested by the silhouette of an elk; rimmed by a gilded weave that's enveloped by a teal surround and proudly bearing a unicorn's visage; or mutilated by a muddy strip of blood red paint that runs haphazardly around its perimeter and clashes discordantly with the royal blue that surrounds its hammer and anvil emblem&mdash;this fine cloak appears very differently depending on its current owner, and where their loyalties lie.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Cloak of the Chaperone is traditionally a fixture of the closest and most senior bodyguard to a young prince or princess. Not only is it a symbol of their rank and station, but it also serves as a shining beacon to those who might question their allegiance and the oaths that they've taken to protect their young charge; and it also helps them discharge their duties more effectively.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Attunement Requirement</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">In order to attune to the Cloak of the Chaperone, you must swear a solemn oath to dedicate your victories and failures to a particular sovereign, kingdom, family, or deity on whose behalf you fight; or accept a charge and protect them with your life.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Fealty</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A person who chooses to wear the Cloak of the Chaperone volunteers to reveal where their loyalties lie. Its colors and markings shift to match the heraldry of the house or nation you serve.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Line of Duty (3/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">For a few brave souls, the protection of another is their primary motivation. As a reaction to an ally within 5 foot of you being the target of a melee or ranged weapon attack, you can choose to become the target instead if the attack could target you.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Threatened</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A creature wearing the Cloak of the Chaperone is well-equipped to defend against hostile incursion. You deal an additional 1d4 damage on opportunity attacks.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":3,"max":"3","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":200000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/cloak.png","effects":[],"_id":"OFFbOqVYiQy6nVXN"}
{"name":"Vivisectarum","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb06/vivisectarum.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"161\" />\"This treatise of esoteric lore was written by a physician with a disturbing interest in the anatomy and inner workings of monstrous creatures. Although written in the dry, impassive, and clinical tone of a technical manual, the bulk of the entries contained within the pages of this beastly book speak of vivisections and autopsies in excruciating detail, complete with comprehensive annotations.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">By all accounts, when this manuscript was first published, its author was already a celebrated scientist with a long and promising career ahead of him. However, the contents of Vivisectarum were so shocking, explicit, and, some would say, cruel, that the researcher's peers and contemporaries ostracized him; questioning his methods, moral fortitude, and even his mental stability. Deeply affected by the scandal surrounding his work, the penman behind the piece shied away from further publication and spent his prevailing years recused from the public eye, where he could continue his research in private. All that&nbsp; outwardly remains of his macabre legacy is the Vivisectarum.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tome of Monstrous Lore</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When consulting Vivisectarum for at least 10 minutes, you gain several useful insights:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You have advantage on Intelligence checks to recall information about creatures that are not of the humanoid or beast type with a challenge rating of 3 or lower.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You have advantage on checks made to extract poisons, remove glands or organs, or harvest other components from creatures that are not of the humanoid or beast type with a challenge rating of 3 or lower.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You have advantage on Medicine checks made to provide treatment and healing to creatures that are not of the humanoid or beast type with a challenge rating of 3 or lower.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":19700000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/book.png","effects":[],"_id":"OOMwKBWaYJtczQci"}
{"_id":"OTFjOWUxNzNiYjc5","name":"Appendix D: Magic Items","permission":{"default":0},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\" rd__b--1\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" data-title-index=\"176\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Appendix D: Magic Items</span></span> <p>The unique magical-mechanical crafting techniques seen in the Monastery of the Distressed Body and the lost city of Daoine Gloine are the basis of a number of unique magic items found in the adventure. Because of their power and rarity, the items in this section (or at least those that aren't cursed) are best suited for characters in a high-magic campaign. Alternatively, treat each item as the equivalent of two or more magic items appropriate for characters of 5th to 10th level.</p><p>You can also treat this section as potential treasure for future play at higher levels. Some of these items might be experiments that Kwalish is working on, which can be made available to the characters if they return to the Barrier Peaks. Alternatively, if you'd like to make full use of these items during the adventure but don't want to make them part of your long-term campaign, some of them might function only in the monastery or Daoine Gloine, while others might be charge-dependent. When an item's charges run dry, its magic drains away—or the item might malfunction or explode, with effects determined by you.</p><p>The \"<a href=\"https://5e.tools/book.html#DMG,9,alien technology\"  >Alien Technology</a>\" section in chapter 9 of the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/book.html#DMG\"  >Dungeon Master's Guide</a> offers useful general guidelines for dealing with strange devices of the sort found in this adventure. If Kwalish's notes can't be deciphered (or if the inventor doesn't show up when the characters need him), you might ask for successful Intelligence checks on the Figuring Out Alien Technology table from anyone trying to operate magical technology. It might take one success to operate a trinket, two successes to operate a force pike or a teleportation-field device, and four successes to operate Kwalish's <i>powered armor</i>.</p><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#blade of the medusa_llk\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.mouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'LLK', 'blade of the medusa_llk', false, null)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Blade of the Medusa</a></li><li ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#deck of several things_llk\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.mouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'LLK', 'deck of several things_llk', false, null)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Deck of Several Things</a></li><li ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#galder's bubble pipe_llk\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.mouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'LLK', 'galder\\'s bubble pipe_llk', false, null)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Galder's Bubble Pipe</a></li><li ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#gambler's blade_llk\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.mouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'LLK', 'gambler\\'s blade_llk', false, null)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Gambler's Blade</a></li><li ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#heward's hireling armor_llk\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.mouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'LLK', 'heward\\'s hireling armor_llk', false, null)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Heward's Hireling Armor</a></li><li ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#ioun stone_llk\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.mouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'LLK', 'ioun stone_llk', false, null)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Ioun Stone</a></li><li ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#leather golem armor_llk\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.mouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'LLK', 'leather golem armor_llk', false, null)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Leather Golem Armor</a></li><li ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#polymorph blade_llk\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.mouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'LLK', 'polymorph blade_llk', false, null)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Polymorph Blade</a></li><li ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#powered armor_llk\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.mouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'LLK', 'powered armor_llk', false, null)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Powered Armor</a></li></ul></div><br><p>Next handout: <a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=JournalEntry data-id=MjM3NGNiMzdiNjgx ><i class=\"fas fa-book-open\"></i>Appendix E: New Spells</a></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Magic Items","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"","identified":true},"folder":"MGZjZWRmMGNkNTY1","sort":0,"flags":{},"img":"","effects":[]}
{"_id":"OTQyMmRhNGVjNTFm","name":"Daylight","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A 60-foot-radius sphere of light spreads out from a point you choose within range. The sphere is bright light and sheds dim light for an additional 60 feet.</p><p>If you chose a point on an object you are holding or one that isn't being worn or carried, the light shines from the object and moves with it. Completely covering the affected object with an opaque object, such as a bowl or a helm, blocks the light.</p><p>If any of this spell's area overlaps with an area of darkness created by a spell of 3rd level or lower, the spell that created the darkness is dispelled.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 230","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":60,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":500000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/beam-royal-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"OWMxNGFjMzVlYjRi","name":"Arcane Lock","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You touch a closed door, window, gate, chest, or other entryway, and it becomes locked for the duration. You and the creatures you designate when you cast this spell can open the object normally. You can also set a password that, when spoken within 5 feet of the object, suppresses this spell for 1 minute. Otherwise, it is impassable until it is broken or the spell is dispelled or suppressed. Casting knock on the object suppresses arcane lock for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>While affected by this spell, the object is more difficult to break or force open; the DC to break it or pick any locks on it increases by 10.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 215","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"perm"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"object"},"range":{"value":null,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"Gold dust worth at least 25 gold, which is consumed.","consumed":true,"cost":25,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/runes-orange-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"OWUxNzY4NjYzZmE0","name":"Ice Storm","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A hail of rock-hard ice pounds to the ground in a 20-foot-radius, 40-foot-high Cylinder centered on a point within range. Each creature in the cylind⁠er must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 2d8 bludgeoning damage and 4d6 cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>Hailstones turn the storm’s area of effect into difficult terrain until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the bludgeoning damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 4th.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 252","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cylinder"},"range":{"value":300,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d8","bludgeoning"],["4d6","cold"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A pinch of dust and a few drops of water","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1030000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/ice-blue-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Harakiki","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This pair of twinned poi feels unnaturally light given their weighted ends. Each culminates in a metal ball bound within a wick wrapping, tethered to a leather handle by a cord of plaited flax strands. The pair are intended to be used lit like twin flaming torches, but despite their wicks being easily flammable, the poi themselves seem immune to the depredations of the flames they create. Neither wick ever actually burns through, and the fire never spreads to their flaxen cords.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A regular fixture at any event or festival that took place at night, entertainment featuring the use of Harakiki was often the highlight of such an occasion. While common dances employing fire poi typically symbolize the wild and destructive nature of fire, or are used as part of rituals designed to venerate gods of summer, those involving Harakiki were more often used to revel in the explosive and infectious essence of laughter and celebration.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapons</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Fire Poi can be used as a set of two flails.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Dual Weapons</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Fire Poi are designed to be wielded together, their synchronized motions weaved into a slow and intricate dance. While you are wielding both of them at once, they are considered to have the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><em>Light</em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">weapon property.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Flaming Poi (1/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Fire Poi spark and burn with a searing white-hot flame. When making the first attack on your turn and wielding them both at once, you can decide to convert</span></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"> all of the weapon damage dealt by the poi into fire damage for the rest of your turn, instead of bludgeoning. Once this feature has been used, it cannot be used again until the next dawn.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":2,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+@mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":6000000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"OapaUfxp0rsUhhFX"}
{"_id":"OjE8yjaqQg4g0OKh","name":"Booming Blade (SCAG)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>As part of the action used to cast this spell, you must make a melee attack with a weapon against one creature within the spell's range, otherwise the spell fails. On a hit, the target suffers the attack's normal effects, and it becomes sheathed in booming energy until the start of your next turn. If the target willingly moves before then, it immediately takes [[/r 1d8]] thunder damage, and the spell ends.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>This spell's damage increases when you reach higher levels. At 5th level, the melee attack deals an extra [[/r 1d8]] thunder damage to the target, and the damage the target takes for moving increases to [[/r 2d8]]. Both damage rolls increase by [[/r 1d8]] at 11th level and 17th level.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"SCAG","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"round"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8","thunder"],["1d8","thunder"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a weapon","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"cantrip","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":12000001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/scag-booming-blade.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Polymorphic Scourge","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb06/polymorphic-scourge.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"199\" height=\"256\" />\"This 'whip' has a distinctly menacing appearance due to the sharp and jagged tooth-like barbs that protrude from its deep purple skin in places, most notably its handle and tip. Clusters of blinking eyes and a vicious-looking mouth that periodically yawns, dribbles, and chatters madly to itself only serve to make the bizarre object even more unsettling.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Polymorphic Scourge is a living mimic that was granted immortality by a magical mishap that impaired its ability to shapeshift into objects. The same spell also re-wrote the mimic's anatomy so that its true form became that of a whip, the likeness it had adopted at the time of the accident. The mimic now forms the whip's handle, with its long pseudopod forming its thong.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Polymorphic Scourge can be used as a whip.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Indentured Shifter</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Polymorphic Scourge has been irrevocably altered by an unfortunate run-in with magic gone awry. It can change into other effectively mundane objects of a similar size to a whip if you will it to do so, but these always look perverted to retain elements and visual clues as to the mimic&rsquo;s true nature.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Sticky</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Certain properties innate to mimics render the Polymorphic Scourge ideal for use as a whip. Its tip is sticky and adhesive, enough so that you can use to pull objects within the whip&rsquo;s reach to you. Such objects cannot be held, worn, or secured; and must not weight greater than 10 lbs.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Grappling</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">As many an unfortunate adventurer has discovered, there are few things in the universe stickier than a mimic. You can use the Polymorphic Scourge to attempt to grapple a creature, even if you don't have a free hand. While grappling a creature using the whip, you cannot use it to make further attacks.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":true,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":8800000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"P1O848r2SUYH5zIo"}
{"name":"Gorbengouger","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb03/gorbengouger.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"64\" height=\"256\" />\"This unusual implement takes the form of a small metal knife with a serrated edge. Though it serves perfectly adequately as a weapon<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>as effective at slicing or shearing as it is piercing and puncturing<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>this blade's true potential lies elsewhere thanks to several clever features of its design. Both serrated and slotted, it is often used in place of a paring knife to peel fruit or remove skins and organs from animal carcasses. A ring of coarse bristles protrude from the point where the object's metal blade meets its wooden handle, held tightly in place by a cord binding. These bristles act as a guard of sorts, preventing a creature using the implement from getting peel shavings or blood spatter on their hands.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Gorbengouger can be used as a dagger.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>One-of-a-Kind</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Gorbengouger is a very unusual implement. It possesses the following unique qualities:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Your attacks with it can deal piercing or slashing damage (wielder's choice).</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">When you use it to deal damage, you deal an additional 1d4 damage.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">It grants you advantage on checks made to extract poisons, harvest organs and glands, and skin animals.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">It never dulls or rusts, and cannot be damaged or destroyed by the effects of creatures that innately damage or corrode metal objects, such as rust monsters.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You can use it as a whetstone to sharpen other blades.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You can use it as a flint for the purposes of starting fires.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d4 + @mod","piercing"],["","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":5700000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[{"_id":"La8fJu29lZT8O8p2","flags":{},"changes":[],"disabled":false,"duration":{"rounds":1},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"New Effect","origin":"Item.YBduF5h1StpJO05c","transfer":true}],"_id":"PG49ZIWpA7yEfvhL"}
{"_id":"PdSYHlVgW5qfFZn9","name":"Greater Restoration (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You imbue a creature you touch with positive energy to undo a debilitating effect. You can reduce the target's <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#exhaustion_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'exhaustion_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >exhaustion</a> level by one, or end one of the following effects on the target:</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">One effect that <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> or <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#petrified_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'petrified_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >petrified</a> the target</li><li class=\"rd__li \">One curse, including the target's attunement to a cursed magic item</li><li class=\"rd__li \">Any reduction to one of the target's ability scores</li><li class=\"rd__li \">One effect reducing the target's hit point maximum</li></ul></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":5,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"diamond dust worth at least 100 gp, which the spell consumes","consumed":true,"cost":100,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":5500001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-greater-restoration.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Sootynga","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Measuring a little under four foot in length, this fukiya blowgun is formed of bamboo that magically remains perpetually green and vibrant. The object's long, thin shaft has been decorated with numerous small notches that have been cut into it in geometric shapes. It has also been ringed in five evenly spaced intervals by layered blades of grass-leaf sweet flag.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Sootyngā belonged to a rōnin who cut it from his murdered master's bamboo garden after his death, determined to fashion a weapon from it that could be used to avenge him. The fallen samurai blessed his apprentice from beyond the grave, bestowing greatness upon the symbolic keepsake that had been taken. When the rōnin awoke the next morning, the length of bamboo had a dozen songbirds gathered around it and had been transformed into Sootyngā.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Sootyngā can be used as a blowgun.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Multishot</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Sootyngā is a superior blowgun, far more suited to combat than mundane alternatives. Attacks made with it deal 1d4 piercing damage, instead of 1. Additionally, it can be loaded with 2 pieces of ammunition at once and when loading a piece of ammunition into it, you can choose to spend a bonus action to load a second piece of ammunition. When you use </span>Sootyngā to make an attack and it has two pieces of ammunition loaded into it, you can fire either or both pieces of ammunition. When you fire two pieces of ammunition at the same time, you roll once to determine if you hit your target. If you do, roll damage for each piece of ammunition individually and then add your Dexterity modifier to the combined total.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Swiftshot.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Sootyngā can be brought to bare at a moment's notice. You can make a single ranged attack with it as a bonus action. As with Multishot, you can discharge 1 or 2 pieces of ammunition already loaded into it as part of this attack.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Staggering Shot</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Shots fired from Sootyngā have a little bite from beyond the grave. When you use it to make an attack, if you hit, you can forgo dealing damage to instead have the target attempt a DC 13 Constitution saving throw, becoming poisoned until the start of your next turn on a fail.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":25,"long":100,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialR","properties":{"amm":true,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":true,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":10900000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-ranged-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"PhO57e1P5VEELbxC"}
{"name":"Baileywick","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb10/baileywick.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"138\" />\"This hardy wooden truncheon serves as a tool for policing urban communities. The club is carved from mahogany</span></em><em>&mdash;</em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">chosen for its rugged durability</span></em><em>&mdash;</em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">and has been topped with a sturdy brass crown. The object also serves as a tipstaff, its interior hollowed out and containing a rolled-up scroll on a spool within it. This scroll can be pulled out and read from if the baton's crown is unscrewed. Both the scroll, and the tipstaff itself, signify the person who bears it as an agent of the law.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Baileywick has served as proof of office for many sheriffs, bailiffs, bondsmen, and law enforcement agents over the years. The tipstaff has proved invaluable in the apprehension of numerous thieves, brigands, killers, and ne&rsquo;er-do-wells, many of whom were able to be successfully arrested without any major incident or serious injury because of it.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Baileywick can be used as a club.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Peacekeeper</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Baileywick is designed to prevent crimes, not take lives. It gains the <em>Non-lethal</em></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> weapon property.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Rule Clarification, Non-lethal.</strong> The non-lethal weapon property can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.wlHHsHmNANE9pSbd]{Weapon Properties}.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Judgement</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Few who've carried Baileywick have suffered criminality easily, enforcing the law without mercy. You deal +1 bonus damage on a hit when using it to strike a creature with a chaotic alignment.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Local Legislation</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Thanks to Baileywick, its bearer and their companions are always kept up to date on local laws, so that they can both enforce them and avoid running afoul of them. The text on the parchment contained within the tipstaff shifts and changes depending on where in the world you happen to be, always reflecting local laws. If the region doesn't have a written statute of laws, this feature doesn't function.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Lawman</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Baileywick identifies its bearer as a bastion of law and order. You have advantage on Charisma (persuasion) checks made to interact with law enforcement officials and on Charisma (intimidation) checks made to threaten criminals, within the confines of the law.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":400000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"PjUoUaxxDT3cHAqT"}
{"_id":"PmE9IwQ1zy8lkTRs","name":"Sleep","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>This spell sends creatures into a magical slumber. Roll [[/r 5d8]]; the total is how many hit points of creatures this spell can affect. Creatures within 20 feet of a point you choose within range are affected in ascending order of their current hit points (ignoring <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#unconscious_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'unconscious_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >unconscious</a> creatures).</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Starting with the creature that has the lowest current hit points, each creature affected by this spell falls <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#unconscious_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'unconscious_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >unconscious</a> until the spell ends, the sleeper takes damage, or someone uses an action to shake or slap the sleeper awake. Subtract each creature's hit points from the total before moving on to the creature with the next lowest hit points. A creature's hit points must be equal to or less than the remaining total for that creature to be affected.</p><p>Undead and creatures immune to being <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> aren't affected by this spell.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, roll an additional [[/r 2d8]] for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":90,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d8",""]],"versatile":""},"formula":"5d8","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a pinch of fine sand, rose petals, or a cricket","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"2d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":12400001,"flags":{"itemacro":{"macro":{"_data":{"name":"Sleep","type":"script","scope":"global","command":"// based on @ccjmk macro for sleep. Gets targets and ignores those who are immune to sleep.\n// Requires https://gitlab.com/crymic/foundry-vtt-macros/-/blob/master/Callback Macros/Cub_Condition.js\n(async ()=>{\nasync function wait(ms) {\n  return new Promise(resolve => {\n    setTimeout(resolve, ms);\n  });\n}\nlet sleepHp = await args[0].damageTotal;\nif(!sleepHp) {\n  ui.notifications.error(\"No arguments passed to Sleep macro\");\n  return;\n}\nconsole.log(`starting Sleep macro with sleepHp[${sleepHp}]`);\n// Get Targets\nlet targets = await args[0].targets.filter(a=> !canvas.tokens.get(a._id).actor.data.data.traits.ci.custom?.includes(\"Sleep\")).sort((a,b) => canvas.tokens.get(a._id).actor.data.data.attributes.hp.value < canvas.tokens.get(b._id).actor.data.data.attributes.hp.value ? -1 : 1);\nlet Cub_Condition = game.macros.getName(\"Cub_Condition\");\nlet remainingSleepHp = await sleepHp;\nconst condition = \"Unconscious\";\nlet slept_target = [];\nfor(let i = 0; i < await targets.length; i++) {\n  let target = await canvas.tokens.get(targets[i]._id);\n  let targetHpValue = target.actor.data.data.attributes.hp.value;\n  if(targetHpValue != 0){\n  if (game.cub.hasCondition(condition, target)){\n    console.log(`${target.name} with hp ${targetHpValue} already asleep, skipping.`);\n    slept_target.push(`<div class=\"midi-qol-flex-container\"><div>skip</div><div class=\"midi-qol-target-npc midi-qol-target-name\" id=\"${target.id}\"> ${target.name}</div><div><img src=\"${target.data.img}\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" style=\"border:0px\"></div></div>`);\n    }\n    if((remainingSleepHp >= targetHpValue) && (!game.cub.hasCondition(condition, target))){\n      remainingSleepHp -= targetHpValue;\n      console.log(`${target.name} with hp ${targetHpValue} falls asleep, remaining hp from dice ${remainingSleepHp}.`);\n      slept_target.push(`<div class=\"midi-qol-flex-container\"><div>hits</div><div class=\"midi-qol-target-npc midi-qol-target-name\" id=\"${target.id}\"> ${target.name}</div><div><img src=\"${target.data.img}\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" style=\"border:0px\"></div></div>`);\n      Cub_Condition.execute(target, condition, \"add\");\n    }\n    if((remainingSleepHp < targetHpValue) && (!game.cub.hasCondition(condition, target))) {\n      console.log(`${target.name} with hp ${targetHpValue} resists asleep, skipping.`);\n      slept_target.push(`<div class=\"midi-qol-flex-container\"><div>miss</div><div class=\"midi-qol-target-npc midi-qol-target-name\" id=\"${target.id}\"> ${target.name}</div><div><img src=\"${target.data.img}\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" style=\"border:0px\"></div></div>`);\n    }\n  }\n}\nawait wait(500);\nlet slept_list = slept_target.join('');\nlet slept_results = `<div><div class=\"midi-qol-nobox\">${slept_list}</div></div>`;\nconst chatMessage = await game.messages.get(args[0].itemCardId);\nlet content = await duplicate(chatMessage.data.content);\nconst searchString =  /<div class=\"midi-qol-hits-display\">[\\s\\S]*<div class=\"end-midi-qol-hits-display\">/g;\nconst replaceString = `<div class=\"midi-qol-hits-display\"><div class=\"end-midi-qol-hits-display\">${slept_results}`;\ncontent = await content.replace(searchString, replaceString);\nawait chatMessage.update({content: content});\n})();","author":"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0"},"data":{"name":"Sleep","type":"script","scope":"global","command":"// based on @ccjmk macro for sleep. Gets targets and ignores those who are immune to sleep.\n// Requires https://gitlab.com/crymic/foundry-vtt-macros/-/blob/master/Callback Macros/Cub_Condition.js\n(async ()=>{\nasync function wait(ms) {\n  return new Promise(resolve => {\n    setTimeout(resolve, ms);\n  });\n}\nlet sleepHp = await args[0].damageTotal;\nif(!sleepHp) {\n  ui.notifications.error(\"No arguments passed to Sleep macro\");\n  return;\n}\nconsole.log(`starting Sleep macro with sleepHp[${sleepHp}]`);\n// Get Targets\nlet targets = await args[0].targets.filter(a=> !canvas.tokens.get(a._id).actor.data.data.traits.ci.custom?.includes(\"Sleep\")).sort((a,b) => canvas.tokens.get(a._id).actor.data.data.attributes.hp.value < canvas.tokens.get(b._id).actor.data.data.attributes.hp.value ? -1 : 1);\nlet Cub_Condition = game.macros.getName(\"Cub_Condition\");\nlet remainingSleepHp = await sleepHp;\nconst condition = \"Unconscious\";\nlet slept_target = [];\nfor(let i = 0; i < await targets.length; i++) {\n  let target = await canvas.tokens.get(targets[i]._id);\n  let targetHpValue = target.actor.data.data.attributes.hp.value;\n  if(targetHpValue != 0){\n  if (game.cub.hasCondition(condition, target)){\n    console.log(`${target.name} with hp ${targetHpValue} already asleep, skipping.`);\n    slept_target.push(`<div class=\"midi-qol-flex-container\"><div>skip</div><div class=\"midi-qol-target-npc midi-qol-target-name\" id=\"${target.id}\"> ${target.name}</div><div><img src=\"${target.data.img}\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" style=\"border:0px\"></div></div>`);\n    }\n    if((remainingSleepHp >= targetHpValue) && (!game.cub.hasCondition(condition, target))){\n      remainingSleepHp -= targetHpValue;\n      console.log(`${target.name} with hp ${targetHpValue} falls asleep, remaining hp from dice ${remainingSleepHp}.`);\n      slept_target.push(`<div class=\"midi-qol-flex-container\"><div>hits</div><div class=\"midi-qol-target-npc midi-qol-target-name\" id=\"${target.id}\"> ${target.name}</div><div><img src=\"${target.data.img}\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" style=\"border:0px\"></div></div>`);\n      Cub_Condition.execute(target, condition, \"add\");\n    }\n    if((remainingSleepHp < targetHpValue) && (!game.cub.hasCondition(condition, target))) {\n      console.log(`${target.name} with hp ${targetHpValue} resists asleep, skipping.`);\n      slept_target.push(`<div class=\"midi-qol-flex-container\"><div>miss</div><div class=\"midi-qol-target-npc midi-qol-target-name\" id=\"${target.id}\"> ${target.name}</div><div><img src=\"${target.data.img}\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" style=\"border:0px\"></div></div>`);\n    }\n  }\n}\nawait wait(500);\nlet slept_list = slept_target.join('');\nlet slept_results = `<div><div class=\"midi-qol-nobox\">${slept_list}</div></div>`;\nconst chatMessage = await game.messages.get(args[0].itemCardId);\nlet content = await duplicate(chatMessage.data.content);\nconst searchString =  /<div class=\"midi-qol-hits-display\">[\\s\\S]*<div class=\"end-midi-qol-hits-display\">/g;\nconst replaceString = `<div class=\"midi-qol-hits-display\"><div class=\"end-midi-qol-hits-display\">${slept_results}`;\ncontent = await content.replace(searchString, replaceString);\nawait chatMessage.update({content: content});\n})();","author":"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0"},"options":{},"apps":{},"compendium":null}},"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":"ItemMacro"}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-sleep.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"PoUFRT5b8RBI24It","name":"Counterspell (3rd Level)","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3,"OGI1ZmNiNjZhNWIz":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<div>\n\t\t\t<div><i>Scroll, minor tier, uncommon</i></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"flex w-100\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-4\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-8 text-right\">  </div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<hr>\n\t\t<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p>A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written as a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.</p><p>If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make an ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. The DC is 13. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.</p><p>Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and the scroll itself crumbles to dust.</p><p>A spell cast from this scroll has a save DC of 15 and an attack bonus of [[/r 1d20+7]] (+7).</p><p>A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 13 Intelligence (<span class=\"help--hover\" onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseOver(event, this, 715, {})\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseMove(event, this)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseLeave(event, this)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Arcana</span>) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"DMG","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":"","autoDestroy":true,"autoUse":true},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"scroll","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"tMPMWheY9FGPdLEs","sort":300001,"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"items.html","source":"DMG","hash":"spell%20scroll%20(3rd%20level)_dmg","data":{"item":{"name":"Spell Scroll (3rd Level)","source":"DMG","page":202,"srd":true,"type":"SC","tier":"minor","rarity":"uncommon","entries":["A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written as a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.","If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make an ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. The DC is 13. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.","Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and the scroll itself crumbles to dust.","A spell cast from this scroll has a save DC of 15 and an attack bonus of {@hit 7}.","A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 13 Intelligence ({@skill Arcana}) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed."],"lootTables":["Magic Item Table B"],"_isEnhanced":true,"_category":"Other","_typeListText":["scroll"],"_typeHtml":"scroll","_attunement":null,"_attunementCategory":"No","_fProperties":[],"_fMisc":["SRD","Magic"],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["minor"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Scroll"}}},"magicitems":{"enabled":true,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"1","chargeType":"c1","destroy":true,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l","destroyCheck":"d1","destroyType":"dt1","spells":{"0":{"id":"M2M1NmE4OWI2NDRm","name":"Counterspell","pack":"world","img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/slice-orange-3.jpg","baseLevel":"3","level":"3","consumption":"3","upcast":"3","upcastCost":"1","flatDc":false}}}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/tied-scroll.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Norma's Spectacles","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This pair of rounded spectacles, complete with small silver case, is in pristine condition and has a chain linking the edges of its frames. This chain prevents the glasses, primarily used for reading and for watching over the proclivities of other readers, from slipping off the head of their wearer.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Norma's Spectacles were a gift from the head wizard of a ministry of magic to Norma Barking, the institute's librarian, as a thank you for her many years long service. Norma served the organization as custodian over its manifold parchments and tomes for almost a century. In her time, she attempted to retire on no less than fourteen occasions, however she was the only one who could navigate the heaving, overpacked shelves of the inscrutable library. Norma was reported missing one day when she failed to show up for work, her remains discovered between two towering stacks of books several decades later.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Shush (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Former owners of Norma's Spectacles have had no trouble maintaining order within their respective domains. While wearing them, you can point </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">at a single creature within 60 foot and utter a stern reprimand a</span>s an action. Should you do so, the target must make a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw, becoming unable to speak or intentionally produce any audible sound for 1 minute on a fail. The creature can attempt its saving throw again each time it takes damage. This feature resets at dawn.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Sagacity of the Librarian</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Norma's Spectacles afford their wearer certain advantages while in a library, athenaeum, study, or other repository of books and scholarly learning. Consequently, you gain the following benefits: </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you know the name of a book, the name of its credited author&mdash;if there is one&mdash;, or another distinguishing feature of it, you can picture where it can be found if it's in the same location as you.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have advantage on any checks made to recall the name of&mdash;or details about&mdash;a book related to a subject that you're currently pondering, assuming one has ever been published and you could possibly know of it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you're attempting to find a specific reference or mote of information from a book that you have in your possession, including one found in or taken from the location you are in, you can close the book and automatically open it to the relevant page.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have advantage on Wisdom (perception or insight) checks to notice if things have been moved, a creature is attempting to hide from you, or anything else untoward is taking place in your location. Additionally, you also have advantage on Intelligence (investigation) checks made to discover hidden or secret passageways in your location.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":0.1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":7700000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"Pz4p94Lc9LTqXTBZ"}
{"_id":"QMdpLAGw2f5SY4OB","name":"Potion of Greater Healing","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3,"jSIbaKrMQZ5trOzn":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<div>\n\t\t\t<div><i>Potion, minor tier, uncommon</i></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"flex w-100\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-4\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-8 text-right\">  </div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<hr>\n\t\t<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p>You regain [[/r 4d4 + 4]] hit points when you drink this potion. The potion's red liquid glimmers when agitated.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"DMG","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"charges","autoDestroy":true,"autoUse":true},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["4d4 + 4","healing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"potion","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"tMPMWheY9FGPdLEs","sort":800001,"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"items.html","source":"DMG","hash":"potion%20of%20greater%20healing_dmg","data":{"item":{"name":"Potion of Greater Healing","source":"DMG","page":187,"srd":true,"type":"P","tier":"minor","rarity":"uncommon","entries":["You regain {@dice 4d4 + 4} hit points when you drink this potion. The potion's red liquid glimmers when agitated."],"lootTables":["Magic Item Table A","Magic Item Table B"],"_isEnhanced":true,"_category":"Other","_typeListText":["potion"],"_typeHtml":"potion","_attunement":null,"_attunementCategory":"No","_fProperties":[],"_fMisc":["SRD","Magic"],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["minor"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Potion"}}},"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""},"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/items/potions/major-red.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"ygUkiGscd0MOdMeO","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":true},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"aura":"None","radius":null}},"changes":[{"key":"data.bonuses.heal.damage","value":"4d4+4","mode":2,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"New Effect","origin":"Item.QMdpLAGw2f5SY4OB","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"QlQKxiuBo9rnQ4b5","name":"Leomund's Secret Chest","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You hide a chest, and all its contents, on the Ethereal Plane. You must touch the chest and the miniature replica that serves as a material component for the spell. The chest can contain up to 12 cubic feet of nonliving material (3 feet by 2 feet by 2 feet).</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>While the chest remains on the Ethereal Plane, you can use an action and touch the replica to recall the chest. It appears in an unoccupied space on the ground within 5 feet of you. You can send the chest back to the Ethereal Plane by using an action and touching both the chest and the replica.</p><p>After 60 days, there is a cumulative 5 percent chance per day that the spell's effect ends. This effect ends if you cast this spell again, if the smaller replica chest is destroyed, or if you choose to end the spell as an action. If the spell ends and the larger chest is on the Ethereal Plane, it is irretrievably lost.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":""},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"an exquisite chest, 3 feet by 2 feet by 2 feet, constructed from rare materials worth at least 5,000 gp, and a Tiny replica made from the same materials worth at least 50 gp","consumed":false,"cost":500000,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":2500001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/evil-eye-eerie-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Presto","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb07/presto.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"85\" height=\"256\" />\"Intended for use by a magician, this dapper suit has been bespokely tailored to make anyone wearing it stand out. It comes complete with a swanky tophat, golden bowtie, white leather gloves, and a pair of sparkling, brightly-polished shoes. Not only are the fabrics and materials used throughout the outfit of exquisite quality, but its detailing has also been stitched with a reflective silk to finish the entire ensemble with a golden sheen.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Magician&rsquo;s Outfit was commissioned by an eccentric aristocrat who loved throwing elaborate gatherings at his weekend retreat just outside the city where he resided. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As much a showman as a socialite, the gregarious aristo couldn&rsquo;t help but insinuate himself into the evening&rsquo;s entertainment in some way, eventually becoming as renowned for his magical talent as he was for the lavish parties he hosted. When he passed, he left this outfit, along with the rest of his estate, to various local theaters, troupes, and bardic colleges&mdash;hoping to encourage others to pick up the performing arts that had brought him so much joy in life.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Trade Secrets</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Though wizards share the nature of their gift with the world, true magicians never reveal their secrets. While you are wearing Presto, Intelligence (arcana and investigation), and Wisdom (perception) checks made by others to identify whether magic performed by you</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> is genuine or not are made with disadvantage.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Family Show</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Working with certain groups is every stage performer&rsquo;s worst nightmare. You have advantage on checks made to interact with children and animals as part of a magic act or when making a Charisma (performance) check to perform a magic trick while wearing Presto.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Secret Spellcasting</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Unless one watches closely, it&rsquo;s very easy to miss a magician&rsquo;s subtle gestures or hushed whispers. When you attempt to cast a spell with a somatic or material component while wearing Presto, you can attempt a Dexterity (sleight of hand) check with advantage against your audiences&rsquo; Wisdom (perception) result or passive Perception score. On a success, your spellcasting goes unnoticed. Additionally, when casting any spell with a verbal component, you can choose any number of creatures within sight and have those creatures not hear your spellcasting. Any spell that stipulates that affected creatures become aware of the spell&rsquo;s effect once it wears off function as normal.</span> </span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":11700000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/clothing.png","effects":[],"_id":"R34nlANTnnaLnhRd"}
{"_id":"RD4j4VT6oDkDwflO","name":"Wall of Stone (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A nonmagical wall of solid stone springs into existence at a point you choose within range. The wall is 6 inches thick and is composed of ten 10-foot-by-10-foot panels. Each panel must be contiguous with at least one other panel. Alternatively, you can create 10-foot-by-20-foot panels that are only 3 inches thick.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If the wall cuts through a creature's space when it appears, the creature is pushed to one side of the wall (your choice). If a creature would be surrounded on all sides by the wall (or the wall and another solid surface), that creature can make a Dexterity saving throw. On a success, it can use its reaction to move up to its speed so that it is no longer enclosed by the wall.</p><p>The wall can have any shape you desire, though it can't occupy the same space as a creature or object. The wall doesn't need to be vertical or rest on any firm foundation. It must, however, merge with and be solidly supported by existing stone. Thus, you can use this spell to bridge a chasm or create a ramp.</p><p>If you create a span greater than 20 feet in length, you must halve the size of each panel to create supports. You can crudely shape the wall to create crenellations, battlements, and so on.</p><p>The wall is an object made of stone that can be damaged and thus breached. Each panel has AC 15 and 30 hit points per inch of thickness. Reducing a panel to 0 hit points destroys it and might cause connected panels to collapse at the DM's discretion.</p><p>If you maintain your concentration on this spell for its whole duration, the wall becomes permanent and can't be dispelled. Otherwise, the wall disappears when the spell ends.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":100,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"wall"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":5,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a small block of granite","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":6000001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-wall-of-stone.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Playt","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"On its own, this modest example of padded armor displays no unusual or noteworthy characteristics. However, when donned, its appearance can change radically to meet the desires of its wearer. Originally created by a knight who truly understood the power of misdirection, this individual crafted the item to help him protect his king from the machinations of a group of treasonous mages. Unfortunately, the spellslingers succeeded in their quest for regicide and were able to assassinate the king. The noble knight's mission then turned from one of protection to vengeance as he pursued, persecuted, and, ultimately, punished those who'd moved against his former charge. Having been misplaced in the aftermath of the knight who invented Playt's passing, the item faded into antiquity for many years. Although, such a useful and powerful artifact rarely languishes in total obscurity for too long before someone discovers it and recognizes its value.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Magically Warded</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Playt protects its wearer against the depredations of magic spells and arcane machinations. You gain a +1 bonus to your Armor Class against melee and ranged spell attacks while wearing it.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Glamor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Paired up with an individual whose bluster and bravado equal its own, Playt can ably confound all but the most astute into thinking that its wearer is a hulking, heavily-armored tank. When worn, it can magically disguise itself as any suit of heavy armor. Its exact appearance is determined by you and you can change it on a whim. Strikes against Playt sound as if they're connecting with metal and you can choose for your movements to sound just like those of a creature moving in heavy metal armor while wearing it. If you do so, you must also take disadvantage on Dexterity (stealth) checks just like you would with actual plate or chainmail armor, though you can choose to end this effect at any time. Playt cannot be used to conceal items or other equipment; only hide its own true nature. Its real form can be revealed through the use of spellcasting and</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> with Truesight. Additionally, each time a creature that sees Playt as heavy armor makes an attack roll against you while you are wearing it and hits, they must attempt a DC 13 Wisdom (perception) check. On a success, they're able to dispel the illusion and see Playt for what it really is.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":8,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":11,"type":"light","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":10600000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/light-armor.png","effects":[],"_id":"RiMCXpAnc3KvGEmZ"}
{"name":"Slaver's Sapper","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"1wUd3uOZ5zJCugQT":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"When not in use, this object resembles a small leather baton or truncheon. In this state, it doesn't look especially foreboding or intimidating, however, when swung with the intent of ensnaring a target, it reveals its hidden potential. At the apex of its swing, a net, formed entirely of bright, bluish energy, springs from its tip and unfurls to entangle its target. Once the net is no longer in use, it flickers and falters before abruptly fading into nothingness, only to reappear a moment later if called upon again. An instrument of the vile and wicked, this strange device belonged to slavers who used it to capture those whose freedom they would see stripped away for the prospect of coin.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Slaver's Sapper can be used as a blackjack.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong style=\"font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification: Blackjacks.</strong><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"> Rules for blackjacks can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Dirty Double-cross</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Slaver's Sapper is no common implement. </span>It resembles a small leather sap whenever you are not actively using it to restrain a creature. However, w<span class=\"fontstyle0\">hen you use it to make an attack against a creature within reach and you hit, you can cause its energy net to spring forth and restrain your target. This functions as a net but with the following changes:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>It has a range of 5 foot.</li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It only affects Medium or smaller creatures.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It is considered to have 10 hit points, instead of 5; and an armor class of 13, instead of 10. Its handle has 40 hit points, but an armor class of just 8. However, its handle has immunity to nonmagical bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature restrained by it must succeed on a DC 13 Strength check to break free.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If a creature fails a Strength check made to break free of it or deals it damage but fails to break it, they take 1d4 lightning damage and it recovers hit points equaling the damage dealt.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If damage is dealt to it that brings the energy net to 0 hit points, it dissipates and the Slaver's Sapper cannot be used as a net again for 24 hours. Only damage dealt to its handle can destroy the item.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"str","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":true,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":11800000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"S01q9SWS0Kg2oJsb"}
{"name":"Navigator's Sextant","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"tool","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb05/navigators-sextant.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"253\" height=\"256\" />\"Already manufactured to exacting standards by a veteran sailor, before being further blessed by a wish-granting efreeti, this useful instrument is both functional and enchanted with certain advantages over a mundane sextant.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">For obvious reasons, it has a tendency to make its way into the possession of navigators, helmsmen, and naval captains, who are often sighted atop their ship's bow making use of the object. Looking through its telescopic sight, a creature who understands how to read its markings can use it to estimate the angle and altitude of celestial bodies relative to the horizon, aiding them in steering a ship safely towards its destination.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tool of the Navigator</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Navigator's Sextant is a boon to any wayfarer seeking the right path. While at sea, it can be used as a set of navigator's tools. You can still add your proficiency bonus to checks made to use it as a set of navigator's even if you are not proficient with navigator's tools. If you are proficient in the use of navigator's tools, you add you double your proficiency bonus instead.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Eyeglass</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Navigator's Sextant's lens provides its user with telescopic magnification. It can be used as a spyglass, except its magnification is reduced so that objects viewed through it appear at 1.5 times their usual size, instead of double their usual size.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Weather Whisperer</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Navigator's Sextant can reveal all kinds of useful things about the world. While you are at sea and it is about your person, you can predict weather patterns in your current location for the next three days. Additionally, you can always tell how far you've traveled on a ship or boat for the last 24 hours as well as your direction of travel.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Ocean Object</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Navigator's Sextant loves the ocean and is never content to be hidden away. If stored below deck and left unsupervised, it will always eventually turn up somewhere on the deck.</span></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"ability":"int","chatFlavor":"","proficient":1,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":20300000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/tool.jpg","effects":[],"_id":"S7t4ZlqXqPqburkx"}
{"_id":"SAseBUNp93EIOiAG","name":"Polymorph (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>This spell transforms a creature that you can see within range into a new form. An unwilling creature must make a Wisdom saving throw to avoid the effect. The spell has no effect on a shapechanger or a creature with 0 hit points.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The transformation lasts for the duration, or until the target drops to 0 hit points or dies. The new form can be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flsttype:beast=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >any beast</a> whose challenge rating is equal to or less than the target's (or the target's level, if it doesn't have a challenge rating). The target's game statistics, including mental ability scores, are replaced by the statistics of the chosen beast. It retains its alignment and personality.</p><p>The target assumes the hit points of its new form. When it reverts to its normal form, the creature returns to the number of hit points it had before it transformed. If it reverts as a result of dropping to 0 hit points, any excess damage carries over to its normal form. As long as the excess damage doesn't reduce the creature's normal form to 0 hit points, it isn't knocked unconscious.</p><p>The creature is limited in the actions it can perform by the nature of its new form, and it can't speak, cast spells, or take any other action that requires hands or speech.</p><p>The target's gear melds into the new form. The creature can't activate, use, wield, or otherwise benefit from any of its equipment.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a caterpillar cocoon","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":4900001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-polymorph.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"SMbCWb0PS2hD4Msk","name":"Hail of Thorns (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The next time you hit a creature with a ranged weapon attack before the spell ends, this spell creates a rain of thorns that sprouts from your ranged weapon or ammunition. In addition to the normal effect of the attack, the target of the attack and each creature within 5 feet of it must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes [[/r 1d10]] piercing damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"137\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>If you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d10]] for each slot level above 1st (to a maximum of [[/r 6d10]]).</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"self","type":"self"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d10","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d10"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":9400001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-hail-of-thorns.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Tarpentorde","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Formed of layers upon layers of interwoven strands of fabric spun and compressed together, this auburn poncho is as tough as raw leather and scarcely weightier than a feather. Usually flecked with dirt or caked in dried mud, it looks like it ought to belong to someone most at home in the wilds, though that isn't necessarily the case. Its seams are covered with a gold-beige colored trim that, although faded, adds a splash of extravagance to an otherwise utilitarian garment.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Deceptively Padded</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Though unusually thin and light for a poncho, Tarpentorde is resilient and protective. Though it doesn't count as light, medium, or heavy armor, it is worn in place of armor. While wearing it, you have an armor class equal to 11 + your Dexterity modifier.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Vital Protection (1/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Tarpentorde has an astounding and inexplicable knack for keeping its wearer out of harm's way. Once per day, when you are struck with a critical hit while wearing it, you can spend your reaction to nullify the critical strike. The triggering attack is still considered to have struck you; however, it is not considered to be a critical hit.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"If you are struck with a critical hit while wearing Tarpentorde"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":11,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":12800000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/clothing.png","effects":[],"_id":"SbXHk0aQ52pZVpGQ"}
{"_id":"Sg8AqgvfmveYNoGK","name":"Antimagic Field (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A 10-foot-radius invisible sphere of antimagic surrounds you. This area is divorced from the magical energy that suffuses the multiverse. Within the sphere, spells can't be cast, summoned creatures disappear, and even magic items become mundane. Until the spell ends, the sphere moves with you, centered on you.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Spells and other magical effects, except those created by an artifact or a deity, are suppressed in the sphere and can't protrude into it. A slot expended to cast a suppressed spell is consumed. While an effect is suppressed, it doesn't function, but the time it spends suppressed counts against its duration.</p><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"128\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Targeted Effects.</span></span> <p>Spells and other magical effects, such as magic missile and charm person, that target a creature or an object in the sphere have no effect on that target.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"129\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Areas of Magic.</span></span> <p>The area of another spell or magical effect, such as <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#fireball_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'fireball_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >fireball</a>, can't extend into the sphere. If the sphere overlaps an area of magic, the part of the area that is covered by the sphere is suppressed. For example, the flames created by a wall of fire are suppressed within the sphere, creating a gap in the wall if the overlap is large enough.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"130\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Spells.</span></span> <p>Any active spell or other magical effect on a creature or an object in the sphere is suppressed while the creature or object is in it.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"131\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Magic Items.</span></span> <p>The properties and powers of magic items are suppressed in the sphere. For example, a +1 longsword in the sphere functions as a nonmagical longsword.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>A magic weapon's properties and powers are suppressed if it is used against a target in the sphere or wielded by an attacker in the sphere. If a magic weapon or a piece of magic ammunition fully leaves the sphere (for example, if you fire a magic arrow or throw a magic spear at a target outside the sphere), the magic of the item ceases to be suppressed as soon as it exits.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"132\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Magical Travel.</span></span> <p>Teleportation and planar travel fail to work in the sphere, whether the sphere is the destination or the departure point for such magical travel. A portal to another location, world, or plane of existence, as well as an opening to an extradimensional space such as that created by the rope trick spell, temporarily closes while in the sphere.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"133\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Creatures and Objects.</span></span> <p>A creature or object summoned or created by magic temporarily winks out of existence in the sphere. Such a creature instantly reappears once the space the creature occupied is no longer within the sphere.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"134\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Dispel Magic.</span></span> <p>Spells and magical effects such as <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#dispel%20magic_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'dispel%20magic_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >dispel magic</a> have no effect on the sphere. Likewise, the spheres created by different <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#antimagic%20field_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'antimagic%20field_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >antimagic field</a> spells don't nullify each other.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":10,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":8,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a pinch of powdered iron or iron filings","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":9000001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-antimagic-field.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Sj1YG7CPhun1hbtk","name":"Greater Restoration (5th Level)","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3,"jSIbaKrMQZ5trOzn":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<div>\n\t\t\t<div><i>Scroll, minor tier, rare</i></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"flex w-100\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-4\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-8 text-right\">  </div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<hr>\n\t\t<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p>A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written as a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.</p><p>If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make an ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. The DC is 15. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.</p><p>Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and the scroll itself crumbles to dust.</p><p>A spell cast from this scroll has a save DC of 17 and an attack bonus of [[/r 1d20+9]] (+9).</p><p>A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 15 Intelligence (<span class=\"help--hover\" onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseOver(event, this, 717, {})\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseMove(event, this)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseLeave(event, this)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Arcana</span>) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"DMG","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":"","autoDestroy":true,"autoUse":true},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"scroll","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"tMPMWheY9FGPdLEs","sort":1000001,"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"items.html","source":"DMG","hash":"spell%20scroll%20(5th%20level)_dmg","data":{"item":{"name":"Spell Scroll (5th Level)","source":"DMG","page":204,"srd":true,"type":"SC","tier":"minor","rarity":"rare","entries":["A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written as a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.","If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make an ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. The DC is 15. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.","Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and the scroll itself crumbles to dust.","A spell cast from this scroll has a save DC of 17 and an attack bonus of {@hit 9}.","A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 15 Intelligence ({@skill Arcana}) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed."],"lootTables":["Magic Item Table C"],"_isEnhanced":true,"_category":"Other","_typeListText":["scroll"],"_typeHtml":"scroll","_attunement":null,"_attunementCategory":"No","_fProperties":[],"_fMisc":["SRD","Magic"],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["minor"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Scroll"}}},"magicitems":{"enabled":true,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"1","chargeType":"c1","destroy":true,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l","destroyCheck":"d1","destroyType":"dt1","spells":{"0":{"id":"6tfdNiGJqBZLgijH","name":"Greater Restoration","pack":"world","img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/heal-sky-3.jpg","baseLevel":"5","level":"5","consumption":"5","upcast":"5","upcastCost":"1","flatDc":false}}}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/tied-scroll.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Shipwrecker","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb05/shipwrecker.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"256\" />\"This enormous heavy crossbow puts most others of its ilk to shame, thanks to its size and weight. Rather than load common, off-the-rack bolts suited for just any crossbow, its lock is so large that it only takes full-sized marlinspikes. Legend has it that its wooden stock was cut from the keel of the Renard, a priceless racing yacht that once belonged to a beloved queen. Though the crossbow has seen much use over the years, it was, until recently, retired from service by its owner&mdash;a tavern master in a seedy, lawless dockside wharf&mdash;and hung up as an ornament. That said, this individual has a predilection for cards and has been known to offer up the crossbow as a wager when the grog starts flowing.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Shipwrecker can be used as a heavy crossbow.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Oversized Shooter</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Shipwrecker is impressively large&mdash;even for a heavy crossbow&mdash;and only fires marlinspikes. A satchel of 20 Marlinspikes costs 4 GP, weighs 4 lb., and confers a +1 bonus to attack rolls due to their size and armor penetration. Additionally, the implement itself weighs 24 lb. and you must have a Strength score of 12 or higher when using it to make attack rolls or suffer disadvantage.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Wrecker of Ships</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Though Shipwrecker is most often brought to bare against sailors, pirates, and oceanic creatures, it has brought about the demise of several craft over the years. Attacks made with it benefit from the following perks:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">They bypass the damage threshold of land and sea vehicles.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Objects made of wood are considered to have vulnerability to damage dealt by it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A flight of a shot fired from it is not interrupted by breaking through a wooden object as a result of destroying it, allowing it to continue until it loses momentum or strikes another object. If it should strike another object during its flight, make a second attack roll against this object, but with disadvantage. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">On a success, it also strikes this object and deals damage as normal. Otherwise, the marlinspike bounces off of it and falls to the ground or misses it altogether.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":24,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":100,"long":400,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"1","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d10 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialR","properties":{"amm":true,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":true,"lgt":false,"lod":true,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":9900000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-ranged-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"TMkTV7YXfgDjnvd6"}
{"_id":"TMy7RAuWZfcYikyO","name":"Shadow of Moil","permission":{"default":-1,"bOqyKS8LL2EWqEnK":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Flame-like shadows wreathe your body until the spell ends, causing you to become heavily obscured to others. The shadows turn dim light within 10 feet of you into darkness, and bright light in the same area to dim light.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Until the spell ends, you have resistance to radiant damage. In addition, whenever a creature within 10 feet of you hits you with an attack, the shadows lash out at that creature, dealing it [[/r 2d8]] necrotic damage.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"XGE","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d8","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"an undead eyeball encased in a gem worth at least 150 gp","consumed":false,"cost":150,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":null,"sort":800001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/xge-shadow-of-moil.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"kvyopVz8Ljsi1bS1","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"transfer":true}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Concentration","origin":"Item.TMy7RAuWZfcYikyO","tint":"","transfer":true},{"_id":"0smJz6LysCGHeK48","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":true},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"24 - T10 - Evil Aura\"","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/xge-shadow-of-moil.jpg","label":"Shadow of Moil","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"name":"Boarding Axegun","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb05/boarding-axegun.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"94\" />\"This deadly weapon serves simultaneously as a boarding axe and also a flintlock pistol. Formed of rust-resistant stainless steel, and wood treated to protect against the depredations of oceanic spray, the implement has been specifically engineered for use at sea. Built for function and utility over other considerations, the one indulgence its creator afforded themselves is the elaborate stencils of skulls and roses that have been cut into its metallic surfaces.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Boarding Axegun can be used as a battleaxe.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Ranged Shot</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">There's more to this unusual-looking axe than it seems. You can use the Boarding Axegun to make a ranged attack as a bonus action. Ranged attacks </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">made with it are calculated as normal and only require you to be proficient in battleaxes to be able to apply your proficiency bonus to your attack rolls. Such attacks deal 1d10 + your Dexterity modifier piercing damage, and have a range of 30/90 foot. For the purposes of making such an attack, the axegun is considered to have the loading and ammunition properties, and sling bullets can be used as ammunition for it. When fired, the Boarding Axegun creates a booming noise that can be heard out to a distance of 120 foot.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Boarder's Blaster</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The weapon of a vanguard, the Boarding Axegun can usually be found amongst the first wave of those brave enough to board an opposing ship. Your ranged attack with it</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> deal an additional 1d4 damage on the first round of combat.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":90,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":"1d10 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":2900000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"TOwhwv5uZY8kHFdH"}
{"name":"Emperor's Chosen","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This exquisite jewelled pendant is a treasure by any measure of such things. Its masterfully shaped face is formed of striking jade and cut to resemble a dragon's terrifying visage, right down to its snarling countenance. Light shone through the pendant casts a silhouette of an ancient emperor's seal. A band of gold loops around the impression of a dragon, before joining a golden chain that runs up to a gilded clasp&ndash;allowing its wearer to fasten the accessory securely in place. The object&mdash;pendant and chain&mdash;is surprisingly heavy, offering a weight that speaks volumes as to its quality and refinement.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Emperor's Chosen is a distinctive accessory previously worn by an emperor's most trusted servant, who acted as his mouthpiece. This individual traveled far and wide at the emperor's behest, ruling and arbitrating in his stead. Of the duties that the servant had to perform, maintaining peaceful relations with the many dragons who lived throughout the kingdom was perhaps the most important. Emperor's Chosen proved time and time again to be a significant boon in this mission.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Voice of the Emperor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Emperor's Chosen identified its bearer as uniquely authorized to speak on the emperor's behalf, even in the company of mighty dragons. While wearing it, you gain the following benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can speak and understand draconic.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Dragons have disadvantage on checks made to intimidate you.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You gain a +1 bonus on Charisma checks made to interact with followers of dragons and their worshippers.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can choose to have your facial features become sharp and dragon-like as a bonus action. Your voice booms to 3 times its usual volume while you've manifested dragon-like features.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Obedience (1/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Emperor's Chosen still bears a residual spark of the authority it once signified. Once per day, you can choose a creature within 30 foot of you that can see, hear, and understand you while wearing it and attempt a Charisma (intimidation) check. The target must then succeed on a Wisdom saving throw with a DC equal to the result of your Intimidation check. If the creature fails their check, you are able to dominate them briefly as per the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><em>Command</em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">spell.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":1.5,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"special","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":3700000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"TP3l4BfIuBJn7NWW"}
{"name":"Shishi","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb09/shishi.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"137\" height=\"256\" />\"This immaculate porcelain vase is in perfect condition, utterly free from chips, imperfections, and tarnishes&mdash;as if fresh from the kiln. In addition to natural patterns and other decorations around its base and rim, the vase has also been lovingly hand-painted, with an unusual scene splashed across its front. This illustration depicts a sun setting over a peaceful temple that has a picturesque Zen garden surrounding it. Two mythical lions, known as Ming and Miang, bar the entrance of this sanctuary from the viewer as they snarl and roar menacingly.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Outpouring (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Though a glance inside this mystical vase might reveal it to be empty, in truth it contains not one but two souls. As an action, you can tip it over to release two guardian lions that 'pour out' of the vase. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Each lion </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">can immediately take one turn to act, before disappearing at the end of their turn. Once used, the images of the two lions disappear from the vase and don't return until dawn, at which time this feature can be used again.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 14px; font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Guardian Lion.</strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 14px; font-style: italic;\">&nbsp;Statistical information necessary to use the Guardian Lions in combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.R6MC102sjy1cI4I4]{Guardian Lion}.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Vigilant Guardians</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Shishi's guardian spirits take their sacred duty to guard those under their protection very seriously. If you leave it at the entrance of a building or at the edge of a campsite, those within are guarded by the vase. While the likeness of the lions is displayed on the vase (see Outpouring), any creature that attempts to locate or discern information about the warded creatures through magical means, such as via a scrying spell, must succeed on a DC 15 Wisdom saving throw or fail in their attempt. Such creatures have disadvantage on their check if Shishi is outside a religious building, holy site, or is on consecrated ground.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":8,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":16200000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"TZbcjrLh5s5dXXRQ"}
{"_id":"TpSLt47Kj82Gp5xh","name":"Resurrection","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You touch a dead creature that has been dead for no more than a century, that didn't die of old age, and that isn't undead. If its soul is free and willing, the target returns to life with all its hit points.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>This spell neutralizes any poisons and cures normal diseases afflicting the creature when it died. It doesn't, however, remove magical diseases, curses, and the like; if such effects aren't removed prior to casting the spell, they afflict the target on its return to life.</p><p>This spell closes all mortal wounds and restores any missing body parts.</p><p>Coming back from the dead is an ordeal. The target takes a −4 penalty to all attack rolls, saving throws, and ability checks. Every time the target finishes a long rest, the penalty is reduced by 1 until it disappears.</p><p>Casting this spell to restore life to a creature that has been dead for one year or longer taxes you greatly. Until you finish a long rest, you can't cast spells again, and you have disadvantage on all attack rolls, ability checks, and saving throws.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"hour","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":""},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["","healing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":7,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a diamond worth at least 1,000 gp, which the spell consumes","consumed":true,"cost":100000,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":1000001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/heal-sky-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"U5hCQVVMMKKKeVSO","name":"Charm Person (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You attempt to charm a humanoid you can see within range. It must make a Wisdom saving throw, and does so with advantage if you or your companions are fighting it. If it fails the saving throw, it is <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> by you until the spell ends or until you or your companions do anything harmful to it. The <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> creature regards you as a friendly acquaintance. When the spell ends, the creature knows it was <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> by you.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"114\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 1st. The creatures must be within 30 feet of each other when you target them.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":6300001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-charm-person.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Jester's Jinglestick","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb10/jesters-jinglestick.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"75\" height=\"256\" />\"This garish jinglestick features a kobold's severed head wearing a jester's hat with a harlequin pattern; a long, black-white-and-red-striped pole; and the small bells which jingle when the object is shaken to earn it its moniker. The kobold head is authentic, although it has been thoroughly cleaned by a taxidermist then stuffed, dried, and preserved; before being palmed off to an enchanter for its 'final touches'&mdash;a spell to allow the kobold head to animate upon the command of its wielder.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Jester's Jinglestick was originally commissioned for use by an up-and-coming buffoon who was pegged to become the favorite entertainer of a king who was notoriously difficult to please. Unfortunately, there was a delay and the jester's staff wasn't completed in time to save the poor fool who was desperately awaiting it. Without it in his repertoire, the jester's tomfoolery wore thin and he was thrown to a performing owlbear. In what became his final punch line, his arm caught in the owlbear's throat, and it choked to death.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Wand</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Jester's Jinglestick can be used as a wand that has 3 charges. While holding it, you can expend 1 of its charges as an action to cast </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Dancing Lights</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">,&nbsp;</span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Minor Illusion</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">, or&nbsp;</span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Vicious Mockery</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">. The wand regains 1d3 expended charges each day at dawn.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Jinglestick</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Jester's Jinglestick has aided many jesters and fools in their attempts to win over difficult audiences. If you undertake a performance that incorporates it and you make a Charisma (performance) check as a result, you can roll 1d4 and add it to the total of your roll.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Puppeteer</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Thanks to its enchantment, the Kobold head that adorns the Jester's Jinglestick isn't just for show. While holding the object, you can will the kobold head to animate and use it like you might a ventriloquist doll.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":3,"max":"3","per":"charges","autoDestroy":false},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"wand","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":900000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wand.png","effects":[],"_id":"U9X0z4MjrZwORIbU"}
{"_id":"UPYOjye2qbw8AddB","name":"Cloak of Protection","permission":{"default":-1,"bOqyKS8LL2EWqEnK":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<div>\n\t\t\t<div><i>Wondrous item, major tier, uncommon (requires attunement)</i></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-4\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-8 text-right\">  </div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<hr>\n\t\t<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p>You gain a +1 bonus to AC and saving throws while you wear this cloak.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"DMG","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":5,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":0,"type":"clothing","dex":0},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"folder":null,"sort":400001,"flags":{"dae":{"activeEquipped":true,"alwaysActive":false},"pick-up-stix":{"pick-up-stix":{"width":1,"height":1}},"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"betterCurses":{"isCurse":false,"curseName":"","formula":"","mwak":false,"rwak":false,"msak":false,"rsak":false}},"img":"https://5e.tools/img/items%2FCloak%20of%20Protection.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"h66aWiyP3EglhJqB","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"transfer":true}},"changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.ac.value","value":1,"mode":2,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"https://5e.tools/img/items%2FCloak%20of%20Protection.jpg","label":"AC","tint":"","transfer":true},{"_id":"xfXyKZAlLbdP5xRm","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"transfer":true,"specialDuration":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"data.bonuses.abilities.save","value":"+1","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"https://5e.tools/img/items%2FCloak%20of%20Protection.jpg","label":"Save","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"name":"War Cleric's Crosier (Spear)","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb04/war-clerics-crosier.png\" alt=\"\" />\"As a crosier, this holy staff has a curled head akin a shepherd's crook. It is formed of lustrous, 24-carat gold, although, despite the supremely exorbitant quality and purity of the gold used in its construction, it features no gemstones or other similarly ornate trappings. The head of the crosier ends in a depiction of an angelic figure running a serpentine creature through with a spear. At one time, this implement would have no doubt been carried by a notable battle priest or war cleric who fought tirelessly to drive back the tides of darkness.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Weapon</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The War Cleric's Crosier can be used as a @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.7bVuU9Ao02SS8i9S]{War Cleric&rsquo;s Crosier (Quarterstaff)} and a spear (see Fiend Foe).</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Spellcasting Focus</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The War Cleric's Crosier can be used as a holy symbol.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Terrifying Visage (1/Day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The War Cleric's Crosier's chosen champion strikes terror into the hearts of those who ought fear them and the implement they wield. As an action, you can point at a fiend of CR 1 or less and utter a condemnation at them. If you do, the creature must attempt a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw, becoming frightened of you on a fail.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Fiend Foe</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The War Cleric's Crosier is vigilant in the fight against those deemed abhorrent. In the presence of fiends, its head uncurls and the weapon functions as a spear, instead of a quarterstaff. Additionally, when you use it as a spear, it deals an extra 1d6 damage to fiends and overcomes fiendish resistances to damage from nonmagical weapons.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":"1d8 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":true,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":17800000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"USlUZMS4dkdG5zCe"}
{"_id":"UYGDyUAPdQF9AWC3","name":"Shillelagh (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The wood of a <a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#club_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'phb', 'club_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >club</a> or <a href=\"https://5e.tools/items.html#quarterstaff_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'items.html', 'phb', 'quarterstaff_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >quarterstaff</a> you are holding is imbued with nature's power. For the duration, you can use your spellcasting ability instead of Strength for the attack and damage rolls of melee attacks using that weapon, and the weapon's damage die becomes a [[/r d8]]. The weapon also becomes magical, if it isn't already. The spell ends if you cast it again or if you let go of the weapon.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"spec","type":"object"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"mistletoe, a shamrock leaf, and a club or quarterstaff","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":11300001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-shillelagh.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Loxen","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"tool","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb07/loxen.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"237\" height=\"256\" />\"Constructed by an aboriginal people, this box lyre is crafted in the likeness of an ox and formed of wood, bronze, and bone. Elaborate patterns and colorful decorations cover much of its surface. Those who created it believed in the importance of quieting the beast inside oneself, and not letting the savagery that lives in everyone take over. In the case of this eleven-stringed harp, the instrument was played to soothe the people&rsquo;s crown prince, who had a fitful and unpredictable temper. However, the beast, represented by the object&rsquo;s bullish headpiece, proved too great a draw and he went on to become a terrible and feared conqueror king.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Musical Instrument</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Loxen can be used as a lyre.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Soothing Melodies</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Loxen&rsquo;s bearer has little to fear from beasts. As an action, you can strum it in order to have each hostile creature of the beast type within 30 foot of you make a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw. On a fail, they become indifferent to you and your allies. This indifference ends if an affected creature is attacked, harmed by a spell, witnesses any others of its kind being injured, or is threatened in any other way by you or your allies. Once a creature has been affected by this feature, it cannot be affected by it again for 24 hours.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Rage Redemption (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Loxen can quieten a call to bloodlust and still even the most rage-filled hearts. If you play it while a raging barbarian is within earshot, they can choose to roll a d20. On a result of 10 or higher, their rage ends immediately and they regain one use of their Rage feature, as if they hadn&rsquo;t raged.</span></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"ability":"cha","chatFlavor":"","proficient":0,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":17900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/instrument.png","effects":[],"_id":"UYxW5sP0WECjcmny"}
{"name":"Mordebus","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb08/mordebus.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"153\" height=\"256\" />\"These wickedly indulgent robes are as lavish as they are eye-catching&mdash;sure to draw the attention of devout priests, holy knights, and brave adventurers, though not for reasons of fashion. Between the mantle's black and crimson coloration, bone-and-skull-like detailing, jagged protrusions, and the depictions of screaming demons that adorn its shoulder pads, the garment singles its wearer out as a cultist, black mage, or something equally despotic.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Though the moniker Mordebus has become synonymous with this set of robes, it wasn't originally their name, nor the name of the individual who fashioned them. In truth, there have been many Mordebus' over the years, as each individual who has taken up wearing the robes has cast off their own identity and assumed the </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">same dark alias. Each of these so-called Mordebus' quickly rose to prominence amongst or within occult circles, often ascending to the highest echelons of leadership.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Apostate Appeal</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Evildoers are drawn to Mordebus like moths to a flame. You have advantage on Charisma (deception and persuasion) checks made to influence or mislead wicked cultists, dark acolytes, and vile priests while wearing it.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Glimpses From Beyond</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Mordebus' wearer sometimes experiences strange omens and insights. While wearing it, you can apply your proficiency bonus whenever making Arcana or Religion checks as long as you are proficient in either skill.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Fork Tongued</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">There can be little doubt that Mordebus was forged in hellfire. You can speak and understand Infernal and Abyssal while wearing it, though you cannot read or write either language unless you are proficient in their use.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Latest in Line</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Many have donned Mordebus, and they have all contributed towards its legacy. While wearing it, your voice is modified to sound deep and gravelly. Consequently, it is difficult for other creatures to ascertain your true accent, pitch, race, or even gender and they have disadvantage on checks made to do so.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":6900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/clothing.png","effects":[],"_id":"UZQQbqEgnNSQESDi"}
{"name":"Guardgoyle","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb04/guardgoyle.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"238\" height=\"256\" />\"Formed of two integral elements, this curious shoulder adornment serves as far more than a mere ornamentation. Its first, and less noteworthy, component is a leather pauldron designed to sit comfortably over its wearer&rsquo;s shoulder or armor and fasten securely in place. Affixed to this hide epaulette is an oddly-lifelike statuette of a stone gargoyle with turquoise gems for eyes. At a paltry eight inches tall while hunched, the tiny sculpture appears to be screeching, though is otherwise lifeless.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Guardgoyle is quite literally a guardian angel, albeit an unusual one. Aesthetically similar to those found on churches and cathedrals, it seems useless until its wearer&rsquo;s life is seriously threatened. When such a dire situation occurs, the gargoyle comes to life and uses its strength to protect its fallen ward.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Attunement Requirement. </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Guardgoyle diligently watches over the individual it has chosen to safeguard. Only the object's leather pauldron is visible until you attune to it. A small stone gargoyle appears perched on it the morning after you attune to it. Should you ever cease to be attuned to Guardgoyle, the gargoyle disappears once more. The gargoyle can also be destroyed as per Lifelife (below), in which case it must be restored through other means as described in that feature or be attuned to by a new creature that hasn't attuned to it</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&nbsp;before.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Lifeline</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Guardgoyle does not squat idly by as its ward bleeds out beside it. When you are knocked unconscious as a result of being reduced to 0 hit points, it comes to life, takes flight, and attempts to protect you from harm to the best of its ability. The Guardgoyle continues to fight and defend you until you have stabilized and there are no longer any immediate threats to your wellbeing in your vicinity, at which time it returns to its position on your shoulder and reverts to being nothing more than an inanimate object of stone.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Guardgoyle.</strong> Statistical information necessary to use Guardgoyle in combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.tiwrYBLZvKlmNf9i]{Guardgoyle}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Settling Up</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Guardgoyle may be a useful and vigilant ally, but its loyalty comes with a price. Any time it is forced to animate and fight to defend you, you discover that you have lost an amount in GP equal to your level x 20 when you regain consciousness. This total can be in GP, other coinage, or objects of an equivalent value. If you don't have the funds about your person, any creature within earshot can utter the words, 'I shall pay your toll', and settle up on your behalf after the battle instead. If they do so, the GP disappears from their coinpurse or similar when you regain consciousness.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Should the gargoyle be slain or no one pay its toll, it vanishes, leaving only the Guardgoyle's leather pauldron in its place. You can resummon the gargoyle at a later date by undertaking a ritual that takes 1 hour to complete and requires you to make an offering worth your level x 50 GP.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":5200000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/clothing.png","effects":[],"_id":"UhdNRmtSOgIk18aY"}
{"name":"Ley Compass","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>\"This funny-looking compass is formed of sterling silver with a sliver of transparent glass used to provide a peek inside at its face. Its exterior has lots of small buttons, dials, and switches on it, which are used to configure the device into its different modes of use. Many of these are completely unnecessary and aren't linked to any function whatsoever, as if its inventor intended on adding features to it that ultimately never saw inclusion. Though, to a creature not versed in spellcasting, even the buttons it has are perfectly redundant.\"</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Attunement Requirement</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In order to make use of the Ley Compass' features, you must be attuned to it and able to cast at least one spell. If you do not fulfil these requirements, you can still use it as a mundane, nonmagical compass. Any effects created by the Ley Compass are considered to be a form of Conjuration magic and can be detected through Truesight or the use of spells</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Magical Marker</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Using the Ley Compass, a creature can quickly and easily find their way back to a significant location. Pressing one of its buttons causes it to create an invisible, formless magical marker in its current location. Using its other controls, you can configure it to recognise a specific marker as due north. It can maintain five such markers at once, though any attempt to exceed this number causes all of its existing magical markers to fizzle away into nothingness.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Arcane Breadcrumbs</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A creature armed with the Ley Compass has certain advantages against becoming lost. By flicking a switch on it, you can set it to deposit discrete magical waypoints every 50 foot for 1 hour. You can then use it to locate the nearest marker in whichever direction it is facing. These markers degrade after 24 hours, vanishing entirely.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Portal Insights</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Ley Compass is linked closely with portals and teleportation circles, affording its wielder certain insights into them. Should the device be brought within 50 foot of any kind of magical portal or gateway, its surface becomes tranquil and crystal clear. Creatures on the Ley Compass' side of the portal or gateway can then peer through it and see the area where it emerges.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Additionally, while within 50 foot of a magical gateway that re-emerges elsewhere on the same plane of existence the Ley Compass is on, you can touch your current location on a map if you have one, enter a trance-like state, and trace your finger to the place in the world where the gateway leads. If it doesn't emerge within the confines of the map, you're able to trace its trajectory until you reach the edge of the map instead.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":20900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"Umx3oLTHNY6PHpJX"}
{"name":"Barliman's Barricade","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This enormous bulwark is formed from thick wooden planks that allow it to provide excellent cover but also cause it to more closely resemble a door than a traditional shield. Lifting the object requires tremendous strength, let alone bringing it to bare effectively as a defensive tool.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A knight from a faraway land called Barliman was once offered a parcel of land in exchange for his service to the crown. It was assumed that he'd use his newfound barony for agriculture, pastoral farming, or homesteading, as was traditionally expected, however instead Barliman erected a free house that he named the Tipsy Tactician. Several </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">years later, a mysterious tornado blew through the region, spitting out wind elementals as it went. When an unusually strong gust tore the inn's door from its hinges, Barliman scooped it up without hesitation and charged into the typhoon in order to defend his premises from the elementals.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Shield. </strong>Barliman's Barricade can be used as a shield.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Barricade Bash</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Though Barliman's Barricade takes great strength to lift due to its weight, that same heft gives it great potential as a weapon. As an action, you can make a melee weapon attack with it. On a hit, you deal 1d8 + your Strength modifier bludgeoning damage. In order to add your proficiency bonus to your attack roll, you must be proficient in the use of shields.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Take Cover</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A door-sized palisade makes for perfect cover. If you are wielding Barliman's Barricade and you're subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you can use your reaction to&nbsp;</span>duck behind the shield and take no damage if you succeed on the saving throw.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Barliman's Belly</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If Barliman knew how to do anything, it was; drink, wrestle bulls, and wrestle bulls while drinking. You have advantage on Constitution saving throws made to resist the negative effects of imbibing alcohol while within 120 foot of the shield.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Tipsy Toboggan</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Thanks to its size and form factor, Barliman's Barricade is configured perfectly to serve another purpose, in addition to being a door and shield. If it is laid down flat on an incline in snowy or icy conditions, it can be used as a vehicle for up to 1 Medium or 2 Small creatures, as long as they're traveling downhill. If used in this way, its passengers may be called upon to make Vehicle (land) checks in order to steer or control it. Its speed is 60 feet per round on shallower inclines and 120 feet per round on steeper ones. While on steeper inclines, creatures operating it have disadvantage on any checks that they make to do so.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":12,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":2,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":500000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/shield.png","effects":[],"_id":"UpktTG3fSopKnqRK"}
{"_id":"VMecFINcnt1Nl830","name":"Detect Thoughts (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>For the duration, you can read the thoughts of certain creatures. When you cast the spell and as your action on each turn until the spell ends, you can focus your mind on any one creature that you can see within 30 feet of you. If the creature you choose has an Intelligence of 3 or lower or doesn't speak any language, the creature is unaffected.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>You initially learn the surface thoughts of the creature—what is most on its mind in that moment. As an action, you can either shift your attention to another creature's thoughts or attempt to probe deeper into the same creature's mind. If you probe deeper, the target must make a Wisdom saving throw. If it fails, you gain insight into its reasoning (if any), its emotional state, and something that looms large in its mind (such as something it worries over, loves, or hates). If it succeeds, the spell ends. Either way, the target knows that you are probing into its mind, and unless you shift your attention to another creature's thoughts, the creature can use its action on its turn to make an Intelligence check contested by your Intelligence check; if it succeeds, the spell ends.</p><p>Questions verbally directed at the target creature naturally shape the course of its thoughts, so this spell is particularly effective as part of an interrogation.</p><p>You can also use this spell to detect the presence of thinking creatures you can't see. When you cast the spell or as your action during the duration, you can search for thoughts within 30 feet of you. The spell can penetrate barriers, but 2 feet of rock, 2 inches of any metal other than lead, or a thin sheet of lead blocks you. You can't detect a creature with an Intelligence of 3 or lower or one that doesn't speak any language.</p><p>Once you detect the presence of a creature in this way, you can read its thoughts for the rest of the duration as described above, even if you can't see it, but it must still be within range.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"self","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a copper piece","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":6400001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-detect-thoughts.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Vfxy2hgMISUJRJq6","name":"Prestidigitation (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>This spell is a minor magical trick that novice spellcasters use for practice. You create one of the following magical effects within range:</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">You create an instantaneous, harmless sensory effect, such as a shower of sparks, a puff of wind, faint musical notes, or an odd odor.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">You instantaneously light or snuff out a candle, a torch, or a small campfire.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">You instantaneously clean or soil an object no larger than 1 cubic foot.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">You chill, warm, or flavor up to 1 cubic foot of nonliving material for 1 hour.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">You make a color, a small mark, or a symbol appear on an object or a surface for 1 hour.</li><li class=\"rd__li \">You create a nonmagical trinket or an illusory image that can fit in your hand and that lasts until the end of your next turn.</li></ul><p>If you cast this spell multiple times, you can have up to three of its non-instantaneous effects active at a time, and you can dismiss such an effect as an action.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":11100001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-prestidigitation.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Writ of the Covenant","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb08/writ-of-the-covenant.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"209\" height=\"256\" />\"This venerable document takes the form of a vellum scroll that is every bit as impressive as it is imposing, thanks to its age, appearance, and nature. The parchment itself is old, thick, and discolored&mdash;clearly ancient, though not yet as brittle as one might expect. The faded canvas is affixed top and bottom to bones which act as rollers. The lower of which has a jawbone hanging from it as a decoration, while the top has ferocious horns protruding from either side of it and a skull mounted in its center. Perhaps most interestingly of all, both the eyes of this skull and the text written on the scroll glow with an unholy blue tint. Glowing particles of fluorescent blue also lazily drift off the parchment's crisp surface.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Writ of the Covenant is a very old contract that offers mortal humans the means with which to make a bargain with an even older devil. The terms of this deal are explained in the document itself, and they're non-negotiable.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Attunement Requirement</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Writ of the Covenant forms a binding agreement between a humanoid and a devil. A creature must attune to it in order to unlock its other features. When you attune to it, your signature, name, crest, or other identifying mark appears on the contract and you are bound by its</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&nbsp;Terms</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">. Once attuned to it, you cannot unattune to the Writ of the Covenant by any means short of a </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Wish&nbsp;</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">spell or paying its Termination Fee while alive.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Terms</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The powers of the Writ of the Covenant come with a terrible price. If you agree to its Terms,</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"> 1 GP in coinage disappears from your personal wealth each day at midnight, commencing 30 days after you first attune to it. Should a midnight arrive and you have insufficient funds to pay your debt, you die instantly. It is not important whether you're physically carrying the gold about your person or it's stored in a remote location, as long as it's your property or in your possession. Additionally, the Terms stipulate that when you die, your body will be raised in the service of a powerful devil for 1 year before being returned to the grave. However, you're released from your bondage (temporarily) if resurrection magic is performed on you during this period.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong>Termination Fee.</strong> Breaking any contract comes with consequences. If you wish to end your attunement to Writ of the Covenant, you can pay a one off fee as per Terms that's equal to your level x 20 GP. If you do so, your attunement to it ends immediately.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Bargain's Benefits</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">In exchange for their terrible sacrifice, a creature who accepts the Writ of the Covenant's&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Terms&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">receives a useful boon. For attuning to it, you gain temporary hit points equal to twice your proficiency bonus. These last until used or replaced, and replenish at the end of a long rest. Additionally, you also gain access to Terrible Gamble.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Terrible Gamble</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A creature close to death can tap into the power of the Writ of the Covenant, should they be willing to roll the dice with their life. When making a death saving throw while bound by its Terms, you can choose to roll 2d20, instead of 1d20, and take the lower result. If you choose to do so, you can spend one or more of your hit die after seeing the result. Each hit die spent in this way adds a +2 bonus to your result.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":19400000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/scroll.png","effects":[],"_id":"VlbikbDxBVKj6iy5"}
{"name":"Scryer's Orbuculum","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This clear glass ball is 8 inches in diameter and its reflective surface is utterly without imperfection or flaw. The globe rests upon a wooden plinth made of varnished ebony that stands upon three taloned feet. When not in use, a square of purple velvet cloth covers the ball to keep prying eyes from looking upon it, and alien eyes from peering out.</span></span></em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Used to glimpse portents of the future and to lift the veil between the realm of the living and the domain of the dead, the Scryer's Orbuculum has graced the tables of both legitimate crystal gazers and charlatans to great effect. Often to the surprise of the con artists who've used it, this curious ball does have a genuine connection to the supernatural and even the most cynical individuals can reach out to something beyond their mundane existence while using it as a conduit.\"</span></span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Augury (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Scryer's Orbuculum is no mere ornament. Once per day, you can peer into it and perform a special reading for another creature. If you do so, you should roll 1d20 in secret, with only the game master seeing and noting the result. Results of 2-19 correspond to the 18 skills available to creatures respectively, while results of 1 and 20 are handled separately. The first time the creature who received the reading attempts an ability check using the skill that matches with the result, a D6 should be rolled and added to their check. The player attempting the check does so if the reading was for a player character, while the game master does it if it was for a non-player character. If the result of the check was a 1, the creature instead subtracts 1d6 from the next ability check they make using a skill that they're proficient in. While, if it was a 20, they instead add 1d6 to the next ability check they make using a skill that they're proficient in.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Seer</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">As a creature stares deeply into the misty haze that fills the Scryer's Orbuculum, the fog parts and the crystal ball fills with visions of the future. You can attempt to divine the future of another creature using it. Providing another creature with a basic fortune telling takes 10 minutes. To do so, you should attempt a Charisma (performance) check. Depending on your result, the Scryer's Orbuculum can create as many of the following harmless magical effects as you are eligible for during your reading to add dramatic effect:</span></span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">DC 5</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The clear Scryer's Orbuculum clouds over into a vaporous white.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">DC 10</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A light mist forms around the area in which the reading is being performed, affecting a 10 foot cube centered on the Scryer's Orbuculum.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">DC 10</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Scryer's Orbuculum begins to float.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">DC 10</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Whispers, distant howls, and the sound of scratching can be heard within 10 foot of the Scryer's Orbuculum.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">DC 10</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Candles flicker within 20 foot of the Scryer's Orbuculum and other light sources dim within 10 foot of it.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">DC 15</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The world seems to fade to darkness beyond 10 foot of the Scryer's Orbuculum.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">DC 15</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Ghostly visages take form within 20 foot of the Scryer's Orbuculum, usually on the outside of those gathered around it.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">DC 15</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You appear to levitate, your eyes glow brightly, or you modulate your voice.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">DC 20</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You conjure the silent likeness of a Medium or smaller creature that you can envisage in your minds' eye.</span></span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":7,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"minute","cost":10,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day","autoDestroy":false},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"trinket","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":20600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"WLdMoRG1i39wn97b"}
{"name":"Tamotuki","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb09/tamotuki.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"159\" />\"As rarefied treasures imbued with magical properties go, this plain red sheet of paper might seem underwhelming, especially given that it has been folded and crumpled many times&mdash;leaving it creased and wrinkled. However, a creature who becomes familiar with the nature of its enchantment will quickly come to recognize its usefulness and utility as much more than a paltry scrap of discarded paper.</em></p>\n<p><em>Tamotuki is surprisingly old, much more so than a cursory inspection of it might reveal. It's extremely hardwearing and durable and has been folded into unusual shapes thousands of times. Once upon a time, the object was perfectly mundane. It came to life after it was shaped into a crane by a dying father and left for his daughter beside her bed the last time he laid eyes on her. The very next morning he was gone, but the crane he left behind seemed to be very much alive.\"</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Paper Folds</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This unassuming slip of paper is astoundingly versatile, as any who explore its seams and folds quickly discovers. As an action, you can fold Tamotuki to imitate the rudimentary shape and configuration of any Tiny object, though it is clearly only an origami replica and isn't mistaken for the genuine article without a much more elaborate ruse. The folded parchment is surprisingly strong and durable and can fulfil the same basic function as the object it is imitating, as long as that purpose is simple in nature. For example, Tamotuki cannot be used to manipulate a complicated lock's pins and tumblers while imitating a key, however it could be used as a doorstop. You can unfold it so that it returns to its flat form as an action. Tamotuki is waterproof and can be used in any of the following ways, though this list is by no means exhaustive:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can fold it to serve as any basic piece of ammunition.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can fold it to serve as a dagger or sickle.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can fold it to serve as a cup, plate, bowl, or other tiny receptacle or container.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can fold it to serve as a paper plane or boat.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can fold it to serve as a key that opens any simple lock which can be unlocked with a DC 12 Dexterity check using thieves' tools.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can also fold&nbsp;</span>Tamotuki <span class=\"fontstyle0\">to loosely resemble a creature of any size, though the imitation itself is Tiny. If you fold it in such a way, the paper becomes animated and acts as per the natural instincts of </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">the creature being imitated or your psychic wishes, as long as you remain within 120 feet of it. If you move further from it, it becomes inert and crumbles to floor in a crumpled up ball.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Variant Origami Folds.</strong> When Tamotuki is folded into certain forms, it gains special features. You can find these in the Biography section of both of its statblocks (linked below).</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Animated Origami Parchment.</strong><span style=\"font-style: italic;\">&nbsp;Statistical information necessary to use Tamotuki in combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.wYuIuoMvEVtU76IV]{Animated Origami Parchment}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Multiply (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A single origami creation is little more than a novelty, though several hundred of them is another matter altogether. When Tamotuki is folded to resemble a creature, and thus animated, you can psychically instruct it to multiply as a bonus action. This effect lasts for 1 minute or until Tamotuki is reduced to 0 hit points.</span></span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong style=\"font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Animated Origami Swarm.</strong><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"> Statistical information necessary to use Tamotuki as a swarm in combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.4NalQBxJYaNXbFl5]{Animated Origami Swarm}.</span></span></span></p>\n</blockquote>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":17600000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/scroll.png","effects":[],"_id":"WUfJauu9wwFW7IgI"}
{"_id":"Wsu85hub3fjfxLNa","name":"Lightning Bolt","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A stroke of lightning forming a line 100 feet long and 5 feet wide blasts out from you in a direction you choose. Each creature in the line must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes [[/r 8d6]] lightning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The lightning ignites flammable objects in the area that aren't being worn or carried.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1038\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d6]] for each slot level above 3rd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":100,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["8d6","lightning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a bit of fur and a rod of amber, crystal, or glass","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d6"},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":2400001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/lightning-blue-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Argon Anchor","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb05/argon-anchor.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"168\" height=\"256\" />\"Due to its rusted and barnacle-ridden nature, this compact anchor looks like it has spent a long time, possibly years, resting on the ocean floor. Originally belonging to a small, lightweight craft, it is only about twice the size of a buckler and can be carried comfortably by any creature with the strength to lift and swing a heavy greataxe.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Argon Anchor originally served a utilitarian vessel called the CNS Argon Petard which was requisitioned by its navy and repurposed into a warship. However, the craft was ill-suited for naval combat and was instead given another purpose. Laden with explosives and manned by a skeletal crew, it was sent on a demolitions run against the enemy's flagship during a blockade, sinking it and killing both crews.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Ram, Portable</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Argon Anchor can be used as a portable ram.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Breach &amp; Clear (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Argon Anchor can be brought to bare with the raw fury of a tidal wave. When you use it to break down or through a door, you can will it to unleash a deafening sonic boom that sounds like waves crashing on </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">a rocky coastline as a bonus action. If you do so, creatures within 60 foot of the door on its far side must succeed on a DC 13 Constitution saving throw or be incapacitated for 1 round and take 1d4 thunder damage. Creatures with total cover automatically succeed on this check while those partially exposed or behind smaller barricades have advantage on it. The noise generated when this ability is activated is audible out to a range of 300 foot.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Obvious Signs</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Use of the Argon Anchor rarely goes unnoticed, given the obvious signs left in its wake. After it is used to break down a door, several unusual phenomena manifest over the ensuing 1d4 hours. The door itself becomes rotten and riddled with barnacles, while tendrils of calcite salt form around the door's frame and snake out across the surrounding wall for several feet.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":35,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"object"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"abil","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["d20 + @abilities.str.mod +4",""]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":2200000,"flags":{"mess":{"isBonusDamage":false,"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/utensil.png","effects":[],"_id":"X9VO9Flur7LsZci6"}
{"name":"Head of Zorbo","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb08/head-of-zorbo.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"221\" height=\"256\" /></em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This severed goblin head has been shrunken and preserved through ancient rituals and forbidden rites known only to practitioners of voodoo witchcraft. Its eyelids and mouth have been sewn shut, while its skin has been pulled taut over its cranium and fastened to a bone weight with a small cord that can be used to hold it aloft. Additionally, a single humanoid eye hangs down beneath the head from a hook inserted into its lower gum.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zorbo was a goblin shaman whose preternatural insights quickly elevated his status into overseeing the most powerful tribe in his region. As his legend and ambition grew, Zorbo's minions spread to raid beyond his cosseted borders, eventually accosting a voodoo priestess who saw their master as unfit for his gifts. She marched her attackers back to their camp and proceeded to slay every goblin in her path to Zorbo. She dismembered the goblin but decided to keep a few parts around to make use of his unique insights herself.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Belligerent Biter</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A semblance of life remains yet within Zorbo's head. His head reanimates at random, gibbering and gurgling through his stitches, often madly or incoherently. As an action, you can use a free hand to throw the Head of Zorbo at a hostile creature that you can see within 30 feet of you. If you do so, the thread around his mouth loosens momentarily and he attempts to bite the target. The target must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or take 2d4 piercing damage as Zorbo's head latches on to it. At the start of its subsequent turns, the target takes an additional 1d4 piercing damage and suffers disadvantage on ability checks and attack rolls until it can shake him off (escape DC 15).</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Two Heads</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Sometimes two heads are better than one, just sometimes though. Once per long or short rest, you can ask Zorbo for insight when attempting an ability check that uses Wisdom or Intelligence. If you do so, the thread around his mouth loosens and he stirs to life just long enough to offer you his opinion. If you do so, you should roll 2d20, instead of one. If the result of both d20 are odd, you must use the lower result. If the results are both even, or are split between odds and evens, you take the higher result.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Mouthpiece</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">For a time, Zorbo's killer amused herself with his remains, treating them as a plaything. While within 60 feet of the Head of Zorbo, you can will it to stir to life as an action, causing the threads sealing its eyes and mouth to loosen and Zorbo to perform one of the following feats:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zorbo's eyes light up and glow, roll back in his head, or fill with blood.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zorbo acts as your mouthpiece, speaking whatever words you mentally command.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zorbo allows you to communicate verbally in goblinoid through him for a moment, acting as a translator even if you wouldn't normally know how to speak or understand it.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zorbo's nostrils flare, his mouth whistles, or his head spins on the spot unaided.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"sr"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d4","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"1d4","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":20700000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"XV0xudPLC69Xgnv7"}
{"name":"Misaku-sol","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"At a glance, it appears as if this pretty pink parasol has been cleverly designed to resemble a cherry blossom tree. However, the longer one studies it, the harder it is to tell if it's merely an imitation of sakura, or if it is in fact an uprooted tree itself. The umbrella's handle and shaft are formed of what looks like a wooden tree trunk, albeit one that is oddly thin and wiry. Meanwhile, its canopy depicts the underside of a cherry blossom tree on the inside and the top of one on the outside. Strangely, though these images are two-dimensional, they're incredibly detailed, authentic, and lifelike. A creature that studies their flat lines for more than a few seconds discovers hidden depths in their contours. Moreover, tiny cherry blossom bulbs which are quite real hang down from the branches that can be seen on the inside of the umbrella's canopy, while petals periodically waft out from within the sunshade while it is open.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Blossom Spin</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Misaku-Sol is often seen spinning and twirling gleefully, scattering cherry blossoms into the wind. You can hold the parasol aloft and spin it as an action, doing so projects a flurry of cherry blossoms into a 5 foot space adjacent you. The cherry blossoms bounce off the forms of invisible creatures in the affected area and reveal their outline until the start of your next, at which point the blossoms disperse. Affected creatures are no longer considered invisible, however they are considered lightly obscured.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Blossom Blast (1/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A blast of blossoms can spell downfall every bit as easily as dragonfire. Once per day, you can use Misaku-Sol to spew a thick plume of cherry blossoms from its tip as an action. If you do so, each creature in a 15-foot cone must attempt a DC 13 Constitution saving throw or be showered in cherry blossoms. Creatures that fail their saving throw are incapacitated until the start of your next turn. Additionally, invisible creatures in the affected area are also subjected to the effects of </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Blossom Spin </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">as part of this feature.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Blossom Brolly</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Magically linked with cherry blossoms, the small pink-petalled flowers are never far away when Misaku-Sol is around. The following peculiar phenomena manifest in the presence of the umbrella:</span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">There is a strong odor of cherry blossoms.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">When the parasol is open, cherry blossoms steadily drift out from beneath its canopy.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Cherry blossoms within 300 foot of it do not rot.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">If the parasol is kept within a small woodlands no larger than 4 square miles for ten days, the woods become a cherry blossom grove over the next thirty days.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":7600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/utensil.png","effects":[],"_id":"Xti4IEk9aK5jKixE"}
{"name":"Picaroon's Pantaloons","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Finishing just below the knee on a human or elf, or around the ankle on a gnome or halfling, these baggy, voluminous pantaloons are designed to be as unobtrusive as possible, providing maximum freedom of movement to their wearer. Favored by riggers, pirates belonging to a boarding party, or privateers and sailors that lead the vanguard against enemy incursion, these loose trousers are not just another common set of fashionable pants.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Picaroon's Pantaloons originally belonged to an expert rigger who earned enough coin 'working the ropes' to purchase a small ship of his own, retire from a harsh life at sea, and pursue his true dream; opening his own circus. He had his ship brought onto dry land, scraped, painted, and mounted onto wheels so that he could use it as both his main stage and also a wagon to transport his troupe and everything else needed for his 'bazaar of the bizarre'. He traveled the countryside for years, using pack animals to park his ship in front of hills where spectators would gather to see his performers fight animals on the deck or execute dizzying trapeze and tightrope acts between the vessel's masts and rigging.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Rigrunner</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature wearing the Picaroon's Pantaloons feels comfortable and confident on boats, and an overwhelming sense of adventure. While wearing them, you gain a climb speed equal to your movement speed when climbing&nbsp;</span>the masts and rigging of ships and you have advantage on Dexterity (acrobatics) checks made to swing from one vessel to another.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Swift Swimmer</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Normally baggy, the Picaroon's Pantaloons shrink when wet, becoming skintight and preventing drag in water much like a wetsuit. You gain a swim speed equal to your movement speed while wearing them.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":9200000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/clothing.png","effects":[],"_id":"YG7Z8mnjIUwX9ftB"}
{"_id":"YT3zMCbgywi0uT3i","name":"Hold Monster (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Choose a creature that you can see within range. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#paralyzed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'paralyzed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >paralyzed</a> for the duration. This spell has no effect on undead. At the end of each of its turns, the target can make another Wisdom saving throw. On a success, the spell ends on the target.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"115\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 5th. The creatures must be within 30 feet of each other when you target them.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":90,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":5,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a small, straight piece of iron","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":6800001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-hold-monster.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YTFjNGFlYzNmODQ1","name":"Shield","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>An invisible barrier of magical force appears and protects you. Until the start of your next turn, you have a +5 bonus to AC, including against the triggering attack, and you take no damage from magic missile.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 275","activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"Which you take when you are hit by an attack or targeted by the magic missile spell"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"round"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":820000,"flags":{"_sheetTab":"description","midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""},"autoanimations":{"killAnim":false,"override":false,"animType":"t1","animName":"","hmAnim":"a1","color":"n1","dtvar":"dt1","explosion":false,"explodeVariant":"ev1","explodeColor":"ec1","explodeRadius":"0","explodeLoop":"1","selfRadius":"5","animTint":"#ffffff","auraOpacity":0.75,"ctaOption":false}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/protect-magenta-1.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"hUw22TVgNVJ5GZQ9","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":true},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"aura":"None","radius":null}},"changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.ac.valu