{"name":"Goldstrand","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"At a glance, this maple oar looks identical to any other paddle. The only notable exception to this is the strand of flaxen hair that runs through its shaft and protrudes out of the bottom of its handle. However, this plain, unassuming implement harbors several unusual secrets.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Goldstrand began life as a perfectly mundane oar. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It wasn't until the ship that it belonged to sank in a vicious storm that it was blessed with exceptional power. A mighty sea deity caused the storm in question in a fit of rage. When this god of the waves calmed down and saw the destruction it had caused, it lamented its hasty and </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">thoughtless outburst. It located a single sailor clinging to life on a piece of driftwood, the sole survivor of the storm, and it blessed his oar by imbuing with a strand of its hair so that he might make it back to shore safely.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Goldstrand can be used as a greatclub.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Peculiar Quirks</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Magically enchanted or blessed in some way, Goldstrand possesses the following unusual traits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your attacks with it deal +1 damage on a hit.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It is incredibly buoyant and continues to float in water without sinking unless at least 2,000 pounds of weight is placed upon it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When placed in a body of water, it drifts towards the nearest shoreline by the most expedient route possible, bringing up to 5 Medium or small creatures clinging or fastened to it along with it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When placed in fresh water and allowed to sit for a couple of minutes, the water around it begins to taste salty and bitter. Conversely, if it is placed in salt water, it has the effect of purifying this into freshwater suitable for consumption at the same rate, although this doesn't remove any toxins, poisons, or diseases present in the water. Additionally, if placed in fresh water, algae and other organic matter begins to form around the object within 24 hours.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If it is placed close to metal objects, interned in the same pack as them, or placed within a metal container for extended periods of time, it causes any exposed metalwork to rust, requiring that extra care and attention be required to maintain these objects.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It smells faintly of odors one might normally associate with the sea; such as fish, salt water, seaweed, or seagull guano. Its scent also changes subtly with the turning of the tides, corresponding precisely with their ebb and flow.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":10,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod +1","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":5600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"YVcAjOWQ43RRJILv"}
{"_id":"YWNkYTI3NTdmZDYx","name":"Lightning Bolt","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A stroke of lightning forming a line 100 feet long and 5 feet wide blasts out from you in a direction you choose. Each creature in the line must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 8d6 lightning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>The lightning ignites flammable objects in the area that aren't being worn or carried.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 3rd.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 255","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":100,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["8d6","lightning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A bit of fur and a rod of amber, crystal, or glass","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d6"}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":900000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/lightning-blue-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YWYwOTMyMGU2OWQ4","name":"Modify Memory","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You attempt to reshape another creature’s memories. One creature that you can see must make a Wisdom saving throw. If you are fighting the creature, it has advantage on the saving throw. On a failed save, the target becomes Charmed by you for the Duration. The cha⁠rmed target is Incapacitated and unaware of its surroundings, though it can still hear you. If it takes any damage or is targeted by another spell, this spell ends, and none of the target’s memories are modified.</p>\n<p>While this charm lasts, you can affect the target’s memory of an event that it experienced within the last 24 hours and that lasted no more than 10 minutes. You can permanently eliminate all memory of the event, allow the target to recall the event with perfect clarity and exacting detail, change its memory of the details of the event, or create a memory of some other event.</p>\n<p>You must speak to the target to describe how its memories are affected, and it must be able to understand your language for the modified memories to take root. Its mind fills in any gaps in the details of your description. If the spell ends before you have finished describing the modified memories, the creature’s memory isn’t altered. Otherwise, the modified memories take hold when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>A modified memory doesn’t necessarily affect how a creature behaves, particularly if the memory contradicts the creature’s natural inclinations, Alignment, or beliefs. An illogical modified memory, such as implanting a memory of how much the creature enjoyed dousing itself in acid, is dismissed, perhaps as a bad dream. The DM might deem a modified memory too nonsensical to affect a creature in a significant manner.</p>\n<p>A Remove Curse or Greater Restoration spell cast on the target restores the creature’s true memory.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels</strong>. If you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, you can alter the target’s memories of an event that took place up to 7 days ago (6th level), 30 days ago (7th level), 1 year ago (8th level), or any time in the creature’s past (9th level).</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 261","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":5,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1070000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/air-burst-jade-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Yhzwe3ZB1eAYthrL","name":"Fireball","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A bright streak flashes from your pointing finger to a point you choose within range and then blossoms with a low roar into an explosion of flame. Each creature in a 20-foot-radius sphere centered on that point must make a Dexterity saving throw. A target takes [[/r 8d6]] fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The fire spreads around corners. It ignites flammable objects in the area that aren't being worn or carried.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1037\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d6]] for each slot level above 3rd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":150,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["8d6","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a tiny ball of bat guano and sulfur","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d6"},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":2300001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/fireball-red-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YjBlOGU4MDQzMWRk","name":"Animate Dead","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This spell creates an undead servant. Choose a pile of bones or a corpse of a Medium or Small humanoid within range. Your spell imbues the target with a foul mimicry of life, raising it as an undead creature. The target becomes a skeleton if you chose bones or a zombie if you chose a corpse (the DM has the creature's game statistics).</p>\n<p>On each of your turns, you can use a bonus action to mentally command any creature you made with this spell if the creature is within 60 feet of you (if you control multiple creatures, you can command any or all of them at the same time, issuing the same command to each one). You decide what action the creature will take and where it will move during its next turn, or you can issue a general command, such as to guard a particular chamber or corridor. If you issue no commands, the creature only defends itself against hostile creatures. Once given an order, the creature continues to follow it until its task is complete.</p>\n<p>The creature is under your control for 24 hours, after which it stops obeying any command you've given it. To maintain control of the creature for another 24 hours, you must cast this spell on the creature again before the current 24-hour period ends. This use of the spell reasserts your control over up to four creatures you have animated with this spell, rather than animating a new one.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you animate or reassert control over two additional undead creatures for each slot level above 3rd. Each of the creatures must come from a different corpse or pile of bones.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 212","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":24,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"object"},"range":{"value":10,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A drop of blood, a piece of flesh, and a pinch of bone dust","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1080000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/horror-red-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YmU2ZThjZWJjODIx","name":"Sending","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You send a short message of twenty-five words or less to a creature with which you are familiar. The creature hears the message in its mind, recognizes you as the sender if it knows you, and can answer in a like manner immediately. The spell enables creatures with Intelligence scores of at least 1 to understand the meaning of your message.</p><p>You can send the message across any distance and even to other planes of existence, but if the target is on a different plane than you, there is a 5 percent chance that the message doesn't arrive.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 274","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"round"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"mi","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"any"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A short piece of fine copper wire","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1500000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/shadow_20.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YpLladWe0U90atuK","name":"Wind Wall","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A wall of strong wind rises from the ground at a point you choose within range. You can make the wall up to 50 feet long, 15 feet high, and 1 foot thick. You can shape the wall in any way you choose so long as it makes one continuous path along the ground. The wall lasts for the duration.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>When the wall appears, each creature within its area must make a Strength saving throw. A creature takes [[/r 3d8]] bludgeoning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><p>The strong wind keeps fog, smoke, and other gases at bay. Small or smaller flying creatures or objects can't pass through the wall. Loose, lightweight materials brought into the wall fly upward. Arrows, bolts, and other ordinary projectiles launched at targets behind the wall are deflected upward and automatically miss. (Boulders hurled by giants or siege engines, and similar projectiles, are unaffected.) Creatures in gaseous form can't pass through it.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":50,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"wall"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d8","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"str","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a tiny fan and a feather of exotic origin","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":14200001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-wind-wall.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"8p9oQLDRaj8pTf1a","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-wind-wall.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Eadwig's Crackowes","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb06/eadwigs-crackowes.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"251\" height=\"256\" />\"This unusual pair of crackowes originally belonged to a venerable wizard called Hensible Eadwig. Hensible commissioned their creation late in his twilight years to help him adjust to certain frustrating physiological changes that he found he had to endure<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>the kind that came with old age. Arcane runes have been carefully stenciled across each shoe, both of which end in the gilded likeness of a raven. The shoes are identical other than for one small discrepancy, in that the left poulaine includes a space intended to hold a pen, as Hensible kept forgetting his.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Hensible's intention when he set out to have his crackowes manufactured was more than mere practical utility, but rather a desire to relive his best days as a valedictorian wizard. Consequently, he insisted that the 'middling magicians' and 'hedge mages' who worked on his marvellous new shoes imbue them with magic reminiscent of his favorite spells.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Practical Perks</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Eadwig's Crackowes have certain innate properties designed to ease the burdens of age:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can verbally command the shoes to lace and unlace themselves.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have advantage on checks made to resist falling prone while wearing them.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If the left crackowe and attached pen are ever more than 30 foot apart, the pen disappears and re-appears in its sheath.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have advantage on checks made to maintain concentration while wearing them.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Eadwig's Favorites.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Elementary versions of some of Hensible Eadwig's favorite spells have been imbued into </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Eadwig's Crackowes. These can be cast at will:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Eadwig's Hand.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As per the spell </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Mage Hand</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, except the spell's duration is instantaneous, with the hand resolving a single action before disappearing.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Reading Light.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As per the spell </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Light</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, except the spell only casts 5 foot of dim light.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Feather Fall-over.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As per the spell </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Feather Fall</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, except only targets the wearer and can only be activated when they 'fall over' rather than 'fall'.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Magic Missile.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As per the spell </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><em>Magic Missile</em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">at 1st-level, except each dart only deals 1 force damage.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>'Improved' Sending.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As per the spell </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Sending</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, except the range is only 1 mile and the recipient cannot answer.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Alarm Clock.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As per the spell </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Alarm</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, except the spell's trigger is changed so that it only goes off after a certain amount of time has elapsed or at a specified time, as per your wishes.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":4100000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/boots.png","effects":[],"_id":"ZH6IYVyu99f8Ut8c"}
{"_id":"ZTBhNmVhNDgyNWQx","name":"Lesser Restoration","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You touch a creature and can end either one disease or one condition afflicting it. The condition can be blinded, deafened, paralyzed, or poisoned.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 255","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1150000,"flags":{"itemacro":{"macro":{"_data":{"name":"Lesser Restoration","type":"script","scope":"global","command":"// Requires GM mod for CUB. Uses Item macro and Midi-qol On Use.\nlet Cub_Condition = game.macros.getName(\"Cub_Condition\");\nlet target = canvas.tokens.get(args[0].targets[0]._id);\nlet condition_list = [\"Blinded\", \"Deafened\", \"Paralyzed\", \"Diseased\", \"Poisoned\"];\nlet effect = target.actor.effects.filter( i=> condition_list.includes(i.data.label));\nlet selectOptions = \"\";\nfor (let i = 0; i < effect.length; i++){\nlet condition = effect[i].data.label;\nif (condition_list){\n    selectOptions +=`<option value=\"${condition}\">${condition}</option>`;\n  }\n}\nif (selectOptions === \"\") {\nreturn ui.notifications.error(`Nothing happens.. There's nothing to Cure on ${target.name}.`);\n}\nelse {\nlet the_content = `<form class=\"flexcol\"><div class=\"form-group\"><select id=\"element\">${selectOptions}</select></div></form>`;\n  new Dialog({\n\t  title: `Casting Lesser Restoration on ${target.name}.`,\n\t  content: the_content,\n\t\tbuttons: {\n            yes: {\n                icon: '<i class=\"fas fa-check\"></i>',\n                label: 'Remove it!',\n                callback: (html) => {\n                    let element = html.find('#element').val();\n                    Cub_Condition.execute(target, element, \"remove\");\n                    const chatMessage = game.messages.get(args[0].itemCardId);\n                    let chatContent = `<div class=\"midi-qol-hits-display\"><div><div class=\"midi-qol-nobox\"><div class=\"midi-qol-flex-container\"><div>Cures ${element}:</div><div class=\"midi-qol-target-npc midi-qol-target-name\" id=\"${target.data._id}\"> ${target.name}</div><div><img src=\"${target.data.img}\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" style=\"border:0px\"></img></div></div></div></div></div>`;\n                    let content = duplicate(chatMessage.data.content);\n                    const searchString =  '<div class=\"midi-qol-hits-display\"></div>';\n                    const replaceString = `<div class=\"midi-qol-hits-display\">${chatContent}</div>`\n                    content = content.replace(searchString, replaceString);\n                    chatMessage.update({content: content});\n                }\n              }\n            }\n        }).render(true);\n}","author":"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0"},"data":{"name":"Lesser Restoration","type":"script","scope":"global","command":"// Requires GM mod for CUB. Uses Item macro and Midi-qol On Use.\nlet Cub_Condition = game.macros.getName(\"Cub_Condition\");\nlet target = canvas.tokens.get(args[0].targets[0]._id);\nlet condition_list = [\"Blinded\", \"Deafened\", \"Paralyzed\", \"Diseased\", \"Poisoned\"];\nlet effect = target.actor.effects.filter( i=> condition_list.includes(i.data.label));\nlet selectOptions = \"\";\nfor (let i = 0; i < effect.length; i++){\nlet condition = effect[i].data.label;\nif (condition_list){\n    selectOptions +=`<option value=\"${condition}\">${condition}</option>`;\n  }\n}\nif (selectOptions === \"\") {\nreturn ui.notifications.error(`Nothing happens.. There's nothing to Cure on ${target.name}.`);\n}\nelse {\nlet the_content = `<form class=\"flexcol\"><div class=\"form-group\"><select id=\"element\">${selectOptions}</select></div></form>`;\n  new Dialog({\n\t  title: `Casting Lesser Restoration on ${target.name}.`,\n\t  content: the_content,\n\t\tbuttons: {\n            yes: {\n                icon: '<i class=\"fas fa-check\"></i>',\n                label: 'Remove it!',\n                callback: (html) => {\n                    let element = html.find('#element').val();\n                    Cub_Condition.execute(target, element, \"remove\");\n                    const chatMessage = game.messages.get(args[0].itemCardId);\n                    let chatContent = `<div class=\"midi-qol-hits-display\"><div><div class=\"midi-qol-nobox\"><div class=\"midi-qol-flex-container\"><div>Cures ${element}:</div><div class=\"midi-qol-target-npc midi-qol-target-name\" id=\"${target.data._id}\"> ${target.name}</div><div><img src=\"${target.data.img}\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" style=\"border:0px\"></img></div></div></div></div></div>`;\n                    let content = duplicate(chatMessage.data.content);\n                    const searchString =  '<div class=\"midi-qol-hits-display\"></div>';\n                    const replaceString = `<div class=\"midi-qol-hits-display\">${chatContent}</div>`\n                    content = content.replace(searchString, replaceString);\n                    chatMessage.update({content: content});\n                }\n              }\n            }\n        }).render(true);\n}","author":"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0"},"options":{},"apps":{},"compendium":null}},"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":"ItemMacro"}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/heal-sky-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZTI0MTE2MmI2NTM1","name":"Web","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You conjure a mass of thick, sticky webbing at a point of your choice within range. The webs fill a 20-foot cube from that point for the Duration. The webs are difficult terrain and lightly obscure their area.</p>\n        <p>If the webs aren’t anchored between two solid masses (such as walls or trees) or layered across a floor, wall, or ceiling, the conjured web collapses on itself, and the spell ends at the start of your next turn. Webs layered over a flat surface have a depth of 5 feet.</p>\n        <p>Each creature that starts its turn in the webs or that enters them during its turn must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is Restrained as long as it remains in the webs or until it breaks free.</p>\n        <p>A creature Restrained by the webs can use its action to make a Strength check against your spell save DC. If it succeeds, it is no longer Restrained.</p>\n        <p>The webs are flammable. Any 5-foot cube of webs exposed to fire burns away in 1 round, dealing 2d4 fire damage to any creature that starts its turn in the fire.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 287","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cube"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"A bit of spiderweb","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1100000,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-web.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"MxmwW9mY2nbuSap5","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-web.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"ZTg4NTkzZDc2OGNi","name":"Knock","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Choose an object that you can see within range. The object can be a door, a box, a chest, a set of Manacles, a padlock, or another object that contains a mundane or magical means that prevents access.</p>\n<p>A target that is held shut by a mundane lock or that is stuck or barred becomes unlocked, unstuck, or unbarred. If the object has multiple locks, only one of them is unlocked.</p>\n<p>If you choose a target that is held shut with Arcane Lock, that spell is suppressed for 10 minutes, during which time the target can be opened and shut normally.</p>\n<p>When you cast the spell, a loud knock, audible from as far away as 300 feet, emanates from the target object.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 254","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1700000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/runes-orange-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZWJkNDRlOGQ3OGVm","name":"Feather Fall","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Choose up to five falling creatures within range. A falling creature's rate of descent slows to 60 feet per round until the spell ends. If the creature lands before the spell ends, it takes no falling damage and can land on its feet, and the spell ends for that creature.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 239","activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"which you take when you or a creature within 60 feet of you falls"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A small feather or piece of down","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":850000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/wind-magenta-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Jandzuroth","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb06/jandzuroth.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"256\" />\"This statuette takes the form of a miniature stone keep the size of a large stein or tankard. An exceptionally detailed and lifelike dragon, also formed of rock, is depicted coiled around the keep's highest tower in an unusually natural pose. A set of steps lead up into the keep, which is hollow. Just inside the keep rests a sand timer that doesn't appear to serve any purpose as, at glance, there doesn't seem to be a way to rotate or activate it. The name 'Jandzuroth' is chiseled into the bottom of the statuette.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Those unversed in Jandzuroth's history might presume him to be the dragon featured prominently on the diorama of the keep, however they'd be mistaken. In truth, Jandzuroth was the name of a powerful and influential mage who constructed an unusual draconic familiar which he was notorious for spoiling rotten. Over the years, this detail has become lost and the dragon, much more than a mere feature of a stone relic, has simply began answering to its former master's name.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Attunement Requirement</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Until you attune to Jandzuroth, it is exactly as it appears&mdash;a completely mundane, stone statuette of a keep and dragon. Afterwards, its other features activate.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Pet Dragon</strong>. T</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">he diminutive red dragon atop the tower comes to life as the loyal pet of you, its bearer.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 14px; font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Jandzuroth.</strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 14px; font-style: italic;\"> Statistical information necessary to use Jandzuroth in the game and combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.7urlpWi1o3LT8biI]{Actors Directory (Jandzuroth)}.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">In combat, Jandzuroth rolls its own initiative and acts on its own turn. If the dragon is slain, its inanimate body is returned to its place on the statuette and the hourglass swivels around to begin the countdown until its return. It takes 24 hours for the sand to fully filter into the bottom bulb of the hourglass and, once it does, Jandzuroth comes alive once more.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">While Jandzuroth is within 100 feet of you, you </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">can communicate with it telepathically. Additionally, as an action, you can see through its eyes and hear what it hears until the start of your next turn, gaining the benefits of any special senses that Jandzuroth has. During this time, you are deaf and blind with regards to your own senses.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Jandzuroth is a curious little character. He craves attention and can be fiercely territorial, especially against creatures he considers rivals for your affection. He will harass, attack, and try to chase away other familiars, animal companions, and pets that vie for your attention.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":16600000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"ZeomqUvQJ2PdOaYu"}
{"_id":"Zh8aC62Pw4DtJac9","name":"Faerie Fire","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Each object in a 20-foot cube within range is outlined in blue, green, or violet light (your choice). Any creature in the area when the spell is cast is also outlined in light if it fails a Dexterity saving throw. For the duration, objects and affected creatures shed dim light in a 10-foot radius.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Any attack roll against an affected creature or object has advantage if the attacker can see it, and the affected creature or object can't benefit from being <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#invisible_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'invisible_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >invisible</a>.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cube"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":12900001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-faerie-fire.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"OUnWqSNJZaMhiUtB","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-faerie-fire.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Vexillam","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb03/vexillam.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"93\" height=\"256\" />\"This towering banner stands at an impressive 13-foot-tall, though the shadow it casts over a battle stretches far further than that. For, to those gathered beneath it, the standard itself serves as a symbol around which they can rally, spurring them on to perform feats far grander than might be otherwise possible. The flag itself is formed of an elaborate depiction of a golden stag framed within a striking red border. The object is crowned by a half-star enshrined within the outline of a round disc.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Vexillam has made its way to the front lines of many a war over the years. Throughout it's storied existence, it has witnessed the downfall of heroes, the deaths of despots, and the demise of kingdoms. And, throughout all this, it has often proved instrumental in determining the outcome of many of these great battles.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Flag Fling</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Thanks to its long and slender flagpole, and its unnaturally light weight, Vexillam can be flung great distances, soaring like a javelin or spear. Weather permitting, you can throw it up to 60 foot and have it land at a point within range that you can see of your choosing.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Rally (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When times are at their darkest, those gathered beneath Vexillam can look to the almighty banner and find the strength to muster once more. As a bonus action, while you are within 120 feet of Vexillam you can command it to rally your troops. If you do so, creatures who you consider your allies that are within 30 foot of the flag can immediately spend one of their hit die to regain a number of hit points equal to their result + their Constitution modifier. Additionally, they can also choose to spend their reaction to move up to half their speed.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Banner of Bravery</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Standing proudly over the heads of those who fight for it, Vexillam serves as a symbol for hope. You can nominate up to five allies. While you and your designated allies are within 30 feet of the flag, you all benefit from a +1 bonus to fear and morale checks.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":13400000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"ZhadJuI2IN3ADgq1"}
{"_id":"ZjAwMTY2M2JmZDZl","name":"Comprehend Languages","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>For the duration, you understand the literal meaning of any spoken language that you hear. You also understand any written language that you see, but you must be touching the surface on which the words are written. It takes about 1 minute to read one page of text.</p><p>This spell doesn't decode secret messages in a text or a glyph, such as an arcane sigil, that isn't part of a written language.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 224","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":null,"type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":true,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A pinch of soot and salt","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":840000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/runes-royal-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZjFhMjJkMjIyNGFj","name":"Invisibility","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A creature you touch becomes invisible until the spell ends. Anything the target is wearing or carrying is invisible as long as it is on the target's person. The spell ends for a target that attacks or casts a spell.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 2nd.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 254","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":2,"school":"ill","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"An eyelash encased in gum arabic","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":900000,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/fog-sky-2.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"Cl1pJbfQlGqoXnDk","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/fog-sky-2.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"ZjI4Y2E4ZGEwNWFi","name":"Find Familiar","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your familiar acts independently of you, but it always obeys your commands. In combat, it rolls its own initiative and acts on its own turn. A familiar can’t attack, but it can take other actions as normal.</p>\n<p>When the familiar drops to 0 hit points, it disappears, leaving behind no physical form. It reappears after you cast this spell again.</p>\n<p>While your familiar is within 100 feet of you, you can communicate with it telepathically. Additionally, as an action, you can see through your familiar’s eyes and hear what it hears until the start of your next turn, gaining the benefits of any special senses that the familiar has. During this time, you are deaf and blind with regard to your own senses.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can temporarily dismiss your familiar. It disappears into a pocket dimension where it awaits your summons. Alternatively, you can dismiss it forever. As an action while it is temporarily dismissed, you can cause it to reappear in any unoccupied space within 30 feet of you.</p>\n<p>You can’t have more than one familiar at a time. If you cast this spell while you already have a familiar, you instead cause it to adopt a new form. Choose one of the forms from the above list. Your familiar transforms into the chosen creature.</p>\n<p>Finally, when you cast a spell with a range of touch, your familiar can deliver the spell as if it had cast the spell. Your familiar must be within 100 feet of you, and it must use its reaction to deliver the spell when you cast it. If the spell requires an attack roll, you use your action modifier for the roll.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 240","activation":{"type":"hour","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"perm"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":10,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"10gp worth of charcoal, incense, and herbs that must be consumed by fire in a brass brazier.</p><p>You gain the service of a familiar, a spirit that takes an animal form you choose: bat, cat, crab, frog (toad), hawk, lizard, octopus, owl, poisonous snake, fish (quipper), rat, raven, sea horse, spider, or weasel. Appearing in an unoccupied space within range, the familiar has the statistics of the chosen form, though it is a celestial, fey, or fiend (your choice) instead of a beast","consumed":true,"cost":10,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":860000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/wild-eerie-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZjJmZGJmMDVhZjQ1","name":"Light","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You touch one object that is no larger than 10 feet in any dimension. Until the spell ends, the object sheds bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet. The light can be colored as you like. Completely covering the object with something opaque blocks the light. The spell ends if you cast it again or dismiss it as an action.</p><p>If you target an object held or worn by a hostile creature, that creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw to avoid the spell.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 255","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"object"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A firefly or phosphorescent moss.","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":400000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/light-sky-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZjMxOTYyMGE1MmRm","name":"Wish","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Wish is the mightiest spell a mortal creature can cast. By simply speaking aloud, you can alter the very foundations of reality in accord with your desires.</p>\n        <p>The basic use of this spell is to duplicate any other spell of 8th level or lower. You don’t need to meet any requirements in that spell, including costly Components. The spell simply takes effect.</p>\n        <p>Alternatively, you can create one of the following Effects of your choice:</p>\n        <ul>\n        <li>You create one object of up to 25,000 gp in value that isn’t a magic item. The object can be no more than 300 feet in any dimension, and it appears in an unoccupied space you can see on the ground.</li>\n        <li>You allow up to twenty creatures that you can see to regain all hit points⁠, and you end all Effects on them described in the Greater Restoration spell.</li>\n        <li>You grant up to ten creatures that you can see resistance⁠ to a damage type you choose.</li>\n        <li>You grant up to ten creatures you can see immunity to a single spell or other magical effect for 8 hours. For instance, you could make yourself and all your companions immune to a lich’s life drain attack⁠.</li>\n        <li>You undo a single recent event by forcing a reroll of any roll made within the last round (including your last turn). Reality reshapes itself to accommodate the new result. For example, a wish spell could undo an opponent’s successful save, a foe’s critical hit, or a friend’s failed save. You can force the reroll to be made with advantage or disadvantage, and you can choose whether to use the reroll or the original roll.</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p>You might be able to achieve something beyond the scope of the above examples. State your wish to the DM as precisely as possible. The DM has great latitude in ruling what occurs in such an instance; the greater the wish, the greater the likelihood that something goes wrong. This spell might simply fail, the effect you desire might only be partly achieved, or you might suffer some unforeseen consequence as a result of how you worded the wish. For example, wishing that a villain were dead might propel you forward in time to a period when that villain is no longer alive, effectively removing you from the game. Similarly, wishing for a legendary magic item or artifact might instantly transport you to the presence of the item’s current owner.</p>\n        <p>The stress of casting this spell to produce any effect other than duplicating another spell weakens you. After enduring that stress, each time you cast a spell⁠ until you finish a Long Rest, you take 1d10 necrotic damage per level of that spell. This damage can’t be reduced or prevented in any way. In addition, your Strength drops to 3, if it isn’t 3 or lower already, for 2d4 days. For each of those days that you spend Resting and doing nothing more than light activity, your remaining recovery time decreases by 2 days. Finally, there is a 33 percent chance that you are unable to cast wish ever again if you suffer this stress.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 288","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":9,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1130000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/runes-royal-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZjQzZWQ5MDZiNzJm","name":"Identify","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You choose one object that you must touch throughout the casting of the spell. If it is a magic item or some other magic-imbued object, you learn its properties and how to use them, whether it requires attunement to use, and how many charges it has, if any. You learn whether any spells are affecting the item and what they are. If the item was created by a spell, you learn which spell created it.</p><p>If you instead touch a creature throughout the casting, you learn what spells, if any, are currently affecting it.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 252","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"A pearl worth at least 100gp and an owl feather","consumed":false,"cost":100,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1110000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/light-eerie-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Zjc5MDNmNjE5ZmY1","name":"Conjure Elemental","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You call forth an elemental servant. Choose an area of air, earth, fire, or water that fills a 10-foot cube within range. An elemental of challenge rating 5 or lower appropriate to the area you chose appears in an unoccupied space within 10 feet of it. For example, a fire elemental emerges from a bonfire, and an earth elemental rises up from the ground. The elemental disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The elemental is friendly to you and your companions for the duration. Roll initiative for the elemental, which has its own turns. It obeys any verbal commands that you issue to it (no action required by you). If you don’t issue any commands to the elemental, it defends itself from hostile creatures but otherwise takes no actions.</p>\n<p>If your concentration is broken, the elemental doesn’t disappear. Instead, you lose control of the elemental, it becomes hostile toward you and your companions, and it might attack. An uncontrolled elemental can’t be dismissed by you, and it disappears 1 hour after you summoned it.</p>\n<p><strong>Higher Levels.&nbsp;</strong>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the challenge rating increases by 1 for each slot level above 5th.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 225","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":"10 ft. Cube of appropriate element near by"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":10,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"space"},"range":{"value":90,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":5,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"Burning incense for air, soft clay for earth, sulfur and phosphorus for fire, or water and sand for water.","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1200000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/runes-orange-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZjczZmYxZDNiZDFi","name":"Symbol","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>When you cast this spell, you inscribe a harmful glyph either on a surface (such as a section of floor, a wall, or a table) or within an object that can be closed to conceal the glyph (such as a book, a scroll, or a treasure⁠ chest). If you choose a surface, the glyph can cover an area of the surface no larger than 10 feet in diameter. If you choose an object, that object must remain in its place; if the object is moved more than 10 feet from where you cast this spell, the glyph is broken, and the spell ends without being triggered.</p>\n<p>The glyph is nearly invisible⁠, requiring an Intelligence (Investigation) check against your spell save DC to find it.</p>\n<p>You decide what triggers the glyph when you cast the spell. For glyphs inscribed on a surface, the most typical triggers include touching or stepping on the glyph, removing another object covering it, approaching within a certain distance of it, or manipulating the object that holds it. For glyphs inscribed within an object, the most common⁠ triggers are opening the object, approaching within a certain distance of it, or seeing or reading the glyph.</p>\n<p>You can further refine the trigger so the spell is activated only under certain circumstances or according to a creature’s physical characteristics⁠ (such as height or weight), or physical kind (for example, the ward could be set to affect hags or shapechangers). You can also specify creatures that don’t trigger the glyph, such as those who say a certain password.</p>\n<p>When you inscribe the glyph, choose one of the options below for its effect. Once triggered, the glyph glows, filling a 60-foot-radius sphere⁠ with dim light for 10 minutes, after which time the spell ends. Each creature in the sphere⁠ when the glyph activates is targeted by its effect, as is a creature that enters the Sphere for the first time on a turn or ends its turn there.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Death.</strong> Each target must make a Constitution saving throw, taking 10d10 necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful save.</li>\n<li><strong>Discord.</strong> Each target must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a target bickers and argues with other creatures for 1 minute. During this time, it is incapable of meaningful communication⁠ and has disadvantage on Attack rolls and Ability Checks.</li>\n<li><strong>Fear.</strong> Each target must make a Wisdom saving throw and becomes Frightened for 1 minute on a failed save. While Frightened, the target drops whatever it is holding and must move at least 30 feet away from the glyph on each of its turns, if able.</li>\n<li><strong>Hopelessness.</strong> Each target must make a Charisma saving throw. On a failed save, the target is overwhelmed with despair for 1 minute. During this time, it can’t attack⁠ or target any creature with harmful Abilities, Spells, or other magical Effects.</li>\n<li><strong>Insanity.</strong> Each target must make an Intelligence saving throw. On a failed save, the target is driven insane for 1 minute. An insane creature can’t take Actions, can’t understand what other creatures say, can’t read, and speaks only in gibberish. The DM controls its Movement, which is erratic.</li>\n<li><strong>Pain.</strong> Each target must make a Constitution saving throw and becomes Incapacitated with excruciating pain for 1 minute on a failed save.</li>\n<li><strong>Sleep.</strong> Each target must make a Wisdom saving throw and falls Unconscious for 10 minutes on a failed save. A creature awakens if it takes damage or if someone uses an action to shake or slap it awake.</li>\n<li><strong>Stunning.</strong> Each target must make a Wisdom saving throw and becomes Stunned for 1 minute on a failed save.</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 280","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"perm"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["10d10","necrotic"]],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":0,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":7,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"Mercury, phosphorus, and powdered diamond and opal with a total value of at least 1,000 gp, which the spell consumes","consumed":true,"cost":1000,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":1120000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/runes-blue-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Zjg1MzI2MzlkMTYy","name":"Clairvoyance","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You create an invisible sensor within range in a location familiar to you (a place you have visited or seen before) or in an obvious location that is unfamiliar to you (such as behind a door, around a corner, or in a grove of trees). The sensor remains in place for the duration, and it can’t be attacked or otherwise interacted with.</p>\n<p>When you cast the spell, you choose seeing or hearing. You can use the chosen sense through the sensor as if you were in its space. As your action, you can switch between seeing and hearing.</p>\n<p>A creature that can see the sensor (such as a creature benefiting from see invisibility or truesight) sees a luminous, intangible orb about the size of your fist.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 222","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":10,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":"space"},"range":{"value":1,"long":0,"units":"mi"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":3,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"A focus worth at least 100gp, either a jeweled horn for hearing or a glass eye for seeing.","consumed":false,"cost":100,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":950000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/evil-eye-eerie-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZmQ4NGZhZWJkZDg5","name":"Dominate Beast","permission":{"default":0},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You attempt to beguile a beast that you can see within range. It must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be charmed by you for the duration. If you or creatures that are friendly to you are fighting it, it has advantage on the saving throw.</p>\n<p>While the beast is charmed, you have a telepathic link with it as long as the two of you are on the same plane of existence. You can use this telepathic link to issue commands to the creature while you are conscious (no action required), which it does its best to obey. You can specify a simple and general course of action, such as \"Attack that creature,\" \"Run over there,\" or \"Fetch that object.\" If the creature completes the order and doesn't receive further direction from you, it defends and preserves itself to the best of its ability.</p>\n<p>You can use your action to take total and precise control of the target. Until the end of your next turn, the creature takes only the actions you choose, and doesn't do anything that you don't allow it to do. During this time, you can also cause the creature to use a reaction, but this requires you to use your own reaction as well.</p>\n<p>Each time the target takes damage, it makes a new Wisdom saving throw against the spell. If the saving throw succeeds, the spell ends.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell with a 5th-level spell slot, the duration is concentration, up to 10 minutes. When you use a 6th-level spell slot, the duration is concentration, up to 1 hour. When you use a spell slot of 7th level or higher, the duration is concentration, up to 8 hours.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 234","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""}},"folder":"ZmNjZDA4MjI4NzU4","sort":2000000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/air-burst-jade-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Spirit Sake","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This brown glass corked bottle has a label that reads Oki-Shan, though no further details are offered by it other than a simplistic depiction of an auburn sun setting over a farmstead, with the ocean in the background. The bottle's interior smells strongly of sake, while a residue of crystallized salt build-up regularly forms around its top. Irrespective of the temperature, the bottle remains frosty to the touch.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Deathly Pallor</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This unassuming bottle has a curious connection to the ethereal plane. If you fill the Spirit Sake bottle with sea water and cork it, 24 hours later the water turns into a powerfully intoxicating wine. A creature who drinks this wine gains the following traits for 1 hour:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">They turn a deathly white and appear to be close to death.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">They can see incorporeal undead within 30 foot, whether the undead are invisible, on the ethereal plane, or visible.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">They have advantage on checks made to resist being possessed and creatures attempting to possess them have disadvantage on their checks.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">They have advantage on saving throws related to resisting the adverse affects of&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Life Drain</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Age Drain</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">, and&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Withering Touch</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">They have a +1 bonus on saving throws made to avoid being frightened by incorporeal undead.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The bottle can be filled with enough sea water for four creatures to drink from it.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDestroy":false},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"trinket","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":17000000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/potion.png","effects":[],"_id":"ZqT4tIGYS9nyAOwP"}
{"_id":"ZryuWRReEQza7yfu","name":"Vampiric Touch","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The touch of your shadow-wreathed hand can siphon life force from others to heal your wounds. Make a melee spell attack against a creature within your reach. On a hit, the target takes [[/r 3d6]] necrotic damage, and you regain hit points equal to half the amount of necrotic damage dealt. Until the spell ends, you can make the attack again on each of your turns as an action.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d6]] for each slot level above 3rd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"self","type":"self"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"msak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d6","necrotic"],["","healing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d6"},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":100001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/rip-sky-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Bow of the Able Eagle","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Thanks to several modifications, this shortbow is able to compete with larger recurves at long ranges whilst still being compact and lightweight enough for creatures with small frames to wield it comfortably. It was originally designed for use by a halfling who struggled to effectively utilize the bulky longbows favored by her larger contemporaries. To compensate for its smaller size, the bow is reinforced with two strings that crisscross at the point where arrows are notched, effectively doubling the force with which they can be propelled. A spyglass is affixed to its sight, further cementing the bow as a long range weapon. This simple but expensive addition serves to improve the bow's accuracy over longer distances, though at the cost of diminishing its usefulness against nearer, more immediate threats.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The bow of the Able Eagle is formed of a dark brown wood which gradually lightens up towards it tips and has been overlaid with majestic bird-like feathers of a rich, brown color. The tip of the bow's spyglass protrudes past its shaft and is designed to resemble the golden beak of an eagle. Given these features, when viewed side-on, the bow looks akin a bird-of-prey, an eagle most specifically, being viewed from above.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Bow of the Able Eagle can be used as a shortbow.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Tool</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Bow of the Able Eagle can be used as a spyglass.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Modified Shortbow</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Bow of the Able Eagle has been modified so that it is much more adept and accurate at hitting targets at medium-range. When using it to make a ranged attack, you have disadvantage on attack rolls against targets up to 80 feet away, however you can shoot targets between 85 and 320 feet away without disadvantage.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Significant Upgrades</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Bow of the Able Eagle has seen significant upgrades to ensure that it fires fast and true. Your attacks with it deal +1 damage.</span></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Superior Aim. </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Master marksmen know to wait for the perfect opportunity to strike. While holding it, y</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">ou can use a bonus action to take aim with the Bow of the Able Eagle before making an attack with it. If you do, the target takes an additional 1d4 damage on your next attack this turn if it successfully hits.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":80,"long":320,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod +1","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"1d4","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleR","properties":{"amm":true,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":3300000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-ranged-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"ZvPkgnnlVJOmVEuC"}
{"name":"Shortbow of the Down Below","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This shortbow looks and functions much like any other smaller recurve, however it is constructed out of an extremely dark wood compared to most such implements. In fact, the material used in its construction is so starkly sable that it could just easily be mistaken for obsidian stone as black walnut. If, that is, the bow is spotted at all, as it would be easy to overlook altogether in a darkened environment.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Shortbow of the Down Below is the signature weapon of a god of the myriad subterranean caverns and chambers, tunnels and corridors, and wells and shafts that link the world below the surface together. Having been unable to find a suitable candidate from beneath the soil, this deity chose a champion from the surface, gifting them with this bow in exchange for their devotion and fealty.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Shortbow of the Down Below can be used as a shortbow.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Sensory Superiority</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Shortbow of the Down Below was once utilized by a resolute soul in service to the deity that they pledged their life to. While you are holding it, it is about your person, or it is within 5 feet of you, you have darkvision out to a distance of 30 foot. If you already possess darkvision, the distance out to which you can see in darkness increases by 30 feet.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Sureshot</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When alone and in the darkness, a wise man fires first. You gain a +1 bonus to attack rolls made with the&nbsp;</span>Shortbow of the Down Below . Additionally, you deal 1d4 bonus damage with it on the first round of combat.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":80,"long":320,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"1","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleR","properties":{"amm":true,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":10000000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-ranged-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"a2wT3Yt2sexCIgaL"}
{"name":"Forger's Finger","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb02/forgers-finger.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"221\" />\"The appearance of this remarkable ring changes frequently however it always features a highly-detailed, intricate gold band. This gives the item an ornate appearance and imparts a sense that this is an item that is noteworthy for its quality, even if its true focus is on utility and not on being luxurious or flashy. As a signet ring, the object's function is to seal letters with the emblem of its owner or else leave their signature mark on dossiers and other documents. However, due to the object's real purpose, as an arcane aid to forgers and fraudsters, the face of the ring is often bare and featureless, while it adopts unusual shapes and symbols at other times.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Cure for the Curious</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Forger's Finger allows a creature to discretely peruse letters and other documents without permission and without arousing suspicion; or else create false dossiers and fake missives with relative ease. When pressed against a seal or signature, the wax, ink, or markings are stripped from the page or envelope and absorbed into the ring, appearing embossed onto its surface. Pressing the ring to another parchment transplants the wax seal or signature onto it. Forger's Finger can only hold one signature or seal at a time. This feature can be used to mask that existing seals have been broken, or else to add credibility to falsified documents.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Pilfered Penmanship</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Using Forger's Finger, and their own cunning and guile, a savvy fraudster might mislead</span> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">just about anyone. If you touch the personal pen or quill of another creature for at least 1 minute while </span>wearing Forger's Finger, you can duplicate their handwriting for 24 hours. Handwriting replicated in this way is similar enough to fool anyone but the creature whose handwriting has been imitated, close or long-standing personal or professional contacts of theirs, or an expert in calligraphy who has another example of their writing to hand for comparison.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Sigil</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When not being used to transplant a seal or signature, Forger's Finger can be willed to present an ornate crest of its own. Any time Forger's Finger's face would be otherwise blank, the ring instead shows your family crest, another emblem of your choosing, or else a generic seal if you wish it.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":8000000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/ring.png","effects":[],"_id":"a77dVb0oBSF4NDuP"}
{"_id":"aFnWW76bqIDHuLxT","name":"Lightning Bolt (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A stroke of lightning forming a line 100 feet long and 5 feet wide blasts out from you in a direction you choose. Each creature in the line must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes [[/r 8d6]] lightning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The lightning ignites flammable objects in the area that aren't being worn or carried.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"117\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d6]] for each slot level above 3rd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":100,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["8d6","lightning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a bit of fur and a rod of amber, crystal, or glass","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d6"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":7200001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-lightning-bolt.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Pirene","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb04/pirene.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"179\" height=\"256\" />\"This resplendent ciborium demands the attention of those who look upon it and signifies its bearer as a person of authority thanks to the jewels that lavishly decorate it. The virtuous nature of this chalice is perhaps best exemplified by the pair of twin pegasi that appear to bear the object's basin upon their backs. Should the taint of corruption ever despoil the goblet, these pegasi become twisted and are transformed into nightmares.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Font of Purification</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Pure and divine in every sense of the word, Pirene can purify almost any type of liquid. Liquids&mdash;including alcohol, poisons, toxic or diseased water, or unholy water&mdash;poured into it are turned into blood that functions exactly as holy </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">water. Once removed from the chalice, the blood becomes regular blood and ceases to function as holy water after 6 seconds&mdash;or 1 round&mdash;has elapsed.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Divine Blessing (1/Day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Pirene bestows a useful blessing upon the pious and the meek. Once per day, you can utter a simple prayer and have it fill with blood that grants a certain effect, or have the blood already in it turn from holy water to blood that grants one of the following effects if it is already filled. Each blessing lasts for 8 hours and the effect is determined at random by rolling 1d8:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">1</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You gain a 5 foot fly speed.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">2</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Your speed increases by 5 foot.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">3</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You learn the celestial language, though you cannot speak it.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">4</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You gain the benefits of the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><em>Feather Fall</em>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">spell any time you are falling, but you are the only creature affected by it.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">5</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You lose the ability to speak or communicate in any way, including via written messages and gestures. However, you are able to understand celestial, sylvan, and elvish.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">6</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You have advantage on checks made to win the friendship of animals.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">7</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can pick one harmful effect affecting you when you drink the blood. It ceases to apply for 8 hours.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">8</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can walk on water, though water is considered difficult terrain for the purposes of doing so.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Corrupted Bauble</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Each creature that forms a link with Pirene leaves a mark upon it. Should the object be attuned to by an evil creature, it must be reconsecrated before it can be attuned to by a good or neutral character again. It can be reconsecrated by a paladin, cleric, or other priest if they undertake a 1 hour ritual which requires them to utter a prayer while holding the object for the duration.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"weight","value":1,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":16100000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/goblet.png","effects":[],"_id":"aGieIB4QcgbdrzEM"}
{"name":"Babushaboxes","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This set of seven luxurious lock boxes seems perfect for storing keepsakes, jewelry, and other small belongings of monetary or sentimental value. Though rarely encountered together, each box in the set is differently sized so that they can be stacked snugly within each other. Arranged in a classic baroque style with sterling silver detailing, 24-carat gold trim, and a rich red velvet padded interior, each case that forms this magnificent collection is needlessly indulgent; as much a work of art as it is a functional receptacle for the treasured keepsakes of its owner.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In reality, the Babushaboxes are a sham and, correctly appraised, these phony coffers are only worth a fraction of what they appear to be at face value. The sterling silver is actually silver-plated brass, the 24-carat gold instead 4-carat with a lacquer coating that masks its impurities, and the red velvet is just a cheaper felt substitute. However, the chests' real worth lies in their hidden potential and rests with whomever holds dominion over the largest box in the set.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>True Value</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">To those without a keen eye for such things, the Babushaboxes appear to be exceptional, both </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">individually and as a set. Superficially, they seem like they're worth 50 GP each, or 400 GP for the complete collec</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">tion. However, a creature studying them to discern or appraise their true value should make a DC 13 Intelligence (investigation) check. On a success, they identify that the Babushaboxes are only worth a tenth of what they might have otherwise suspected.</span></span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Defined Item Values. </strong>Although this feature specifies the value of the</span></span> Babushaboxes<span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, this doesn't determine how much an NPC in a game might offer a PC for their purchase. Just like all equipment has a specific value, the figures provided simply confer a baseline valuation for the purposes of comparing their worth against other items. NPCs may arrive at different valuations, be generous, be stingy, or be inclined to haggle as the GM sees fit. And, if an NPC becomes aware of the true function of the set, they may even be willing to offer even more to acquire it.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Nesting Chests</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The true purpose of the Babushaboxes is more nefarious than one might realize. A creature in possession of any box from the set can use it to achieve one of several results, all of which function irrespective of the distance between the Babushaboxes&mdash;as long as those affected are on the same plane of existence:</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">An individual in possession of the largest box can snap the lid of their box closed between one and seven times. Slamming it closed one to six times causes the corresponding coffer&mdash;starting with the smallest and ascending in order of size&mdash;to reappear within theirs with its current contents intact. If they instead slam the lid seven times, all six other boxes reappear stacked within it, although their contents is left precisely where it was when they were recalled.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The smaller Babushaboxes aren't without their own intrinsic value either. Should objects be placed in any Babushabox besides the master and their lid slammed a number of times equalling any other box in the set&mdash;starting with the smallest and ascending in order of size&mdash;these items reappear in that chest, as long as they fit. Should the lid of a box be slammed a number of times equal to its own place in the hierarchy, it vanishes&mdash;along with its contents&mdash;and reappears in the master box</span>.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Attunement.</strong> In order for the Babushaboxes to function, a creature must be attuned to the master box.</span></p>\n</blockquote>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":12,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":2100000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/container.png","effects":[],"_id":"aJiClqi1QghqeFI7"}
{"name":"Fawlty","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"Formerly the property of a dishonest hotelier who desperately wanted to break into the roguish trade, this unusual ledger is indistinguishable from any common guest book at a glance. That said, its true function is far more vile and insidious. Able to gather the darkest secrets of those who write in it, the sneering innkeeper to whom it once belonged planned on using the item to blackmail those unwise enough to seek rest and repose at his establishment. And he did, extorting a small fortune for himself over the course of ten years before pushing one of his guests too far. The guest in question had placed several bad investments of late, was far less well off than he seemed, and was already on the brink of despair when he'd checked in. Faced with the prospect of his naughtiest, most salacious secret coming to light, he took a hatchet to the hotelier, his family, and then, finally, himself. The ledger's true purpose unknown, it passed into obscurity and was forgotten about.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Cipher</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Fawlty can be used to translate messages written in Thieves' Cant using a hidden cipher located just inside its back cover. You can read the text hidden on its rearmost page</span>&mdash;which is otherwise invisible without the use of magic&mdash;and this information can be used to transcribe written examples of thieves' cant at a rate of 1 sentence per minute.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Dirty Secrets</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Few creatures are able to keep their darkest thoughts private when they make the critical mistake of marking Fawlty. A creature attempting to write or draw in it other than you must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw. On a success, they write precisely whatever they intended to. On a fail, they unknowingly write whatever they intended to plus a dark or embarrassing secret. Creatures make this check each time they try to write in the ledger, but they must always write a different secret if they can think of one they haven't revealed before.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Alternatively, you can write two questions into the margin of a page</span>. Should another creature attempt to read the page, they must attempt a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw. On a success, they only consciously acknowledge the first question. On a fail, they consciously acknowledge the first question and subconsciously acknowledge the second question as well. Should they decide to write a response to the first question having unknowingly noticed the second, they answer both without realizing it. If a creature beats the DC by 10 or more, they see both questions and can decide how to proceed from there.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Without the use of magic, creatures other than you can only see the messages and depictions of other creatures that they intended to write. Meanwhile, you can read everything recorded in it</span>, including your own words.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":15700000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/book.png","effects":[],"_id":"aY7xUv5vYRouSaeU"}
{"name":"Wildsting","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Most commonly wielded by the nobleman who holds the esteemed position of huntmaster</span></em><em>&mdash;</em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">also known as the master of the hunt in some cultures</span></em><em>&mdash;</em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">this fine foil is often seen held aloft at the front of a precession of hunters, leading the charge as the group pursues some elusive quarry on horseback through thick and treacherous undergrowth. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Much more than a merely ornamental object, the blade itself is keenly sharp and provides a useful tool should the individual charged with it find themselves separated from the other hunters in their party and at risk of being gored by a frenzied beast as it enters its final desperate death throes.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Stinging Strikes</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A deft and perfectly-balanced rapier, Wildsting provides far greater finesse than the type of armament a hunter might typically employ. Strikes from it throw its victims off-balance. When you </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">land an attack on a creature of the beast type with it, all attack rolls against the creature benefit from a 1d4 bonus until the start of your next turn.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Perfect Pursuit</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Wildsting loves the hunt and was born for the chase itself. For the next 24 hours after it has been used to deal damage to a creature of the beast type&mdash;or until the wound has closed and the creature has regained all of its lost hit points&mdash;the blade's tip points towards the creature's location if you hold it loosely aloft. If this feature is activated by two or more creatures simultaneously, you feel its tip tugging sluggishly in different directions.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":14600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"ai2qFADQzkPBFOtv"}
{"name":"Rhellu-Enme","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This tapered hexagonal box is formed of rich mahogany wood, has gilded gold detailing and a red velvet interior, and is quite clearly a coffin intended for a very small creature. Within it rests a bat that has been laid on its back with its wings folded over its chest. A stake has been stabbed directly through the bat's wings and into its heart, and the perfectly preserved creature now sleeps peacefully in death's cold embrace. At a glance, this bat could be easily mistaken for a vampire bat, but a closer inspection reveals that it is actually a somewhat undersized fruit bat.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The name Rhellu-Enme denotes both the bat, Enme, and its final resting place, Rhellu. Once belonging to an infamous vampire hunter, the winged bat was used to gather information, bypassing&mdash;or, infrequently, triggering&mdash;the traps and snares of powerful vampires, since the undead bat was rarely noticed by their wards&mdash;which were prepared with the living in mind. Its origins prior to use in hunting vampires are unknown.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Attunement Requirement</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Neither Rhellu nor Enme recognise or obey just anyone. You must not be an evil-aligned creature in order to attune to it.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Laid to Rest</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Even while Enme is resting, Rhellu is able to provide its keeper with certain other advantages. While Enme is staked within Rhellu, you gain blindsight out to a distance of 5 foot. Additionally, whenever you take damage from a creature of the Undead type, you gain 1 temporary hit point at the start of your next turn. This feature doesn't function if you begin your turn with 0 hit points.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Loyal Servant</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Though Enme seems utterly still and lifeless at first, there remains a measure of life in its ancient bones yet. If you remove the stake from Enme's heart and take the bat's body out of Rhellu,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">it animates and acts as your faithful companion. Enme uses the statistics of a </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\">Bat</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">, however its type is Undead. It understands any languages that you speak however it cannot communicate. In combat, Enme rolls its own initiative and acts on its own turn. If it is reduced to 0 hit points, its body becomes inanimate once more and it cannot be reanimated until it has spent at least 24-hours staked within Rhellu.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Large Servant (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Though Rhellu-Enme has been used to fight back against the darkness, its origins are born of the blackest night. A</span>s a bonus action,<span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"> you can verbally command Enme to tap into dark powers in order to grow into a much larger, more threatening creature w</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">hile it is animated as per the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Loyal Servant&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">feature</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">. This transformation can be undertaken once per day and lasts for 1 minute. During the transformation, Enme uses the statistics for a <strong>Giant Bat</strong>, instead of a<strong> Bat</strong>.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"items","value":1,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":18800000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/container.png","effects":[],"_id":"alTeLGKwSQLuYPyR"}
{"name":"Jilliere Odeur","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb02/jilliere-odeur.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"232\" height=\"256\" />\"This small, elegant leather case contains six numbered glass vials, each of which holds a distinct scent from the Jilliere Odeur line of premium perfumes. It has a metal clasp on the outside to keep it shut and a purple satin cushion padded interior designed to protect its exquisite contents from harm.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Fragrances</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Jilliere Odeur contains the following signature scents:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Jilliere No I</strong>. T</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">his fragrance alters itself to immediately become a fine perfume or cologne perfectly suited to your tastes and preferences. The scent may, for example, be an earthy sandalwood for an adventurous halfling or a floral jasmine for a jovial half-elf.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Jilliere No II</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This pungent fragrance has a musky and smoky aroma that is not obviously appealing to the nose of humanoids but provides a powerful draw to beasts. After you spray it on a creature, including yourself, the creature has advantage on Wisdom (animal handling) checks made to influence domesticated beasts, such as dogs and cats. Untrained, wild, and feral beasts remain unaffected by it.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Jilliere No III</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The foul, acrid bouquet in this odious spray can be used to nauseating effect. As an action, you can direct this vial towards a creature within 5 foot of you who must then make a DC 13 Constitution saving throw, taking 1d4 poison damage on a fail and becoming </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><em>Poisoned</em>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">until the start of your next turn.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Jilliere No IV</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The fumes from this balmy fragrance linger on the palette, affecting the short term memories of those exposed to it. Those who observe you close up while you are wearing it must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or else they find it a struggle to remember defining characteristics about </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">you. They might, for example, mistake an individual of a different race, age, or gender for you.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Jilliere No V</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This zesty spray conveys motes of lemons or limes and can be turned on an unconscious creature to prolong their natural sleep by 1d4 hours. A creature affected in this way is also less likely to be woken by disturbances around them. Consequently, their passive Perception score is reduced by an additional 5 until they wake.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Jilliere No VI</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This odorless spray neutralizes scents already in the air, masking their presence. A creature sprayed with it, including yourself, cannot be tracked by scent or smell for one hour.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span style=\"color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">Scents that do not specify a duration last until a creature completes a long rest or washes them away.</span></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"items","value":6,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":18500000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/potion.png","effects":[],"_id":"arh40j2SwL10wg8j"}
{"name":"Siren's Helm","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb05/sirens-helm.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"253\" height=\"256\" />\"This ligneous ship wheel once served as the helm of the renowned cutter-class ship, The Siren. The vessel earned notoriety for its ability to complete voyages in record time thanks in large part to its rather stately, erudite, and, some would say, ostentatious helmsman. Despite his swagger and charm, he was known to be a dreadful drunkard and was regularly intoxicated at the wheel. Conversely, he was applauded and highly sought-after for his ability to cut sharply between towering rocks, navigate crowded ports, and cleave through perilous storms at breakneck speeds. Unfortunately, his ship did eventually find ruin when he quit drinking and lost his nerve along with his stupor. The Siren capsized as a result of a critical error in judgment on his part and the wheel, along with what remained of the crew, were recovered from the wreck several weeks later.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Siren's Helm can be used as a shield.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Sailor's Shield</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Siren's Helm can steer an entire ship</span> <span class=\"fontstyle2\">to safety as easily as it can safeguard a single creature. You can lay it over the top of a ship's wheel or remove it from one as an action. While deployed in this fashion, the wheel can be used to steer the ship as normal and Siren's Helm also confers the following benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The ship moves 1 mile per hour faster in poor winds, and 2 miles per hour in favourable winds.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You or another creature piloting the ship has advantage on handling checks made to steer it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">When checks are made to determine if the ship is flipped or capsized, the dice are rolled twice and the more favourable result is used.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Hard to Port (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Siren's Helm is often seen spinning in the hands of a stalwart defender of others. While wielding it, you can twirl it as a bonus action to cause an invisible force to manifest itself around creatures within 30 foot of you. Each creature within the affected area must attempt a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw. On a fail, they lurch violently in the direction you spun the shield, as if their surroundings were a ship that was abruptly banking to the side. Affected creatures move 5 foot in the direction indicated, before dropping prone. Creatures who have experienced this phenomena previously have advantage on their saving throw.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":8,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":2,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":11200000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/shield.png","effects":[],"_id":"arkdReAT4UKyZ0ow"}
{"name":"Book of the Bard","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This tawny leather tome serves as an ensemble piece collecting rich, compelling narratives; music sheets, poems, and other literary works for performers to find inspiration in. Amongst its contents can even be found several line-by-line scripts for short plays. To survive the depredations of being held open for protracted periods of time, as well as general wear and tear, its pages have been expertly bound into its spine.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Book of the Bard is the result of a compilation effort coauthored by a society of lyricists, bards, poets, skalds, minstrels, and storytellers who each contributed original poems and ballads toward its creation. However, a whimsical lot, the lyrics and instrumentals have been laced with hidden enchantments to heighten the resonance of performances that utilize it.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Rousing Recitals</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">In the hands of a gifted laureate or skald, the Book of the Bard is a powerful tool for entertaining audiences. As long as you are proficient in Performance, you can choose one of the following effects to occur when you read from the tome for at least 5 minutes and have it apply to non-hostile humanoids that can hear you and understand your words:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Listeners begin swaying to the beat, nodding along with your words, or dancing in time your the melody.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Listeners are easily amused by the your jokes or impressed by your limericks.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">To the listeners, you appear to become a master of replicating accents and affectations, and you're able to impersonate general mannerisms with ease.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Listeners are unable to heckle you, unless you invite disruptions.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If you attempt to describe a scene or present a narrative with your performance, listeners are able to conjure an extremely vivid picture of it in their mind&rsquo;s eye.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Any creature that doesn&rsquo;t want to be affected in the way described, can attempt a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw to end the effect on them.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Magic-laced Lyrics</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Book of the Bard contains more than mere words, much of its content laced with magical incantations. While reading from it for at least 5 minutes, you can choose to have non-hostile humanoids&nbsp;</span>within earshot that can understand you attempt a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw. On a fail, you can choose to affect such creatures in one of the following ways:</p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The audience feels rejuvenated and refreshed, temporarily shrugging off 1 level of exhaustion during your performance and for 1 hour after it concludes.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The audience feels heavy beneath the crushing weight of your words, temporarily gaining 1 level of exhaustion during your performance and for 1 hour after it concludes.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The audience members are drawn in by your words, suffering a -5 penalty to their passive Perception scores for the duration of your performance.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":13900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/book.png","effects":[],"_id":"avlWotwvQVbSIj5w"}
{"name":"Hatchet of the Hinterlands","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This magnificent example of dwarven craftsmanship is as exquisite as it is exceptional, and is truly a testament to the expertise and imagination of the artisans who created it. For, the dwarves responsible for its construction toil away in a guildhall deep beneath the earth<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>never to look upon the surface, let alone a tree or the kind of frigid hinterland where the object they've so diligently designed might be used.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Hatchet of the Hinterlands resembles any other hatchet in terms of form and function, except that it has been manufactured to the highest standards by dwarven smiths, and their own preferences have bled into its design. It is very angular, utilitarian, lightweight, formed of stone, and is both functional and fit-for-purpose. It is adorned in lettering in dwarven script</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><em>&mdash;</em></span><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">which lists the names of those who had a hand in its creation and their forebears<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>and also small symbols, runes, and other markings in the signature style of dwarves.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Plantbane. </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Hatchet of the Hinterlands is the bane of plant life and organic matter, wood especially. You have advantage on attack rolls made with it against creatures of the plant subtype.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Superior Craftsmanship</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Hatchet of the Hinterlands is the product of dwarven engineering, constructed using only the finest stone&mdash;with metal alloys injected into it through a technique known only to their artisans&mdash;and it shows. You </span>have advantage on Strength (athletics) checks made to fell trees, chop wood, or undertake similar tasks while using it, and you deal double damage to objects made of wood and timber. Additionally, you<span class=\"fontstyle0\"> can work for twice as long without gaining levels of exhaustion or being required to make Constitution saving throws to resist the onset of exhaustion and you make any such checks with advantage.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":7200000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"bC1CMaFtf5GY7tpc"}
{"name":"Hornswoggle","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"tool","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This small wooden gaming box has a sliding top that can be removed to reveal its contents. Its lid is felted on the inside so that it can be laid flat upon which its contents can be used. The box contains the components necessary to play several simple games&mdash;a shell game, one involving a set of dice, another involving a different set of dice and a dice cup, and a deck of playing cards&mdash;and rudimentary diagrams of each game being played adorn each side of the box itself. Meanwhile, the container's top features decorative carvings of geometric patterns on its outside, while its bottom is recessed with small ridges so that it can be used to store and organize chips, tokens, or coins if flipped upside down.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Originally created by a wealthy cheat who'd built a very successful career for herself as a professional gambler, Hornswoggle's original purpose wasn't quite as nefarious as one might assume given its origin. In truth, it was created so that businessmen and leaders of industry could practice their bluffing skills at its creator's Confidence Academy&mdash;though no doubt more than one aspiring con artist ponied up the exorbitant entry fee to also study under the best.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Games of Confidence</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Hornswoggle can be used to play several games, all of which are rigged to your benefit in the following ways:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Shell Game</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This game includes a set of 3 scallop shells with a small pearl. You can will the pearl to magically move between the shells, causing it to vanish from one and appear in another instantaneously. Observers can detect the trickery with a contested Wisdom (insight) check against your Charisma (deception or performance) check.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Bone Dice</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This game includes a&nbsp;set of 6 bone dice that are weighted. 3 of these return unusually low results, while the other 3 roll above average. You can always tell the dice apart, while another creature rolling them can only detect the off-balance weight of the dice with a DC 18 Wisdom (perception) check.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Dice Cup</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This game includes a dice cup with 4 obsidian dice in it. When the dice are placed into the cup, shaken, and poured out, you can telepathically determine their result before it's revealed.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Playing Cards</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This game includes a&nbsp;set of playing cards with depictions of noble men and women on their rear side. Though this deck appears ordinary to most creatures, you can see a mirror-image of each card's front transplanted onto its back, so that you can tell what cards your opponents are holding.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"ability":"dex","chatFlavor":"","proficient":0,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":16400000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/gaming-set.png","effects":[],"_id":"bsQwtQRNdCLSnBAO"}
{"_id":"btagDD0ju3cgVRLa","name":"Major Image (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You create the image of an object, a creature, or some other visible phenomenon that is no larger than a 20-foot cube. The image appears at a spot that you can see within range and lasts for the duration. It seems completely real, including sounds, smells, and temperature appropriate to the thing depicted. You can't create sufficient heat or cold to cause damage, a sound loud enough to deal thunder damage or deafen a creature, or a smell that might sicken a creature (like a <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#troglodyte_mm\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'bestiary.html', 'MM', 'troglodyte_mm', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >troglodyte's</a> stench).</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>As long as you are within range of the illusion, you can use your action to cause the image to move to any other spot within range. As the image changes location, you can alter its appearance so that its movements appear natural for the image. For example, if you create an image of a creature and move it, you can alter the image so that it appears to be walking. Similarly, you can cause the illusion to make different sounds at different times, even making it carry on a conversation, for example.</p><p>Physical interaction with the image reveals it to be an illusion, because things can pass through it. A creature that uses its action to examine the image can determine that it is an illusion with a successful Intelligence (<span class=\"help--hover\" onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseOver(event, this, 9, {})\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseMove(event, this)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseLeave(event, this)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Investigation</span>) check against your spell save DC. If a creature discerns the illusion for what it is, the creature can see through the image, and its other sensory qualities become faint to the creature.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"139\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the spell lasts until dispelled, without requiring your concentration.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cube"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"ill","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a bit of fleece","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":10000001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-major-image.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Lioc Epori","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb07/lioc-epori.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"231\" />\"Within this wicker basket resides a decorated wooden pungi and a coil of hempen rope. A lace of black canvas completes its lid and the same lace is looped around the set&rsquo;s pungi. With the rope and instrument packed away&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">neatly within the package, and its lid in place, the ensemble looks rather unimpressive. However, once the lid is removed and a creature begins to play the pungi, the purpose of the rope becomes clear.</span></em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Lioc Epori was created by an individual born into a long line of snake charmers. This man believed that his family&rsquo;s trade was a dying tradition and decided to branch out, adding a peculiar wrinkle to his own act. He went on to develop a street performance than utilized an inanimate object, a rope, in place of a reptile; weaving magic into a conventionally mundane art.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Musical Instrument. </strong>Lioc Empori can be used as a flute.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Adventuring Gear</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Lioc Epori can be used as a 50-foot hempen rope.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Animated Rope</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">What it lacks in subtlety, Lioc Epori more than makes up for in usefulness. As an action, you can play a melody on it to command its rope to perform a task. On subsequent turns, you can use your bonus action to have the rope continue its task if it could not be completed in a single action. Lioc Epori&rsquo;s rope can be commanded to perform any of the following actions:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Shoot upward to no more than its full length and attempt to tie itself onto a suitable anchor.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Adjust itself to grant advantage on Dexterity (acrobatics) checks to creatures attempting to balance on it, walk across it, or otherwise traverse it.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Attempt to grapple and restrain a Large or smaller creature as per the rules for Grappling. If it is directed to do so, it makes a grapple check with a +5 modifier against the result of the target&rsquo;s Strength (athletics) or Dexterity (acrobatics) check. If it prevails, the rope subjects the target to the <em>Grappled</em> condition.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Reform itself if it is split, sheered, or otherwise torn, as long as at least 5 foot of it is left intact.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tie up a willing or incapacitated creature or untie a creature it has bound. A creature bound by the rope has disadvantage on checks made to escape.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":12,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":"","autoDestroy":false},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"abil","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"str","dc":17,"scaling":"flat"},"consumableType":"trinket","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":17200000,"flags":{"mess":{"isBonusDamage":false,"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/instrument.png","effects":[],"_id":"c2rtiPm0PStoqkwR"}
{"name":"Maritime Marble","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb05/maritime-marble.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"254\" />\"Barely larger than a fingernail, the first clue that this tiny glass marble is magical in nature is the fact that the diminutive galleon preserved within it couldn't have been crafted by mortal hands due to its impossibly exquisite detailing. The marble itself is partly filled with water that sloshes around the ship and appears to form tiny waves and kick up oceanic spray if the object is disturbed or jostled at all. Interestingly, small pinpricks of light shine out from several points on the vessel and if the marble is&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">tilted in a way that causes the water to splash over the boat, these are extinguished momentarily, before flickering back into view a moment later. Even more impressively, if viewed through a magnifying lens or with preternatural eyesight, it seems like the ship's bilge pump actually functions, as the ship sinks lower and lower in the glass when it takes on water, before dumping this to regain its buoyancy.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Oceanic Intuition</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You gain the following insights into matters relating to the ocean while holding the Maritime Marble aloft and rolling it between your fingers:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You do not require navigator's tools to add your proficiency bonus to checks made to chart a ship's course, following or interpreting navigation charts, or to ability checks made to avoid getting lost at sea.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can detect the approximate depth between yourself and the ocean floor.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can sense the direction of, and approximate distance to, landmasses within 1,000 miles. This tells you nothing of the formation or configuration of such landmasses.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can detect the submerged Lairs of aquatic Legendary Creatures&mdash;both those found on the seabed or in underwater caves&mdash;up to a depth of 1 mile, and out to a radius of 5 miles.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can sense the development and movements of storm fronts within a day's travel of your current location.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">While on shore, you can always determine the direction of the nearest coastline.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":17400000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"cOymtO8VGXmJzKEC"}
{"name":"Ticktop","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb07/ticktop.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"233\" height=\"256\" />\"This wooden trunk is solidly constructed, formed of dark leather, and features a pair of latches and a key lock to keep it securely fastened when not in use. An elaborate circus grounds can be found just within the trunk, complete with miniscule props that have been scaled to allow fleas to perform various traditional circus acts. These props can be removed and folded down to allow only an inch between the flea circus and the lid when the trunk is closed. Meanwhile, when the trunk is open, the inside of its lid forms a carnival-themed backdrop. The panel that forms the circus grounds can be lifted to reveal a thriving vivarium, usually host to dozens of tiny performing fleas.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Flea Swarm (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Nestled deep within Ticktop is a ravenous horde of fleas, waiting to be loosed upon the world by their ringmaster. As an action, you can lift its circus area to reveal a concealed vivarium filled with fleas beneath it. If you choose to do so, you can will the fleas to multiply and flood out of the box for one minute before dispersing as part of this action or at any time that the lid is raised. For the duration, the fleas are your verbal, telepathic, and somatic command and will follow your directions. Ticktop refills with fleas each morning at dawn, at which time this feature can be activated again.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Swarm of Fleas.</strong><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-style: italic;\"> Statistical information necessary to use Ticktop in combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.oZfgMbsPkaTbZEYp]{Swarm of Fleas}.</span><br /></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Ticks&rsquo; Tricks</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">In addition to its concealed vivarium, Ticktop is also a fully functioning flea circus. Fleas placed within the circus area of the box when it is open follow any simple instructions given to them by you to the best of their ability. These directions can be provided verbally, telepathically, or through gestures. Ticktop innately has a number of basic props sized for fleas, such as a tiny chariot that can be pulled, a set of flaming hoops that can be jumped through, a mountain that can be climbed, and even a diminutive crossbow with a target. All fleas in Ticktop leave it when Flea Swarm is activated, however more fleas appear the next dawn.</span></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":8,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"items","value":1,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":19300000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/container.png","effects":[],"_id":"cQ7BnUKZ3hqvNdpt"}
{"name":"Salbjorn","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Visually, there doesn't appear to be anything noteworthy about this common-looking steel hauberk. However, this particular ringed byrnie possesses certain special properties that set it aside from any other boilerplate shirt of interlocking rings.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Originally owned by the brutal captain of a crew of savage coastal marauders, Salbjorn possesses a small measure of the man who once owned it. This notorious crew earned its reputation for the grisly path of destruction that they left in their wake and their captain was the most infamous of all&mdash;both for his cruelty and malice, and for his skill with axes.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Salbjorn can be used as a chain shirt.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Axe Master</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Salbjorn's former master was an expert with axes and a creature that wears it can feel a lingering sense of that expertise permeating them. While wearing the chain shirt and wielding a battleaxe, you gain the following perks:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The damage you deal with battleaxes is increased to 1D10; and 1D12 when wielded in both hands as per the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Versatile weapon </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">property.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can throw battleaxes as per the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Thrown weapon </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">property. You have a range of 10/20 when doing so.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When you throw a battleaxe, until the start of your next turn, any other creature attempting to lift it must attempt a DC 13 Strength (athletics) check to be able to do so.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Creatures armed with battleaxes have disadvantage on attack rolls against you.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":20,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":13,"type":"medium","dex":2},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":10700000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/medium-armor.png","effects":[],"_id":"cTOLs1oMUZdxX0Td"}
{"_id":"cmF1B2KtHtg40p4G","name":"Cloud of Daggers (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You fill the air with spinning daggers in a cube 5 feet on each side, centered on a point you choose within range. A creature takes [[/r 4d4]] slashing damage when it enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"121\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 2d4]] for each slot level above 2nd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":5,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cube"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["4d4","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a sliver of glass","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"2d4"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":7800001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-cloud-of-daggers.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"cn3if3JzUZkQLDDX","name":"Evard's Black Tentacles (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Squirming, ebony tentacles fill a 20-foot square on ground that you can see within range. For the duration, these tentacles turn the ground in the area into difficult terrain.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>When a creature enters the affected area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 3d6]] bludgeoning damage and be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#restrained_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'restrained_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >restrained</a> by the tentacles until the spell ends. A creature that starts its turn in the area and is already <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#restrained_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'restrained_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >restrained</a> by the tentacles takes [[/r 3d6]] bludgeoning damage.</p><p>A creature <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#restrained_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'restrained_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >restrained</a> by the tentacles can use its action to make a Strength or Dexterity check (its choice) against your spell save DC. On a success, it frees itself.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"square"},"range":{"value":90,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d6","bludgeoning"],["3d6","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a piece of tentacle from a giant octopus or a giant squid","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":10500001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-evards-black-tentacles.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"cp5YL8enKpN8WFQU","name":"Earthquake","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You create a seismic disturbance at a point on the ground that you can see within range. For the duration, an intense tremor rips through the ground in a 100-foot-radius circle centered on that point and shakes creatures and structures in contact with the ground in that area.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The ground in the area becomes difficult terrain. Each creature on the ground that is concentrating must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the creature's concentration is broken.</p><p>When you cast this spell and at the end of each turn you spend concentrating on it, each creature on the ground in the area must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is knocked <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#prone_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'prone_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >prone</a>.</p><p>This spell can have additional effects depending on the terrain in the area, as determined by the DM.</p><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"12\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Fissures.</span></span> <p>Fissures open throughout the spell's area at the start of your next turn after you cast the spell. A total of [[/r 1d6]] such fissures open in locations chosen by the DM. Each is [[/r 1d10 × 10]] feet deep, 10 feet wide, and extends from one edge of the spell's area to the opposite side. A creature standing on a spot where a fissure opens must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or fall in. A creature that successfully saves moves with the fissure's edge as it opens.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>A fissure that opens beneath a structure causes it to automatically collapse (see below).</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"13\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Structures.</span></span> <p>The tremor deals 50 bludgeoning damage to any structure in contact with the ground in the area when you cast the spell and at the start of each of your turns until the spell ends. If a structure drops to 0 hit points, it collapses and potentially damages nearby creatures. A creature within half the distance of a structure's height must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/r 5d6]] bludgeoning damage, is knocked <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#prone_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'prone_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >prone</a>, and is buried in the rubble, requiring a DC 20 Strength (Athletics) check as an action to escape. The DM can adjust the DC higher or lower, depending on the nature of the rubble. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage and doesn't fall <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#prone_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'prone_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >prone</a> or become buried.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":100,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":500,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d6","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":8,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a pinch of dirt, a piece of rock, and a lump of clay","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":1600001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/rock-orange-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Shadowplay","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb07/shadowplay.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"230\" />\"When closed, this purple canvas box with black fabric handle looks perfectly ordinary. However, a little pressure placed on its front facade reveals that it opens from the side, rather than the top. Once this panel has been laid flat, the rest of the box opens to reveal that it's a cleverly designed shadow puppet theater. Within the container can be found, a magical light source; housings, hooks, and sleeves that intern small, two-dimensional figurines; and five small rails into which these cutouts can be placed for the purposes of projecting a performance onto a suitable surface.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Lightbox</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Even when it's not being used to cast shadows or project silhouettes, Shadowplay's light source can be extremely useful. You can will its bulb to activate or deactivate as an action while holding, carrying, or within 5 feet of it. While the bulb is lit and there are no figurines placed in their slots, the object can be used as a hooded lantern.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Frightening Visages</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">An explosion of sudden, unexpected light and shadows can be startling&mdash;doubly so if they're in the guise of warriors or monsters. If you activate its bulb as per Lightbox while there are figurines placed in their slots, you can choose to make all hostile creatures within a 15 foot cone centered on you attempt a DC 8 Wisdom saving throw. On a fail, they're startled and have disadvantage on ability checks, attack rolls, and saving throws until the start of your next turn.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Puppet Shadows (1/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Though it might seem like little more than a instrument to entertain audiences or a toy designed to capture the attention of children, Shadowplay is a deadly weapon. If you holding, carrying, or within 5 feet of it and will it as an action, its bulb will suddenly flare brightly, as long as it is not activated already. This causes 1d4 Puppet Shadows to appear in the nearest unoccupied spaces to you. Puppet Shadows created in this way act on your turn in combat and follow your commands for 1 minute, before dispersing. Once this feature has been used, it cannot be used again until the next dawn.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px; font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Puppet Shadow.</strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-size: 13px; font-style: italic;\"> Statistical information necessary to use Puppet Shadows in combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.4eKEJ6jPkaVcwAZM]{Puppet Shadow}.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Shadow Performance</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Despite its other functions, Shadowplay is still a fully functional puppet theater. You can programme a script into it that uses its models and props and lasts no longer than 5 minutes. This takes one hour to do. It includes several dozen figurines and objects </span></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">which cover common themes, such as there being humanoids in various heroic, fawning, and indignant poses. Once a play has been scripted, you can press a button on the object and have it run through the necessary motions to bring it to life, though you must provide your own audio track.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":12900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/lantern.png","effects":[],"_id":"d6ZH3VR0PtjQSRLI"}
{"name":"Zanziver's Piece","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb02/zanzivers-piece.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"130\" /></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"The front face of this coin depicts a grinning goblin in profile, adorned in a kingly crown. Meanwhile, its rear facade showcases an overflowing tankard of ale. Both sides of the coin feature an identical dagger, though this is easy to overlook at a glance. Though it isn't clear where this rather unusual coin was minted or on whose authority, it does have several useful tricks up its sleeve that elevate its value beyond merely that of the weight of the gold used in its construction.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Odd Quirks</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">An unusual almanac, Zanziver's Piece has the following traits:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zanziver's Piece appears mundane at all times and a&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><em>Detect Magic</em>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">spell does not reveal it to be any way special or significant. Interestingly, this extends to include any future enchantments you place upon the object in addition to those already present.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zanziver's Piece is immune to natural heat and cannot be melted down by non-magical means.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If up place Zanziver's Piece into a tankard or glass that contains an alcoholic beverage, the drink lasts twice as long as it would otherwise, as if it has double the volume.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Unless interfered with, if you spin Zanziver's Piece on its side, it will continue to spin unaided for 1d10 minutes.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You have advantage on Dexterity checks made to roll Zanziver's Piece back and forth across your knuckles.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Trick Coin</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">While attuned to Zanziver's Coin you can use it to perform each of the following tricks:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zanziver's Piece can roll around freely while not being held. It has a 10 foot movement speed and can roll unaided within 60 foot. You can guided or steer it to avoid objects telepathically.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When Zanziver's Piece is flipped, you can mentally decide which way it will land, or have it land on its edge, while you are within 60 foot of it.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can will Zanziver's Piece to vanish from one location and reappear in another within 30 foot of you at will.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can will Zanziver's Piece to replicate itself up to five times while holding it. You can always tell the real coin from the fakes, but other creatures cannot. These duplicates are real for all intents and purposes, although they cease to exist after 1 hour. The number of fake coins in existence at any one time cannot exceed five.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Zanziver's Piece can be made to sink, float, or increase in weight by up to 5 times if you will it.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Each dawn, Zanziver's Piece reappears in your pocket regardless of the distance between you and it, so long as it is on the same plane of existence as you are and you're wearing clothing with pockets.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":18300000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"d9i8ILZcZLYwE9Yk"}
{"name":"Farshot","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb01/farshot.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"134\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This humble bycocket seems plain and unassuming, much like any other perfectly ordinary feathered cap in the style favoured by many archers and marksmen. However, it has enjoyed a rich and storied existence, owned by many famous<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>and a handful of infamous<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>individuals. Some of these were hunters, rangers, wildmen, and lovers of nature who despised people, civilization, and urban sprawls. </span></em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Others were more moderate. A few were instead bandits who preyed upon travelers and traders like verminous parasites on remote, isolated roadways far from the safety and protection of civilization.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Hard Hitting</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Farshot has been the prized possession of many an archer. While wearing the humble bycocket, your ranged attacks deal an additional 1 point of damage on a hit.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Twitch Reflexes</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Favored by archers and marksmen alike, those who wear Farshot are often noted for their swift reactions. When you are the target of a melee attack that misses while wearing it, you can make a ranged attack against the creature who attempted to strike you as a reaction. This attack is still made with disadvantage if it normally would be.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Keen Eye</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A veteran bowyer wearing Farshot will often land shots that others might deem impossible, this is no coincidence. While it doesn't modify the ranges of ranged weapons, you don't suffer disadvantage when making attacks at </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Long Range while wearing it and attuned to it</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":0.1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":4800000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/headgear.png","effects":[],"_id":"dAXk1vtcO4v4TTzy"}
{"_id":"dENimZjcbDHdJHuj","name":"Bless","permission":{"default":0,"gSvPH9u5wzkE1oU1":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You bless up to three creatures of your choice within range. Whenever a target makes an attack roll or a saving throw before the spell ends, the target can roll 1d4 and add the number rolled to the attack roll or saving throw.</p>\n<p><strong>Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 1st.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 219","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":3,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"1d4","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":1,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"A sprinkling of holy water","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":""},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":null,"sort":1400001,"flags":{"dynamiceffects":{"equipActive":true,"alwaysActive":false,"effects":[{"modSpecKey":"data.bonuses.abilities.save","value":"1d4","mode":"+","targetSpecific":false,"id":1,"itemId":"hYWYJJbVMe5U7GbQ","active":true,"_targets":[],"label":"Bonuses Abilities Save"},{"modSpecKey":"data.bonuses.All-Attacks","value":"1d4","mode":"+","targetSpecific":false,"id":2,"itemId":"hYWYJJbVMe5U7GbQ","active":true,"_targets":[]}]},"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""},"autoanimations":{"killAnim":false,"override":false,"animType":"t1","animName":"","hmAnim":"a1","color":"n1","dtvar":"dt1","explosion":false,"explodeVariant":"ev1","explodeColor":"ec1","explodeRadius":"0","explodeLoop":"1","selfRadius":"5","animTint":"#ffffff","auraOpacity":0.75,"ctaOption":false}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/haste-sky-1.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"lsEz6wG7eXIutwZI","flags":{"dae":{"transfer":false}},"changes":[{"key":"data.bonuses.abilities.save","value":"1d4","mode":2,"priority":20},{"key":"data.bonuses.All-Attacks","value":"1d4","mode":0,"priority":0}],"duration":{},"icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/haste-sky-1.jpg","label":"Bless","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"dFmPxBU5vtlEYmTi","name":"Jim's Glowing Coin","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Of the many tactics employed by master magician and renowned adventurer Jim Darkmagic, the old glowing coin trick is a time-honored classic. When you cast the spell, you hurl the coin that is the spell's material component to any spot within range. The coin lights up as if under the effect of a <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#light_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'light_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >light</a> spell. Each creature of your choice that you can see within 30 feet of the coin must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be distracted for the duration. While distracted, a creature has disadvantage on Wisdom (<span class=\"help--hover\" onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseOver(event, this, 29, false)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseMove(event, this)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseLeave(event, this)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Perception</span>) checks and initiative rolls.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"AI","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"enc","compo