{"_id":"dGGSdV9KGXW2x2Ac","name":"Gust of Wind (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A line of strong wind 60 feet long and 10 feet wide blasts from you in a direction you choose for the spell's duration. Each creature that starts its turn in the line must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be pushed 15 feet away from you in a direction following the line.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Any creature in the line must spend 2 feet of movement for every 1 foot it moves when moving closer to you.</p><p>The gust disperses gas or vapor, and it extinguishes candles, torches, and similar unprotected flames in the area. It causes protected flames, such as those of lanterns, to dance wildly and has a 50 percent chance to extinguish them.</p><p>As a bonus action on each of your turns before the spell ends, you can change the direction in which the line blasts from you.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":60,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"str","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a legume seed","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":5300001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-gust-of-wind.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Ouroboros Chakram","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb04/ourobos-chakram.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"154\" />\"This circular chakram is designed to resemble a snake eating its own tail, signifying the cyclical nature of life. The bulk of it is formed of jadeite, while the small circular blade that runs around its rim is a fine folded steel. The craftsmanship evident throughout this exotic piece is so extravagant that it makes it difficult to discern if its creator intended for it to be a practical, or purely ornamental, item. Either way, this exquisite chakram could justify its position in any soldier or warrior&rsquo;s armory just as easily as it might a collector&rsquo;s vault.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In truth, the Ouroboros Chakram was the chosen weapon of the high priest of a serpentine cult. What is most surprising about it is not just the expert craftsmanship that went into its creation, but rather that the object was forged by reptilian hands, deep in a dense jungle where knowledge of such metallurgic techniques are a rarity.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Ouroboros Chakram can be used as a chakram.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Rule Clarification, Chakram.</strong> Rules for chakrams can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Return To Sender</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Ouroboros Chakram has a curious habit of finding its way back to its thrower's hand. When you use it to make a ranged attack, it bounces from </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">various objects and surfaces before landing deftly back in your hand.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Razorsharp</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Ouroboros Chakram has an incredible knack for finding arteries, chinks in armor, or other soft and vulnerable spots. It deals an additional 1d6 slashing damage on a critical hit.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Bleed Effect</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The edge of the Ouroboros Chakram has been polished to be as thin, sharp, and deadly as any dagger. When it is used to make a ranged attack and that attack hits, roll a d4. The target takes 1 point of additional damage at the start of each of its turns for a number of rounds equal to the result of the d4. This effect doesn&rsquo;t stack and isn't refreshed or replenished until it expires.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":7100000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"dvxKQpH8LqsAs9VW"}
{"name":"Ravosashi","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This long pike stands out starkly against others of its kind due to the hundreds of small, sharp fang-like teeth that line its shaft, protruding with a pronounced air of menace. These are authentically formed from enamel and look like they're taken from kobolds and juvenile drakes or alligators, however they're not. The pearly white adornments are actually human teeth that have been whittled to resemble dragon teeth but at a fraction of their true size. Studying the polearm, it would seem that a creature would need to risk their grip in order to bring it to bare, however the razorsharp hazards retreat into the object respectfully as a potential wielder reaches for it.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Ravosashi has long been found amongst the crazy and </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">the reckless, those brave knights who consider themselves dragon hunters. It was first constructed by a famous knight called Ser Galldrum and used to slay the great red wyrm Ravosashi, a feat for which it earned it's namesake.\"</span></span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Ravosashi can be used as a pike.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Dragon Slayer's Blade</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Ravosashi is a blight upon dragon kind. Your attacks with it deal an additional 1d4 necrotic damage to draconic humanoids and creatures of the dragon type.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>By Human Hand</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Both those who forged Ravosashi and those who've fielded the polearm have been enemies of dragons. Its fangs are enchanted with a harmful effect that targets such creatures. Should any creature who is descended from dragons, whose blood has a strong draconic lineage, or who has the dragon type attempt to hold Ravosashi, they must attempt a DC 13 Constitution saving throw. They take 2d6 necrotic damage on a failed save. They must repeat the saving throw each round that they continue to hold the weapon.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><strong>Dragon Hunter</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As Ser Galldrum himself used to say, killing a dragon is easy, the real test is in finding one to slay. Should it come within five miles of a dragon that is an adult or older, Ravosashi's form changes to reflect the type of dragon it is in close proximity to. If the dragon is chromatic, its leather hilt changes to match their color; if the dragon is metallic, its blade changes to match the type of metal it is associated with. Its blade and hilt can both change simultaneously if there are both chromatic and metallic dragons within range. The polearm's features change to represent the type of the oldest and most powerful dragon (or dragons) within range. If there are multiple dragons of the same age and strength within range, the blade instead changes to mimic the type of the nearest dragon. While Ravosashi's blade is formed of silver, it functions as a silvered weapon.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":18,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d10 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":true,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":true,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":1200000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"eDU84noYiBxk0oEy"}
{"_id":"eGeZEIOpweptcc5A","name":"Half Plate Armor","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Half plate consists of shaped metal plates that cover most of the wearer's body. It does not include leg protection beyond simple greaves that are attached with leather straps.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 145","quantity":1,"weight":40,"price":750,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Common","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":15,"type":"medium","dex":2},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":true,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":null,"sort":100001,"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","equipped":false,"attuned":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","sorting":"l"},"betterRolls5e":{"critRange":{"value":null}},"autoanimations":{"killAnim":false,"override":false,"animType":"t1","animName":"","hmAnim":"a1","color":"n1","dtvar":"dt1","explosion":false,"explodeVariant":"ev1","explodeColor":"ec1","explodeRadius":"0","explodeLoop":"1","selfRadius":"5","animTint":"#ffffff","auraOpacity":0.75,"ctaOption":false}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/items/armor/halfplate.png","effects":[]}
{"name":"Tomoro","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb03/tomoro.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"116\" height=\"256\" />\"To most, this lightweight and flexible suit of armor merely has a faintly exotic look to it. However, those who recognize its signature style, and know a little about the kind of soldier who might wear it, are likely filled with a morbid dread at its mere visage. For this armor belongs to the Forsaken, an order of highly-disciplined warriors resigned to dying on the battlefield, and determined to make such a death glorious and bloody. Warriors belonging to this order are known to wield swords and charge into combat with a reckless abandon bordering on zealotry. They often wrap their body in tourniquets before entering battle to prevent blood loss and delay succumbing to their wounds until they've wounded, maimed, and killed as many as possible.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Tomoro belonged to a Forsaken warrior of great repute. It is said that he took more than a dozen men to the grave with him when he finally fell</span></em><em>&mdash;</em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">each a champion in their own right. This individual believed arrogance, hubris, and, most of all, unpreparedness to be cardinal sins. He was known to believe that even Gods could be slain, if you could only catch them off-guard.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Tomoro can be used as lamellar armor.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Lamellar.</strong> Rules for lamellar armor can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Master of Blades</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Tomoro retains the spirit of its former master, at least insofar as its preference for slashing weapons. While wearing this armor, you cannot apply your proficiency bonus to attacks made with melee weapons that do not deal slashing damage.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Guerilla Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Tomoro was once favoured by a deadly assassin, and for good reason. You gain a 1d4 bonus to your Dexterity (stealth) checks while wearing it.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Surprise Strike</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A combatant already adept at turning the element of surprise to their advantage can rise to new heights while wearing this comfortable and flexible armor. The first time you hit with a melee attack while wearing it during a surprise round, you deal an additional 1d6 damage.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":30,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":14,"type":"medium","dex":2},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":12600000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/heavy-armor.png","effects":[],"_id":"eS2u4ZksEsJTG6SK"}
{"name":"Crimepiece","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb02/crimepiece.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"176\" height=\"256\" />\"At first glance, this stylish brass and mother-of-pearl timepiece resembles any common, everyday pocket watch; well-manufactured and a little on the showy side, but otherwise mundane. However, a closer inspection, even a cursory one, quickly reveals it to be noteworthy compared to other such benign and innocuous objects. Most significantly, the watches' face doesn't display numeric symbols or depict markings that can be used as a point of reference to denote the passage of time. Instead, its clock face is littered with a confusing and muddled </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">menagerie of strange symbols and sigils, which are worked together into a dizzying, headache-inducing pattern. The object does have three hands, in the form of swords and daggers, but deciphering what these are attempting to track or convey is simply beyond most people. In truth, this clock is used to track down those who might be sympathetic to an individual at odds with the law, and to provide warning should lawmen approach.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Roguish Requirements</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Crimepiece's creator was no friend to those who use power to oppress. In order to study it or set its alarm function you must be able to speak thieves' cant. Additionally, in order for it to operate, Crimepiece must be wound at least once a month. Winding it requires thieves' tools.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Felon's Friend.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Those who understand how to interpret Crimepiece's bizarre symbols and hands can use it to steer themselves towards friends and opportunities, and away from danger. While in an urban environment, you can study the watch to gain advantage on checks made to...</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">...locate or avoid lawmen or areas with a strong law enforcement presence.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">...find the location of a fence or black market vendor.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">...identify the presence of local gangs and criminal syndicates.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">...avoid 'bad neighborhoods' and less safe areas of a town or city.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Tick-tock Alarm Clock</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Crimepiece can be used to set useful reminders, or as an equally handy tool for distracting others. By compressing, rotating, and then releasing its crown, you can configure the timepiece to sound a shrill alarm that can be heard out to a distance of 30 foot after a certain amount of time has elapsed. The time that can be set ranges anywhere from 1 second, up to 11 hours, 59 minutes, and 59 seconds.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":5500000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"eb5x3K914fXKCQwo"}
{"_id":"edhK5BDpqm0iLIiE","name":"Foresight","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You touch a willing creature and bestow a limited ability to see into the immediate future. For the duration, the target can't be surprised and has advantage on attack rolls, ability checks, and saving throws. Additionally, other creatures have disadvantage on attack rolls against the target for the duration.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>This spell immediately ends if you cast it again before its duration ends.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":8,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":""},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":9,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a hummingbird feather","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":700001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/evil-eye-eerie-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"f1wNmGYKEJHUogFr","name":"Detect Magic","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>For the duration, you sense the presence of magic within 30 feet of you. If you sense magic in this way, you can use your action to see a faint aura around any visible creature or object in the area that bears magic, and you learn its school of magic, if any.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The spell can penetrate most barriers, but it is blocked by 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood or dirt.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":true,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":12700001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-detect-magic.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"yQgHXu8TbepVeLGz","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" 