{"name":"Ringmaster's Whip","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This dark leather whip has layered black and white ribbon wrapped tightly around its handle, giving an otherwise mundane whip in the style of those typically used by a circus ringmaster or lion tamer a slightly unusual appearance.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Ringmaster's Whip was owned by a notorious ringmaster called Thomas Fawlkner, who was renowned for his ability to command the respect and attention of his audience. Unlikely many circuses, which would focus their appeal on a particular socioeconomic crowd or demographic, his saw prince mix with pauper&mdash;both sharing the same bleachers in order to witness the spectacle of his show.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Ringmaster's Whip can be used as a whip.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Thunderous</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Ringmaster's Whip is deafeningly loud. Your attacks with it deal 1 additional thunder damage.</span></span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Echoing</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Used to silence rowdy crowds, the Ringmaster's Whip is capable of producing unnaturally loud noises. When you strike the whip against the ground or a hard surface, it produces a resonating cracking sound that is audible out to a distance of 300 feet.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Deafening Boom (1/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A creature in possession of the Ringmaster's Whip can utilize its powers to sow confusion amongst their enemies. As an action, you can crack the whip against the ground or a hard surface with exceptional force. If you do so, all hostile creatures within 60 foot who can hear must attempt a DC 13 Constitution saving throw, becoming deafened for 1 minute on a fail. Creatures with </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Keen Hearing </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">have disadvantage on their check</span>.<br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","slashing"],["1","thunder"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":true,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":12400000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"f3958XYe8dVFAbOP"}
{"name":"Censer of Dragons' Wrath","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb04/censer-of-dragons-wrath.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"146\" height=\"256\" />\"This golden incense burner has the likenesses of three dragons worked into its design, revealing much about the object's draconic origins. It hangs from several chains like a thurible and, also tellingly, is able to burn gold and precious stones in place of incense. It has been designed so that the smoke that the censer produces billows out of the three dragons' maws and nostrils.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">From the adoration of simple kobolds to the more sinister proclivities of certain occult groups, the Censer of Dragons' Wrath has played a role in many factions that have been sycophantically aligned with dragons and draconic overlords. What is prevalent throughout each instance of this occurring is that the object has allowed the members of these organizations to feel a certain closeness and kinship with dragons&ndash;some even claiming that they've been contacted by mighty dragons through the object itself.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Spellcasting Focus</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Censer of Dragons' Wrath can be used as a holy symbol.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Dragons' Ire (1/Day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The wielder of the Censer of Dragons' Wrath can direct visages of gold dragons to form within its cloud of smoke and have them hinder their foes. While the censer is lit, you can choose a target within 30 foot and will the guise of a dragon to appear and make a breath attack against it. A creature targeted in this way must attempt a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw, suffering a -2 penalty on Strength ability checks and saving throws for 1 minute on a failed save.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Dragons' Divinity</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Neither the Censer of Dragons' Wrath or the smoke that billows forth from it should be overlooked, nor dismissed as mundane. The censer possesses the following unusual characteristics:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Instead of requiring incense to burn, the censer can also be lit with a gold coin or similar sized piece of gold. The gold is consumed immediately upon the censer being lit and burns for 2 hours unless it is extinguished prematurely.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When the censer is lit, it masks unpleasant smells. Any creature needing to make saving throws to resist the effects of foul odors does so with advantage while within 20 foot of the censer. However, they also have disadvantage on Wisdom (perception) checks made to notice strong and offensive smells, such as the stench of rot and decay.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">While the censer is lit, creatures within 20 foot of it can understand draconic and converse telepathically with gold dragons in place of speaking aloud. This does not grant creatures who cannot speak draconic the ability to read it or speak it aloud.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">While the censer is lit, gems, pearls, and other precious or semi-precious stones sparkle and gleam while within 30 foot of it. Consequently, creatures have advantage on Wisdom (perception) checks made to notice them.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If the censer is lit with a jewel, gemstone, or a similar precious stone valued at 100 GP or higher, it burns for 8 hours, emitting a golden smoke. If there is a gold dragon within 4 miles of the location of the censer, anyone within 20 foot of it who goes to sleep while the censer continues to burn becomes aware of the dragon and can attempt to speak to it telepathically through their dreams. They do not become aware of the dragon's location or any other details about it besides those it willingly provides through conversation. Additionally, the dragon is under no compulsion to interact with them and may decline to do so.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":14200000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"fDT7XmJZVaYMp8qS"}
{"_id":"fKef7GaD3sLRcKbY","name":"Enhance Ability","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You touch a creature and bestow upon it a magical enhancement. Choose one of the following effects; the target gains that effect until the spell ends.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"10\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Bear's Endurance.</span></span> <p>The target has advantage on Constitution checks. It also gains [[/r 2d6]] temporary hit points, which are lost when the spell ends.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"11\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Bull's Strength.</span></span> <p>The target has advantage on Strength checks, and his or her carrying capacity doubles.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"12\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Cat's Grace.</span></span> <p>The target has advantage on Dexterity checks. It also doesn't take damage from falling 20 feet or less if it isn't <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#incapacitated_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'incapacitated_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >incapacitated</a>.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"13\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Eagle's Splendor.</span></span> <p>The target has advantage on Charisma checks.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"14\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Fox's Cunning.</span></span> <p>The target has advantage on Intelligence checks.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"15\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Owl's Wisdom.</span></span> <p>The target has advantage on Wisdom checks.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"16\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 2nd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6","temphp"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"2d6","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"fur or a feather from a beast","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":13400001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-enhance-ability.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"5SSl0eQIE9pokJXt","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-enhance-ability.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Tsukodaiko","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb09/tsukodaiko.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"123\" height=\"256\" />\"Known as a den-den daiko, this small child&rsquo;s toy takes the form of a wooden paddle fashioned after a simple drum with two small pellets on strings that twirl and bash against it as its handle is rotated. This particular den-den daiko is several hundred years old and over that time has become inhabited by a powerful spirit which has transformed the toy into a sentient being, albeit an unconventional one. A tusked face with monstrous features has grown from the head of the den-den daiko, with a pair of tiny armless hands emerging from its sides to hold its cheeks&ndash;while the toy&rsquo;s handle has grown a two-toed foot that wears a sandal.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tsukodaiko&rsquo;s sentience occurred in the wake of a tragedy. Its last owner was a young boy who was kidnapped by a cruel oni who snuck into his room at night and snatched him away. The boy was never found, and the drum was left all alone until its transformation into a tsukogami. The Tsukodaiko has never forgotten the kidnapping of its former owner, and the fervent animosity it holds for the yōkai responsible persists to this day.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Sentience</strong>. Once you attune to it,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tsukodaiko animates and becomes a sentient chaotic good wondrous item with an Intelligence of 10, a Wisdom of 11, and a Charisma of 15. It has hearing and darkvision out to a range of 120 feet. It can also awkwardly hop unaided, granting it a movement speed of 5 ft. Tsukodaiko can understand Common but can only communicate through percussive noises and by pulling faces.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Tsukodaiko.</strong><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-style: italic;\">&nbsp;Statistical information necessary to use Tsukodaiko in combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.4FKSY2Zu8PbVTbBf]{Tsukodaiko}.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Oni Bane</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Just as Tsukodaiko hates oni, so too do oni revile and despise it. Whenever an oni hears you playing it, including if the den-den daiko is playing itself, the oni cannot shapechange and must remain in its true form. If an oni that is already shapechanged hears the drum, it reverts to its true form.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Din</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tsukodaiko is no friend to bullies. Anytime a creature within 30 foot of it attempts a Charisma (intimidation) check. The den-den daiko starts to play and makes a din, imposing disadvantage on the check.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Sucker Punch</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Anyone can feel confident standing up for themselves while in possession of Tsukodaiko, even when faced with a far bigger rival. While it is about your person, you have advantage on your first attack roll against a creature at least one size larger than you during the first round of combat.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":18200000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"fXC5nlqQUVnpYqeo"}
{"name":"Clemency","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"The blade of this large, two-handed Zweih&auml;nder is made of bright polished steel and has a blunted groove just above its guard that allows for its edge to be safely nestled against its bearer's shoulder. Supple black leather covers the sword's grip which has softened through years of use.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Clemency was commissioned by a spirit medium who feared for the immortal souls of the deceased after a brush with the darker side of death. He came to interact with a troubled spirit during a botched s&eacute;ance and the encounter turned violent. In addition to a desire to safeguard those already lost to death's cold embrace, he also developed a healthy disdain for those naive enough to entreat such evils. The medium spent the remaining years of his life dedicated to the exorcism of ghosts and wraiths; and the execution of cultists, necromancers, and apostates&ndash;in the hopes that he could spare them an eternity of torment. It was with this same blade, Clemency, that he ended his own life on the night of his 60th birthday, leaving the sword to whomsoever would pick up the mantle and continue his work.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Clemency can be used as a greatsword.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Sanctity</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Clemency is a powerful tool in the fight against the cold, reaching grasp of the grave. You gain the following benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Humanoids you slay with Clemency do not return as incorporeal undead, and their physical remains cannot be reanimated through necromancy.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Attacks you make with Clemency against undead creatures that are incorporeal bypass resistances and immunities to nonmagical weapons.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Clemency provides you with advantage on checks made to resist being possessed while you are within 5 foot of it; and creatures attempting to do so have disadvantage on their own checks.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While you are within 5 foot of it, Clemency prevents incorporeal undead creatures from moving through you.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Clemency provides you with advantage on saving throws related to resisting the adverse affects of Life Drain, Age Drain, and Withering Touch while you are within 5 foot of it.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Forlorn Elegy</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature who chooses to wield Clemency may have cause to feel the weight of their actions more keenly than most. Between the hours of 3 and 4 am each night, you see the spectral apparitions of every sentient creature that you've slain with the blade appear around you. These impassive observers do not speak or interact with you in any way, nor do they block your line of sight. Instead they just solemnly observe you for one hour, before fading away into nothingness once more.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":true,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":3600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"fbvoULAlfefPoEOb"}
{"_id":"fkLnNiiAaiO8f4cF","name":"Summon Fiend","permission":{"default":-1,"bOqyKS8LL2EWqEnK":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You call forth a fiendish spirit. It manifests in an unoccupied space that you can see within range. This corporeal form uses the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#fiendish%20spirit_tce\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'bestiary.html', 'TCE', 'fiendish%20spirit_tce', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Fiendish Spirit</a> stat block. When you cast the spell, choose Demon, Devil, or Yugoloth. The creature resembles a fiend of the chosen type, which determines certain traits in its stat block. The creature disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The creature is an ally to you and your companions. In combat, the creature shares your initiative count, but it takes its turn immediately after yours. It obeys your verbal commands (no action required by you). If you don't issue any, it takes the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#dodge_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'dodge_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Dodge</a> action and uses its move to avoid danger.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"2470\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 7th level or higher, use the higher level wherever the spell's level appears in the stat block.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"TCE","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":90,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":6,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"humanoid blood inside a ruby vial worth at least 600 gp","consumed":false,"cost":600,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":null,"sort":1000001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[{"_id":"jqnPGjt5hnUY1CXx","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"transfer":true}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Concentration","origin":"Item.fkLnNiiAaiO8f4cF","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"name":"Blade of the High Keep","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb03/blade-of-the-high-keep.png\" alt=\"\" />\"Both impressive and imposing, this grand longsword serves as a fine example of heraldic design sensibilities incorporated into a weapon. However, rather than an ornamental or ceremonial piece, this armament is functional and deadly; fully intended to see use in the theatre of combat. The blade has several unusual features worked into its design, indicative of nobility or regality. These include a cruciform opening in its guard that's reminiscent of a heaume or the kind of great helm a knight or holy crusader might wear; and mock crenellations, formed of a series of embrasures and merlons, worked into its guard and pommel that resemble a keep's battlements. The Blade of the High Keep was the honorary blade of a castellan, originally awarded to a brave and determined soul who held his motte-and-bailey for weeks against a force that possessed superior numbers, mages and magical wards, and siege weapons. Through good fortune, unorthodox tactics, and sheer force of will, the castellan&ndash; and a handful of his finest&ndash;endured until reinforcements could arrive, and rout the enemy once and for all.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Blade of the High Keep can be used as a longsword.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Entrenched</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A creature wielding the Blade of the High Keep feels inspired to stand their ground, even in the face of overwhelming odds. If you don't move on your turn while wielding it, you gain a +1 bonus to your AC until the start of your next turn.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Defiant</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">It's possible to draw strength and determination from the Blade of the High Keep just from its reassuring presence. You gain a +1 bonus on morale checks and savings throws related to being feared or charmed while holding it or when it is about your person.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Last Stand</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Blade of the High Keep is most at home gripped tightly in the hand of a stalwart defender as they fight to protect their stronghold to the bitter end. If you spend 72-hours or more in a single defensible location&mdash;such as a dungeon complex; monster's lair, cave, or cavern; keep, watchtower, castle, or fortress; or similar&mdash;, you gain several benefits while you remain within the confines of this location. These benefits end after you spend at least 24-hours elsewhere:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You're able to survive on half as much food and water as normal.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You're able to survive on half as much sleep as normal (the duration of long and short rests remains unchanged).</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You're able to roll twice when spending hit dice to regain hit points during a short rest and take the higher result.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":"1d10 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":2600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"frNKEZE5QUadgTZh"}
{"_id":"fzt33JjIYnkBI5RH","name":"Counterspell (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You attempt to interrupt a creature in the process of casting a spell. If the creature is casting a spell of 3rd level or lower, its spell fails and has no effect. If it is casting a spell of 4th level or higher, make an ability check using your spellcasting ability. The DC equals 10 + the spell's level. On a success, the creature's spell fails and has no effect.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"97\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the interrupted spell has no effect if its level is less than or equal to the level of the spell slot you used.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"which you take when you see a creature within 60 feet of you casting a spell"},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":false,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":4400001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-counterspell.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Bokar's Sticker","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb03/bokars-sticker.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"106\" /></span></em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This deadly bayonet, used to impale the unsuspecting and skewer the unwary, has an unusually ornate appearance for an instrument of death. This is thanks to the exquisite and elaborate filigree used to form its mount. An off-white color, this leafy latticework not only serves to affix the object to a crossbow, but also serves as a handle when it isn't attached to a larger implement. Meanwhile, although less striking, the bayonet's business end is much more threatening. Rather than take the form of a simple blade, its shape is that of a triangular wedge, rapidly thinning before ending in a razor-sharp point. It is said that the owner of Bokar's Sticker&ndash;presumably Bokar himself&ndash;slew over a hundred orcs with his signature bayonet at the siege of Aysel, the reckless creatures </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">hastily rushing in before realizing that his crossbow had been modified for use in hand-to-hand combat. Ultimately, however, the marauding orcs proved triumphant that day, and Bokar fell during the battle. What happened to his crossbow, and the bayonet that was attached to it, after that is anyone's guess.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Bokar's Sticker can be used as a bayonet.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Bayonet.</strong> Rules for bayonets can be found in </span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">@Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Potent Piercer</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Razorsharp and deadly, those foolish enough to let strikes from this triangular wedge slip through their defences quickly come to regret it. Your melee weapon attacks with Bokar's Sticker deal +1 damage.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Sudden Jab</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It's easy to overlook this perilous weapon modification in the face of seeing a crossbow raised with intent, especially if one is recoiling in pain. You can make a single melee attack with Bokar's Sticker as a bonus action each of your turns if it's affixed to a crossbow you're wielding. Additionally, if you have already hit the target with a bolt during this round, you make the melee attack with advantage.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod +1","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":true,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":3000000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"g4HAgpOAfYDpRuHu"}
{"_id":"g4MfUu6VPIFUFfvP","name":"Concentration Check - Midi QOL","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"special","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":10,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"mgc":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"sil":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false,"nodam":false,"fulldam":false,"halfdam":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"sort":23700000,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":"ItemMacro","isConcentrationCheck":true},"itemacro":{"macro":{"_data":{"name":"Concentration Check - Midi QOL","type":"script","scope":"global","command":"for (let targetData of args[0].targets) {\n let target = canvas.tokens.get(targetData._id);\n if (MidiQOL.configSettings().removeConcentration && (target.actor.data.data.attributes.hp.value === 0 || args[0].failedSaves.find(tData => tData._id === target.id)))\ngame.cub.removeCondition(game.settings.get(\"combat-utility-belt\", \"concentratorConditionName\"), target,  {warn: false});\n}","author":"devnIbfBHb74U9Zv"},"data":{"name":"Concentration Check - Midi QOL","type":"script","scope":"global","command":"for (let targetData of args[0].targets) {\n let target = canvas.tokens.get(targetData._id);\n if (MidiQOL.configSettings().removeConcentration && (target.actor.data.data.attributes.hp.value === 0 || args[0].failedSaves.find(tData => tData._id === target.id)))\ngame.cub.removeCondition(game.settings.get(\"combat-utility-belt\", \"concentratorConditionName\"), target,  {warn: false});\n}","author":"devnIbfBHb74U9Zv"},"options":{},"apps":{},"compendium":null}},"exportSource":{"world":"testWorld","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"0.7.9","systemVersion":"1.2.4"},"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"}},"img":"modules/combat-utility-belt/icons/concentrating.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Arcanus Compendum","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This aging tome is every bit as impressive as it is worn, and clearly magical. Its gilt edged inside pages seem brittle and crisp, and are noticeably foxed, however life remains in them yet. The book's exterior is formed of a dark green, stained leather with a large circular seal running across its front, rear, and spine. Eight smaller circles are arranged at various points around the larger seal, each containing a rune that denotes a specific school of magic. The entire emblem emits a soft, diffused purple glow that lights up the tome unless it is stowed at the very bottom of a deep satchel or pack. Interestingly, the book feels as if it weighs double what it should, and causes a loud thud if dropped from almost any height.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Spellbook</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Arcanus Compendum can be used as a spellbook.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Master Preparation</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A creature who studies Arcanus Compendum at length gleans many insights from it. When preparing spells as part of a long rest, you can choose one to prepare one additional cantrip from your spell list that you wouldn't normally be able to prepare. You can make use of this cantrip until you swap the cantrip out for another or end your attunement to Arcanus Compendum.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Spell Recording</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Copying a spell into Arcanus Compendum requires less time and costs less than usual. Each spell copied into it is calculated as if it were two levels lower for the purposes of calculating time and gold. Though, you still cannot copy a spell of a higher level than you are able to cast into the spellbook.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Summoned Spells</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A wizard with Arcanus Compendum has little fear of losing their magical research. Should it ever be destroyed, it reappears beside you after 4d12 + 12 hours.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":14700000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/book.png","effects":[],"_id":"gKu8IJFempLowlJ6"}
{"name":"Battle Aspergillum","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Long used in rituals undertaken by priests to bless the righteous, redeem the repentant, and purify the unhallowed; aspergillums are maces that have long, thin handles with spherical heads. The head of an aspergillum has numerous small holes which are used to release a reservoir of liquid interned within the implement when it is swung or shaken. Unlike its contemporaries, this particular aspergillum is larger, weightier, and better balanced, designed for use more in combat than ceremonies.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Though aspergillums are traditionally filled with holy water in order to best combat most supernatural undead or fiendish threats, the Battle Aspergillum is able to store any type of liquid&mdash;though some deities may frown on its use as a pseudo hip flask. A golden crown tops the head of this priestly mace with words written in celestial inscribed on it. This brief passage reads; 'Deliverance unto the repentant, damnation take the shameless.'\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Battle Aspergillum can be used as a mace.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Swing Spray</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Battle Aspergillum can deliver much more than a mere blow when swung. Its head can be </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">used to hold 1 pint of any liquid, equivalent to a flask. It requires a bonus action to fill it and you need to have both hands free in order to do so. You can will the Battle Aspergillum to discharge the liquid interned within it when you swing it in one of the following ways:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can douse a close-quarters combatant as part of making a melee attack against a hostile creature within reach. To do so, you must declare your intention to discharge the object's contents before making your attack roll. If the attack hits, the target takes damage as normal and the contents of the Battle Aspergillum also douses the target; causing its effect, if any, to be applied. If the attack misses, the liquid is wasted.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can douse a non-hostile target or a creature at a greater distance by swinging the weapon in thin air in the direction of your target as an action. The object's contents sprays outward in a 5-foot-wide, 15-foot-long line that ends when its path is interrupted by a Small or larger creature. The target must make a Dexterity saving throw with a DC of 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Strength modifier in order to dodge out of the way in time. On a success, they avoid the </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Battle Aspergillum's discharge. On a fail, they're caught in the spray and its contents take effect. A creature can choose to fail this save voluntarily.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":2400000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"gOxo6KMyfvRAUGtB"}
{"_id":"ga4ZTgW15mPqraNs","name":"Acid Splash (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You hurl a bubble of acid. Choose one creature you can see within range, or choose two creatures you can see within range that are within 5 feet of each other. A target must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 1d6]] acid damage.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>This spell's damage increases by [[/r 1d6]] when you reach 5th level ([[/r 2d6]]), 11th level ([[/r 3d6]]), and 17th level ([[/r 4d6]]).</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6","acid"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"cantrip","formula":"1d6"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":4700001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-acid-splash.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"geoea79qPtJ9g7P6","name":"Forbiddance (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You create a ward against magical travel that protects up to 40,000 square feet of floor space to a height of 30 feet above the floor. For the duration, creatures can't teleport into the area or use portals, such as those created by the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#gate_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'gate_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >gate</a> spell, to enter the area. The spell proofs the area against planar travel, and therefore prevents creatures from accessing the area by way of the Astral Plane, Ethereal Plane, Feywild, Shadowfell, or the plane shift spell.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>In addition, the spell damages types of creatures that you choose when you cast it. Choose one or more of the following: celestials, elementals, fey, fiends, and undead. When a chosen creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature takes [[/r 5d10]] radiant or necrotic damage (your choice when you cast this spell).</p><p>When you cast this spell, you can designate a password. A creature that speaks the password as it enters the area takes no damage from the spell.</p><p>The spell's area can't overlap with the area of another forbiddance spell. If you cast forbiddance every day for 30 days in the same location, the spell lasts until it is dispelled, and the material components are consumed on the last casting.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":10,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"day"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":""},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d10","radiant"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":6,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":true,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a sprinkling of holy water, rare incense, and powdered ruby worth at least 1,000 gp","consumed":false,"cost":1000,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":10600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-forbiddance.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Gaiden","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This six-pronged throwing star is formed of a high-grade metal that has few impurities and has been folded and sharpened until deadly. Its spokes have been affixed to a revolving bracket that is both connected to and separate from the shuriken's main body, so that its protrusions can swivel and spin independently of it. Careful consideration has been given to the object's aerodynamics during its construction, specifically with regards how air passes through its spokes. As a result, the floating plate and its spokes actually rotate counter-intuitively when thrown, spinning against the centrifugal forces placed upon them. Though novel when viewed in flight, neophytes usually need some time to grow acquainted with the unusual tool and its unique configuration.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Gaiden has long served assassins. Traditionally, it has passed from master to student upon their retirement<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>sometimes by way of bloodshed, as an apprentice has usurped and surpassed their now-former teacher. Before his untimely death, it was the proclamation of the first assassin to use Gaiden that, at the end of all things, the throwing star would return to his hand<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>each of its other master's merely temporary distractions in its, and by extension his, tale.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Gaiden can be used as a shuriken.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong style=\"font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification: Shuriken.</strong><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"> Rules for shurikens can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Assassin's Tool</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Gaiden is as useful a tool to a master assassin as it is a young apprentice. If you use it to make a ranged attack while hidden and miss, you are not automatically seen.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Poison-Pronged</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">There's more than one way to take a life. The DC to resist any poison applied to Gaiden is increased by 1.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Returning Star</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Most assassins know better than to leave their greatest assets behind. If you use Gaiden to make a ranged attack and don't retrieve it, it flies back to you 12 hours later at a rate of 600 feet per minute. Once within 5 foot of you, the shuriken buries itself into a wooden object or lands on the ground beside you. Gaiden doesn't return to you once thrown if it's unable to do so. For example, if pinned down, held, its path is blocked by a locked door, or it is caught in an antimagic field.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":0.25,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","piercing"],["1d4 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialR","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":4300000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-ranged-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"gkg3OQYtoV3cjRur"}
{"name":"Jötynnbaen","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb03/jotynnbaen.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"134\" height=\"256\" />\"Formed of dark rock that has been decorated with yellow paint in places and debossed to resemble brickwork elsewhere, this imposing stone maul has a pronounced air of menace about it. This is due in large part to its size and weight, although the fact that its face is covered in dozens of small spiked protrusions only serves to heighten its ferocious appearance, giving it more than a passing resemblance to a meat tenderizer. However, it is neither the fact that the object is a large maul nor its painful prongs that contribute most to its harrowing guise. That honor is reserved for the detailed, three-dimensional depiction of a troll that has been carved carefully into the maul's cheek. At times, this dour, scowling presence feels almost alive, as if seething with anger. This is most common as daylight starts to fail around dusk, causing the troll's features to cast a terrifying shadow as its silhouette stretches out and becomes monstrously long and deformed. The maul itself appears to be in a bad state of disrepair; its rock cracked and crumbling in places, paint fading, details weathered, and most of its surface buried under a thick layer of moss. However, as anyone who's wielded the item can attest, it still has life in it yet, and a thirst for troll blood.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">J&ouml;tynnbaen was the pride and joy of a deranged, near-crazy dwarf lord who made it his life's work to hunt down every troll in the world and kill them<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>a lofty, if a little unrealistic, goal. However, unlike others of his kind, who were content to simply denounce, oppose, and slay trolls, J&ouml;tynnbaen's former master was fascinated by them and their supernatural healing abilities. He eventually became </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">utterly convinced that the secret to immortality lay in the consumption of their foul flesh. Even despite his dwarven constitution, he ended up contracting a wasting disease from eating tainted meat and died of consumption some months later.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">J&ouml;tynnbaen can be used as a maul.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Trollbeater</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">J&ouml;tynnbaen was forged for a singular purpose, to bring about the end of all trolls. For this reason, it has the following traits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your attacks with J&ouml;tynnbaen have a +1 bonus to hit creatures of the giant subtype.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If a creature of the giant subtype has a Regeneration trait and you deal it damage with J&ouml;tynnbaen, the amount of hit points it regenerates at the start of its next turn is reduced by the amount of damage it was dealt, to a minimum of 0.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While wielding it or it is about your person, you have advantage on </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">ability checks made to intimidate trolls.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Mossy</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">For some bizarre reason, moss grows on J&ouml;tynnbaen at an alarming rate and it requires almost constant attention to prevent the maul from becoming choked in a thick blanket of lichen. 2 lbs of moss grows on it each day and this takes you at least 5 minutes to remove. It gains a cumulative -1 penalty to attack and damage rolls for each 24-hours that have passed since you last cleaned it until it hasn't been cleaned for at least 96-hours, at which time your attacks with it have disadvantage and it deals half damage instead.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":10,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":true,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":7500000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"gwogxIUSA7GDkPCs"}
{"name":"Symbol of Unity","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb10/symbol-of-unity.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"109\" height=\"256\" />\"This bejewelled faberge egg has a golden stand and gilded figurehead in the style of a proud dragon. Blue, bead-like pearls form lines that crisscross its surface, while bright red rubies are cut to resemble flames licking up from its stand. The object is designed to open, with the top half of the egg tilting backward on a small, discrete hinge.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Symbol of Unity was a gift from a powerful gold dragon to a dwarven castellan after soldiers under his command stumbled upon an abandoned dragon's egg during a small regional conflict. Despite all that was taking place, the castellan ensured that the dragon egg was safeguarded until it could be returned to dragonkind. The dragon birthed from it was in fact a red dragon, however its return to its chromatic family&mdash;orchestrated by the gold dragon who received the infant&mdash;ushered in a rare peace between the chromatic and metallic dragons of the area that lasted many years.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Drake Distraction</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Though not the most cunning of beasts, drakes are smart enough to recognize the size and shape of a dragon egg. As a reaction to being the target of a melee attack by a drake, you can brandish the Symbol of Unity. If you do so, the drake must attempt a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw. On a fail, it flinches and its attack is wasted. Once a drake has been subjected to this feature, it automatically passes the same check in the future.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Kobold Commander</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">As a result of their reverence for dragons, kobolds might feel unsure how to proceed when faced with the Symbol of Unity. You have advantage on Charisma (deception) checks made to convince kobolds that you represent a dragon, that the faberge egg contains an actual dragon egg, or that the object itself is a holy relic related to dragonkind&nbsp;</span>when you present it to them.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Breath Attack (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Imbued with the might of metallic dragons, great power resides within the Symbol of Unity. Once per day, you can open the faberge egg as an action in order to have it unleash a blast similar to a dragon's breath attack. Affected creatures must make a DC 13 saving throw, taking 2d6 damage on a failed save and nothing on a successful one. The area and damage type of this blast varies each time the egg is opened in this way and is randomly determined&nbsp; by rolling 1d10 and comparing the result to the following options:</span></span></p>\n<table style=\"user-select: text; width: 409px; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">D10</strong></td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Damage Type</strong></td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Breath Weapon</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">1-2</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Acid</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">5 by 30 ft. line (Dex. save)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">3-4</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Lightning</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">5 by 30 ft. line (Dex. save)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">5-6</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Fire</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">15 ft. cone (Dex. save)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">7-8</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Poison</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">15 ft. cone (Con save)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">9-10</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Cold</td>\n<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">15 ft. cone (Con. save)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Incubator</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Befitting its legacy, the Symbol of Unity serves to protect the innocent from harm. When you place a dragon egg in it and close its lid, the item seals and safeguards the egg until it is ready to hatch. It has an Armor Class of 17, hit points of 14 (4D6), and resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage. While the Symbol of Unity is sealed, you cannot use its </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Breath Attack&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">feature.</span></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"items","value":1,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":1900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"h3aUJVj3Mf3DT6O3"}
{"_id":"h75YsuNY8Ga0fMgV","name":"Evard's Black Tentacles","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Squirming, ebony tentacles fill a 20-foot square on ground that you can see within range. For the duration, these tentacles turn the ground in the area into difficult terrain.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>When a creature enters the affected area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 3d6]] bludgeoning damage and be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#restrained_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'restrained_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >restrained</a> by the tentacles until the spell ends. A creature that starts its turn in the area and is already <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#restrained_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'restrained_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >restrained</a> by the tentacles takes [[/r 3d6]] bludgeoning damage.</p><p>A creature <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#restrained_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'restrained_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >restrained</a> by the tentacles can use its action to make a Strength or Dexterity check (its choice) against your spell save DC. On a success, it frees itself.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"square"},"range":{"value":90,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d6","bludgeoning"],["3d6","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a piece of tentacle from a giant octopus or a giant squid","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":1400001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/vines-eerie-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"h7jjzJTDB7Q4qwih","name":"Sleet Storm (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Until the spell ends, freezing rain and sleet fall in a 20-foot-tall cylinder with a 40-foot radius centered on a point you choose within range. The area is heavily obscured, and exposed flames in the area are doused.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The ground in the area is covered with slick ice, making it difficult terrain. When a creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, it falls <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#prone_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'prone_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >prone</a>.</p><p>If a creature starts its turn in the spell's area and is concentrating on a spell, the creature must make a successful Constitution saving throw against your spell save DC or lose concentration.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":40,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cylinder"},"range":{"value":150,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a pinch of dust and a few drops of water","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":10700001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-sleet-storm.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Stoneshaper's Wand","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This quirky wand looks more like something that was unearthed than constructed, thanks to the fact that it is formed entirely of jagged, unrefined metals and minerals that run up to a tip that's little more than a hunk of raw copper ore. Despite its appearance indicating otherwise, the implement was indeed constructed, forged by a dwarven geomancer. This individual was fascinated with magic that physically interacted with the world and he became preoccupied with studying the arcane arts, something many of his kin shunned, in the hopes that he could revolutionize the way dwarves extract stones, minerals, metals, and gems from the earth.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Spellcasting Focus</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Stoneshaper's Wand can be used as an arcane focus (wand).</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Geomancy</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Stoneshaper's Wand can create several magical effects when used on rock and stone:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">As an action, you can touch it to the ground or ceiling in order to create stalactites or stalagmites in a 5 foot area. The affected area becomes difficult terrain for 10 minutes, before the new rock formations crumble into dust.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If you touch its tip against a rock wall, boulder, or piece of natural stone for 10 seconds; you can mark a 5 foot area with engravings and etchings in a language that you're familiar with or rudimentary cave paintings.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If you touch its tip against stone blocks, bricks, or any other kind of engineered stonework for 10 seconds within 5 foot of a doorway that's magically or mechanically hidden, its presence is revealed.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Stonebreaker (3/Day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Stoneshaper's Wand is a menace to minerals and metals alike. A weapon you touch with it deals an additional 1d6 damage to objects made of stone and rock, as well as elementals or constructed creatures made of those materials, for the next minute.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":3,"max":"3","per":"day","autoDestroy":false},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"wand","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":18900000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wand.png","effects":[],"_id":"hC1wP6hkh2PXcG4W"}
{"_id":"hEV7EX6VUp8guVzH","name":"Goodberry (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Up to ten berries appear in your hand and are infused with magic for the duration. A creature can use its action to eat one berry. Eating a berry restores 1 hit point, and the berry provides enough nourishment to sustain a creature for one day.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The berries lose their potency if they have not been consumed within 24 hours of the casting of this spell.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":""},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["","healing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a sprig of mistletoe","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":9300001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-goodberry.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hKiks3pdqWDMzCzL","name":"Shield of Faith (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A shimmering field appears and surrounds a creature of your choice within range, granting it a +2 bonus to AC for the duration.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a small parchment with a bit of holy text written on it","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":3700001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-shield-of-faith.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hLXeJmcim1QMXwBn","name":"Keoghtom's Ointment","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3,"OGI1ZmNiNjZhNWIz":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<div>\n<div><em>Wondrous item, minor tier, uncommon</em></div>\n</div>\n<hr />\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<p>This glass jar, 3 inches in diameter, contains [[/r <span class=\"roller render-roller\" title=\"Click to roll. SHIFT/CTRL to roll twice.\" data-packed-dice=\"{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;dice&quot;,&quot;rollable&quot;:true,&quot;toRoll&quot;:&quot;1d4 + 1&quot;}\">1d4 + 1]]</span> doses of a thick mixture that smells faintly of aloe. The jar and its contents weigh &frac12; pound.</p>\n<p>As an action, one dose of the ointment can be swallowed or applied to the skin. The creature that receives it regains [[/r <span class=\"roller render-roller\" title=\"Click to roll. SHIFT/CTRL to roll twice.\" data-packed-dice=\"{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;dice&quot;,&quot;rollable&quot;:true,&quot;toRoll&quot;:&quot;2d8 + 2&quot;}\">2d8 + 2]]</span> hit points, ceases to be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#poisoned_phb\">poisoned</a>, and is cured of any disease.</p>\n</div>\n<div><span class=\"bold\">Found On: </span><a href=\"https://5e.tools/tables.html#magic%20item%20table%20b_dmg\">Magic Item Table B</a></div>\n</div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"DMG","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"The ointment needs to be swallowed or applied to the skin."},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":5,"max":"5","per":"charges","autoDestroy":true,"autoUse":true},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d8 +2","healing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"potion","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"tMPMWheY9FGPdLEs","sort":200001,"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"items.html","source":"DMG","hash":"keoghtom's%20ointment_dmg","data":{"item":{"name":"Keoghtom's Ointment","source":"DMG","page":179,"srd":"Restorative Ointment","tier":"minor","rarity":"uncommon","wondrous":true,"entries":["This glass jar, 3 inches in diameter, contains {@dice 1d4 + 1} doses of a thick mixture that smells faintly of aloe. The jar and its contents weigh ½ pound.","As an action, one dose of the ointment can be swallowed or applied to the skin. The creature that receives it regains {@dice 2d8 + 2} hit points, ceases to be {@condition poisoned}, and is cured of any disease."],"lootTables":["Magic Item Table B"],"_isEnhanced":true,"_category":"Other","_typeListText":["wondrous item"],"_typeHtml":"wondrous item","_attunement":null,"_attunementCategory":"No","_fProperties":[],"_fMisc":["SRD","Magic"],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["minor"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Wondrous item"}}},"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""},"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/items/potions/grand-red.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"E7MfLnn9lH9WwWva","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":true},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"aura":"None","radius":null}},"changes":[{"key":"data.bonuses.heal.damage","value":"2d8+2","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Heal","origin":"Item.hLXeJmcim1QMXwBn","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"hTljrCdnHtK4sGAZ","name":"Dominate Monster","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You attempt to beguile a creature that you can see within range. It must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> by you for the duration. If you or creatures that are friendly to you are fighting it, it has advantage on the saving throw.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>While the creature is <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a>, you have a telepathic link with it as long as the two of you are on the same plane of existence. You can use this telepathic link to issue commands to the creature while you are conscious (no action required), which it does its best to obey. You can specify a simple and general course of action, such as \"Attack that creature,\" \"Run over there,\" or \"Fetch that object.\" If the creature completes the order and doesn't receive further direction from you, it defends and preserves itself to the best of its ability.</p><p>You can use your action to take total and precise control of the target. Until the end of your next turn, the creature takes only the actions you choose, and doesn't do anything that you don't allow it to do. During this time, you can also cause the creature to use a reaction, but this requires you to use your own reaction as well.</p><p>Each time the target takes damage, it makes a new Wisdom saving throw against the spell. If the saving throw succeeds, the spell ends.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"14\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell with a 9th-level spell slot, the duration is concentration, up to 8 hours.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":8,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":2200001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/air-burst-magenta-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Crayona-in-hand","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"Used by crooks and felons who reside deep below the surface, this everlasting crayon is used to warn other ne'er-do-wells of danger, or else sometimes to lead them into traps. A rogue in possession of it might, for example, place a warning beside a passageway that can only be read by other lawbreakers, indicating that it is frequented by soldiers. How much stock should be placed in such a caution really depends on who wrote it, and their intentions in doing so. Conversely, it can also be used to ward tunnels and shafts, providing criminals with an early warning system of sorts, should their hideout become compromised. The object itself looks like an ordinary crayon, though one end is a phosphorus orange color while the other is a milky blue.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Hidden Messages</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Crayona-in-hand can be used to leave discrete messages and warnings. Markings created with its blue tip are invisible to creatures that cannot read thieves' cant. Creatures that can see through invisibility or possess truesight are not affected by this feature.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">E</strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">arly Warnings</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Crayona-in-hand warns unscrupulous individuals of danger, all of them. You can use its orange side to leave almost imperceptible sigils and wards on the ground, walls, or ceiling&mdash;if you can reach it&mdash;that fill a five-foot area. Should a creature or inanimate object pass close to these sigils, all creatures that can speak thieves' cant within one mile receive a mental ping, telling them the following:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">T<span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">he location, if they know it, or general direction of where the ping originates from.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Whether whatever triggered the ping is alive or not. And, if it is a creature, what its type is.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Whether the creature has a lawful alignment or not.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The sigils are not completely invisible and can be noticed with a DC 13 Wisdom (perception) check or by a creature with a passive Perception score of 13 or higher. If the sigils are smudged or broken, the effect ends immediately without a mental ping being triggered. The Crayona-in-hand can create sigils in up to six separate five-foot areas at once, for a total of 30 square feet of warded areas</span>.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":0.01,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":15000000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"hsmkDkVakS5uq8CA"}
{"_id":"hwRk9zJzyFh9dCxF","name":"Spirit Shroud","permission":{"default":-1,"bOqyKS8LL2EWqEnK":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You call forth spirits of the dead, which flit around you for the spell's duration. The spirits are intangible and invulnerable.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Until the spell ends, any attack you make deals [[/r 1d8]] extra damage when you hit a creature within 10 feet of you. This damage is radiant, necrotic, or cold (your choice when you cast the spell). Any creature that takes this damage can't regain hit points until the start of your next turn.</p><p>In addition, any creature of your choice that you can see that starts its turn within 10 feet of you has its speed reduced by 10 feet until the start of your next turn.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"2463\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] for every two slot levels above 3rd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"TCE","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["","healing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":null,"sort":700001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[{"_id":"VQyGo8tRI2i0zJF6","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"transfer":true}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Concentration","origin":"Item.hwRk9zJzyFh9dCxF","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"name":"Current's Courier","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This simple, corked glass bottle could be easily misconstrued as any other piece of floating debris or garbage, however such a rash assessment of it would be foolish. Its true nature is revealed when its cork is removed and a creature blows air into it, causing the glass to fog up and reveal an intricate pattern of arcane runes smudged into its surface.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The architect behind the creation of Current's Courier was a wizard studying interplanar communication. His hope had been to use the object as a new means of communication between his own plane and one of elemental water, using the ocean itself as a gateway between the two. His study fell slightly shy of the mark and, to date, the bottle has never successfully traveled to another plane of existence, though its ability to navigate the physical plane is unquestioned.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Distant Destinations</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Current's Courier has a curious habit of making its way into the hand of the intended recipient of the messages it carries. You can write a message on a scrap of paper, place the scrap of paper inside it, toss it in the ocean, and have the currents deliver it to a location or person of your choosing, as per any of the following:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A specific person whose name you know.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A representative of a specific faction that you've heard of.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A specific ship or vessel that you're familiar with or know the name of.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A coastal location or settlement that you're familiar with or know the name of.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If it is possible for Current's Courier to reach its destination via a body of water connected to the one that it was tossed into, the corked bottle arrives after 2d6 days, irrespective of the distance traveled.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Return to Sender</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Current's Courier has a magical knack for making its way back to the person it considers its owner. If you send it to relay a message to a recipient as per Distant Destinations, it shatters and reappears in your hand or pack, or adjacent you, 1 minute after it has been uncorked and its contents removed.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">S.O.S</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A marooned or lost creature that uses Current's Courier's unusual blessings to call for aid can rest assured that their plea will be heard. If you write a request for help or assistance and seal it inside the bottle as per Distant Destinations, you should make a Charisma (persuasion) check with advantage at the time of writing the note. The result of this check should be recorded and may be relevant to the GM or another player when the message is later read, perhaps requiring an NPC or PC to contest it then or have it factor into how they react.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"items","value":1,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":19200000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/backpack.png","effects":[],"_id":"iFx9bk5VdvB0aXco"}
{"_id":"iWwGB4pMr7hiZXqX","name":"Identify (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You choose one object that you must touch throughout the casting of the spell. If it is a magic item or some other magic-imbued object, you learn its properties and how to use them, whether it requires attunement to use, and how many charges it has, if any. You learn whether any spells are affecting the item and what they are. If the item was created by a spell, you learn which spell created it.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If you instead touch a creature throughout the casting, you learn what spells, if any, are currently affecting it.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"object"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":true,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a pearl worth at least 100 gp and an owl feather","consumed":false,"cost":100,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":7000001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-identify.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Nordenzeik","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Unusually, this enormous greatsword isn't forged from metal or alloys, but rather is composed entirely of white stone. Its blade is made of gleaming opalized white agate that has a semi-translucent appearance; while its guard and grip are instead rough howlite, which has vein-like tendrils of darkish grey streaking through them. Nordenzeik is either the last remnant of a fallen kingdom that the history books have forgotten, or else a clever ruse by a bored and powerful being that is designed to impart a valuable lesson to the kind of bloodthirsty, warmongering person who might choose to wield such an unapologetically deadly implement. In either case, the memories that the blade shares with the creature bonded to it seem real, as do the lessons these memories impart.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Nordenzeik can be used as a greatsword.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Blade of Unity</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Nordenzeik believes that conflicts should be settled through discourse, not violence. If you plunge it into the ground as an action, the area within 30 foot of it becomes sanctified with a peaceful aura. While within this area, Charisma checks made to convince creatures to lay down arms or walk away peacefully have advantage, while those made to threaten, intimidate, strongarm, or incite violence have disadvantage. Additionally, all creatures within the affected area who stow their weapons and make no attempt to move, take actions, or do anything other than talk benefit from the effects of the <em>Sanctuary </em>spell (DC 15 to save) until they act in a hostile manner, leave the affected area, or the sword is retrieved.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Condemnation</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Nordenzeik does not forgive or forget, it leaves that to the aggrieved. Should you ever use its</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"> Blade of Unity </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">feature for evil&mdash;such as to intentionally lure an enemy into lowering their guard before striking&mdash;the ability stops functioning for you permanently. In order to use it again, you must be forgiven by either the wronged or their next of kin.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Foreign Memories</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Nordenzeik's bearer carries with them the last vestiges of a fallen kingdom. When you first attune to it, you are flooded with the memories of an individual who acted as an advisor to a stubborn king. This person bore witness to a bloody war that lasted many years and brought about the kingdom's downfall. Although the king was afforded many opportunities to surrender, he chose to see everything around him crumble into oblivion, rather than swallow his pride. Though you are unable to discern too many specifics or details from these memories, your emotional response to what you're witnessing may feel as real and sharp as it would have been for the person who lived through them.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":true,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":8700000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"ikhRV3WW1Q1nYP4u"}
{"name":"Masuta-malay (Masuta)","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb09/masuta-malay.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"84\" />\"This impressive three piece collection is formed of a katana, a wakizashi, and a small display stand that is able to be broken down into three sections for transportation and then quickly re-assembled anywhere. The glistening metal blades present with gold detailing and indulgent red leather covers their grips. Clearly, the luxurious set has been forged to a grand master's exacting standards and could be used for ceremonial purposes every bit as easily as used to cut a man down.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Formed of the katana, Masuta, and the wakizashi, Malay, Masuta-malay once belonged to a revered shogun. It is said that he would allow his enemies to inspect the quality of his blades before entering into battle with him and, reportedly, won several dozen battles without a drop of blood being spilled as a result. Moved by his majestic armaments, many opposing commanders merely surrendered&ndash;preferring to throw themselves on his mercy than meet him in battle.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapons</strong>. Masuta-Malay includes </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Masuta and @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.TLLpKNm1aCQ9I3xJ]{Malay}, which can be used as a longsword and shortsword respectively.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Perfect Partners</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In matters of life and death, some brothers are as blades, and some blades are as brothers. While you are wielding both Masuta and Malay, Masuta is considered to have the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Light&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">weapon property. Additionally, while wielding both weapons, you deal +1 bonus damage with each.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Quick Draw</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A life can be snuffed out with a single motion. Whenever you draw Masuta or Malay, you can draw both weapons instead.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":"1d10 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":6200000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"io5qDMfWujW8C9ts"}
{"name":"Brunswick's Bell","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"At first glance this simple metal bell in the style of one used to summon a butler, servant, or nanny doesn't seem especially grand or noteworthy, however there is far more to it than first impressions might suggest.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Brunswick's Bell was once the property of one master William Brunswick, a butler of startling character, poise, and professionalism. He served a wealthy household for several years before becoming a soldier, seeing combat on the front lines, and suffering a terrible injury which ended his military career. William returned to his former position after his discharge, serving the next two generations of the same family. However, his injuries caused him tremendous pain and he deteriorated over the decades to the point that he was no longer able to serve in his capacity as butler. Rather than oust him, the then-master of the house gave William his bell as a mark of gratitude and respect, and allowed him to live out the rest of his days in the home that had become his as much as its owners.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Seen Servant</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When rung, Brunswick's Bell summons the spectral form of Master Brunswick, whose spirit is bound to the bell. Master Brunswick can perform a litany of tasks as per the spell&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><em>Unseen Servant</em>,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">however while summoned in this way he is not invisible</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">In addition to the duties outlined in&nbsp;</span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Unseen Servant</span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">, Master Brunswick can also assist with donning and doffing armor, fletching arrows, and sharpening blades thanks to his military background. Once summoned, Master Brunswick remains present and loyal to you until you ring it again to dismiss him.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Master Brunswick</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Master Brunswick is a cranky, cantankerous old curmudgeon who's as set in his ways as he is convinced that those ways are the best ways. Master Brunswick has the following personality traits, ideals, bonds, and flaws:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Personality Traits</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Master Brunswick is stubborn, sarcastic, uncompromising, and belligerent.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Ideals</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Master Brunswick believes that those charged with discharging a specific duty know more about it than their masters ever could.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Bonds</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Master Brunswick is compelled to serve his 'master' to the best of his ability.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Flaws</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Master Brunswick is hard of hearing and prone to yelling, 'What?', at the least convenient of times.</span></span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":600000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"itr4e5yfPQJNJfKt"}
{"_id":"j7HyNcPSwDitWEWX","name":"Lesser Restoration (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You touch a creature and can end either one disease or one condition afflicting it. The condition can be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#blinded_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'blinded_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >blinded</a>, <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#deafened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'deafened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >deafened</a>, <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#paralyzed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'paralyzed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >paralyzed</a>, or <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#poisoned_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'poisoned_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >poisoned</a>.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":8700001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-lesser-restoration.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Sprocket of the Warmonger","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Thanks to both its style and quality, this cog looks almost-dwarven in design. It is not, however, the result of the stout folks' ingenuity and hard work. Rather, this large gear is actually the product of human hands. It was once part of a great war machine, a wheel-mounted siege weapon so large that the missiles it fired were almost as large as the tree trunks from which they were formed. The war it was constructed for eventually came to an end and, after seeing it through dozens of clashes and skirmishes, </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">the crew that manned it stripped it down and each took a memento from it to keep for themselves. This sprocket is one such keepsake.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Sprocket of the Warmonger was a vital component of a siege weapon called the Warmonger. This terrifying ballista became legendary thanks to the tenacity of its crew and its uncanny ability to pass through the most harrowing and perilous of battles completely unscathed. The 12-inch cog now serves merely as a good luck charm.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Attunement Requirement</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Sprocket of the Warmonger celebrates camaraderie above all else. For its features to function, you must be in close proximity to it. Additionally, if you behave in a deeply selfish or uncooperative way, you lose attunement to it and cannot attune to it again for 48 hours.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Good Fortune (3/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A creature that carries the Sprocket of the Warmonger is blessed with good luck. You can announce your intent to do one of the following 3 times per day before making the relevant roll:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Add your proficiency bonus to an ability check, attack roll, or saving throw that doesn't include it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Add double your proficiency bonus to an ability check, attack roll, or saving throw that includes it.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Add your proficiency bonus to one death saving throw.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In order for this feature to function, you must roll a d20 before making your other check. On a result of 16-20, you are able to expend 1 use of this ability for the day and have the declaration come into effect. On a 6-15, you are not able to do so but do not lose 1 use of this ability for the day. On 1-5, you are unable to do so and lose 1 use of this ability for the day.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Stronger Together</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The crew of the Warmonger always managed to pull through whatever life threw at them, together. Whenever the game master calls for a group check, your party is considered to have 1 more member than it does and this additional individual automatically succeeds on its check, contributing to the total number of successes.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Ammunition Retrieval</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It's astounding how often a creature carrying the Sprocket of the Warmonger experiences minor feats of good fortune, especially when it comes to firing projectiles. Unless the GM rules otherwise due to them being damaged or destroyed, you always manage to retrieve all of your ammunition after using it, not half like usual.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"none","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":3,"max":"3","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":11300000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"jO1yCsfJkbZJ1lmT"}
{"name":"Ternion Tome","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb06/ternion-tome.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"220\" height=\"256\" />\"This strange book is the result of an unusual collaboration between a wizard, bard, and necromancer. The bard, a renowned artist, was of a venerable age and not long for the world when he met the two women destined to help him bring his final project to life. Using their knowledge of life, death, and the arcane, the female spellcasters were able to capture the soul of the bard at the moment of his death and imbue it into the book. Though no longer in possession of sentience, a measure of the bard's persona lingers within the tome's leather-bound pages, allowing him to continue his work in a fashion for all time.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Ternion Tome is able to create very detailed sketchings of whatever it is angled towards, as well as help a creature who draws, sketches, or paints in it with their work. To use the book, its bearer simply holds the book aloft, with its cover faced towards the object or area they want to depict and will the book to capture it. The arcane sigil in the top corner of the book's cover then rotates and twists as if to adjust its focus and aperture before creating a highly detailed sketch of the object on one of its blank pages. Conversely, if a creature would rather make a sketch of something themselves, the spirit of the bard helps guide their hand.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Inscribe</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Ternion Tome is a useful tool for capturing details about a scene or location. As an action, you can will the book to record whatever it is facing onto to one of its pages in the style of a charcoal sketch. The level of detail is equivalent to what a professional sketch artist with a passive skill level of 18 using a set of Artisan&rsquo;s tools</span> might create. Such illustrations are entirely devoid of color. <span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The book of recording has exactly 100 pages, should one or more pages be removed from the book they turn blank and another page appears in the book after 24 hours.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Signature Features</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Each of Ternion Tome's creators bestowed a unique feature into the tome:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong>Bard's Feature.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can use the book as a set of calligrapher's supplies, cartographer's tools, or painter's supplies.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong>Necromancer's Feature.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When using the book's</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&nbsp;Inscribe&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">feature, if you aim the book towards the body of a deceased creature, the illustration created also depicts the dead creature as it appeared in life, standing over its body.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong>Wizard's Feature.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can will the book to make a sketch of one or more objects that have a combined weight of no greater than 5 lb. These objects disappear, transplanted onto the in-leaf page in sketch form. They can be retrieved by destroying the page, which deposits them on the floor within 5 feet of Ternion Tome. There can be no more than one object or set of objects contained within the book at one time.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":19900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/book.png","effects":[],"_id":"jQ4F02Y0zZyRsyUe"}
{"name":"Tub of the Mad Shark","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"To the uninitiated, this unassuming bucket looks ordinary and harmless, though those who've witnessed the devastation that the ferocious spirit bonded with it can wreak know better. The tub is filled with a thick, gloopy slurry of blood and fish entrails, the kind a deep sea fisherman might use as chum. Bizarrely, the spirit of a great white shark appears to have developed a certain fondness for the object and has been known to appear in its vicinity when its contents are spilled, poured out, or otherwise disturbed.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Tub of the Mad Shark is a strange object indeed. It was discovered on the beaches of a remote tropical island, placed there by a tribe of indigenous people who no longer wanted the item in their village&mdash;or indeed the same jungle as them&mdash;as they believed that it was cursed and that the spirit of a mighty shark called Matu-Makas had taken up residence within it. They were only too pleased when travelers from far away visited their island, didn't share in their superstition and dread, and took the bucket away with them.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Sharkbait</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Those brave enough can use the Tub of the Mad Shark to summon Matu-Makas' spirit. As an action, you can pour the contents of the bucket onto the ground or attempt to throw the chum over a creature within 5 feet of you. If you target a creature, it must attempt a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw, becoming covered in chum on a fail. Maku-Makas appears within 40 foot of a creature covered in chum at the end of the round and takes its turn then. It attacks only this creature and continues to do so until the creature is dead, the shark is slain, or 5 minutes have passed, at which time it disappears until summoned again. If slain, the shark can be resummoned once the bucket is full again (as per Resupply</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">). If the bucket is instead emptied onto the ground or a creature targeted by it succeeds on its saving throw, Matu-Makas instead appears at the end of the round in the 5 foot area where the chum hit the ground and circles a 10-foot cube centered on this location for the duration. While summoned in this way, it remains within its area and is considered hostile to any creatures who come within range of it. For this feature to function, the bucket must be full of chum.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Matu-Makas.</strong><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-style: italic;\">&nbsp;Statistical information necessary to use&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Matu-Makas </span>in combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.NY9O1nc3o57NH2HG]{Matu-Makas}.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Resupply</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The chum stored within the Tub of the Mad Shark slowly replenishes once emptied, completely refilling once 24 hours have passed. Once the bucket is one quarter full, it starts to smell strongly of blood and guts. Creatures have advantage on Wisdom (perception) checks made to track you&nbsp;</span>via smell well you bear it from now on and, at the game masters's discretion, the object may begin to attract predators and scavengers.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day","autoDestroy":false},"consume":{"type":"charges","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"consumableType":"trinket","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":19600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"jT7d7WSxlo3SvxkS"}
{"_id":"jby85bKIDOPxrq5F","name":"Astral Projection","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You and up to eight willing creatures within range project your astral bodies into the Astral Plane (the spell fails and the casting is wasted if you are already on that plane). The material body you leave behind is <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#unconscious_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'unconscious_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >unconscious</a> and in a state of suspended animation, it doesn't need food or air and doesn't age.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Your astral body resembles your mortal form in almost every way, replicating your game statistics and possessions. The principal difference is the addition of a silvery cord that extends from between your shoulder blades and trails behind you, fading to invisibility after 1 foot. This cord is your tether to your material body. As long as the tether remains intact, you can find your way home. If the cord is cut-something that can happen only when an effect specifically states that it does-your soul and body are separated, killing you instantly.</p><p>Your astral form can freely travel through the Astral Plane and can pass through portals there leading to any other plane. If you enter a new plane or return to the plane you were on when casting this spell, your body and possessions are transported along the silver cord, allowing you to re-enter your body as you enter the new plane. Your astral form is a separate incarnation. Any damage or other effects that apply to it have no effect on your physical body, nor do they persist when you return to it.</p><p>The spell ends for you and your companions when you use your action to dismiss it. When the spell ends, the affected creature returns to its physical body, and it awakens.</p><p>The spell might also end early for you or one of your companions. A successful <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#dispel%20magic_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'dispel%20magic_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >dispel magic</a> spell used against an astral or physical body ends the spell for that creature. If a creature's original body or its astral form drops to 0 hit points, the spell ends for that creature. If the spell ends and the silver cord is intact, the cord pulls the creature's astral form back to its body, ending its state of suspended animation.</p><p>If you are returned to your body prematurely, your companions remain in their astral forms and must find their own way back to their bodies, usually by dropping to 0 hit points.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"hour","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"spec"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":9,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"for each creature you affect with this spell, you must provide one jacinth worth at least 1,000 gp and one ornately carved bar of silver worth at least 100 gp, all of which the spell consumes","consumed":true,"cost":110000,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":2900001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/wind-grasp-eerie-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jcnzGvmTUVnnlXKG","name":"Jim's Magic Missile","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p class=\"rd__quote-line rd__quote-line--last\"><i>Jim's magic missile is an ancient and powerful spell, as well as being the name of my band in Wizard Academy.</i></p><p><span class=\"rd__quote-by\">— Jim Darkmagic</span></p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Any apprentice wizard can cast a boring old magic missile. Sure, it always strikes its target. Yawn. Do away with the drudgery of your grandfather's magic with this improved version of the spell, as used by Jim Darkmagic!</p><p>You create three twisting, whistling, hypoallergenic, gluten-free darts of magical force. Each dart targets a creature of your choice that you can see within range. Make a ranged spell attack for each missile. On a hit, a missile deals [[/r 2d4]] force damage to its target.</p><p>If the attack roll scores a critical hit, the target of that missile takes [[/r 5d4]] force damage instead of you rolling damage twice for a critical hit. If the attack roll for any missile is a 1, all missiles miss their targets and blow up in your face, dealing 1 force damage per missile to you.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"159\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the spell creates one more dart, and the royalty component increases by 1 gp, for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"AI","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rsak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d4","force"],["5d4","force"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":3500001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jxUU2BQOafTEFsKj","name":"Eldritch Blast","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A beam of crackling energy streaks toward a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target takes [[/r 1d10]] force damage.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The spell creates more than one beam when you reach higher levels: two beams at 5th level, three beams at 11th level, and four beams at 17th level. You can direct the beams at the same target or at different ones. Make a separate attack roll for each beam.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rsak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d10","force"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":1700001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/fireball-eerie-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kADWLZ91Y7lL4Xqg","name":"Conjure Animals (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You summon fey spirits that take the form of beasts and appear in unoccupied spaces that you can see within range. Choose one of the following options for what appears:</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><ul class=\"rd__list\"><li class=\"rd__li \">One <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&2,flsttype:beast=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >beast of challenge rating 2 or lower</a></li><li class=\"rd__li \">Two <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&1,flsttype:beast=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >beasts of challenge rating 1 or lower</a></li><li class=\"rd__li \">Four <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&1/2,flsttype:beast=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >beasts of challenge rating 1/2 or lower</a></li><li class=\"rd__li \">Eight <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#blankhash,flstchallenge%20rating:min=&0~max=&1/4,flsttype:beast=1,flstmiscellaneous:swarm=2\"   >beasts of challenge rating 1/4 or lower</a></li></ul><p>Each beast is also considered fey, and it disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p><p>The summoned creatures are friendly to you and your companions. Roll initiative for the summoned creatures as a group, which has its own turns. They obey any verbal commands that you issue to them (no action required by you). If you don't issue any commands to them, they defend themselves from hostile creatures, but otherwise take no actions.</p><p>The DM has the creatures' statistics.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"122\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using certain higher-level spell slots, you choose one of the summoning options above, and more creatures appear: twice as many with a 5th-level slot, three times as many with a 7th-level slot, and four times as many with a 9th-level slot.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"any","type":"space"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":7900001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-conjure-animals.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Buccaneer's Bargain","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This exquisite scimitar is made of burnished bone that has been buffed unrelentingly until a glossy, almost glassy, finish has been achieved. Its edge is as flat and sharp as steel and it has small depictions of boats scrimshawed into it. What might be considered the weapon's 'hilt' takes the form of a wrist as the bottom of the blade gives out to a skeletal hand. In order to wield the scimitar, a creature must grab it by its pale appendage. Somewhat unnervingly, the blade's hand grips them back firmly to form a handshake with nary a rattle of its ancient bones.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The skeletal hand of Buccaneer&rsquo;s Bargain once belonged to a freebooter named Carrington Whitfield who dedicated his life to sailing the high seas in search of fame and fortune. One such adventure brought Carrington to the home of a witch doctor who promised the intrepid corsair immortality in exchange for performing a small favor. Carrington accepted the offer and sealed the deal with a handshake only to find his hand and forearm turn to bone at the shaman&rsquo;s touch.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Buccaneer&rsquo;s Bargain can be used as a scimitar.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Firm Handshake</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As a creature firmly clasps Buccaneer&rsquo;s Bargain's grip, it in turn seizes their wrist just as tightly. When you attempt to wield it, it latches onto your hand and cannot be removed by non-magical means for 4 hours.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Sharp Scimitar</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Carrington Whitfield was no common sailor, and Buccaneer&rsquo;s Bargain is no common blade. Attacks you make with it benefit from a +1 bonus to hit.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Poetic Irony (1/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Though Carrington Whitfield was promised the prize of immortality in life, through Buccaneer&rsquo;s Bargain, he instead helps others achieve a measure of it. Once per day, when you use it to slay a creature of the humanoid type, you extend your natural lifespan by one day.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Last Hurrah</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Carrington Whitfield's legacy lives on through those who choose to take him on their own adventures. While holding Buccaneer&rsquo;s Bargain, you gain the following personality trait: \"I'm a swashbuckling thrill-seeker who thirsts for action-packed adventures\".</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"1","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":3200000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"kLtg6pPfiHgZdsoy"}
{"_id":"kTKuI21fr9xEag8W","name":"Stone of Good Luck (Luckstone)","permission":{"default":0,"gSvPH9u5wzkE1oU1":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Wondrous item, (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">While this polished agate is on your person, you gain a +1 bonus to ability checks and saving throws.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"DMG pg. 205","quantity":1,"weight":0.1,"price":4200,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"none","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":null,"sort":1300001,"flags":{"dae":{"activeEquipped":false,"alwaysActive":false},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.2SXMmAq0xJ0bu9bP"},"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"betterCurses":{"isCurse":false,"curseName":"","formula":"","mwak":false,"rwak":false,"msak":false,"rsak":false}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/items/inventory/gem-yellow.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"6uTSUGYHrI3JC5sg","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"transfer":true,"specialDuration":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"data.bonuses.abilities.check","value":"1","mode":0,"priority":20},{"key":"data.bonuses.abilities.save","value":"1","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/items/inventory/gem-yellow.jpg","label":"New Active Effect","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"l4RJvjszzr1x8kZ0","name":"Remove Curse (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>At your touch, all curses affecting one creature or object end. If the object is a cursed magic item, its curse remains, but the spell breaks its owner's attunement to the object so it can be removed or discarded.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":8800001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-remove-curse.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lC7gOI7liKffBg08","name":"Animate Dead (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>This spell creates an undead servant. Choose a pile of bones or a corpse of a Medium or Small humanoid within range. Your spell imbues the target with a foul mimicry of life, raising it as an undead creature. The target becomes a <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#skeleton_mm\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'bestiary.html', 'MM', 'skeleton_mm', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >skeleton</a> if you chose bones or a <a href=\"https://5e.tools/bestiary.html#zombie_mm\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'bestiary.html', 'MM', 'zombie_mm', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >zombie</a> if you chose a corpse (the DM has the creature's game statistics).</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>On each of your turns, you can use a bonus action to mentally command any creature you made with this spell if the creature is within 60 feet of you (if you control multiple creatures, you can command any or all of them at the same time, issuing the same command to each one). You decide what action the creature will take and where it will move during its next turn, or you can issue a general command, such as to guard a particular chamber or corridor. If you issue no commands, the creature only defends itself against hostile creatures. Once given an order, the creature continues to follow it until its task is complete.</p><p>The creature is under your control for 24 hours, after which it stops obeying any command you've given it. To maintain control of the creature for another 24 hours, you must cast this spell on the creature again before the current 24-hour period ends. This use of the spell reasserts your control over up to four creatures you have animated with this spell, rather than animating a new one.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"127\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you animate or reassert control over two additional undead creatures for each slot level above 3rd. Each of the creatures must come from a different corpse or pile of bones.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"object"},"range":{"value":10,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a drop of blood, a piece of flesh, and a pinch of bone dust","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":8900001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-animate-dead.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lCPwIAtGaY8sYBYt","name":"Shatter (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A sudden loud ringing noise, painfully intense, erupts from a point of your choice within range. Each creature in a 10-foot-radius sphere centered on that point must make a Constitution saving throw. A creature takes [[/r 3d8]] thunder damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. A creature made of inorganic material such as stone, crystal, or metal has disadvantage on this saving throw.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>A nonmagical object that isn't being worn or carried also takes the damage if it's in the spell's area.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"106\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 2nd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":10,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d8","thunder"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a chip of mica","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":5900001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-shatter.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Masuta-malay (Malay)","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb09/masuta-malay.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"84\" />\"This impressive three piece collection is formed of a katana, a wakizashi, and a small display stand that is able to be broken down into three sections for transportation and then quickly re-assembled anywhere. The glistening metal blades present with gold detailing and indulgent red leather covers their grips. Clearly, the luxurious set has been forged to a grandmaster's exacting standards and could be used for ceremonial purposes every bit as easily as used to cut a man down.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Formed of the katana, Masuta, and the wakizashi, Malay, Masuta-malay once belonged to a revered shogun. It is said that he would allow his enemies to inspect the quality of his blades before entering into battle with him and, reportedly, won several dozen battles without a drop of blood being spilled as a result. Moved by his majestic armaments, many opposing commanders merely surrendered&ndash;preferring to throw themselves on his mercy than meet him in battle.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapons</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">Masuta-Malay includes @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.ncaVlPJ7tU7wDJhU]{Masuta}</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;and Malay, which can be used as a longsword and shortsword respectively.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Perfect Partners</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In matters of life and death, some brothers are as blades, and some blades are as brothers. While you are wielding both Masuta and Malay, Masuta is considered to have the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Light </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">weapon property. Additionally, while wielding both weapons, you deal +1 bonus damage with each.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Quick Draw</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A life can be snuffed out with a single motion. Whenever you draw Masuta or Malay, you can draw both weapons instead.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":6100000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"lF4MKYYPoR4hK8fj"}
{"name":"Blade of Troz'gor","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Though a relatively uncommon weapon, this sacrificial katar doesn't appear innately magical at first glance. However, those who created the blade placed within it a vile utensil for evil that is anything but mundane. The object is held and operated in the usual way, its wielder clenching their fist around a pair of cross beams and using the katar as a kind of punch dagger, sometimes squeezing its two handles together to operate a spring that splits the blade open down its center. However, where most katars merely contain another, smaller blade within, this one hides something truly nefarious.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Blade of Troz&rsquo;gor contains a vicious, forked-tongue that is seemingly formed of obsidian, the tips of which are razor-sharp. However, in the presence of blood or when brought close to exposed skin the tongue animates and does its best to lap up the blood or grievously wound whoever it can. The Blade of Troz'gor has been used in several occult rituals involving human sacrifice over the years. These have usually involved its hidden tongue being revealed and inserted into an offering, whereupon it </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">slowly drains the victim of all their blood until they're little more than a desiccated husk.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Blade of Troz'gor can be used as a dagger.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Accursed Armament</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Able to siphon lifeforce from those it strikes and confer vitality to its wielder, the Blade of Troz'gor is an especially potent weapon. When you use it to make a melee attack and the attack hits, you gain 2 temporary hit point if the result of your attack roll is an even number, or deal +1 bonus damage if it's an odd number.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Foul Tongue</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Forged for evil by wicked hands, the Blade of Troz'gor is no friend of angels. Creatures of the celestial type can sense the blade within 120 foot and it deals an additional +1 bonus damage to them.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":2500000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"lZoXtzS9sR1yKYXd"}
{"_id":"lp3KLyqjNQj8PTRm","name":"Darkness (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Magical darkness spreads from a point you choose within range to fill a 15-foot-radius sphere for the duration. The darkness spreads around corners. A creature with <span class=\"help--hover\" onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseOver(event, this, 7, {})\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseMove(event, this)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseLeave(event, this)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">darkvision</span> can't see through this darkness, and nonmagical light can't illuminate it.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If the point you choose is on an object you are holding or one that isn't being worn or carried, the darkness emanates from the object and moves with it. Completely covering the source of the darkness with an opaque object, such as a bowl or a helm, blocks the darkness.</p><p>If any of this spell's area overlaps with an area of light created by a spell of 2nd level or lower, the spell that created the light is dispelled.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"bat fur and a drop of pitch or piece of coal","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":8400001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-darkness.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Ruozan","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This fine red mahogany sword cane strikes an imposing figure thanks to the pewter likeness of a growling wolf that adorns its handle with its fangs bared. The shaft of the sword cane is likewise noteworthy not only for its rich red coloration, but also for the streaks of even darker red that run through its grain, like veins or arteries. The tip of the object has been felted with dark canvass so that it can be used without clinking on stone floors. Within the cane component of the item resides a sharp, slender blade.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Ruozan can be used as a sword cane.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Sword Cane.</strong> Rules for sword canes can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Attunement Requirement</strong>. You can only attune to Ruozan if your alignment is lawful.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Blade of Tradition</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Ruozan has always belonged to those that revere and honor tradition, and it continues that legacy. When you use it to make an attack against a creature with a chaotic alignment, you deal +1 damage on a hit.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Vigilant</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Ruozan's bearer is rarely caught with their guard lowered. While it is about your person, you gain a +2 bonus to your Wisdom (perception) checks and passive Perception score for the purposes of noticing ambushes or ambushers.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Reactionary Haste</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The element of surprise provides a powerful edge on the field of battle, though not so powerful that it cannot be overcome. If Ruozan is about your person and you are surprised, you can still move up to half your speed and take the attack action with disadvantage on your turn during a surprise round. If you weren't surprised, you can act as normal.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":8900000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"lqqIqPEFmEbb4ulh"}
{"name":"Camilion","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This enchanted tent is shaped like a round pavilion with a conical roof and a single front entrance which is approximately the size of a set of common double-doors. Externally, the walls of the tent are striped in alternating bands of red and white fabric which run up to a ring of crenallated merlons, while its top is formed of a solid white canvas. It is crowned with a red flag that has been emblazoned with a depiction of a watchtower. The marquee is composed of a cotton canvas which has been treated with a protective, waterproof coating and is held together by several wooden poles and a band of guy ropes. Able to pitch itself upon command, these guy ropes bury themselves in the ground or tie onto whatever else is within reach when the tent unfurls. The shelter is also able to pull the same trick in reverse; its guy ropes releasing and tying themselves up in neat little bundles, poles folding down neatly, and canvas rolling itself up once more, before the whole item curls into its attached bag.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Miracle Tent</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Camilion is a marvellous fusion of magic and intelligent design. When stowed, this miraculous tent measures just 1 foot in all dimensions and weighs only 40 lbs. When pitched, its footprint measures a 10-foot circle and stands 12-foot-tall. Although Camilion</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">is only 10-foot-wide when pitched, its interior is larger than it appears from outside due to its magical nature. Inside, its chamber actually measures 30 foot across in either direction, though its height remains unchanged.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You can verbally command Camilion to pitch itself with the command words 'set camp', or to stow itself with the command words 'break camp'. It takes 1 minute for it to accomplish either task and it can only pitch itself in areas that provide sufficient space for it to do so. Any objects interned within it when it stows itself are shrunk down so that the object's stowed size is unchanged, and they remain safely within the tent until it is next deployed. Any objects stored within Camilion weigh half as much as usual for the purposes of calculating the object's weight when stowed. It cannot stow itself when living creatures are within it.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tent of Repose</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Camilion can be a bastion of refuge and safety for those trapped behind enemy lines. When you and your allies take a long or short rest inside it, you ecah gain temporary hit points equal to your respective Constitution modifiers. Additionally, if taking a short rest and spending hit dice to recover hit points as part of it, affected creatures gain 1 temporary hit point for each hit die spent and add this to the total number of temporary hit points received. A creature can only benefit from this feature once per day.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":40,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":14000000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"mC3k50lW144Cjkpp"}
{"name":"Notwug'ye","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"What looks like a small bundle of folded cloth is actually something far more sinister and significant. Within the folds of this luxurious purple fabric resides a desiccated hand that once belonged to a humanoid, cut short across the forearm. Someone has clearly gone to great pains to preserve the appendage, treating it with embalming fluid and other chemicals designed to ensure that it won't perish to the elements too quickly, before wrapping it tightly in a satin shroud.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Nothing is known of Notwug'ye's true origins, nor about the individual to whom it once belonged. Though, the object is clearly special, even if only for the miracles known to manifest in its presence. Although the hand appears otherwise still and lifeless, its fingernails continue to grow and need cutting at least once a month by its keeper.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Restoration (1/Year)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Incredible miracles have been known to manifest around Notwug'ye, sometimes with far reaching consequences. Once per year, you can touch it against a magical item that once had changes but has permanently exhausted all of them and have its recharges restored to full.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Benevolent Blessings.&nbsp;</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Notwug'ye has also been known to perform other, lesser miracles. Roll a d100 the first time you touch it against any of the following, on a result of 100 the listed effect occurs:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When touched against a dead, withered plant or tree, it returns to life.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When touched against a deceased creature of the beast subtype, it is restored to life, even if it died of natural causes. If the creature died of old age, it's age is halved when it is restored to life.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When touched against a creature who has permanently lost their vision, sense of taste or smell, or hearing, it restores them to use.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When touched against a creature currently suffering from a disease, it is cured.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When touched against a creature suffering from the Petrified condition, it is immediately reversed.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When touched against a broken or damaged object, it is miraculously fixed.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tremendous Worth</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Notwug'ye is of tremendous religious, cultural, and historical value. Private collectors, museum curators, and others may be willing to purchase it from its current owner. Additionally, priests, clerics, and other holy or scholarly individuals might be willing to undertake minor personal favors for its bearer just to be able to see it or study it up close. Conversely, spellcasters or those in possession of exhausted magical items might be willing to go to great lengths to acquire it.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Curious Aura</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Much of Notwug'ye's history and origin remains unknown. Strangely, the hair and fingernails of the dead within 1 mile of it continue to grow indefinitely.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":15300000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"mGKzi6vN4cXHbJ4d"}
{"_id":"mgOQaQUF4EO2JmnQ","name":"Healing Word (1st Level)","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3,"jSIbaKrMQZ5trOzn":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<div>\n\t\t\t<div><i>Scroll, minor tier, common</i></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"flex w-100\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-4\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"col-8 text-right\">  </div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<hr>\n\t\t<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p>A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written as a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.</p><p>If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make an ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. The DC is 11. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.</p><p>Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and the scroll itself crumbles to dust.</p><p>A spell cast from this scroll has a save DC of 13 and an attack bonus of [[/r 1d20+5]] (+5).</p><p>A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 11 Intelligence (<span class=\"help--hover\" onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseOver(event, this, 713, {})\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseMove(event, this)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handlePredefinedMouseLeave(event, this)\" ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\">Arcana</span>) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"DMG","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Common","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":"","autoDestroy":true,"autoUse":true},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"scroll","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"tMPMWheY9FGPdLEs","sort":600001,"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"items.html","source":"DMG","hash":"spell%20scroll%20(1st%20level)_dmg","data":{"item":{"name":"Spell Scroll (1st Level)","source":"DMG","page":200,"srd":true,"type":"SC","tier":"minor","rarity":"common","entries":["A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written as a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost.","If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make an ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. The DC is 11. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect.","Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and the scroll itself crumbles to dust.","A spell cast from this scroll has a save DC of 13 and an attack bonus of {@hit 5}.","A wizard spell on a spell scroll can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a spell scroll, the copier must succeed on a DC 11 Intelligence ({@skill Arcana}) check. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the spell scroll is destroyed."],"lootTables":["Magic Item Table A"],"_isEnhanced":true,"_category":"Other","_typeListText":["scroll"],"_typeHtml":"scroll","_attunement":null,"_attunementCategory":"No","_fProperties":[],"_fMisc":["SRD","Magic"],"_fValue":0,"_fTier":["minor"],"_fIsMundane":false,"_fBonus":[],"_vType":"Scroll"}}},"magicitems":{"enabled":true,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"1","chargeType":"c1","destroy":true,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l","destroyCheck":"d1","destroyType":"dt1","spells":{"0":{"id":"3KYRG2wvveYrhy0A","name":"Healing Word (PHB)","pack":"world","img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-healing-word.jpg","baseLevel":"1","level":"1","consumption":"1","upcast":"1","upcastCost":"1","flatDc":false}}}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/tied-scroll.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mpKe8U66vmFLR6q5","name":"Cure Wounds (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A creature you touch regains a number of hit points equal to [[/r 1d8]] + your spellcasting ability modifier. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"107\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the healing increases by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","healing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":6100001,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"betterRolls5e":{"quickDamage":{"context":{"0":""},"value":{"0":true},"altValue":{"0":true}}}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-cure-wounds.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Underlantern","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This lantern looks perfectly ordinary for one very important reason; at the time of its creation, it was. However, it didn't stay that way for too long. The object originally belonged to a mortal who lived on the surface but fell into a deep fissure that opened up during an earthquake that wracked his small hillside village. He narrowly survived both the fall and the lengthy journey it took to make his way back to surface, guided in large part by this lantern. The sorry soul in question was believed to be dead by his friends and family for thirteen days before he emerged from a nearby cavern unscathed. As a result of this incident, he went on to live in infamy as a folk hero.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Underlantern is a lantern which a subterranean spirit took up residence in after its owner fell into their world after an accident which they were partly responsible for. Consequently, other such spirits are compulsively drawn to it like moths to a flame.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Adventuring Gear</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Underlantern can be used as a bullseye lantern.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Queer Light</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Blessed by underworld spirits, the Underlantern has the following unusual properties:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It requires no fuel to burn.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Any time you are using it, you hear strange whispers all around you if you're alone and underground.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Objects illuminated by it cast no shadow. Additionally, shadows with a CR of 1 or less cannot enter the area illuminated in bright light by the lantern and must use their turn to retreat from it if they do. If they're cornered or otherwise unable to move away from the lit area, such creatures take 2d4 force damage at the start of their turn.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you hold the lantern aloft and calls for underworld spirits to aid you, you can have the spirits fetch firewood, set up a campsite using your supplies, break down a campsite and disguise any signs of its existence, or seek out nearby sources of food or water.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":120,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d4","force"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":11100000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/lantern.png","effects":[],"_id":"mrLDJECbff3NOsIr"}
{"_id":"n4PuxiJYY9IE6KbP","name":"Contagion","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Your touch inflicts disease. Make a melee spell attack against a creature within your reach. On a hit, the target is <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#poisoned_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'poisoned_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >poisoned</a>.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>At the end of each of the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#poisoned_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'poisoned_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >poisoned</a> target's turns, the target must make a Constitution saving throw. If the target succeeds on three of these saves, it is no longer <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#poisoned_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'poisoned_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >poisoned</a>, and the spell ends. If the target fails three of these saves, the target is no longer <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#poisoned_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'poisoned_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >poisoned</a>, but choose one of the diseases below. The target is subjected to the chosen disease for the spell's duration.</p><p>Since this spell induces a natural disease in its target, any effect that removes a disease or otherwise ameliorates a disease's effects apply to it.</p><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"5\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Blinding Sickness.</span></span> <p>Pain grips the creature's mind, and its eyes turn milky white. The creature has disadvantage on Wisdom checks and Wisdom saving throws and is <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#blinded_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'blinded_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >blinded</a>.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"6\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Filth Fever.</span></span> <p>A raging fever sweeps through the creature's body. The creature has disadvantage on Strength checks, Strength saving throws, and attack rolls that use Strength.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"7\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Flesh Rot.</span></span> <p>The creature's flesh decays. The creature has disadvantage on Charisma checks and vulnerability to all damage.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"8\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Mindfire.</span></span> <p>The creature's mind becomes feverish. The creature has disadvantage on Intelligence checks and Intelligence saving throws, and the creature behaves as if under the effects of the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#confusion_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'confusion_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >confusion</a> spell during combat.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"9\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Seizure.</span></span> <p>The creature is overcome with shaking. The creature has disadvantage on Dexterity checks, Dexterity saving throws, and attack rolls that use Dexterity.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"10\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Slimy Doom.</span></span> <p>The creature begins to bleed uncontrollably. The creature has disadvantage on Constitution checks and Constitution saving throws. In addition, whenever the creature takes damage, it is <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#stunned_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'stunned_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >stunned</a> until the end of its next turn.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":7,"units":"day"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":""},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"msak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":5,"school":"nec","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":1100001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/rip-magenta-3.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"n9HLhA9l0ZTVBN5h","name":"Mage Armor (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You touch a willing creature who isn't wearing armor, and a protective magical force surrounds it until the spell ends. The target's base AC becomes 13 + its Dexterity modifier. The spell ends if the target dons armor or if you dismiss the spell as an action.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":8,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a piece of cured leather","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":9800001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-mage-armor.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"nGZR1EMOmZFG6OVy","name":"Tasha's Caustic Brew","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A stream of acid emanates from you in a line 30 feet long and 5 feet wide in a direction you choose. Each creature in the line must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or be covered in acid for the spell's duration or until a creature uses its action to scrape or wash the acid off itself or another creature. A creature covered in the acid takes [[/r 2d4]] acid damage at start of each of its turns.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"4\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 2d4]] for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"TCE","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d4","acid"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a bit of rotten food","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":13000001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[{"_id":"D2OsS6O30uEYkrkg","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Gantguide","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb01/gantguide.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"208\" /></span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This odd, box-like contraption has a strange, janky appearance to it. It resembles a child's toy, the kind of tacky knickknack one might find at a souvenir stall in the tourist quarter of some far-off metropolis, or else something quite old<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>the product of the archaic engineering of a bygone era. This is largely due to its unnecessarily large size, the cheap tin used in its construction, its bright and garish coloration, and the fact that loose components can be heard rattling around inside it.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Gantguide is a very special compass. Not only does it function exactly as a regular compass while in its default mode, but it can also be configured to locate shelter, sustenance, and water. It has letters across its face indicating the four cardinal directions of North, South, East, and West; as well as symbols of a fish leaping from a pool of water, a haunch of meat, a vine laden with berries, and a warm fireplace in the mouth of a cave.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Compass</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When pressure is applied to any of the four letters on the Gantguide, they descend into the device simultaneously as if all of them are being compressed. Once they are flush to its surface, they lock into place with a satisfying click and remain like this until one of the four symbols on the object is pressed instead. With the letters depressed, the Gantguide functions exactly as any other compass, its orienting arrow indicating which direction it is facing.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Guide</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Each of the four symbols on the Gantguide causes the device to enter a different mode of operation when activated. The modes and corresponding symbols are as follows:</span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">When the symbol depicting a fish leaping from a pool of water is compressed, the Gantguide's orienting arrow points towards a nearby body of water.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">When the symbol showing a haunch of meat is compressed, the Gantguide's orienting arrow points towards a nearby animal, such as a deer, hare, or goose.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">When the symbol indicating a vine laden with berries is compressed, the Gantguide's orienting arrow points towards nearby edible plant matter, such as berries, nuts, and fruit.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">When the symbol resembling a cave mouth is compressed, the Gantguide's orienting arrow points towards nearby refuges, such as natural shelters, settlements, or abandoned campsites.</span> <br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":6500000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"nJ67U5BrhI7iaFym"}
{"name":"Mesmerelda","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb07/mesmerelda.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"173\" height=\"256\" />\"Long favored by street performers, this gypsy blade was forged to dazzle audiences. A strip of bright red cloth has been wrapped around its hilt, winds through the back of its blade, and ends in little golden coins that dangle from it. These coins jingle and sway as the blade is swung, producing a sound similar to a coin purse being rattled.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Mesmerelda was originally carried by a troupe of traveling gypsies but in the years since it has been passed from sword dancer to magician, and beyond, in its travels, during which time it has been an integral part of many daring exhibitions of finesse and skill. Despite its storied history, the blade has never forgotten its roots amongst traveling folk.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Mesmerelda can be used as a scimitar.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Street Sword</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Mesmerelda has oft been used to wow crowds and part them with their hard earned money. You have advantage on Charisma (performance) checks that utilize the blade as part of an exhibition, workshop, or other kind of performance.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Loyalty</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The bonds of family are unusually strong amongst traveling folk. The blade cannot be used to deal weapon damage to your allies for as long as you consider them as such.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Trick Sword</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">As a trick sword, Mesmerelda can be used to perform the following illusions:</span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">It can wreath its blade in harmless flames.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">It can be used to leave an illusory wound on one of your allies, as if it has cut them. This wound lasts for an hour.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">It can appear to cut through wood, metal, or stone. The damage fades after ten minutes.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">When being quickly spun and twirled, it begins to blur itself, as if it is being moved faster than it actually is.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Held aloft and then released, it can appear to float for up to an hour.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A creature can discern that these effects are illusions with a successful DC 13 Intelligence (investigation) check; through the use of spellcasting, such as with <em>Detect Magic</em>; or with Truesight.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":20200000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"nPprAGVaOxB1rfkC"}
{"name":"Auburn Wind (Spear)","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This striking longbow is formed of cherry tree wood and sinew laminated together with a rich red lacquer that serves to protect its properties throughout use. Its top and bottom limbs have been overlaid with sharp, slightly curved oryx horns which elegantly match its contours.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The recurve is extremely flexible and hidden joints on the tip of each of its tillers allow its bowstring to be unfastened and removed. Without the tension that the bowstring provides, the bow straightens up to serve as a deadly, double-tipped spear.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Auburn Wind can be used as a @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.AgVmlRuQuEK3MoRi]{longbow (Autumn Wind)} or a spear.&nbsp;</span></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">It benefits from the&nbsp;</span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Finesse </span></em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">weapon </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">property when you use it as a spear&nbsp;</span></span>in addition to its usual properties, and it takes a bonus action to attach or remove its bowstring.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Fickle</strong>.&nbsp;</span></span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">Auburn Wind's identity is fluid, the object longing to change forms as often as possible. You gain a +1 bonus to the first attack roll you make with it after its bowstring has been attached or removed.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Protector of the wilds</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">Auburn Wind loves the wilds as much as it despises the slow, unrelenting march of civilization. You deal an additional 1d4 points of damage to creatures of a lawful alignment when attacking with it, and 1 less damage to unaligned creatures.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":"1d8 + @mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":true},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":2700000,"flags":{"mess":{"isBonusDamage":false,"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"ntrJVHkcGIC9t6WJ"}
{"name":"Polytheist's Chasuble","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This eminent chasuble serves as a fine example of the kind of lavish trappings worn by a priest or cleric over their other armor or vestments. What sets this particular chasuble apart from other such garments is its ability to magically alter its appearance to best reflect the faith of the devout individual who wears it. For example, it might turn green and present with detailed floral patterns to reflect an alignment with a god of the natural world, or assume a more muted and reserved tone or become featureless for deities with little interest in materialistic things or pursuits of the flesh.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The garment was created in a polytheistic chapel that venerated many different faiths, rather than honoring just a single deity. Each night its revered founder&mdash;a madcap eccentric, but a pillar of the community nonetheless</span></em><em>&mdash;</em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">would choose one faith and write a sermon about their dogma. Her belief was that every doctrine had value, and that it was folly to devote oneself in the service of any single deity in light of there being an entire pantheon of similarly powerful beings.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Symbol of Worship</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Polytheist's Chasuble can ably serve a priest of any faith. When you attune to these sacred vestments, they change to resemble those befitting an ordained minister of your chosen deity.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Convert (1/Day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While a creature adorned in the </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Polytheist's Chasuble no doubt has a faith of their own, the priestly apparel can help them secure favor with other gods. Once per day, you can swap one of your domain spells for a domain spell belonging to a different domain as an action. In order to do so, you must be a cleric. The Polytheist's Chasuble changes to resemble the colors and livery of a deity linked to your chosen domain or generic robes befitting any deity when you do.</span> When you complete a long rest, you revert back to your normal domain spell and the appearance of the chasuble also returns to normal.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":8300000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/clothing.png","effects":[],"_id":"ntsskqHQdARLUof8"}
{"name":"Voyournal","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"Measuring almost two foot from corner to corner, this large, leather-bound writing journal is most likely to be found in the cabin or quarters of a ship's captain. Its pages are thick and loose-fitting, while the front of the journal has the words, 'All journeys are significant, all chronicles important', embossed into its leather cover.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Voyournal is more than a mere logbook, ledger, or chronicle of events. It is a trusted ally and confidant to those who shoulder a burden of responsibility that they often cannot share with those around them. Secrets shared with the journal rarely come to light unless their inscriber is careless and reveals them themselves. The journal can also lead its owner to a strange island that travels the seas, a place where they can go to bury their secrets once and for all.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Hidden Destination</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A captain in possession of Voyournal always has an ace up their sleeve. It contains directions to a lost island that is concealed by magic and roams the ocean at random. This tropical retreat is 4 square miles in size and is configured similarly to a half moon. Sailing to the island takes 10 days irrespective of where a ship sets out from, as long as it does so with the island as its destination. Returning from the island takes only 3 days, but a ship can only return to its point of origin. You can automatically plot a course to the island if you have Voyournal, while any creature that has been there before or has received directions to it can navigate to it with a DC 20 check using navigator&rsquo;s tools, with the island reappearing at the same location as before. This check is made with disadvantage if they're using secondhand directions. A creature that hasn&rsquo;t been to it before and hasn't been given directions by someone who has cannot chart a course to the island without the use of magic.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Secret Journal</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">A captain harbors many secrets in the course of their duties, and Voyournal can be trusted to safeguard them all. You can write notes in it that appear only to you and creatures with Truesight. If you die or become unattuned to the book, your writings fade for good. Voyournal can be used as a diary or even as a spellbook.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Instant Recall (1/Year)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Whether Voyournal is somehow linked with the island it can guide a ship towards or not (see Hidden Destination) is a matter for some debate, however whether or not both items are magical is not. While on a boat, you can spend 1 hour reading aloud a lengthy passage of incomprehensible gibberish that appears on the back pages of Voyournal. At the completion of this reading, you and the vessel you are on vanish and reappear beside the island described in </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Hidden Destination</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">, along with your vessel's crew and cargo. Once completed, the words fade from the book and the ritual cannot be repeated until they reappear a year later, though the passage is never quite the same.</span></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":19000000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/book.png","effects":[],"_id":"nytfmiyigJTcEw8c"}
{"_id":"o4UIYQUrmoZ8oPO2","name":"Antipathy/Sympathy (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>This spell attracts or repels creatures of your choice. You target something within range, either a Huge or smaller object or creature or an area that is no larger than a 200-foot cube. Then specify a kind of intelligent creature, such as red dragons, goblins, or vampires. You invest the target with an aura that either attracts or repels the specified creatures for the duration. Choose antipathy or sympathy as the aura's effect.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"100\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Antipathy.</span></span> <p>The enchantment causes creatures of the kind you designated to feel an intense urge to leave the area and avoid the target. When such a creature can see the target or comes within 60 feet of it, the creature must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#frightened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'frightened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >frightened</a>. The creature remains <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#frightened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'frightened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >frightened</a> while it can see the target or is within 60 feet of it. While <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#frightened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'frightened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >frightened</a> by the target, the creature must use its movement to move to the nearest safe spot from which it can't see the target. If the creature moves more than 60 feet from the target and can't see it, the creature is no longer <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#frightened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'frightened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >frightened</a>, but the creature becomes <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#frightened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'frightened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >frightened</a> again if it regains sight of the target or moves within 60 feet of it.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"101\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Sympathy.</span></span> <p>The enchantment causes the specified creatures to feel an intense urge to approach the target while within 60 feet of it or able to see it. When such a creature can see the target or comes within 60 feet of it, the creature must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or use its movement on each of its turns to enter the area or move within reach of the target. When the creature has done so, it can't willingly move away from the target.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If the target damages or otherwise harms an affected creature, the affected creature can make a Wisdom saving throw to end the effect, as described below.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"102\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Ending the Effect.</span></span> <p>If an affected creature ends its turn while not within 60 feet of the target or able to see it, the creature makes a Wisdom saving throw. On a successful save, the creature is no longer affected by the target and recognizes the feeling of repugnance or attraction as magical. In addition, a creature affected by the spell is allowed another Wisdom saving throw every 24 hours while the spell persists.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><p>A creature that successfully saves against this effect is immune to it for 1 minute, after which time it can be affected again.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"hour","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"day"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":8,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"either a lump of alum soaked in vinegar for the antipathy effect or a drop of honey for the sympathy effect","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":5100001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-antipathysympathy.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"oLZENr6EJP9myr0L","name":"Wrathful Smite (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>The next time you hit with a melee weapon attack during this spell's duration, your attack deals an extra [[/r 1d6]] psychic damage. Additionally, if the target is a creature, it must make a Wisdom saving throw or be <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#frightened_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'frightened_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >frightened</a> of you until the spell ends. As an action, the creature can make a Wisdom check against your spell save DC to steel its resolve and end this spell.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"self","type":"self"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6","psychic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":4200001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-wrathful-smite.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Hatanaka","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb09/hatanaka.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"256\" />\"Between its black leather, gold trim, and red fabric detailing, this dark kabuto is impressive and imposing on its own. However, it's even more captivating when worn, doubly so if worn by a master swordsman with the expertise to bring out its best. A creature that places the helm on their head vanishes a moment later as a full-body iyozane in the same style as the kabuto forms over their flesh. As the last of the armor appears, a mengu also takes form, covering their face and hiding their identity entirely.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Hatanaka originally belonged to a merchant who wore it to protect his identity, unwilling to allow his own misgivings with a local crime triad to negatively affect his business, loved ones, or standing in the community. Safely hidden behind his mask, the merchant was able to confront the triad's operatives over many months, eventually driving them from the city where he resided. He didn't stop there either, putting other such clandestine organizations on notice, ending protection rackets, and guaranteeing justice for the downtrodden. The merchant became known as the lonely swordsman and though he eventually disappeared, reported sightings of him continue to surface periodically.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Hatanaka can be used as lamellar.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong style=\"font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification: Lamellar.</strong><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"> Rules for lamellar armor can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Master Mover</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Hatanaka is perfectly formed to not impede its wearer's movements or restrict their motions. While wearing it, you can use Strength in place of Dexterity when making an Acrobatics check and Dexterity in place of Strength when making an Athletics check.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Sprinter</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Master swordsmen strike swiftly and know to retreat with equal haste. While wearing Hatanaka, you can move up to an additional 10 foot when taking the Dash action.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Secret Assassin</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The lonely swordsman appears when those in need call for him. When not worn, Hatanaka appears only as a kabuto. However, you slip the helm on, the rest of the suit of armor appears over you, covering your skin and any clothes that you're wearing and absorbing any other armor that you're wearing into it. Additionally, a mengu forms over your face, protecting your identity. While wearing Hatanaka, your identity is harder to determine. Creatures who witness you have disadvantage on checks made to identify you based on your body type, movements, or voice.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":30,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":14,"type":"medium","dex":2},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":5300000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/medium-armor.png","effects":[],"_id":"oZ5ySfHj61WJrXQd"}
{"name":"Abrecartas","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This lavish letter opener has a grip formed of sleek black leather, while the rest of its metal frame resembles a long thin stiletto. The knife is actually made of white gold though it could easily be mistaken for silver. A unique blessing of the blade is that its tip turns an inky soot color when it comes in contact with dangerous contaminants. This peculiar trait makes it an excellent tool for those in public office, who might make powerful enemies themselves just as easily as they could be caught up in the assassination plots of those they work for.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Abrecartas served in a royal court for many years, employed by the principal scribe there to open the queen's mail. The queen was obsessed with the notion that someone was planning a coup, and had all of her mail and food pre-checked by her servants before it came anywhere near her. As it turned out the queen&rsquo;s paranoia was justified and Abrecartas was instrumental in preventing two fatal poisonings. Later the letter opener was itself stolen and replaced with a replica in the run up to a third, and ultimately successful, assassination attempt.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Abrecartas can be used as a dagger.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Letter Opener</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Abrecartas is the able tool of a king or queen's letter opener, and is rarely far from their side. It can be gently waved over a letter or envelope to prepare it for presentation to a monarch. The enchanted blade smooths out wrinkles and creases, reseals cuts and tears, and removes water stains and ink runs as if the parchment had </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Mending </span></em><span class=\"fontstyle2\">cast upon it. Letters affected in this way retain all intended words and images placed upon them.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Poison Prescience</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Only the foolish or reckless could forget that even the most popular kings and queens have enemies. You can detect the presence of diseases or poisons on objects and creatures simply by touching the tip or flat of Abrecartas to them. Should the blade detect either hazard its tip turns an inky soot color.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Poison Protection</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Despite the best intentions, sometimes things go wrong. You gain a +1d4 bonus on checks made to resist or overcome poisons and diseases while you are wielding Abrecartas or it is about your person.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":300000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"oi5HhOP56uQYGCr3"}
{"name":"Hunter's Vardo","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This plush living wagon sits atop four wooden cartwheels and is lightweight enough to be pulled by a horse, mule, or similar beast of burden. Its exterior walls are red and lined with lavish golden scrollwork filigree beneath the cart's teal canvas roof, which curves to form its 12-foot-high ceiling. A set of steps leads up into its entrance and, despite its cosy size, its interior manages to provide a surprising number of homely conveniences.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">As its name suggests, the Hunter's Vardo has things to offer beyond the interests of common travelers or wealthy holidaymakers. Filled with magical charms, fetishes, and other wards against fiends; witch, demon, vampire, and other hunters of the supernatural will find it well prepared to serve as their base of operations in the ongoing war against evil.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Stalwart Steeds</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">It is not uncommon for the owner of the Hunter's Vardo to need to make a speedy getaway. Horses or other beasts of burden bridled to it have advantage on checks made to resist fear and prevent gaining levels of exhaustion, and cannot be startled.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Warded Wagon</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Magical fetishes and powerful charms ward the Hunter's Vardo against incursion by those who do not belong, as well as their unwholesome depredations. Creatures of the fiend and undead types cannot willingly enter it by nonmagical means without first&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">making a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw. On a failure, they cannot attempt to enter again until the following dawn. Additionally, creatures within the Hunter's Vardo cannot be charmed, frightened, or possessed by creatures of the fiend or undead types while they remain within it.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Hunter's Refuge</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Hunter's Vardo is warded to protect the secrets of its owner from those ignorant of the monsters of the night. Its interior magically appears as that of a perfectly ordinary, mundane coach unless a creature uses an action to inspect its contents and succeeds on a DC 13 Intelligence (investigation) check.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Truesight</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&nbsp;and magic spells</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&nbsp;can also reveal the wagon's true interior. Once a creature has seen through the illusion, it is no longer affected by it.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":400,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Baubles","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":20800000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/vessel.png","effects":[],"_id":"omxbWg4RReOzDv1A"}
{"name":"Slimestone","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"On its own, this amorphous, shifting black mass seems harmless&mdash;merely an inorganic slime that possesses a kind of surface tension due to its own innate magnetic field. However, the ooze also responds to external electromagnetic stimuli of a very specific frequency, the exact frequency generated by the small obsidian stone that accompanies it. A creature holding this stone is able to give the sludge form, function, and focus.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Without the direction of a mind, both the slime and stone components of the Slimestone are useless, the slime an inert blob and the stone a dejected piece of rock. However, with a keen intellect at the helm, the pair come to life, the slime forming geometric shapes or imitating the form of humanoids and monsters&mdash;either animated or in a statue-like fashion&mdash;, dancing or lapping away happily, or else moving about its environment. Able to absorb moisture, dust motes, and other particles from the atmosphere and add these to its mass, the slime is able to grow from its usual size&mdash;about the size of a chicken<em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&mdash;</em>to the size of a barrel or crate. However, the concentration required by its operator to maintain such a larger mass isn't sustainable for very long.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Tiny Slime</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Slimestone's slime is useless and inert until an intellect generates an electromagnetic field of the right wavelength and of sufficient force to drive it to purpose. While holding its stone, you can have the slime imitate any shape you desire as a bonus action, however it remains a Tiny creature, has a movement speed of 10 foot, and an Armor Class of 13. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The slime contracts itself into a solid rock that weighs 4 lbs and is the size of an apple if it is hit with an attack while it is Tiny sized or you will it to do so. It remains in this form until you will it to return to its slime form.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 14px; font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Tiny Slim.</strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 14px; font-style: italic;\"> Statistical information necessary to use the Tiny Slime in combat can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.monsters.zCMSsFW0SN4a7PwZ]{Tiny Slime}.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Substantial Slime (1/Day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">With no small amount of effort, the mind controlling the Slimestone can drive the creature to grow to a dangerous size and mass. As an action, you can will the slime can increase from Tiny to Medium size once per day. It can maintain this size for up to 10 minutes. You must use your Concentration to maintain the slime's increased size. While enlarged, the slime is affected in the following ways:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Its Armor Class increases to 18, however creatures have advantage on any attacks they make against it that deal lightning damage.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If it should be hit with an attack while Medium size, </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">it immediately reverts back to its Tiny size.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">It acts on your turn and its movement speed increases to 15 feet.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">As a bonus action, you can will it to make two melee slam attacks against a creature within 5 feet of it. The bonus to hit with these is 2 + your proficiency bonus. On a hit, each slam deals 1d6 + 2 bludgeoning damage. Additionally, if the slime hits with its first attack, it has disadvantage on its second. If it misses on its first attack, it has advantage on its second.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":18100000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"p6MSmL384hXRgTVX"}
{"_id":"pHjpT0nZD3FmYBQo","name":"Potion of Invulnerability","permission":{"default":0,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3,"OGI1ZmNiNjZhNWIz":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Potion, minor tier, rare</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>For 1 minute after you drink this potion, you have resistance to all damage. The potion's syrupy liquid looks like liquefied iron.</p>\n<p><strong>Found on:</strong> Magic Item Table C</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"DMG pg. 188","quantity":1,"weight":0.1,"price":300,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"charges","autoDestroy":true,"autoUse":true},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"potion","attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"tMPMWheY9FGPdLEs","sort":100001,"flags":{"dynamiceffects":{"equipActive":true,"alwaysActive":false,"effects":[{"modSpecKey":"data.traits.dr.value","value":"fire","mode":"+","targetSpecific":false,"id":1,"itemId":"AENCWgyRd4Kp5gxG","active":true,"_targets":[]}]},"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""},"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/items/potions/magic-yellow.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"0PK3O2lPNWG9uWO6","flags":{"dae":{"transfer":true,"stackable":false,"specialDuration":["None"],"macroRepeat":"none"},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"aura":"None","radius":null}},"changes":[{"key":"data.traits.dr.all","value":"","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":9,"startRound":null,"startTurn":1},"icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/items/potions/major-red.jpg","label":"Potion of Invulnerability","tint":"","transfer":true}]}
{"_id":"pS6BPpzu4dGiWBkQ","name":"Spiritual Weapon (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You create a floating, spectral weapon within range that lasts for the duration or until you cast this spell again. When you cast the spell, you can make a melee spell attack against a creature within 5 feet of the weapon. On a hit, the target takes force damage equal to [[/r 1d8]] + your spellcasting ability modifier.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the weapon up to 20 feet and repeat the attack against a creature within 5 feet of it.</p><p>The weapon can take whatever form you choose. Clerics of deities who are associated with a particular weapon (as St. Cuthbert is known for his mace and Thor for his hammer) make this spell's effect resemble that weapon.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"99\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] for every two slot levels above 2nd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":5,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"square"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"msak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":2,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":5000001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-spiritual-weapon.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"paFlyiUavxh0uQZO","name":"Fast Friends","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>When you need to make sure something gets done, you can't rely on vague promises, sworn oaths, or binding contracts of employment. When you cast this spell, choose one humanoid within range that can see and hear you, and that can understand you. The creature must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> by you for the duration. While the creature is <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> in this way, it undertakes to perform any services or activities you ask of it in a friendly manner, to the best of its ability.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>You can set the creature new tasks when a previous task is completed, or if you decide to end its current task. If the service or activity might cause harm to the creature, or if it conflicts with the creature's normal activities and desires, the creature can make another Wisdom saving throw to try to end the effect. This save is made with advantage if you or your companions are fighting the creature. If the activity would result in certain death for the creature, the spell ends.</p><p>When the spell ends, the creature knows it was <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#charmed_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'charmed_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >charmed</a> by you.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"158\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 3rd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"AI","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":3100001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/scroll-unfurled.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Yippy-yahooza","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb09/yippy-yahooza.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"154\" />\"This brightly-colored bazooka has been cleverly designed to resemble a many-legged, moustached parade dragon and would look right at home in the midst of any festival or extravagant celebration. The gaudy object is loaded from the rear and an impish mask that's modeled after a moon swivels out from its side and acts as a face guard for anyone operating the unconventional firearm. Traditionally, such an object might be used to propel fireworks, however, thanks to the powerful enchantment that hangs over its firing chamber, it's also very efficient at launching arrows and other missiles too.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Attunement Perk</strong>. Any creature can use Yippy-Yahooza to make ranged attacks as per Supersized Shots, but you can only add your proficiency bonus to these if you are attuned to it.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Supersized Shots</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Shots fired from Yippy-yahooza are formidable indeed, as ammunition loaded into it expands magically within its firing chamber. Ammunition loaded into it is affected in the following ways:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Arrows deal 1d10 piercing damage on a hit, have a range of 80/320 feet, and ignore up to 1 point of a target's armor class that results from wearing armor.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Blowgun needles deal 1d6 piercing damage on a hit, have a range of 50/200 feet, and ignore up to 3 points of a target's armor class that results from natural armor.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Crossbow bolts deal 1d12 piercing damage on a hit, have a range of 60/240 feet, and their critical strike range increases to 18-20 when used to make attacks against objects.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Sling bullets deal 1d8 bludgeoning damage on a hit, have a range of 20/60 feet, and can be used to demolish stubborn doors. Instead of making a ranged attack with it, you can attempt to use Yippy-yahooza to break down a door, granting you advantage on a Strength check to do so and allowing you to do so at distances of up to 40 foot.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":24,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialR","properties":{"amm":true,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":true,"lgt":false,"lod":true,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":19100000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-ranged-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"pbeu5LqxH9bH9aSn"}
{"name":"Beastly Kanabō","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Loosely organized rows of metal studs protrude from this hefty wooden kanabō, forming lines that run up the implement's shaft</span></em><em>&mdash;</em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">many of which are dented through years of use and misuse. The wood around them is also battered and even splintered in places. Stains left from dried blood tarnish the wood, though the weapon is still more than serviceable when it comes to cracking skulls. The kanabō is most notable for its size, large and unwieldy even for a full-blooded orc.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Beastly Kanabō briefly belonged to an oni who used it to smash into the houses of a remote village and steal away food and valuables while the occupants quivered in fear. One day the oni besieged the village's inn while a traveling warrior was staying there. Incensed, the warrior beat the oni into submission, took his weapon, and gave it to the townsfolk. He instructed them to build a wall around their village, and then to take the weapon and place it against the gate. He said this would stop the oni returning after he left, and he wasn't wrong.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Beastly Kanabō can be used as a greatclub.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Enormous.</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Beastly Kanabō is unusually heavy and cumbersome to wield. It gains the </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">Heavy </span></em><span class=\"fontstyle2\">weapon property.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Mighty</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Beastly Kanabō is mightier than most doors. As an action, you can wedge it against any door that opens towards you. While it is placed in this way, the DC of any checks made to break down the door from the other side increase by 3 and the door cannot be opened without being broken down, even if it has a lock or locking mechanism and it is disengaged. Another creature beside you can remove the </span>Beastly kanabō if they're adjacent to it and on your side of the door as an action, however it requires a DC 13 Strength (athletics) check for them to do so.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Flattened</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Many careless creatures have been squashed by the Beastly Kanabō. Your attacks with it deal an additional 1d4 damage against creatures that are at least one size smaller than you.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Shattered</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Brittle creatures should be careful in the presence of the Beastly Kanabō, lest they be shattered by its wielder. You have advantage on attacks made with it against creatures that have vulnerability to bludgeoning damage.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Eastern Riches","quantity":1,"weight":13,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8 + @mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":true,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":true,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":2300000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"peka3sq8UxWsWz2B"}
{"_id":"pfI93wZQohr0yL94","name":"Command (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You speak a one-word command to a creature you can see within range. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or follow the command on its next turn. The spell has no effect if the target is undead, if it doesn't understand your language, or if your command is directly harmful to it.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>Some typical commands and their effects follow. You might issue a command other than one described here. If you do so, the DM determines how the target behaves. If the target can't follow your command, the spell ends.</p><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"108\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Approach.</span></span> <p>The target moves toward you by the shortest and most direct route, ending its turn if it moves within 5 feet of you.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"109\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Drop.</span></span> <p>The target drops whatever it is holding and then ends its turn.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"110\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Flee.</span></span> <p>The target spends its turn moving away from you by the fastest available means.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"111\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Grovel.</span></span> <p>The target falls <a href=\"https://5e.tools/conditionsdiseases.html#prone_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'conditionsdiseases.html', 'PHB', 'prone_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >prone</a> and then ends its turn.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"112\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Halt.</span></span> <p>The target doesn't move and takes no actions. A flying creature stays aloft, provided that it is able to do so. If it must move to stay aloft, it flies the minimum distance needed to remain in the air.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"113\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can affect one additional creature for each slot level above 1st. The creatures must be within 30 feet of each other when you target them.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"round"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"enc","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":6200001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-command.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Firstrike","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This small wooden tinderbox looks quite mundane. However, when it is doused or submerged in water and then removed from it, it becomes clear that it is anything but ordinary. Rather than absorbing the water, it simply runs off the surface of this unadorned matchbox like it might a duck's back. Curious adventurers might be forgiven for theorizing that it has been treated with some kind of oil, resin, or sap-like substance, but it has not. As is often the case, the truth is far weirder and more fascinating.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In reality, Firstrike came into existence as the result of a chance encounter between a lost dwarven miner and a wish-granting efreeti. The efreeti had become trapped deep below the earth but the wandering dwarf freed it and, in return, it offered him a single wish. The dwarf</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><em>&mdash;</em></span><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">cold, tired, and hungry<span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&mdash;</span>hastily traded his wish away for warmth and then spent several hours pleading for sleep and sustenance as well; long before it ever occurred to him to simply ask to be returned home. For its part, the efreeti was grateful enough to the dwarf to be willing to honor such requests but it didn't have the power to grant further wishes so soon. The dwarf perished shortly thereafter, but not before the efreeti had created Firstrike.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Astounding Results</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Starting fires with Firstrike produces phenomenal results, this is because:</span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">So long as Firstrike isn't actively submerged in water, it can always be used to start or ignite fires and never runs out of matches. It isn't affected by rain, wind, or wetness around it; and it can ignite damp kindling or soggy grass as easily as dry timber.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A fire started by Firstrike is much less likely to go out by accident or unintentionally. They tend to burn until they run out of fuel or until they are stamped out deliberately, even in extreme weather conditions.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A fire started by Firstrike produces half as much smoke as normal and only emits half as strong an odor. This means that Wisdom (perception) checks made to spot them or smell them are made with disadvantage, and a creature's passive Perception score when it comes to noticing such a fire is calculated with disadvantage.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Fires started by Firstrike only consume fuel at half the rate as other fires, meaning that they burn for twice as long</span>.<br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":5900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"pm7wML020LeZjQ5v"}
{"name":"Destrier's Joust","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"The exterior facade of this impressive lance is formed of ash wood while a steel rod runs through its core, providing the object with a strength that belies its relatively light weight. A series of dozens of small symbols have been inked along its length in various styles and colors. The object is prized by men-at-arms, knights, and chevaliers for its use in duels, jousting tournaments, and settling matters of honor.</span></em><br /><br /><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">To merely possess the Destrier's Joust was once a great honor. Along with a sizeable pot, the lance was the grand prize of a jousting tournament where combatants of great skill and cunning would gather and compete </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">every four years. The tradition was that, whoever won the tournament would be allowed to mark the lance with their family crest and keep it until the next competition, whereupon they would return with it and use it in the tournament. Conditionally, were a rider injured or slain between tournaments, or otherwise unable to return to compete, their next of kin could return in their stead and compete in their place.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Destrier's Joust can be used as a lance.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Professional Jouster</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When it comes to winning jousting tournaments, the faster rider often prevails. While mounted and wielding the Destrier's Joust, you have a +2 bonus to your Initiative.</span></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Dragoon. </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Destrier's Joust is perfectly manufactured for use in mounted combat. It confers the following benefits:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While mounted and wielding it, you gain a +1 bonus to attack rolls against other mounted combatants.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While mounted and wielding it, your mount can move an additional 10 foot whenever the Dash action is taken.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While mounted and wielding it, you have advantage on any checks you make to remain mounted.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">While mounted and wielding it, once per round when you hit a creature with it that is also mounted, you can choose to have that creature attempt a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw. On a fail, the target is knocked off their mount, landing prone in a space within 5 feet of it.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":10,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d12 + @mod","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":true,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":true,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":100000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"ppVHGGoaDqxbkRgW"}
{"_id":"prj3iq9IH8AraHIi","name":"Goodberry","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Up to ten berries appear in your hand and are infused with magic for the duration. A creature can use its action to eat one berry. Eating a berry restores 1 hit point, and the berry provides enough nourishment to sustain a creature for one day.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The berries lose their potency if they have not been consumed within 24 hours of the casting of this spell.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":""},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["","healing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a sprig of mistletoe","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":1200001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/leaf-acid-1.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"pypY2Tq1OrDBzjQw","name":"Ray of Frost (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A frigid beam of blue-white light streaks toward a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, it takes [[/r 1d8]] cold damage, and its speed is reduced by 10 feet until the start of your next turn.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The spell's damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] when you reach 5th level ([[/r 2d8]]), 11th level ([[/r 3d8]]), and 17th level ([[/r 4d8]]).</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rsak","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8","cold"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"cantrip","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":5800001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-ray-of-frost.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"q841aA0BnSthP0cT","name":"Haste","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Choose a willing creature that you can see within range. Until the spell ends, the target's speed is doubled, it gains a +2 bonus to AC, it has advantage on Dexterity saving throws, and it gains an additional action on each of its turns. That action can be used only to take the <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#attack_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'attack_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Attack</a> (one weapon attack only), <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#dash_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'dash_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Dash</a>, <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#disengage_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'disengage_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Disengage</a>, <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#hide_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'hide_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Hide</a>, or <a href=\"https://5e.tools/actions.html#use%20an%20object_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'actions.html', 'PHB', 'use%20an%20object_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Use an Object</a> action.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>When the spell ends, the target can't move or take actions until after its next turn, as a wave of lethargy sweeps over it.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":0,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a shaving of licorice root","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":300001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/haste-royal-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"q8KbtleoNV2dJh5q","name":"Burning Hands","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>As you hold your hands with thumbs touching and fingers spread, a thin sheet of flames shoots forth from your outstretched fingertips. Each creature in a 15-foot cone must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes [[/r 3d6]] fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The fire ignites any flammable objects in the area that aren't being worn or carried.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1040\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d6]] for each slot level above 1st.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":15,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":0,"long":0,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d6","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d6"},"spellType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"time":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"damageType":{"value":"","_deprecated":true},"concentration":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"ritual":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true},"prepared":{"value":null,"_deprecated":true}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":2800001,"flags":{},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/fog-orange-2.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Ripcord Harness & Chute","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"This curious item resembles a common rucksack, the kind that might be found adorning the back of any adventurer or traveler when encountered out in the wilds far from the comfort and relative safety of civilization. The primary indication that it is more than a mere haversack is the pull cord that hangs down from its right shoulder strap. This seemingly innocuous component of the item need only be firmly pulled for the pack to reveal its true purpose.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This bizarre item represents the latest innovation from serial inventor and wizard Lloyd Spelloyal. It's something that he's tentatively calling a Ripcord Harness &amp; Chute, because that title, while a little flat, succinctly summarizes its key design elements. Rejected names include; the Splat-Stopper, Satchel of Softlanding, and Jellyfish Balloon.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Parachute</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The Ripcord Harness &amp; Chute is a backpack which contains a large canvas webbing that acts as a parachute. It is deployed by pulling on its ripcord, which takes an action to do. Once used, it takes you one hour to repack the parachute for use again. In order to benefit from the parachute, you must be falling and be a Medium or Small creature. Once you deploy the parachute, you</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"> cease to increase the amount of falling damage that you'll take when you hit the ground immediately. Additionally, any accrued falling damage that you would have taken upon hitting the ground is reduced by 1d10 for every further 20 feet you fall. Starting from the </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">moment the parachute is deployed, you can choose to travel outward to a distance of half the height of your remaining fall as you descend, depending on the direction and strength of the wind. Lastly, while parachuting you can grab onto another falling Medium or Small creature if they are within 5 feet of you. If you do so, you both accrue falling damage at a rate of 1d10 per 20 feet fallen for the rest of your descent, instead of every 10 feet fallen.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Hauling Net</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The giant, dome-shaped canopy that the Ripcord Harness &amp; Chute deploys can be handy in other, less disastrous circumstances than just when falling from a cliff or mountainside. When the item's canvas net is deployed on the ground, or before being packed away after use, you can use it to collect items and objects that fill a 20 foot cube. You can then drag these belongings across the ground if you have sufficient strength to do so or are aided by those who do.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Spoils of War","quantity":1,"weight":14,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"weight","value":500,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":16900000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/backpack.png","effects":[],"_id":"q9Vm4XYfuciZCUPM"}
{"_id":"qMr3iUiWQ8swsuDI","name":"Cloudkill (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You create a 20-foot-radius sphere of poisonous, yellow-green fog centered on a point you choose within range. The fog spreads around corners. It lasts for the duration or until strong wind disperses the fog, ending the spell. Its area is heavily obscured.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>When a creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, that creature must make a Constitution saving throw. The creature takes [[/r 5d8]] poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. Creatures are affected even if they hold their breath or don't need to breathe.</p><p>The fog moves 10 feet away from you at the start of each of your turns, rolling along the surface of the ground. The vapors, being heavier than air, sink to the lowest level of the land, even pouring down openings.</p></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"141\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 5th.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":20,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":120,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d8","poison"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":5,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"level","formula":"1d8"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":10400001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-cloudkill.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Myrecloak","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb01/mirecloak.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"173\" height=\"256\" /></span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Despite its appearance, this dense, mottled tangle of vegetation is actually a cloak of sorts, and is warm, odorless, and dry inside. One would be forgiven for mistaking its </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">wearer for an organic abomination, a small shambling mound, or some other plant-type creature due to their appearance while wearing it. The garment itself seems to be steadily reducing to mulch, however it doesn't produce a composting smell. Not only is the cloak formed of many different types of growths, leaves, and vines, but it also seems to attract flies, frogs, and other small critters</span></span></em><em>&mdash;</em><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">many of whom attempt to nest in it.</span></span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Myrecloak wasn't constructed or designed by humanoid hands. Rather, it was discovered floating in the dankest depths of a quagmire. Legend has it that it has been lost or destroyed several times, but it always resurfaces in another bog or swamp sooner or later, awaiting rediscovery.\"</span></span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Blessings of the Bog</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Myrecloak is a powerful tool when worn by a creature qualified to make the most of its unusual blessings in its favored environment. Wearing it grants you the following benefits:</span></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Myrecloak protects your clothes from dampness, keeping you perfectly dry in wet or waterlogged conditions, even when fully submerged.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can hold your breath for an additional 10 minutes.</span> <br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You do not suffer the movement penalties of traversing difficult terrain if the terrain in question is a bog, swamp, or marsh.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your movements have no effect on water. For example, you don't cause audible splashing or sloshing sounds moving through it, and you don't create ripples when stepping in a puddle.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Myrecloak camouflages you while in bogs, swamps, or marshes. Beyond 120 foot, creatures have disadvantage on any Wisdom (perception) checks made to spot you using sight alone, and their passive Perception score is also calculated with disadvantage for the same purposes.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":8400000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/cloak.png","effects":[],"_id":"qfSn6WmQ4vQ1NtFc"}
{"name":"Netcropolis","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Despite any attempts to clean or sterilize it, a foul stench hangs thick over this accursed net. The odor that permeates it is matched visually by a hazy smog that wafts from its fibrous surface, lingering just around it as if clinging to its form. Though this smog is omnipresent around the net itself, it doesn't build up to oppressive or overwhelming levels, even in a relatively small or confined space. Perhaps more striking and unusual though, are the churned up bits and pieces of fish that line the sides of the net, their bodies writhing while their heads snap at anything that comes within range. These fish are corporeal undead and visibly in a bad state of decomposition. Should a creature remove any from the net, they immediately become spectral, reappearing in the net a moment later as corporeal undead once more. Other than the complete destruction of the net itself, these pesky piscine phantoms seem to be impossible to exorcise permanently.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Netcropolis can be used as a net.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Questionable Contents</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Snapping, zombified fish fill this net, chomping at creatures trapped within it. A creature caught in Netcropolis is distracted and has disadvantage on checks made to escape the net. Other creatures don&rsquo;t have disadvantage on helping them out of it. A creature trapped within the net takes 1d4 necrotic damage at the start of its turn.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Awful Edibles</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Aside from its foul aura, Netcropolis is otherwise a very decent net and an effective tool for fishermen. You have advantage on any checks you make using it to catch fish. However, any fish caught within the net are spoiled by the necrotic effect that permeates the its interior, and are riddled with bite marks from the fervent undead in the net. Fish ensnared by Netcropolis can sustain a creature exactly as they normally would, however a creature that eats fish caught in it must attempt a DC 16 Constitution saving throw, becoming poisoned for 1d4 hours on a fail.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":15,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"rwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialR","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":true,"thr":true,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":8600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/martial-ranged-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"qsQZjbZF1abKLTFT"}
{"_id":"r0kWDAP3isbV9PNn","name":"Poison Spray (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You extend your hand toward a creature you can see within range and project a puff of noxious gas from your palm. The creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take [[/r 1d12]] poison damage.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>This spell's damage increases by [[/r 1d12]] when you reach 5th level ([[/r 2d12]]), 11th level ([[/r 3d12]]), and 17th level ([[/r 4d12]]).</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":10,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d12","poison"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"con","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"cantrip","formula":"1d12"}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":4800001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-poison-spray.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"King of Trumpets","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"tool","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"Despite its peculiar and rather unconventional origins, this towering trumpet has been carried by many knights, chevaliers, and bannerets over the years. It was actually forged from a mold of the proboscis of Ssslurp, a nasty menace once referred to as 'the King of Stirges' by the townstead it menaced. Using the stirge's long, tubular protrusion as a foundation for their musical wizardry, a pair adventurous and industrious bard's created the object from bass. Valveless, the instrument relies on the vocal range of its player to make full use of its harmonics, assuming they understand how to properly lip its embouchure to produce just the right acoustics. Thanks to the instrument's unusually long body, it produces very deep, resonance sounds that naturally stir and rouse those who hear it. Its dimensions also afford it sufficient length to allow for a ceremonial banner to be hung from it, all of which serves to provide it with a sense of grandeur that elevates it from a mere wind instrument.\"</em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-weight: 400;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Musical Instrument</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-weight: 400;\">The King of Trumpets can be used as a horn.</span></strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Proclamation (1/day)</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Blessed be those who speak truth, and blessed be those who recognize and decry falsehoods. As an action, you can blow the King of Trumpets and utter a short sentence; either uttering a sweeping statement of truth or a boastful lie. Creatures within 30 foot of you who hear your proclamation must attempt a DC 10 Wisdom saving throw to determine whether or not they believe your statement or find it to be false. Creatures who guess incorrectly take 1d8 thunder damage. Creatures who know if the statement is true or false before it is uttered automatically fail their check.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Crier</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Splendid and grand, the King of Trumpets is not the kind of object to be born by someone who shies away from the limelight. Your voice is amplified while you hold it, doubling its volume and the distance from which you can be heard. Additionally, while holding it and making Charisma (performance) checks related to public speaking, you can roll 1d4 and add the result to your roll.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Rabble-Rouser</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Just as the king of stirges rarely failed in its quest for blood, the King of Trumpets too thirsts for victory. As a bonus action, you can nominate a specific creature that you can see as the object of your ire. The next attack against the target that occurs before the start of your next turn benefits from a +1 bonus to its attack and damage rolls.</span></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"ability":"cha","chatFlavor":"","proficient":0,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":1300000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/instrument.png","effects":[],"_id":"r6Ar4qSu1MeK0CTj"}
{"_id":"r72ovR9l8Ev5ayFn","name":"Fly","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You touch a willing creature. The target gains a flying speed of 60 feet for the duration. When the spell ends, the target falls if it is still aloft, unless it can stop the fall.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"497\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 3rd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a wing feather from any bird","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":12100001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-fly.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"uODzv3PBt8y8JWzJ","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-fly.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"rDyW10Fpxr4OdNU3","name":"Stoneskin","permission":{"default":0,"XE30TcnpPFgl2g1S":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This spell turns the flesh of a willing creature you touch as hard as stone. Until the spell ends, the target has resistance to nonmagical bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 278","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"level":4,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"Diamond dust worth 100 gp, which the spell consumes","consumed":true,"cost":100,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":null,"sort":600001,"flags":{"dynamiceffects":{"effects":[{"modSpecKey":"data.traits.dr.value","value":"physical","mode":"+","targetSpecific":false,"id":1,"itemId":"ccUx49HUGslLri7o","active":true,"_targets":[]}],"equipActive":false,"alwaysActive":false},"dae":{"activeEquipped":false,"alwaysActive":false}},"img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/protect-orange-2.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"fhvmjRblnjrDRxWO","flags":{"dae":{"transfer":false}},"changes":[{"key":"data.traits.dr.value","value":"physical","mode":0,"priority":0}],"duration":{},"icon":"systems/dnd5e/icons/spells/protect-orange-2.jpg","label":"Stoneskin","transfer":false}]}
{"_id":"rFsGx0iCdxuILq4D","name":"Flame Arrows","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You touch a quiver containing arrows or bolts. When a target is hit by a ranged weapon attack using a piece of ammunition drawn from the quiver, the target takes an extra [[/r 1d6]] fire damage. The spell's magic ends on a piece of ammunition when it hits or misses, and the spell ends when twelve pieces of ammunition have been drawn from the quiver.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"21\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the number of pieces of ammunition you can affect with this spell increases by two for each slot level above 3rd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"XGE","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"touch","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6","fire"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"trs","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":14400001,"flags":{"midi-qol":{"onUseMacroName":""}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/xge-flame-arrows.jpg","effects":[{"_id":"HADDIn4TSRSdfNLE","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":false,"specialDuration":[],"macroRepeat":"none","transfer":false},"ActiveAuras":{"isAura":false,"ignoreSelf":false,"hidden":false,"height":false,"alignment":"","type":"","aura":"None","radius":null,"save":"","savedc":null,"hostile":false,"onlyOnce":false,"time":"None"}},"changes":[{"key":"macro.execute","value":"\"Concentrating\" @actor","mode":0,"priority":20}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/xge-flame-arrows.jpg","label":"Concentrating","tint":"","transfer":false}]}
{"name":"Footpad Kicks","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb02/footpad-kicks.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"246\" height=\"256\" />\"The origin of this pair of bizarre clogs is a mystery. At a glance, they appear almost elven in design thanks to their slender curves, graceful filigree, and other minor flourishes, however the stark darkness of their coloration is unusual for elves who tend to prefer colors that are richer, warmer, and, often, bolder, over such drab and miserable shades. To some, this might suggest a drow influence, indicating that the shoes were conceived of and manufactured deep below the earth. However, as those familiar with drow design sensibilities would know, such objects would be far more likely to depict arachnids, or remain plain and utilitarian, than incorporate such an overtly leafy motif. Just to further complicate things, these obsidian slippers are buckled for adjustability&mdash;and thus sized to accommodate feet both smaller and larger than those of elves&mdash;, mounted on 2 foot stilts, and miraculously affixed to a pair of vibrant green lily pads.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Special Shoes</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Despite their unusual appearance, the Footpad Kicks have several noteworthy advantages over other footwear:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">They disperse the weight of their wearer. Your weight while wearing the Footpad Kicks is halved for the purposes of calculating how much pressure you place upon the ground when it comes to not falling through weak or fragile flooring, shattering ice or glass, or triggering pressure plates.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Thick and hardy, they are resilient to hooks, barbs, spikes, and a myriad of other hazards. You automatically negate the effects of ball bearings, caltrops, and other small, similar ground-level impediments wearing the Footdpad Kicks.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">They are surprisingly buoyant and don't immediately break the surface tension of water. If you step onto or walk on water on your turn while wearing the Footpad Kicks, you do not fall into it until your turn ends. You do, however, still take damage from hazards such as molten lava as normal.</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The footprints you leave while wearing the Footpad Kicks are quite unlike anything that occurs naturally or can be explained by the arcane. Your trail does not resemble conventional tracks and it is impossible to glean details about you by non-magical means from studying your footfall, such as your race, height, or weight. However, creatures have advantage on Wisdom (survival) checks made to follow your tracks.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Tools of the Trade","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":7300000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/boots.png","effects":[],"_id":"rRTrEc3lhC2pj1aD"}
{"name":"Garb of the Vigilante","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This complete leather outfit has been carefully constructed for the protection and utility of someone who has taken up the mantle of opposing the terrible creatures of the night. Its underlayer includes a tight leather jerkin that has been lined with enochian runes stitched into the fabric of its underside to ward against its wearer being corrupted by the very evils they seek to oppose. The rest of the suit is composed of a pair of trousers, gloves, boots, and a wide brimmed hat, each with adjustable buckled straps that tighten to fit its wearer safely and securely. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Over all of this fits a slightly oversized longcoat that almost reaches the wearer's ankles. This jacket is packed with an assortment of small pouches and holsters for the carrying of garlic, stakes, vials of holy water, ammunition, and most other implements a monster hunter might need to ply their trade.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Garb of the Vigilante can be used as leather armor.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Delivered from Evil</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Garb of the Vigilante has been an invaluable aid to many aspiring champions of the light, though even with its assistance many have still fallen into shadow. You have advantage on checks made to avoid becoming afflicted by lycanthropy and vampirism while wearing it. Additionally, if you have been afflicted with lycanthropy or vampirism already, you can suppress your lycanthrophic or vampiric nature entirely while wearing it.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>No Quarter</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">A soldier in the fight against evil wearing the Garb of the Vigilante has certain advantages when it comes to preventing their sworn enemies from escaping or revealing their true strength. If you hit a lycanthrope or vampire with a weapon attack while wearing it, they cannot use their Shapechanger feature to change form until the start of your next turn.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Silvered Shots</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Blessed be the bullets that belong to a warrior who chooses to don the Garb of the Vigilante. Ammunition fired by you while wearing it counts as being silvered for the purposes of overcoming damage resistance.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":10,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":11,"type":"light","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":4600000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/light-armor.png","effects":[],"_id":"rasqsYTNrpbd3n5t"}
{"_id":"rfWuQY1hLKF3G3WG","name":"Sanctuary (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You ward a creature within range against attack. Until the spell ends, any creature who targets the warded creature with an attack or a harmful spell must first make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature must choose a new target or lose the attack or spell. This spell doesn't protect the warded creature from area effects, such as the explosion of a <a href=\"https://5e.tools/spells.html#fireball_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'spells.html', 'PHB', 'fireball_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >fireball</a>.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>If the warded creature makes an attack, casts a spell that affects an enemy, or deals damage to another creature, this spell ends.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":1,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"a small silver mirror","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":11200001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-sanctuary.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Astrolabium","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb06/astrolabium.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"255\" height=\"256\" />\"This large, circular disc is an ornate inclinometer, the kind used by astronomers and navigators to identify specific stars and constellations, determine the time of day, establish the angle or steepness of a slope, or correctly identify their present location. While the inside of the object is plain and uninteresting, its exterior facade is far more intriguing. Its surface features several moving components which are used to impart useful information&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">to an individual qualified to interpret their meanings, though few not versed in the object's purpose are able to do so. It is formed of reinforced metal and strong enough to serve as a buckler, while its rim has been sharpened for use as a weapon.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\" />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Astrolabium can be used as a chakram.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Rule Clarification, Chakram.</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"> Rules for chakrams can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Armor</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Astrolabium can be used as a shield.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Astrolabe</strong>. A</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">strolabium can be used as an astrolabe. You can add your proficiency bonus to Intelligence checks made to identify celestial bodies, assess the pitch of a slope, measure the passage of time, or triangulate your position while using it.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Sagely Impedimenta","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":20,"long":60,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6 + @mod","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":2,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":15600000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/shield.png","effects":[],"_id":"rgYwBtQNU04sbMHq"}
{"_id":"rsM7s7WFTf9pnJ2u","name":"Reincarnate","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You touch a dead humanoid or a piece of a dead humanoid. Provided that the creature has been dead no longer than 10 days, the spell forms a new adult body for it and then calls the soul to enter that body. If the target's soul isn't free or willing to do so, the spell fails.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The magic fashions a new body for the creature to inhabit, which likely causes the creature's race to change. The DM rolls a [[/r d100]] and consults the following table to determine what form the creature takes when restored to life, or the DM chooses a form.</p><table class=\" striped-odd\"><caption>Reincarnate Races</caption><thead><tr><th class=\"col-1 text-center no-wrap\" data-rd-isroller=\"true\" >[[/r d100]]</th><th class=\"col-11\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\" >Race</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"col-1 text-center no-wrap\" data-roll-min=\"1\" data-roll-max=\"4\" >01-04</td><td class=\"col-11\"  ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/races.html#dragonborn_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'races.html', 'PHB', 'dragonborn_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Dragonborn</a></td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-1 text-center no-wrap\" data-roll-min=\"5\" data-roll-max=\"13\" >05-13</td><td class=\"col-11\"  ><a href=\"https://5e.tools/races.html#dwarf%20(hill)_phb\"  onmouseover=\"Renderer.hover.pHandleLinkMouseOver(event, this, 'races.html', 'PHB', 'dwarf%20(hill)_phb', null)\" onmouseleave=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseLeave(event, this)\" onmousemove=\"Renderer.hover.handleLinkMouseMove(event, this)\"  ontouchstart=\"Renderer.hover.handleTouchStart(event, this)\" >Dwarf, h