ate({content: content});\n\t\t}\n\t  }\n    }\n}).render(true);\n}\n})();","author":"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0"},"options":{},"apps":{},"compendium":null}}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-magic-missile.jpg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Spirit Stone","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This grey basalt tablet is engraved with the alphanumeric runes that form the dwarven script. These symbols are more roughly hewn than they are calligraphic, hinting at the possibility that the stone block was formed by humanoid hands other than those of a dwarf. However, a closer inspection of its neat, orderly lines, sharply angled sensibilities, and the quality of its construction confirms its dwarven origins enough for most. The object is simply exceptionally old and has grown weathered from age and use. Used in conjunction with the obsidian planchette that accompanies it, the rock slab serves as a ouija board.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Spirit Summoning</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Even in death, only the luckiest can expect true, undisturbed rest. Once per day, while the spirit stone is about your person, you can undertake a 10 minute ritual to attempt to summon the spirit of a deceased dwarf to ask it for guidance or aid. If you do so, the ghostly form of a dwarf who died in your immediate vicinity manifests in an unoccupied space within 10 foot of them. The apparition uses the statistics of a </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Specter </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">and you must attempt a Charisma saving throw when it appears to determine its disposition. On a result of 1-3, the spirit is hostile and attacks you. On a result of 4-13, it is belligerent and refuses to aid you. On a result of 14-17, it is conversant and will offer up short, gruff answers to a handful of questions in dwarven. On a result of 18-21, it is friendly and will offer more thorough answers to a wider variety of questions in common. On results of 22+, it will offers its services for 1 hour, fighting in combat alongside you and acting on its own initiative order. Whatever the result, the ghost departs as soon as its business is concluded or its hit points are reduced to 0.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Dwarven Spirits. </strong>In order for a dwarven spirit to be summoned at all, the game master must determine that a suitable spirit is in the area. Additionally, the game master is the final arbiter on how knowledgeable, helpful, and informed the ghost that manifests is.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Grave Truths</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Spirit Stone acts as a perfect font for peeling back the veil between worlds and seeking information from beyond the grave. While within 5 foot of the body of a deceased dwarf, you can glean certain insights about its life. You can ask any of the following questions and receive an answer through the movements of the planchette if you can read dwarven and the spirit of the dwarf is inclined to answer:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">What was your name?</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">What was your profession?</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">How long has passed since your death?</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">How old were you when you died?</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Did you die of natural causes?</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If not, what type of creature killed you?</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Is your killer still among the living?</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Do you know their name?</span> </span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Esoteric Charms","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"trinket","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":11000000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/wondrous-item.png","effects":[],"_id":"y4FRMo5GIZmN5Ac6"}
{"name":"Bigouchie","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb01/bigouchie.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"121\" height=\"256\" /></span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"Even at a glance, this quilled parka has an unusual look about it&mdash;enough so to give all but the most reckless reason enough to pause and study it more closely before touching its spiky exterior. While its inside is soft and furry, the outside of this jacket is covered with hundreds of sharp, six-inch barbs layered over each other. Though these appear to sag down limply, their foreboding presence alone commands that a certain amount of respect be afforded the item, lest carelessness cause injury.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Armor.&nbsp;</strong>Bigouchie can be used as hide armor.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Prickly Protrusions (1/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The prickly spikes that adorn Bigouchie are not merely for decoration and remain ready to flare up at any time. You can spend your reaction to cause its spurs to rise sharply in response to being </span></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">targeted by a melee attack from a creature within 5 foot of you, imposing disadvantage on the attack. Additionally, if this attack misses, the attacking creature takes 1d8 piercing damage. </span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Absorbent. </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Already heavy with hundreds of barbed quills of its own, arrows and other projectiles fired at Bigouchie stand little chance of puncturing it. While wearing it, n</span></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">on-magical ranged attacks against you suffer a -1 penalty to hit.</span> </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Smallouchie</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Bigouchie has hundreds of needles protruding from it, just begging to be utilized for mischief. A creature can rip a bristle from it with a successful DC 8 Strength (athletics) check. A removed bristle can be used as a </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">dagger</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">. A creature that fails its Strength (athletics) check to safely remove a needle takes 1 point of piercing damage.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /></span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":12,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":12,"type":"medium","dex":2},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":true,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":3800000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":""},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/medium-armor.png","effects":[],"_id":"yIaaMwlIb1uK7fYi"}
{"name":"Masquerade Charade (Comedy)","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb07/masquerade-charade-comedy.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"212\" height=\"256\" />\"This pair of superlative masquerade masks are not only striking in and of themselves but also stand out as deliciously discordant as a set. This is thanks to the striking dissimilarities between them. Though both present with the same baroque patterns, embellishments, and curlicued, bell-adorned swirls; their coloration, expressions, and themes couldn&rsquo;t be more disparate. One is a rich red and conveys a smile so contrived it feels almost like a sneer, while the other is a deep blue and reveals a sadness that is so stilted it seems more akin revulsion.</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The set of twin masks known as Masquerade Charade was created by a visionary playwright who turned his hand to production and directing after becoming disillusioned with how his librettos were being &lsquo;butchered&rsquo; whilst making the transition to the stage. This ambitious trailblazer hoped that the creation of these masks marked the beginning of an explorative expedition into the true possibilities of magic-enhanced method acting. However, they never saw use in the theater after he asked two actors to don them for all their waking hours. One went on to kill himself, while the other was incarcerated for levels of exuberance and recklessness deemed dangerous for society.\"</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Attunement Requirement</strong>. Masquerade Charade includes two pieces, Masquerade Charade (Comedy) and @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.kKhJ6pUCjE2I68hy]{Masquerade Charade (Tragedy)}. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">For any of Masquerade Charade&rsquo;s other features to function, two Medium or Small humanoids must be wearing and attuned to one of its masks each.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Twinned Timing</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Creatures wearing Masquerade Charade&rsquo;s masks share an intrinsic, unspoken bond. When two creatures wearing the masks make an initiative check while within 60 foot of each other, only the one with the highest bonus to initiative makes the check, doing so with advantage. Both creatures act on this result, choosing each round which one will act first. If they cannot agree on who should act first, they should each roll a D20 to determine the order, with the creature with the highest result going first.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Comedy</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The creature wearing this particular mask discovers a wicked sense of humor and a love for mischievous, impish, and otherwise playful behaviour.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Comedic Flaw</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">You gain the following flaw while wearing this mask: &lsquo;I find it very difficult to take anything seriously.&rsquo;</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #000000;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Hopeless Optimist</strong>. You have advantage on checks made to resist fear while wearing this mask.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Hilarious</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If you roll a 1 </span></span>on an ability check while wearing this mask,&nbsp; you start to laugh uncontrollably for 1 minute, until you take damage, or until another creature uses an action to shake you out of it.</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Articles of the Arts","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":18600000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/headgear.png","effects":[],"_id":"yNtMSFxxdr8pzfeA"}
{"name":"Savoy","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"backpack","data":{"description":{"value":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb01/savoy.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"249\" /></span></em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">\"You'd be forgiven for mistaking this curious quiver for a deformed cabbage or defective lettuce, in fact it's difficult to really disprove that it's either. The item is certainly organic in nature, and its origins are shrouded in mystery. It is, however, perfect for storing arrows, and arrows kept within it seem to benefit from several curious but beneficial quirks if used swiftly after removal. The object has a certain reverence amongst farmers due to an old legend surrounding its genesis, though none can say if there's any truth to these tales or they're simply superstition.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Chilling</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Arrows interned within Savoy retain a bit of its icy nature, causing creatures struck with them to become sluggish. When you deal damage to a Medium or smaller creature with an arrow that has been placed within Savoy for at least 24 hours without having been removed from it for more than 10 minutes at any one time, that creature cannot take the Dash action for 1d4 rounds. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Additionally, the first time the target is struck, their movement speed is reduced by 5 foot for 1d4 hours or until they receive magical healing.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Frigid Tendrils</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">The effect Savoy has is stronger on some arrows than others. If you score a critical hit with an arrow that</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"> has been placed within it for at least 24 hours without having been removed for more than 10 minutes at any one time, your attack deals an additional 1d4 cold damage.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Winter's Bounty</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Savoy is a useful tool, even during the harshest of winters. If you plant an arrow that has been placed within it for at least 24 hours without having been removed for more than 10 minutes at any one time, it will grow into a winter-cabbage. For this to occur, you</span></span>&nbsp;must bury the arrow's head in soil, snow, or permafrost while in an arctic environment or during winter months. A large cabbage grows from the arrowhead overnight, providing enough food for a single Medium or smaller creature for a day.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wilderness Essentials","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"capacity":{"type":"items","value":20,"weightless":false},"currency":{"cp":0,"sp":0,"ep":0,"gp":0,"pp":0},"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":15500000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/ammunition.png","effects":[],"_id":"yjMMgVrDuMBfZBc5"}
{"name":"Staynn","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb10/staynn.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"167\" height=\"256\" />\"This head covering acts as both a helm and a face guard, and also protects its wearer's neck. Formed of gold and metal, the object's facade presents a stoic or stony face that's both cold and impassive. The object is in pristine condition and suitably polished for use by an individual of great importance. It has a regal motif worked into its design, most exemplified by the stunning crown that rises from its scowl.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Legend has it that Staynn originally belonged to a warrior-king, a barbarian conqueror from a distant land. They say that many fell to his blade, and that many others fled from it. More recently the unusual helm was discovered in a gaudy 'house of horrors' by the curator of a legitimate museum, an exhibition of bloody trophies from throughout history. The curator purchased the helm with the intention of ascertaining its historical value and displaying it in her museum. However, whether or not there is any truth to the myths about the artifact's origins has never been determined because it was stolen from the caravan that it was traveling with before it reached its destination and could be studied by qualified historians.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Head Protection</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As tough and unyielding as stone, Staynn does a superb job of protecting its wearer from head trauma. You are immune to receiving critical hits while wearing it.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Alpha (1/day)</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">When uncertain, those in the company of a creature wearing Staynn tend to glance its way for approval before acting rashly. If another creature within 30 foot of you attempts a Charisma (intimidation) check, you can choose to attempt a Charisma (intimidation) check of your own as a reaction. If your result is higher, you can decide that it should be used in place of the other creature's roll to improve their chance of success, or you can negate any consequences of their intimidation check to instead have the target of your check become frightened of you until the end of your next turn.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Fierce Visage</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">As any creature who's felt a pair of narrowed eyes boring into them from beneath it can attest, talking to someone wearing Staynn is inherently unsettling. While wearing it, you gain a 1d4 bonus on Charisma (intimidation) checks.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":0,"stealth":false,"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":1800000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/headgear.png","effects":[],"_id":"ylCSb6oLquKYv5mE"}
{"name":"Gaia's Laurel","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This decorative garland wreath is worn around the crown of the head, usually tucked behind the ears. Its appearance is fluid, changing with the seasons to reflect unique aspects of each while never appearing precisely the same from one year to the next. At springtime, the wreath is formed entirely of verdant grasses and laden with flower bulbs which go on to bloom in a myriad of striking colors as the season winds on. It has crisp green leaves with grapes and berries hanging from it over the summer.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">By fall, fiery hues of red and yellow leaves overtake the wreath, while nestled clusters of small pinecones, nuts, squashes, and pumpkins hang from it. Throughout winter, hoarfrost and small icicles form on bright red holly, surrounded by an otherwise snow-white wreath. As indicated by its appearance throughout the year, Gaia's Laurel is closely attuned to nature. So much so that it has played a key role in numerous festivals and celebrations dedicated to the worship of various harvest spirits, woodland fey, and deities linked with fertility, productivity, and nature's bounty.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Sensory Seduction</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The appeal of Gaia's Laurel as a symbol of fertility is undeniable, even to those who don't recognize it as such, and a creature wearing it appears unusually captivating and alluring. You have advantage on Charisma checks made to seduce other sentient creatures while wearing it if they match your sexual orientation. Additionally, while Gaia's Laurel remains within 5 foot of you, you're surrounded by minor phenomena and sensory effects linked to nature. Flowers bloom brighter in your presence, the smells and sights of the countryside are enhanced, plants and flowers appear richer and more vibrant, and fruit and vegetables taste better.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Seasonal Style</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Gaia's Laurel's appearance is fluid and transient, changing with the seasons. It grants the following special traits to you at different times throughout the year while you keep it about your person:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Spring</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have advantage on saving throws against poisons and diseases that are inhaled. Additionally, you can sleep for two hours less each day without needing to make Constitution checks to avoid gaining levels of exhaustion, though this does not affect the duration of any long rests you take.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Summer</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You have resistance to fire damage, can survive on half as much water each day as usual, and do not suffer penalties associated with extremely hot environments.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Fall</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You feel lighter, like a leaf. You have resistance to bludgeoning damage taken as a result of falling and your carrying capacity is increased by 30 lbs. Additionally, campfires started by you are not extinguished by rainfall while you remain within 50 feet of them.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Winter</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You have resistance to cold damage, weigh half as much for the purposes of not cracking ice, and you do not suffer penalties associated with extremely cold environments.</span></li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Religious Regalia","quantity":1,"weight":0.1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"targ