{"name":"Whorl","permission":{"default":0,"IKZcSijaQ4XFwYDB":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">\"This sharp hook is unusual in the sense that its wooden, leather upholstered handle is secured to a short length of rope, and also because this handle has thin ribs cut into it that run entirely through the object. These additions might not make sense to a creature studying it for but a moment, but once they pick it up and begin spinning it, the purpose of these features quickly becomes apparent. </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">For a start, while spinning, the weapon can quickly and easily be brought to bare against a target at range, with painful consequence. More than that though, the object begins to emit a very deep, warbling sound akin whale song as wind is pressed through its openings.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Whorl is a weapon with a close affinity to the sea. It's most commonly employed by mariners and sailors who've come to truly respect and love the ocean, and who recognize its ability to both give, and to take away.\"</span></em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Whorl can be used as a hook.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong style=\"font-style: italic;\">Rule Clarification, Hook.</strong><span style=\"font-style: italic;\"> Rules for hooks can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.</span></span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Reach Weapon</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Whorl is secured to a long rope and usually spun by its wielder, remaining in constant motion. It has a 10 foot reach. It doesn't need to be spun however and can instead by thrown and reeled in via its rope. Consequently, you can still wield it effectively in areas smaller than 10 foot across.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Whale Song</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Whorl longs to sing and, while spinning, it does. While the object is in motion, it emits a deep droning sound that very similar to whale song and confuses oceanic creatures. While it is producing this sound, aquatic Beasts must make a DC 8 Wisdom (insight) check when attempting to attack you. On a fail, they are unable to attack you and must choose to attack another creature, take a different action, or waste their attack action.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Flying Fox</strong>. </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Fingers are great for picking locks or opening doors, but there are also certain advantages to having a hook. You have advantage on Dexterity (acrobatics) checks made to zipline or horizontally traverse expanses via ropes using Whorl.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Maritime Marvels","quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":1,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d4 + @mod","piercing"],["","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":true,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":true,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":true,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":false,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":13500000,"flags":{"mess":{"templateTexture":"","isBonusDamage":false},"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/simple-melee-weapon.png","effects":[],"_id":"zTaeyLATF39IWfIo"}
{"name":"Gilded Chess Set","permission":{"default":0,"GKct8oevKfiR8DZJ":3,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"tool","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><img style=\"float: right; border: 0px;\" src=\"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/images/bb10/gilded-chess-set.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"256\" height=\"148\" />\"Formed of refined gold, red velvet, ivory, and walnut wood, this one-of-a-kind chess set is unusual simply for the materials used in its construction. Combining metals, fabrics, bone, and wood together into such a bespoke piece, the set's crafters have created something of a baroque masterpiece. The detailing, most notably evident on the filigree that runs around the board's perimeter and in the carving of each piece, is exquisite and really needs to be seen up close to fully appreciate.</em></p>\n<p><em>The Gilded Chess Set was fashioned by the members of an adventuring party who, upon disbanding at the end of a long and storied career, each contributed something unique and precious to the project. Its dwarf lord smelted high carat gold, the elven ranger fetched wood from their homeland, human hands stitched the velvet, and the group's half-orc took it upon herself to hunt down and fell a mighty beast for the ivory required to finish the set. When the task was completed, the group left the object at the taproom where they first started their adventures many years before, the Tipsy Tactician.\"</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Tool</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Gilded Chess Set can be used as a chess set.</span></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Rule Clarification, Chess Set.</strong> Rules for chess sets can be found in </span>@Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.rules.LeY4oabJ69pNyECb]{Items &amp; Equipment}.<span class=\"fontstyle2\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Checkmate</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The Gilded Chess Set serves as an able reminder that tactics and critical thinking are powerful tools. So long as it is about your person, you gain a +1 bonus on melee attack rolls against a hostile creature if an ally of yours is on your target's opposite side and the target is also within that ally's reach.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Know Thy Opponent</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">In life, just as in games of chess, studying one's opponent is critical to victory. While it is about your person, you gain a +1 bonus to Wisdom (insight) checks relating to creatures that you can see.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>Chess Champ</strong>.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">The four individuals who came together to create the Gilded Chess Set wanted for others to learn, grow, and, ultimately, follow in their footsteps. You add double your proficiency bonus to checks made to play games of chess or teach others the rules of chess with it. If you aren't trained in its use, you can still add your normal proficiency bonus when using it for the same purposes.</span></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Heraldic Trappings","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":0,"attuned":false,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"Beginner Bauble","identified":true,"ability":"int","chatFlavor":"","proficient":0,"attributes":{"spelldc":10}},"folder":"cWRjvnZeLQUNUCSA","sort":1100000,"flags":{"ddd-beginner-baubles":{"initialization-folder":"Beginner Baubles"}},"img":"modules/ddd-beginner-baubles/icons/gaming-set.png","effects":[],"_id":"zTvu3LwKVj6R0W11"}
{"_id":"zhIA1nKiabSSp9Re","name":"True Strike (PHB)","permission":{"default":-1,"OWUwMjUxOTE5MjE0":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"value":"<div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You extend your hand and point a finger at a target in range. Your magic grants you a brief insight into the target's defenses. On your next turn, you gain advantage on your first attack roll against the target, provided that this spell hasn't ended.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"round"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":0,"school":"div","components":{"value":"","vocal":false,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"always","prepared":true},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"folder":"BkTF1PtvJCbPFObx","sort":4000001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/spell/phb-true-strike.jpg","effects":[]}
